    '{"id":"01KA24FCBSGRQ5K91S3Z9KE1WB","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Distribution**\n\nThe team finalized the podcast episode with **Michelle** and is optimizing video distribution to increase reach and engagement (08:48).\n\n- **Gab** confirmed the episode and five Spotify videos are ready, with plans to upload full videos to Spotify and short clips to YouTube, aiming to boost viewership and new subscribers through bite-sized content.\n    - Short clips have shown higher engagement and subscriber growth compared to full episodes.\n    - This dual approach balances Gab’s need for control over scheduling with broader content distribution handled by Marketers in Demand.\n    - The new workflow starts with the Michelle episode to test the process and scale from there.\n    - Tim highlighted that guest marketing teams like **E Health** and **Michelle** personally sharing posts increased interaction by over **40 actions**, improving customer relationships and renewal likelihood.\n\n- The team addressed guest scheduling challenges, noting frequent rescheduling requires Gab to maintain control over Buzzsprout uploads for flexibility (06:20).\n    - Baylee suggested the internal team handle clip posting after episodes go live to streamline workload while Gab focuses on full episode scheduling.\n    - This division aims to maintain timely releases despite shifting guest availability.\n    - The approach also fosters stronger rapport with guests and their marketing teams by having Gab plugged into scheduling and intake calls, supporting deeper collaboration and promotion.\n\n- Technical issues with asset uploads were resolved through browser tweaks, restoring smooth workflow for guest content submission via the portal (12:17).\n    - Baylee noted recent Zapier UI changes caused earlier disruptions, now fixed.\n    - This stability ensures no delays in publishing and asset sharing moving forward.\n\n\n## **Ebook Performance and Organic Marketing Assets**\n\nThe ebook launch generated over **25 downloads** with ongoing inbound interest, serving as sustainable organic support over holidays and into next year (13:20).\n\n- Gab will obtain detailed lead-to-meeting conversion data from **Sean** to evaluate inbound marketing impact and share updates in Slack.\n    - This snapshot will help assess ebook’s effectiveness in generating qualified leads.\n- Igor delivered final revisions on guest creatives including compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels, awaiting Tim’s approval to deploy (14:09).\n    - Tim praised social assets for making guests feel valued, citing positive feedback such as from the Wendy’s representative who felt spotlighted.\n    - These assets improve guest satisfaction and promote the brand widely, encouraging other clients to adopt similar practices.\n- Baylee shared the organic content visibility internally, boosting team morale by showing the broad exposure and real-world use of created materials (16:24).\n\n\n## **Paid Media Campaign Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe **paid media campaign budget** was approved by **Matt**, enabling the team to advance with the middle-of-funnel (MoFU) strategy targeting financial services (16:52).\n\n- Christina updated the target list to focus more on **finserve** sectors, refining audience alignment for better campaign results.\n- Baylee recommended a staggered launch: start with the top-of-funnel (ToFU) campaign running **December to February**, followed by MoFU and bottom-of-funnel campaigns, which will run concurrently thereafter to maximize exposure (19:03).\n    - ToFU builds awareness and collects audience data for retargeting.\n    - MoFU targets users who interacted with ToFU content or visited specific blog pages, requiring pixel tracking setup.\n    - Baylee emphasized the need for website pixel installation (AdRoll) to enable precise retargeting and improve conversion rates.\n- Gab and Christina requested a walkthrough session from Baylee’s team to build confidence in managing the campaign setup, reflecting their newer experience (18:44).\n- Discussions emphasized **AdRoll** as a cost-effective retargeting tool compared to LinkedIn’s higher ad costs, allowing broader reach within budget constraints (23:28).\n    - If AdRoll approval fails, the fallback is focusing on LinkedIn only, accepting higher costs but maintaining quality B2B targeting.\n- Sean is assembling a matched audience list of nearly **10,000 contacts**, slightly below LinkedIn’s optimal threshold, which will be tested and optimized over time (24:47).\n- Creative asset development is underway, with initial copy drafts paused until all published content is reviewed for alignment (26:20).\n    - Baylee explained ToFU ads will focus on awareness messages, while MoFU ads drive guide downloads, creating a logical funnel progression.\n    - Gab and Christina agreed this approach fits their vision, helping prospects move from general awareness to action.\n\n\n## **Equipment Procurement and Setup Planning**\n\nThe equipment budget was approved, and ordered items are shipping to the **Chicago office** for the new podcast production setup (03:03).\n\n- Becky shared a detailed list of purchased equipment in Slack to keep the team informed and prepare for setup.\n- Baylee offered to provide hands-on videography support and setup guidance, leveraging her experience to optimize lighting and positioning (03:47).\n- Gab, Baylee, and Tim will collaborate on setup and filming responsibilities, ensuring smooth production workflows.\n- This new equipment and setup aim to improve production quality and give the team more control over recording environments, supporting higher content standards.\n\n\n## **Process Improvements and Team Coordination**\n\nThe team identified gaps in guest scheduling and marketing integration, emphasizing restoring Gab’s involvement to strengthen guest and marketing team relationships (11:05).\n\n- Tim acknowledged his role as a bottleneck in providing contacts to Gab for post-episode marketing outreach.\n- Gab stressed the importance of intake calls and Riverside link sharing to build rapport and prepare guests’ marketing teams for promotion.\n- Reintegrating Gab into scheduling aims to increase marketing collaboration, improving social asset sharing and amplification.\n- This process realignment is expected to enhance content reach and renewal opportunities by leveraging guest networks more effectively.\n\n\n## **Long-term Marketing and Engagement Vision**\n\nThe team plans to use organic content as ongoing “air cover” through holidays and into the next year, supporting lead nurturing and brand presence without new spend (14:49).\n\n- Gab expressed excitement about gradually rolling out organic assets to maintain momentum.\n- Tim emphasized the value of guest social sharing as a best practice to increase brand visibility and guest satisfaction.\n- The paid campaigns are designed to complement organic efforts by driving targeted traffic and nurturing prospects through the funnel.\n- This multi-channel approach reflects a thoughtful, layered engagement strategy balancing cost, reach, and relationship-building.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Distribution","Paid Media Campaign","Equipment Setup","Ebook Marketing Assets","LinkedIn Retargeting","Guest Marketing Engagement"],"overview":"- **Podcast Production:** Finalized episode with Michelle; five Spotify videos ready; short clips drive higher engagement and subscriber growth.\n\n- **Ebook Performance:** Launched ebook generated 25+ downloads; ongoing data collection on conversion impact planned for evaluation.\n\n- **Paid Media Campaign:** Budget approved; focus on financial services; staggered launch strategy to improve exposure and audience engagement.\n\n- **Equipment Setup:** New podcast production gear ordered; team to enhance video quality and production control for future projects.\n\n- **Process Improvement:** Reintegrating Gab in guest scheduling to strengthen marketing collaboration and boost content promotion effectiveness.\n\n- **Long-term Vision:** Organic content supports lead nurturing over holidays; multi-channel strategy balances cost and relationship-building for brand visibility.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nProvide update on ebook download conversions and meetings set from form fills to Slack (13:20)\nPlug back into guest scheduling and intake processes to enhance connection with guest marketing teams (10:50)\nShare the email copy and blog link for paid media campaign creative team (26:10)\nCoordinate with Sean on LinkedIn matched audience list creation for FinServe target group (24:39)\nAdd process steps for Spotify video full uploads and YouTube clip uploads starting with the Michelle episode (08:34)\nInform marketing team of launch timing and budget approval for equipment setup (03:03)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nOffer videography and equipment setup training and support call with Gab and Tim (03:47)\nSetup Apple Podcasts ID for better podcast analytics (04:50)\nManage uploading of short podcast clips to YouTube post-episode and coordinate Spotify full video uploads (07:07)\nSupport paid media campaign setup walkthrough and clarify running strategy for TOF and MOF campaigns with Christina and Gab (18:44)\nShare AdRoll license and implementation details for middle funnel retargeting setup (21:40)\nProvide feedback and approval process support for updated guest creatives (compilation videos, LinkedIn carousels) (13:14)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nDeliver final guest creative revisions and monitor feedback for approval (13:14)\nSupport paid media campaign targeting updates and creative alignment (16:50)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nProvide final review and approval on the revised ebook guest creatives (compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels) (13:50)\nSupport coordination of guest marketing team involvement and sharing of episode content to enhance promotional reach (09:10)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nCollaborate with Gab on paid media campaign setup, target list, and creative asset review (16:50)\nParticipate in training call to understand paid campaign setup and retargeting code implementation (18:44)\n\n**Sean**\nContinue to develop matched audience list for LinkedIn targeting under Gab’s guidance (24:39)\n"},"duration":30.170000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Gab"},{"id":2,"name":"Christina Bila"},{"id":3,"name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"I think in the other days, I.","index":0,"end_time":2.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Don''T know if we have like the Thursday and the Friday off.","index":1,"end_time":4.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think the offices are closed for both.","index":2,"end_time":6.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":3,"end_time":7.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it''s Thursday and Friday.","index":4,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":7.56,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":5,"end_time":9.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Should we cancel the meeting next Friday then?","index":6,"end_time":12.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":7,"end_time":13.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.8,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Do you want to meet on a different day?","index":8,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just looking at the calendar, We can probably wait until just the following Friday, the 5th.","index":9,"end_time":31.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":10,"end_time":33.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that should be fine.","index":11,"end_time":34.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If something comes up, we can try for something sooner.","index":12,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great.","index":13,"end_time":40.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You doing anything fun for Thanksgiving?","index":14,"end_time":43.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.609,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s gonna be really small for my family this year.","index":15,"end_time":47.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.81,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s like six people, which is not normal.","index":16,"end_time":49.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Wow.","index":17,"end_time":50.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s usually like 15 to 20 people in a house.","index":18,"end_time":54.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":19,"end_time":55.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s nice that it''s small and that then I can.","index":20,"end_time":60.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I can bring a side dish.","index":21,"end_time":61.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I can make a dessert.","index":22,"end_time":62.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''ve really been wanting to make tiramisu, so I might just do that and say, this is your Thanksgiving dessert.","index":23,"end_time":68.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Wow.","index":24,"end_time":68.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think that sounds really good.","index":25,"end_time":72.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.31,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But Christina, what are you doing?","index":26,"end_time":74.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Same.","index":27,"end_time":75.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.55,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"It''s gonna be very small because everybody''s going and doing stuff, so.","index":28,"end_time":80.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.03,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just me, my parents, and my sisters.","index":29,"end_time":84.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.07,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":84.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Your fiance''s going like, somewhere else?","index":31,"end_time":87.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s going to his family and then he''s going to be here for Christmas, so.","index":32,"end_time":91.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.43,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":92.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Cool.","index":34,"end_time":92.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":35,"end_time":92.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.47,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Nice little trade off action.","index":36,"end_time":94.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":37,"end_time":95.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Tim, what are you doing for Thanksgiving?","index":38,"end_time":98.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Are you even.","index":39,"end_time":98.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Are you even thankful?","index":40,"end_time":99.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Christina, first of all, just let him enjoy his last Thanksgiving with his family.","index":41,"end_time":106.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":100.35,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":42,"end_time":107.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.58,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That''s why I didn''t give him a hassle.","index":43,"end_time":109.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.9,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":110.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because once we''re married, that ends.","index":45,"end_time":112.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.46,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":46,"end_time":113.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Am I thankful?","index":47,"end_time":119.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":118.06,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"What are you doing?","index":48,"end_time":119.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.26,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What are you doing?","index":49,"end_time":121.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Next week I am going up to the great state of Michigan where my in laws have a house and then my parents also live.","index":50,"end_time":129.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":121.26,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So we''ll do double duty on the parents and in laws.","index":51,"end_time":133.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.74,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":52,"end_time":133.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Eat so much food.","index":53,"end_time":135.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":137.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I don''t like turkey.","index":55,"end_time":140.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":138.6,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I don''t eat it.","index":56,"end_time":140.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":140.12,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":57,"end_time":142.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is not your holiday changed.","index":58,"end_time":146.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":59,"end_time":149.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Cool.","index":60,"end_time":150.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a lot to.","index":61,"end_time":151.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, in my mind, I''m like, there''s.","index":62,"end_time":153.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I have questions about lots of things.","index":63,"end_time":155.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So this is a great.","index":64,"end_time":156.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.48,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''ll get into it.","index":65,"end_time":159.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s a lot going on right now.","index":66,"end_time":162.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Even though we launched the ebook, there''s still a lot going on.","index":67,"end_time":164.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got some podcast updates.","index":68,"end_time":169.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Still wrapping up a few things on the ebook.","index":69,"end_time":172.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve got your paid strategy, and then I also have a slide just about, I think the equipment list we sent over.","index":70,"end_time":178.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you have any questions.","index":71,"end_time":179.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On that, but.","index":72,"end_time":180.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anything else on your mind?","index":73,"end_time":182.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, just to.","index":74,"end_time":184.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know if I should jump ahead, but budget got approved for our.","index":75,"end_time":188.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"For our equipment list and all the stuff that we.","index":76,"end_time":190.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So Becky dropped an update in the Slack channel with just like a list of the stuff that we got.","index":77,"end_time":197.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I asked her to do that just in case, like, you know, I have questions about how to set up literally within the space.","index":78,"end_time":206.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Not necessarily like how to use the equipment, but where should we be positioning, lighting and stuff like that.","index":79,"end_time":211.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So the guide that like Justin sent over with the.","index":80,"end_time":214.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The different setup options that will probably be helpful.","index":81,"end_time":217.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But just in case, I. I had her send you the list.","index":82,"end_time":220.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So now you know what we ordered and it''s getting shipped to our Chicago office so we can play with it all.","index":83,"end_time":225.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yay.","index":84,"end_time":226.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":227.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m happy to hop on a call.","index":86,"end_time":229.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did before I started this job.","index":87,"end_time":231.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did a lot of videography.","index":88,"end_time":233.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I will walk you through anything you want to be walked through.","index":89,"end_time":238.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are you going to be the one setting everything up and filming and stuff?","index":90,"end_time":242.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":91,"end_time":243.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":92,"end_time":244.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep.","index":93,"end_time":245.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s you and me.","index":94,"end_time":245.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You and me, Bailey and Tim.","index":95,"end_time":246.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, let''s do it.","index":96,"end_time":248.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":97,"end_time":249.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.39,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":98,"end_time":250.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah, I just wanted to give you an update.","index":99,"end_time":252.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.47,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m fine with it.","index":100,"end_time":253.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.39,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I''m just a pretty face.","index":101,"end_time":255.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":254.27,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But what I''m sad about with this Spotify, I''ve got majority of male viewers and listeners don''t want that.","index":102,"end_time":264.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":255.71,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":103,"end_time":268.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was going through some of the deeper demographic stuff in Spotify creator.","index":104,"end_time":273.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was interesting.","index":105,"end_time":274.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I forget which age group was more listening on Spotify, but I want to.","index":106,"end_time":280.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That was another thing on my list.","index":107,"end_time":282.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is next week a priority is setting up that Apple ID so we can dig deeper into Apple podcasts as well and see the difference.","index":108,"end_time":291.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I guess so.","index":109,"end_time":294.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":294.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":294.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":295.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super interesting stuff there.","index":112,"end_time":298.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so just looking at your podcast, the episode with Michelle, looks like you published that.","index":113,"end_time":307.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So glad we were able to finalize everything there and we got those five Spotify videos ready and then you had sent a message gab about how to distribute on Spotify video moving forward.","index":114,"end_time":319.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So there''s like a couple different ways we can do it.","index":115,"end_time":322.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re happy to do it.","index":116,"end_time":323.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you want to do it, that''s fine.","index":117,"end_time":325.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My recommendation is if you want us to do it, let us help with other things too so you get like your full worth of points.","index":118,"end_time":334.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was thinking about that just because like the reason I think that I like having more control over the like Buzzsprout dissemination process and just a lot of things in general is because sometimes our guests are have to be rescheduled and stuff like that.","index":119,"end_time":354.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I would rather just be able to do it on a back end, on my end so that when it is finally time, I can just get right in there and do it right then and there.","index":120,"end_time":366.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"At least that''s where my thought train of thought was going.","index":121,"end_time":371.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Unless you think there''s a better way to go about everything.","index":122,"end_time":375.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":123,"end_time":376.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.31,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"How often do they get rescheduled?","index":124,"end_time":379.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A lot.","index":125,"end_time":381.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.52,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"A lot.","index":126,"end_time":381.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":127,"end_time":382.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":128,"end_time":383.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And is it usually like, are you scheduling things like a week in advance or the day of what it.","index":129,"end_time":392.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It, it all depends.","index":130,"end_time":393.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like sometimes I''m.","index":131,"end_time":395.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m uploading to buzzfro the day before, sometimes I''m uploading like a week out.","index":132,"end_time":399.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It really depends just also on other workload stuff.","index":133,"end_time":404.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, well if that''s happening a lot, then maybe it does make more sense just for us to plug in and do video after things get published and then.","index":134,"end_time":418.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But the other thing we could add on is we could help you do the video clips afterwards, get those all posted onto YouTube.","index":135,"end_time":424.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you been posting those?","index":136,"end_time":426.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve been doing the full video upload onto YouTube because we embed it on our website.","index":137,"end_time":432.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I like the idea of the video clips.","index":138,"end_time":437.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":435.29,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We could be putting the clips out.","index":139,"end_time":439.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":140,"end_time":440.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s where I notice people get the most views and the most new subscribers is with the shorter clips.","index":141,"end_time":447.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":142,"end_time":447.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":448.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And especially if you take care of like the full episode things, then we know, okay, video clips and this other stuff can go out.","index":144,"end_time":455.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a thought.","index":145,"end_time":458.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.21,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I mean we haven''t really been super targeted with LinkedIn or not with LinkedIn.","index":146,"end_time":464.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"With YouTube.","index":147,"end_time":465.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The last time I feel like we were really thinking about YouTube was when we were doing PMAX campaigns, which was short lived.","index":148,"end_time":474.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But I don''t think it could hurt to just have all of the clips uploaded on the back end.","index":149,"end_time":481.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like it.","index":150,"end_time":482,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re not necessarily looking for conversions from YouTube, but if it''s.","index":151,"end_time":486.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":487.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Leads someone from YouTube to our website, there''s always the chance of that.","index":153,"end_time":492.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So yeah, maybe after each episode we then have marketers in demand upload the shorter clips to our YouTube and also put the full video on Spotify.","index":154,"end_time":506.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is that, does that like package nicely together?","index":155,"end_time":509.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that makes sense to me if that sounds okay to you.","index":156,"end_time":513.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes perfect sense and it sounds really great.","index":157,"end_time":516.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right, so short clips are going up with mid.","index":158,"end_time":521.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And we can start this with the episode with Michelle, if that''s okay.","index":159,"end_time":527.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s perfect.","index":160,"end_time":529.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":161,"end_time":530.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.679,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then this Spotify full video upload as well.","index":162,"end_time":535.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we''ll do that for Michelle as Well, okay.","index":163,"end_time":540.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":164,"end_time":541.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":165,"end_time":542.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''ll add that to our process.","index":166,"end_time":544.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Great.","index":167,"end_time":548.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then.","index":168,"end_time":549.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":550.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, Bailey, can you just go back to Michelle?","index":170,"end_time":553.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":550.13,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":554.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s not like when people ask me who my favorite child is.","index":172,"end_time":559.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":554.77,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I never say who my favorite child is, but I have a favorite child.","index":173,"end_time":562.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":559.33,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Just like this was my favorite episode.","index":174,"end_time":566.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.29,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And Gab, I think, why, like, we need to.","index":175,"end_time":568.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":566.29,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I need a better job getting the marketing team of the people that we''re talking to behind it, like E Health was.","index":176,"end_time":578.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":569.97,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So, Bailey, E. Health not only reposted it, they posted their own and they did the graphics all around their branding.","index":177,"end_time":590.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":578.69,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And then Michelle, also on her own personal LinkedIn, posted it with comments.","index":178,"end_time":595.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":590.61,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And the amount of action that those two did, like, I think it added to the various marketing solutions.","index":179,"end_time":604.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.48,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But usually we don''t get a ton that way.","index":180,"end_time":606.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.24,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but this was, I think, 40 plus interactions with the E. Health.","index":181,"end_time":612,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":606.4,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But what was so good about.","index":182,"end_time":614,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":612.4,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s like UnitedHealthcare, the CEO of Mars.","index":183,"end_time":618.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":614,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The.","index":184,"end_time":619.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":618.88,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"All the people that are affiliate, like, that are affiliated with E Health, which is important because they''re our customer, which helps with the renewal.","index":185,"end_time":629.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.96,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So maybe we can sort of make me cover that.","index":186,"end_time":639.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":629.85,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like.","index":187,"end_time":640.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.33,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, give you.","index":188,"end_time":642.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":641.13,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So as part of your PowerPoint presentation.","index":189,"end_time":644.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.25,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":190,"end_time":644.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.69,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":645.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.97,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Where are we with the.","index":192,"end_time":647.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.25,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The guest posting?","index":193,"end_time":649.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":648.25,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Where are we with.","index":194,"end_time":650.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.85,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You know that.","index":195,"end_time":651.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":651.12,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So we just.","index":196,"end_time":652.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":651.68,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Maybe it''d be good for Gab and I to get more deliberate on that.","index":197,"end_time":657.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":652.16,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":198,"end_time":658.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":657.6,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I think I''m the bottleneck because I need to give Gab the people who.","index":199,"end_time":663.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.32,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"To reach out to.","index":200,"end_time":665.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.76,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I was gonna say, like, part of our process kind of disappears sometimes.","index":201,"end_time":671.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Only because you have the direct content contact to the guest.","index":202,"end_time":675.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So then it''s really easy for you to just say, yeah, I''m just gonna schedule this.","index":203,"end_time":679.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.32,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We don''t need to go through Gab.","index":204,"end_time":681.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.8,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The.","index":205,"end_time":682.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The thing that we lose, though, I think is being connected to those marketing teams through that step of, you know, priming the guest with the intake call and just the Riverside link sharing and stuff like that.","index":206,"end_time":697.709,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.31,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It just builds, no pun intended, but more of a rapport as well.","index":207,"end_time":701.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.709,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And.","index":208,"end_time":703.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, so if we can start plugging me back into those.","index":209,"end_time":707.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Those.","index":210,"end_time":707.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Those processes of, like, scheduling, I think that will help us, Tim, with like, getting more of the marketing side of their teams on board as well.","index":211,"end_time":715.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You''re probably writing, Gab is really mean to me.","index":212,"end_time":723.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So hard.","index":213,"end_time":725.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just admitted that it was my fault.","index":214,"end_time":728.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.67,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"And Gab''s like, yeah, thank you.","index":215,"end_time":730.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.55,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It is your fault.","index":216,"end_time":731.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.15,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Here''s more reasons why it''s your fault.","index":217,"end_time":733.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":731.07,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"No, we''re going to get back on Track.","index":218,"end_time":735.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Together.","index":219,"end_time":737.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":220,"end_time":740.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, and the Kelly Chapman episode.","index":221,"end_time":743.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Igor confirmed that it went through the portal.","index":222,"end_time":748.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep.","index":223,"end_time":749.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Glad it''s working.","index":224,"end_time":750.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":225,"end_time":751.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I did it through Chrome, which usually it doesn''t work through Chrome, so that''s awesome.","index":226,"end_time":756.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Something happened.","index":227,"end_time":758.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Glad it''s working.","index":228,"end_time":759.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, same.","index":229,"end_time":760.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":761.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank goodness.","index":231,"end_time":762.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think a couple months ago Zapier had like made some pretty big UI changes and I think that''s why it went down.","index":232,"end_time":769.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But now we''re back doing good.","index":233,"end_time":772.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re so back.","index":234,"end_time":773.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":774.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank goodness.","index":236,"end_time":775.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, sounds like we''re all good then with this recording.","index":237,"end_time":780.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And once you get all the equipment, we can sync and figure out the final details here.","index":238,"end_time":785.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":239,"end_time":786.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So then I''ll kick it over to Igor just to chat through the final details of the ebook.","index":240,"end_time":793.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":795.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":794.94,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"First question, what''s happening with the downloads?","index":242,"end_time":798.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":796.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How is it going?","index":243,"end_time":799.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":798.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s a really great question.","index":244,"end_time":801.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.46,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I have to get an update from Sean, but the last time I heard it was like 25 plus and more coming.","index":245,"end_time":809.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"How that translated to our inbound marketing manager, Shannon, I''m not sure, like if any meetings were set up based on those form fills or not.","index":246,"end_time":819.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I will get just more of a snapshot and I can put it in the Slack chat.","index":247,"end_time":823.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.94,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s a good point.","index":248,"end_time":824.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":249,"end_time":826.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":825.31,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":250,"end_time":826.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":826.03,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''ll be great.","index":251,"end_time":827.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":826.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":828.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":828.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, as you know, we delivered guest creatives and today two revisions were completed and I also sent it over just after the meeting in Slack.","index":253,"end_time":838.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":828.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels are revised and waiting for your feedback.","index":254,"end_time":845.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":838.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, basically that''s it.","index":255,"end_time":848.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":847.11,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":256,"end_time":850.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I took the first pass at the comp Video edits, Tim.","index":257,"end_time":854.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So for this round we''ll just call it like a final approval.","index":258,"end_time":858.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"On your end I can send you the link from Slack and then the LinkedIn carousels, I gave some edits as well.","index":259,"end_time":866.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So both of those are ready for use essentially once Tim gives the okay.","index":260,"end_time":870.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And that''s really exciting.","index":261,"end_time":873.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And that wraps up everything with the ebook for this year.","index":262,"end_time":876.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But I''ll tell you what, like all of the organic assets that you guys have created for us, it''s gonna keep.","index":263,"end_time":883.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s a nice.","index":264,"end_time":884.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What we, I guess call air cover jargon.","index":265,"end_time":887.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.28,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t know, but it''ll be nice air cover through the holidays and also into the new year as we''re ramping up our planning and.","index":266,"end_time":894.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And executing in the new year.","index":267,"end_time":896.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.72,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So all to say, it''s not all for not.","index":268,"end_time":900.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s all gonna get out there and I''m very excited to trickle it out.","index":269,"end_time":903.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So.","index":270,"end_time":904.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks for sharing too, Bailey.","index":271,"end_time":907.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":272,"end_time":908.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.77,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think Gab reviewed This with you.","index":273,"end_time":910.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":908.73,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"But one of the things that has been.","index":274,"end_time":913.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":910.97,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"We''ve received a lot of great feedback from our guests is the social assets that we gave them.","index":275,"end_time":920.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.17,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So I would tell your other customer clients to do.","index":276,"end_time":923.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":920.09,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Did Tim freeze or am I frozen?","index":277,"end_time":930.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":928.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is that now everybody else okay.","index":278,"end_time":932.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We were all so still.","index":279,"end_time":933.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We lost it.","index":280,"end_time":937.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Tim.","index":281,"end_time":937.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":282,"end_time":939.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":938.2,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"You were saying that we should tell our other clients to do this.","index":283,"end_time":944.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I would, I. I would tell them like as best practices, they should do it because it makes the guests feel really like special.","index":284,"end_time":952.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":944.44,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Like, like the guy from Wendy''s goes, you made me look like you''re making me look like a superstar.","index":285,"end_time":957.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":953.09,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Maybe four people have shared it, but it looks really, really good and it promotes the brain us in a very positive way.","index":286,"end_time":966.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":958.45,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"So.","index":287,"end_time":967.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":966.89,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I love this.","index":288,"end_time":969.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":969.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I want to do this for everyone.","index":290,"end_time":971.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s turned out great.","index":291,"end_time":975.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it was fun to do as well.","index":292,"end_time":978.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like just to see everyone be excited and actually using the stuff we made for them.","index":293,"end_time":982.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So that''s exciting.","index":294,"end_time":983.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":984.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":984.22,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Thanks again for sharing those posts.","index":296,"end_time":986.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I shared that with our entire team and they were so happy to see everything out in the wild.","index":297,"end_time":991.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll share any more that pop up.","index":298,"end_time":994.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":994.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":300,"end_time":995.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks.","index":301,"end_time":997.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then just last is hopping into this paid media campaign.","index":302,"end_time":1003.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know we, Christine and I, we were chatting a little bit over slack, but did you have any other questions or just thoughts on what we sent over?","index":303,"end_time":1010.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":304,"end_time":1012.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.44,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Before you start, I just wanted to give an update like as far as what has been published so far for this campaign.","index":305,"end_time":1019.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m dropping a link to our blog in the chat that is essentially our landing page slash form for our middle of funnel piece of content.","index":306,"end_time":1030.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So this is where we would be driving people in the campaign strategy.","index":307,"end_time":1036.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.48,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1038.709,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.309,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s all I wanted to say.","index":309,"end_time":1041.509,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.949,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We had an email go out, we had initial social go out and now we''re just focused on.","index":310,"end_time":1047.269,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.509,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Or me and Christina, anyway, are focused on the paid strategy that you sent.","index":311,"end_time":1051.349,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.429,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So Christina, take it away.","index":312,"end_time":1053.829,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051.349,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just wanted to get that out of the way.","index":313,"end_time":1055.189,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.829,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"No, that''s okay.","index":314,"end_time":1056.309,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.349,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Couple updates.","index":315,"end_time":1058.149,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.029,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Budget was approved by Matt, so we''re good on that department.","index":316,"end_time":1062.629,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1058.869,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then on I''m just going to click into the doc, Word doc.","index":317,"end_time":1069.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1063.109,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I just updated the target list for the MoFU just because I felt like it was mostly market but we want to.","index":318,"end_time":1079.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.08,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"We wanted to focus on finserve.","index":319,"end_time":1081.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.44,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So I think Igor, you updated that or updated that.","index":320,"end_time":1084.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.24,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I don''t even remember but I see it there.","index":321,"end_time":1087.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1084.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But we do have a couple of questions with the campaign itself.","index":322,"end_time":1093.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.92,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So when we set it up, I know we have tofu, mofu.","index":323,"end_time":1099.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.52,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then the last part of it.","index":324,"end_time":1101.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.59,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Are they all going to run concurrently or are they going to be different campaigns at different times?","index":325,"end_time":1107.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.47,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Because I see that we have all of them say December to February that they''ll be running at the same time.","index":326,"end_time":1115.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.11,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So I just wanted to clarify on that.","index":327,"end_time":1117.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.39,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then when we start building this, are you guys able to.","index":328,"end_time":1121.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.95,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Set a.","index":329,"end_time":1124.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Different meeting where you guys can help us like, walk through it?","index":330,"end_time":1127.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.56,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Because Gab and I are pretty new to this and we want to understand how that works so that for the next campaign we can be more confident when we''re working through this.","index":331,"end_time":1138.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.28,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So.","index":332,"end_time":1139.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1138.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know if I missed anything, Gab.","index":333,"end_time":1141.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.28,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, well, great questions.","index":334,"end_time":1146.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re happy to hop on a call to help you set this up.","index":335,"end_time":1150.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for launching the campaigns, I would recommend getting started with our top of Funnel campaign and letting that run for two to three weeks and then launching the other ones and then they can run simultaneously from there.","index":336,"end_time":1171.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if you can see like the audience recommendation for these other campaigns, it''s mostly coming from like people who have interacted with the previous campaign.","index":337,"end_time":1183.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this one needs to run for a little bit so that we have enough data there.","index":338,"end_time":1188.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then it''s same for this one, so.","index":339,"end_time":1192.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or retargeting.","index":340,"end_time":1194.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s going to be people who have come on your website and read the specific blog posts already.","index":341,"end_time":1200.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you''ll need approvals for this one too, because you have to install like a, like some code on your website in order for it, like the pixel to catch who''s been going to those specific pages.","index":342,"end_time":1215.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"DOM could probably help us with that.","index":343,"end_time":1219.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.45,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just think the logic of like the top of Funnel versus the middle of Funnel, it made sense for top of Funnel.","index":344,"end_time":1227.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.57,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It would make sense to run from like December until.","index":345,"end_time":1230.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"February.","index":346,"end_time":1232.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I''m thinking February, March and maybe onward is the middle of Funnel campaign.","index":347,"end_time":1238.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we can just start.","index":348,"end_time":1242.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Well, and also just to confirm the logic, the reason it''s running for so long that top of Funnel campaign is to get the engagement to then retarget in the middle of Funnel campaign.","index":349,"end_time":1251.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And that would require some code sitting on our website.","index":350,"end_time":1255.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You said.","index":351,"end_time":1255.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Specifically from Adroll.","index":352,"end_time":1260.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"From Adroll.","index":353,"end_time":1261.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.6,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"From Adroll.","index":354,"end_time":1262.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"LinkedIn will LinkedIn should just automatically have that track because they''ll know who clicks on the links right in the platform.","index":355,"end_time":1270.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":356,"end_time":1271.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1271.24,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then if, if possible, it would be beneficial to have them running simultaneously at the same time, especially just so you can get more eyeballs on it.","index":357,"end_time":1284.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So people would hypothetically see both campaigns at the same time.","index":358,"end_time":1290.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But that that can be beneficial.","index":359,"end_time":1292.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re really on the top of their mind.","index":360,"end_time":1295.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":361,"end_time":1297.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So there should be if budget allows.","index":362,"end_time":1299.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":363,"end_time":1300.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So for AdRoll we''d have to get like a license and then get approval essentially.","index":364,"end_time":1305.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I can send over those details.","index":365,"end_time":1308.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":366,"end_time":1309.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that''d be great.","index":367,"end_time":1310.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.08,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":368,"end_time":1312.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you heard of adroll before?","index":369,"end_time":1314.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have.","index":370,"end_time":1315.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.26,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I don''t know what it does.","index":371,"end_time":1316.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s pretty okay.","index":372,"end_time":1319.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s pretty similar to like I think you use Google 6 cents.","index":373,"end_time":1324.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like those retargeting ads have you.","index":374,"end_time":1326.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We used to have a Sixth Sense license, I don''t think anymore.","index":375,"end_time":1330.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1327.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s funny you say that.","index":376,"end_time":1333.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was looking through our old audience list this morning in LinkedIn and like you could tell that it was third party supported from six sense, but yeah, no, never used Apple.","index":377,"end_time":1345.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":378,"end_time":1346.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well it''s pretty similar to that.","index":379,"end_time":1348.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Essentially it''s display ads and there''s a couple different ways you can target.","index":380,"end_time":1356.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can like upload a list of contacts of people you specifically want to use or you can use like that retargeting pixel and either like just have in general people who come to your website, you can retarget them or you can have it to specific pages.","index":381,"end_time":1371.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.629,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So where we''re getting really targeted with this thing, I think just having it focused for anyone who comes to those pages related to this, it''ll be a great way just to follow them around on the Internet.","index":382,"end_time":1383.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ve seen those ads before.","index":383,"end_time":1385.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So let''s say we ask for ad roll permission and we don''t get it, we don''t get approved.","index":384,"end_time":1394.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What can we do beyond the top of funnel campaign?","index":385,"end_time":1401.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like how would you then restructure the middle of funnel ad campaign?","index":386,"end_time":1406.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Then I would just focus on LinkedIn.","index":387,"end_time":1410.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I really recommend AdRoll because the cost is a lot less expensive than LinkedIn.","index":388,"end_time":1417.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can do a lot more with AdRoll for less money.","index":389,"end_time":1420.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like LinkedIn is one of the most expensive ad platforms out there and for good reason.","index":390,"end_time":1426.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like you''re getting a B2B audience.","index":391,"end_time":1428.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like you''re really able to get to the people you want to see.","index":392,"end_time":1431.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But it is more expensive.","index":393,"end_time":1433.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":394,"end_time":1435.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"No, that''s good justification.","index":395,"end_time":1436.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1435.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m just taking some notes.","index":396,"end_time":1438.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah, that makes sense.","index":397,"end_time":1441.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I''m hoping we get ad roll approval.","index":398,"end_time":1444.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.64,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We may even have it and I don''t know.","index":399,"end_time":1445.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"There''s a very good chance we''ll find out.","index":400,"end_time":1449.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.8,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But we can always come back to the table and be like ad rolls out.","index":401,"end_time":1454.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.72,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Let''s just see like a revised middle funnel Plan.","index":402,"end_time":1458.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, no, yeah, we can, we can adjust if that doesn''t get approved.","index":403,"end_time":1463.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":404,"end_time":1465.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.41,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right.","index":405,"end_time":1465.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1465.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s all the questions that I think I had about the paid ad campaign.","index":406,"end_time":1472.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Christina, did we cover everything?","index":407,"end_time":1473.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep, we did double checking.","index":408,"end_time":1477.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.53,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, we did.","index":409,"end_time":1478.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.73,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yep.","index":410,"end_time":1479.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1479.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And Sean, our marketing ops guy, I can''t believe I just called him that.","index":411,"end_time":1485.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But Sean worked with us.","index":412,"end_time":1487.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"He is creating the list with the template that you had linked in the document now.","index":413,"end_time":1491.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":414,"end_time":1492.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we should have a nice size list.","index":415,"end_time":1495.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.71,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I did ask like, because LinkedIn was.","index":416,"end_time":1498.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It had a pop up that was like a 10k minimum is great, that''s most optimal.","index":417,"end_time":1503.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And he was like, it''s gonna be a little bit less than 10,000.","index":418,"end_time":1507.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I was like, well, LinkedIn says that''s suboptimal.","index":419,"end_time":1510.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1507.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And so we will see how it performs, but we can always optimize as we go.","index":420,"end_time":1516.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Is he putting together a list of people to include or people to exclude or both Include people who want to.","index":421,"end_time":1526.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Target like a matched audience list on LinkedIn.","index":422,"end_time":1528.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Amazing, amazing.","index":423,"end_time":1531.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That will be finserve focused.","index":424,"end_time":1534.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1531.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So once we have the list and we have the creative assets approved, we can schedule a separate call to just walk through how we would want to set this type of campaign up, if that sounds good.","index":425,"end_time":1547.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1549.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So should we get started on creative assets or you want to chat through more details on that?","index":427,"end_time":1554.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I submitted that like ask a while ago, but I was thinking as we were talking through top of funnel, middle of funnel, like how do those creative assets, how are they different from one another?","index":428,"end_time":1567.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.35,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I guess that that would be my.","index":429,"end_time":1571.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"My one question is like, well, one, have you guys started designing?","index":430,"end_time":1574.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And two, are you designing based on the strategy that was pulled together?","index":431,"end_time":1580.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.83,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1580.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yes.","index":433,"end_time":1582.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we started some copy and I wasn''t super happy with it, so I never shared it with you because I wanted to see all the published content that you created first.","index":434,"end_time":1596.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it sounds like.","index":435,"end_time":1598.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you published everything you''re wanting to use?","index":436,"end_time":1601.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I can also.","index":437,"end_time":1604.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.83,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I''ll drop that blog link in our channel right here.","index":438,"end_time":1609.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then if you want, you are welcome to submit your name to download the actual asset.","index":439,"end_time":1615.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Or I can just like download the PDF and put it in our channel.","index":440,"end_time":1618.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.83,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Whatever you prefer.","index":441,"end_time":1619.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But that''s everything for now.","index":442,"end_time":1623.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.03,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I can also send you the email copy we landed on that Jill.","index":443,"end_time":1627.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1624.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Jill and I worked on.","index":444,"end_time":1629.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, that would be awesome.","index":445,"end_time":1631.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just to see how you''re positioning it.","index":446,"end_time":1633.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1631.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And like with our last two minutes essentially just the goal of the two campaigns would be different with the way we create the ad.","index":447,"end_time":1644.359,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So usually like with an Awareness campaign.","index":448,"end_time":1646.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1644.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s going to be more like, did you see this?","index":449,"end_time":1649.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you heard about this?","index":450,"end_time":1651.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1649.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, this is how the change is going to affect you.","index":451,"end_time":1653.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1651.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"More like just really high level.","index":452,"end_time":1654.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But then the next set of ads is going to be really focused on download our guide to see how this is going to affect you.","index":453,"end_time":1662.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s really going to be just driving into.","index":454,"end_time":1664.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Click this link so you can download the full guide.","index":455,"end_time":1668.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I like that approach, especially if they''re running concurrently.","index":456,"end_time":1674.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1669.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like you said, more eyeballs.","index":457,"end_time":1677.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It connects the message with the person of, I have heard about this and now I do need to think about it and download this guide.","index":458,"end_time":1683.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I like that logic.","index":459,"end_time":1686.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1683.74,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"What do you think?","index":460,"end_time":1687.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"No, I like that because that''s the vision that when I was chatting with Jill yesterday, like the approach on how we want it to be.","index":461,"end_time":1694.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.98,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"It''s first awareness of this is going to happen and then here''s a guide on how you can prepare for it later on.","index":462,"end_time":1703.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.94,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So this is perfect.","index":463,"end_time":1704.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1703.82,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":464,"end_time":1706.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other questions?","index":465,"end_time":1709.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I am just downloading that email copy for you and then I''ll just send you the PDF of the asset.","index":466,"end_time":1718.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":467,"end_time":1719.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1718.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":468,"end_time":1719.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1719.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not gonna make Shannon wonder who Bailey is.","index":469,"end_time":1724.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I have filled out a couple of those and then I get your emails, but I like actually getting them.","index":470,"end_time":1730.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m like, oh, this is cool.","index":471,"end_time":1731.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like seeing what you guys are doing.","index":472,"end_time":1732.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1731.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a nice to.","index":473,"end_time":1734.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.18,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s nice to see how it all connects.","index":474,"end_time":1735.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1734.22,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1736.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I gotta jump.","index":476,"end_time":1739.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1739.02,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I have a vendor meeting.","index":477,"end_time":1741.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1739.94,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So thank you, Bailey, and thank you, Igor.","index":478,"end_time":1743.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.34,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":479,"end_time":1744.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see you, I guess in two weeks.","index":480,"end_time":1745.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":481,"end_time":1745.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.37,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, bye.","index":482,"end_time":1747.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t have any other questions.","index":483,"end_time":1751.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I will get you that content and you just keep me posted on how I say from here.","index":484,"end_time":1758.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.45,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think it''s good to start dining.","index":485,"end_time":1759.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.01,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think we did put the cart before the horse a little bit on this one just because it was so last minute.","index":486,"end_time":1766.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1760.89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"From my perspective, I would have loved to have gotten the budget approved first before we came to you guys and said, hey, we need these assets.","index":487,"end_time":1774.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But yeah, in the interest of time, I just said, let me just get the ask out there and we''ll figure it out.","index":488,"end_time":1780.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s all good.","index":489,"end_time":1781.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I hope that was okay.","index":490,"end_time":1782.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1781.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we''re good.","index":491,"end_time":1784.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll get started on the copy for those ads now.","index":492,"end_time":1788.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":493,"end_time":1789.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1789.19,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get that to you guys.","index":494,"end_time":1792.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And that, that''s all from me.","index":495,"end_time":1793.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.15,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":496,"end_time":1795.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1794.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll talk again here soon.","index":497,"end_time":1796.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":498,"end_time":1797.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Thanks, friends.","index":499,"end_time":1797.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.23,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Have a good weekend.","index":500,"end_time":1798.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You too.","index":501,"end_time":1799.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-11-21T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84384090979?pwd=CWYLaJlFxbjtxp2qyx0nk6skchlVVg.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com,gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com,tim.finnigan@verisk.com,christina.bila@verisk.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com","tim.finnigan@verisk.com","christina.bila@verisk.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA24FCBSGRQ5K91S3Z9KE1WB","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed budget approval for podcast equipment; shipments en route to Chicago office for setup.","Aligned on video clip and full upload strategy for the Michelle episode across YouTube and Spotify.","Discussed guest engagement wins; Tim noted E. Health''s reposting boosted visibility and brand alignment.","Paid media campaign sequencing clarified; top-of-funnel starts December, with MoFU retargeting to follow.","Creative asset revisions for ebook finalized; assets ready pending final approval from Tim."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Budget got approved for our equipment list and all the stuff that we...","speaker":"Gab"},{"quote":"This was my favorite episode... E. Health reposted it... helped with the renewal.","speaker":"Tim Finnigan"},{"quote":"It''s all gonna get out there and I''m very excited to trickle it out.","speaker":"Gab"}],"topics":["delivery","launch","strategy","paid media","content"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-23T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Distribution**\n\nThe team finalized the podcast episode with **Michelle** and is optimizing video distribution to increase reach and engagement (08:48).\n\n- **Gab** confirmed the episode and five Spotify videos are ready, with plans to upload full videos to Spotify and short clips to YouTube, aiming to boost viewership and new subscribers through bite-sized content.\n    - Short clips have shown higher engagement and subscriber growth compared to full episodes.\n    - This dual approach balances Gab’s need for control over scheduling with broader content distribution handled by Marketers in Demand.\n    - The new workflow starts with the Michelle episode to test the process and scale from there.\n    - Tim highlighted that guest marketing teams like **E Health** and **Michelle** personally sharing posts increased interaction by over **40 actions**, improving customer relationships and renewal likelihood.\n\n- The team addressed guest scheduling challenges, noting frequent rescheduling requires Gab to maintain control over Buzzsprout uploads for flexibility (06:20).\n    - Baylee suggested the internal team handle clip posting after episodes go live to streamline workload while Gab focuses on full episode scheduling.\n    - This division aims to maintain timely releases despite shifting guest availability.\n    - The approach also fosters stronger rapport with guests and their marketing teams by having Gab plugged into scheduling and intake calls, supporting deeper collaboration and promotion.\n\n- Technical issues with asset uploads were resolved through browser tweaks, restoring smooth workflow for guest content submission via the portal (12:17).\n    - Baylee noted recent Zapier UI changes caused earlier disruptions, now fixed.\n    - This stability ensures no delays in publishing and asset sharing moving forward.\n\n\n## **Ebook Performance and Organic Marketing Assets**\n\nThe ebook launch generated over **25 downloads** with ongoing inbound interest, serving as sustainable organic support over holidays and into next year (13:20).\n\n- Gab will obtain detailed lead-to-meeting conversion data from **Sean** to evaluate inbound marketing impact and share updates in Slack.\n    - This snapshot will help assess ebook’s effectiveness in generating qualified leads.\n- Igor delivered final revisions on guest creatives including compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels, awaiting Tim’s approval to deploy (14:09).\n    - Tim praised social assets for making guests feel valued, citing positive feedback such as from the Wendy’s representative who felt spotlighted.\n    - These assets improve guest satisfaction and promote the brand widely, encouraging other clients to adopt similar practices.\n- Baylee shared the organic content visibility internally, boosting team morale by showing the broad exposure and real-world use of created materials (16:24).\n\n\n## **Paid Media Campaign Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe **paid media campaign budget** was approved by **Matt**, enabling the team to advance with the middle-of-funnel (MoFU) strategy targeting financial services (16:52).\n\n- Christina updated the target list to focus more on **finserve** sectors, refining audience alignment for better campaign results.\n- Baylee recommended a staggered launch: start with the top-of-funnel (ToFU) campaign running **December to February**, followed by MoFU and bottom-of-funnel campaigns, which will run concurrently thereafter to maximize exposure (19:03).\n    - ToFU builds awareness and collects audience data for retargeting.\n    - MoFU targets users who interacted with ToFU content or visited specific blog pages, requiring pixel tracking setup.\n    - Baylee emphasized the need for website pixel installation (AdRoll) to enable precise retargeting and improve conversion rates.\n- Gab and Christina requested a walkthrough session from Baylee’s team to build confidence in managing the campaign setup, reflecting their newer experience (18:44).\n- Discussions emphasized **AdRoll** as a cost-effective retargeting tool compared to LinkedIn’s higher ad costs, allowing broader reach within budget constraints (23:28).\n    - If AdRoll approval fails, the fallback is focusing on LinkedIn only, accepting higher costs but maintaining quality B2B targeting.\n- Sean is assembling a matched audience list of nearly **10,000 contacts**, slightly below LinkedIn’s optimal threshold, which will be tested and optimized over time (24:47).\n- Creative asset development is underway, with initial copy drafts paused until all published content is reviewed for alignment (26:20).\n    - Baylee explained ToFU ads will focus on awareness messages, while MoFU ads drive guide downloads, creating a logical funnel progression.\n    - Gab and Christina agreed this approach fits their vision, helping prospects move from general awareness to action.\n\n\n## **Equipment Procurement and Setup Planning**\n\nThe equipment budget was approved, and ordered items are shipping to the **Chicago office** for the new podcast production setup (03:03).\n\n- Becky shared a detailed list of purchased equipment in Slack to keep the team informed and prepare for setup.\n- Baylee offered to provide hands-on videography support and setup guidance, leveraging her experience to optimize lighting and positioning (03:47).\n- Gab, Baylee, and Tim will collaborate on setup and filming responsibilities, ensuring smooth production workflows.\n- This new equipment and setup aim to improve production quality and give the team more control over recording environments, supporting higher content standards.\n\n\n## **Process Improvements and Team Coordination**\n\nThe team identified gaps in guest scheduling and marketing integration, emphasizing restoring Gab’s involvement to strengthen guest and marketing team relationships (11:05).\n\n- Tim acknowledged his role as a bottleneck in providing contacts to Gab for post-episode marketing outreach.\n- Gab stressed the importance of intake calls and Riverside link sharing to build rapport and prepare guests’ marketing teams for promotion.\n- Reintegrating Gab into scheduling aims to increase marketing collaboration, improving social asset sharing and amplification.\n- This process realignment is expected to enhance content reach and renewal opportunities by leveraging guest networks more effectively.\n\n\n## **Long-term Marketing and Engagement Vision**\n\nThe team plans to use organic content as ongoing “air cover” through holidays and into the next year, supporting lead nurturing and brand presence without new spend (14:49).\n\n- Gab expressed excitement about gradually rolling out organic assets to maintain momentum.\n- Tim emphasized the value of guest social sharing as a best practice to increase brand visibility and guest satisfaction.\n- The paid campaigns are designed to complement organic efforts by driving targeted traffic and nurturing prospects through the funnel.\n- This multi-channel approach reflects a thoughtful, layered engagement strategy balancing cost, reach, and relationship-building.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Distribution","Paid Media Campaign","Equipment Setup","Ebook Marketing Assets","LinkedIn Retargeting","Guest Marketing Engagement"],"overview":"- **Podcast Production:** Finalized episode with Michelle; five Spotify videos ready; short clips drive higher engagement and subscriber growth.\n\n- **Ebook Performance:** Launched ebook generated 25+ downloads; ongoing data collection on conversion impact planned for evaluation.\n\n- **Paid Media Campaign:** Budget approved; focus on financial services; staggered launch strategy to improve exposure and audience engagement.\n\n- **Equipment Setup:** New podcast production gear ordered; team to enhance video quality and production control for future projects.\n\n- **Process Improvement:** Reintegrating Gab in guest scheduling to strengthen marketing collaboration and boost content promotion effectiveness.\n\n- **Long-term Vision:** Organic content supports lead nurturing over holidays; multi-channel strategy balances cost and relationship-building for brand visibility.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nProvide update on ebook download conversions and meetings set from form fills to Slack (13:20)\nPlug back into guest scheduling and intake processes to enhance connection with guest marketing teams (10:50)\nShare the email copy and blog link for paid media campaign creative team (26:10)\nCoordinate with Sean on LinkedIn matched audience list creation for FinServe target group (24:39)\nAdd process steps for Spotify video full uploads and YouTube clip uploads starting with the Michelle episode (08:34)\nInform marketing team of launch timing and budget approval for equipment setup (03:03)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nOffer videography and equipment setup training and support call with Gab and Tim (03:47)\nSetup Apple Podcasts ID for better podcast analytics (04:50)\nManage uploading of short podcast clips to YouTube post-episode and coordinate Spotify full video uploads (07:07)\nSupport paid media campaign setup walkthrough and clarify running strategy for TOF and MOF campaigns with Christina and Gab (18:44)\nShare AdRoll license and implementation details for middle funnel retargeting setup (21:40)\nProvide feedback and approval process support for updated guest creatives (compilation videos, LinkedIn carousels) (13:14)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nDeliver final guest creative revisions and monitor feedback for approval (13:14)\nSupport paid media campaign targeting updates and creative alignment (16:50)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nProvide final review and approval on the revised ebook guest creatives (compilation videos and LinkedIn carousels) (13:50)\nSupport coordination of guest marketing team involvement and sharing of episode content to enhance promotional reach (09:10)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nCollaborate with Gab on paid media campaign setup, target list, and creative asset review (16:50)\nParticipate in training call to understand paid campaign setup and retargeting code implementation (18:44)\n\n**Sean**\nContinue to develop matched audience list for LinkedIn targeting under Gab’s guidance (24:39)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f144a8a7-c8cc-40dc-9fce-7edb10c43c18","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
