-- Meeting: VITAL//New North Monthly (November) (2025-11-23 14:21:53+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'a3899b64-d779-4aee-afbb-d43e2125ccf8',
    '2025-11-23 14:21:53+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KARHFES76F2VZ46A7CK71NNZ',
    'VITAL//New North Monthly (November)',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Steven Frydrych","Matt Bernath","Igor Zagradjanin"}'::text[],
    1993,
    NULL,
    '{"id":"01KARHFES76F2VZ46A7CK71NNZ","title":"VITAL//New North Monthly (November)","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Content Strategy**\n\nThe podcast has shown strong growth driven by consistent episode releases and strategic content adjustments (06:50).\n\n- **Achieved 290 downloads in the last 30 days**, surpassing typical benchmarks for similar podcasts (06:50)  \n    - Several episodes have exceeded **100 downloads**, a key success indicator in the podcast space.  \n    - The episode on **common agency traps** performed particularly well, signaling audience interest in practical, industry-relevant topics.  \n    - Removing episode numbers from public titles was agreed upon to keep listings clean and accessible, as the series does not require sequential listening (07:00).  \n    - Internally, episode numbers will remain for organizational purposes, ensuring production continuity while enhancing listener experience externally.  \n- **YouTube channel growth is fueled primarily by shorts**, which attract the majority of new viewers and drive discovery (10:01)  \n    - The channel benefits from increased recommendations through “channel pages,” boosting organic exposure.  \n    - Consistent posting of diverse content types supports audience engagement and platform algorithms, reinforcing the cross-channel content approach.\n\n## **LinkedIn Outreach and Lead Generation**\n\nThe LinkedIn outreach campaign has yielded network growth but limited lead conversion, prompting a strategic reassessment (11:40).\n\n- **Current LinkedIn sequence produced positive responses but low conversion to next steps**, with a rough estimate of one conversation per ten responses (11:41)  \n    - Hand-raiser posts with lead magnets have been the most effective, directly generating some membership sales over the past year.  \n    - The existing campaign relaunch targets unresponsive connections but has not significantly increased engagement, suggesting audience or messaging fatigue.  \n    - Stephen and the team noted **live events remain the most effective conversion point**, highlighting the need to focus efforts there rather than on LinkedIn messaging alone.  \n    - A decision to pause or pivot the LinkedIn campaign is pending further brainstorming for alternative strategies aligned with proven success areas (13:11).  \n- **Future LinkedIn efforts may focus on network growth rather than lead conversion**, maintaining presence while reallocating resources to higher-impact channels (13:11)  \n    - Exploring integration with live event strategies or new audience targeting is advised to improve ROI.\n\n## **Event Planning and Promotion Strategy**\n\nUpcoming events, including a February conference, require early and coordinated promotional efforts to maximize attendance and lead capture (16:30).\n\n- **Lidapalooza event scheduled for mid-February will be promoted starting early January**, focusing on booth visits and three speaking sessions led by Stephen (16:30)  \n    - Stephen will collaborate with Bailey on copy and outreach strategy to drive appointment bookings at the booth, addressing the booth’s current lack of visual or technological appeal.  \n    - A dedicated landing page for scheduling appointments is under development by Fernando and Stephen, incorporating learnings from previous events to improve user flow and calendar management.  \n    - Social media organic posts and HubSpot email blasts to existing contacts will form the core awareness tactics, supplemented by potential GEO-targeted ads during the event.  \n    - If a filming crew is available at Lidapalooza, content capture will be leveraged for post-event promotion, enhancing long-term engagement and content assets (19:30).  \n- **Collaboration opportunities exist to strengthen event-related marketing**, with open invitation for additional creative ideas and support to improve booth traffic and lead quality (20:54).\n\n## **Website Development and Partner Collaboration**\n\nA new landing page project aims to unify service partners under one platform to enhance joint marketing and lead generation efforts (30:37).\n\n- **Plan to develop a single landing page describing complementary service partners**, featuring an interest form to streamline lead capture and referrals (30:37)  \n    - Chris Smith will manage the project, coordinating with Matt for design and content input, ensuring alignment with partner goals.  \n    - The page will not be hosted under the main company URL, reflecting its collaborative nature and distinct purpose.  \n    - This initiative is intended as a foundation for deeper integration and cooperative marketing between service companies, expanding reach and strengthening market positioning.  \n- **Implementation will start with a simple page, allowing room for growth and expansion over time**, supporting evolving partnership dynamics.\n\n## **Website Forms and Anti-Spam Measures**\n\nForm submissions on new and existing pages require management protocols to ensure quality lead capture and minimize spam (22:39).\n\n- **Form notifications for the Flywheel Effect and PR pages will be routed to Matt and May’s emails**, centralizing lead management and response accountability (22:39)  \n    - Separate URLs will be maintained for new pages, preserving current content while expanding offerings.  \n    - Anti-spam measures such as reCAPTCHA will be added to forms to reduce bot-generated junk submissions.  \n    - Monitoring will be ongoing, with the ability to adjust filters and make rules stricter if spam volume increases (23:55).  \n    - May is responsible for flagging spam issues to Bailey for technical adjustments, ensuring a smooth user experience and clean lead data.\n\n## **Trade Show Booth Design Feedback**\n\nThe booth backdrop design requires refinement to maximize visibility and impact in a crowded event environment (24:11).\n\n- **Focus to shift design emphasis to the top two-thirds of the backdrop**, which is most visible to attendees passing by (24:11)  \n    - Current designs have too much white space at the top, wasting prime visual real estate, and some include distracting imagery that diverts attention from key messages.  \n    - Preference leans toward designs with stronger text visibility and less generic photography, favoring authentic, casual images that integrators can relate to rather than staged or irrelevant visuals (27:20).  \n    - Text should be reduced to fewer, more powerful words to capture attention within about three seconds, encouraging curiosity and booth engagement (28:56).  \n    - Potential use of both side panels with consistent or wrapped designs is under consideration pending print specifications (29:38).  \n- **The goal is to create a visually compelling backdrop that sparks immediate interest and drives appointment bookings**, compensating for the booth’s lack of flashy technology or props (20:54, 28:56).  \n- **Matt and the design team will collaborate on revisions incorporating these insights**, balancing visual appeal with functional messaging.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","LinkedIn Outreach","Booth Design","Lidapalooza","Social Media Strategy","Partner Landing Page"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Achieved 290 downloads in 30 days; episodes on agency traps resonate well with listeners.  \n- **YouTube Shorts Impact:** Shorts drive new viewer engagement; diverse content supports audience retention and discovery.  \n- **LinkedIn Strategy Shift:** Low lead conversion on LinkedIn; focus on live events for better engagement and ROI.  \n- **Event Promotion Plans:** Lidapalooza in February; early promo with booth strategy, appointment landing page, and social media outreach.  \n- **Landing Page Development:** New project for service partners; aims to enhance joint marketing and streamline lead generation efforts.  \n- **Booth Design Refinement:** Design focus on top two-thirds for visibility; reduce text and use relatable images for engagement.","action_items":"\n**Matt**\nProvide feedback on booth backdrop revisions and approve final design approach (24:50)\nDiscuss appointment booking strategy with Stephen for Lidapalooza event (20:50)\nDecide on addition of call-to-action buttons linking PR and Flywheel Effect pages on current podcast page (22:50)\nMonitor form submissions for spam and communicate with May/marketing team if issues arise (23:30)\n\n**Stephen**\nCollaborate with Bailey on appointment booking copy and strategy for Lidapalooza booth (18:00)\nWork with Fernando on landing page calendar display improvements and lead generation functionality (17:50)\nSchedule a brainstorming session with Matt and Bailey to discuss LinkedIn campaign improvements or alternatives (13:50)\n\n**Bailey**\nOversee LinkedIn outreach campaign relaunch and track responses; coordinate with Matt and Stephen on strategy follow-ups (11:40)\nCoordinate with Fernando and Stephen on landing page development and event promotion plans for Lidapalooza (17:40)\nManage podcast episode title updates removing episode numbers in public listings while retaining internal organization (07:20)\nLead booth backdrop design revisions based on client feedback and coordinate with graphic designers (24:30)\nConfirm printing specifics for booth including side panels and share details with the client (29:00)\nConnect Chris Smith with Matt for new service partners landing page project handoff and management (31:00)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nLead execution and reporting on social content scheduling and creative projects (22:30)\nSupport form submission and website development queries around Flywheel Effect and PR pages (22:40)\n\n**May**\nMonitor spam/junk form submissions and inform Bailey to adjust anti-spam measures as needed (23:40)\n"},"duration":33.220001220703125,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"id":2,"name":"Matt Bernath"},{"id":3,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, baby, how''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":41.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.85,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Going great.","index":2,"end_time":42.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":44.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Busy couple weeks.","index":5,"end_time":46.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.61,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":47.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you been traveling too?","index":7,"end_time":49.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I was in Chicago last week and then we were at.","index":8,"end_time":54.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.33,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"We did two days in Phoenix this week, so just got back.","index":9,"end_time":57.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.1,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Wow.","index":10,"end_time":58.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How did the events go?","index":11,"end_time":61.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":12,"end_time":63.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.02,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Phoenix was internal.","index":13,"end_time":64.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.5,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Chicago was for ASEAN conference and had a lot of good conversations.","index":14,"end_time":69.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.1,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Got a lot of meetings booked, so successful trip.","index":15,"end_time":72.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.34,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":16,"end_time":74.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":17,"end_time":75.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I.","index":18,"end_time":75.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s good hearing you say that because I was mispronouncing that.","index":19,"end_time":79.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Asion.","index":20,"end_time":82.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a cool name.","index":21,"end_time":83.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How you guys doing?","index":22,"end_time":85.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.95,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve been doing great.","index":23,"end_time":88.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":89.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Busy over here too.","index":25,"end_time":91.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Definitely feel like a lot of companies are.","index":26,"end_time":95.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are.","index":27,"end_time":95.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s always a grind.","index":28,"end_time":97.229,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like in October they''re like, okay, let''s try and get our goals hit.","index":29,"end_time":100.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.229,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So October is always a super busy month and.","index":30,"end_time":104.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll.","index":31,"end_time":105.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll probably start slowing down here in the next few weeks.","index":32,"end_time":107.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, man, vacation start.","index":33,"end_time":112.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":113.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What''s happening, y''?","index":35,"end_time":115.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"All?","index":36,"end_time":116.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"My.","index":37,"end_time":116.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"My camera''s tripping out here, so let me move my.","index":38,"end_time":119.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Move all my goodies onto my tiny little screen over here where the camera''s working.","index":39,"end_time":124.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":40,"end_time":125.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You got a fancy two camera setup?","index":41,"end_time":128.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I just have my laptop and then my actual camera and yeah, it''s.","index":42,"end_time":134.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''m a technical technology geek, but also I spend a lot of time on zoom.","index":43,"end_time":140.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":141.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What is happening?","index":45,"end_time":144.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.23,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Lots of good stuff.","index":46,"end_time":147.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got.","index":47,"end_time":148.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got some cool stuff going on.","index":48,"end_time":150.029,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think with your account.","index":49,"end_time":152.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.029,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like you''ve been traveling lots.","index":50,"end_time":154.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Stephen was telling me you''ve booked a lot of calls, so.","index":51,"end_time":157.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s wild.","index":52,"end_time":160.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''m glad to not be.","index":53,"end_time":163.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''m done with airplanes I think for the rest of the year, which is good.","index":54,"end_time":165.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a huge one.","index":55,"end_time":167.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":169.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just hang out at home for a bit.","index":57,"end_time":170.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is nice.","index":58,"end_time":171.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":172.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"A little, a little bit of road travel, but nothing.","index":60,"end_time":174.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Nothing significant.","index":61,"end_time":175.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":176.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Last time we talked, you were coming out to Utah for like the last week of October.","index":63,"end_time":181.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did you end up coming out here?","index":64,"end_time":182.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":65,"end_time":184.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"We were in and out.","index":66,"end_time":184.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Brandon and I came, we stayed at the Grand American I think is what it was.","index":67,"end_time":190.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, that is a nice hotel.","index":68,"end_time":191.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It sort of made me feel like it was like my grandparents hotel.","index":69,"end_time":194.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":196.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But it was nice nonetheless.","index":71,"end_time":197.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"You know, it''s a different.","index":72,"end_time":198.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I. I sort of prefer a different type of luxury than.","index":73,"end_time":202.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Than that.","index":74,"end_time":202.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But it was, it was.","index":75,"end_time":203.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, nonetheless.","index":76,"end_time":204.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s like very antique.","index":77,"end_time":206.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Lots of pinks and blues.","index":78,"end_time":208.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, right, exactly.","index":79,"end_time":210.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean it''s nice, don''t get wrong.","index":80,"end_time":211.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But yeah, it was, it was a Cool experience.","index":81,"end_time":214.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I, I got to experience the freezing cold morning.","index":82,"end_time":219.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":214.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It was like, I thought, I didn''t even really comprehend that I would have to walk three blocks to the FedEx in, you know, 28 degree weather.","index":83,"end_time":227.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":84,"end_time":228.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But it was fine.","index":85,"end_time":231.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It actually felt amazing.","index":86,"end_time":232.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It was just like a nice brisk morning to walk in the sunshine.","index":87,"end_time":236.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So, yeah, it was cool.","index":88,"end_time":237.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":89,"end_time":239.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I do have a new face I want to introduce you to before I introduce Igor though.","index":90,"end_time":246.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not leaving.","index":91,"end_time":247.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Um, people are always like, are you swapping us out?","index":92,"end_time":253.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, Igor is coming on for additional support.","index":93,"end_time":255.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a lot going on with your account and I''m an account director.","index":94,"end_time":260.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not going anywhere.","index":95,"end_time":261.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m still going to be here.","index":96,"end_time":262.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But Igor is a super talented content creator and content marketer, so he''ll be able to just help keep things moving really quickly.","index":97,"end_time":273.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You will be very grateful to have his help on your account.","index":98,"end_time":276.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool, thank you.","index":99,"end_time":278.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Good to meet you, Igor.","index":100,"end_time":279.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Great to meet you.","index":101,"end_time":280.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Where are you based out of?","index":102,"end_time":283.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Europe.","index":103,"end_time":285.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":104,"end_time":286.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Whereabouts?","index":105,"end_time":287.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The Balkans region, if you''re familiar.","index":106,"end_time":290.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":288.32,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":107,"end_time":292.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Have you heard, like Serbia?","index":108,"end_time":294.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":109,"end_time":297.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":296.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s that region.","index":110,"end_time":300.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":298.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":111,"end_time":302.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Good to have you.","index":112,"end_time":303.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thanks for joining us.","index":113,"end_time":304.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve been enjoying late.","index":114,"end_time":305.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Late in the evening over there right now, isn''t it?","index":115,"end_time":308.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It''s 10pm yeah.","index":116,"end_time":310.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":308.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":311.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Cool.","index":118,"end_time":312.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":312.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.09,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"But I''ve been looking forward to this meeting, honestly.","index":120,"end_time":314.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":312.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, Igor''s been helping for a very long time, so finally we''re able to.","index":121,"end_time":321.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To get him on.","index":122,"end_time":322.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On the calendar invite.","index":123,"end_time":324.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love it.","index":124,"end_time":326.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Cool.","index":125,"end_time":326.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, well, let''s go ahead and get into some, some of your updates.","index":126,"end_time":331.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got lots of things going on.","index":127,"end_time":336.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll start off with our regular podcast updates.","index":128,"end_time":339.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll go to our LinkedIn outreach campaign, chat through some stats in our B2B, some social updates, and then chat through just additional projects that we''ve worked on over the last month.","index":129,"end_time":351.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I have a couple just thoughts and suggestions for your website.","index":130,"end_time":356.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But anything else you all want to get to today?","index":131,"end_time":359.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, two things.","index":132,"end_time":362,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I wanted to give you some feedback on the booth design.","index":133,"end_time":365.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I thought that might be easier.","index":134,"end_time":367.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":368.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"While we''re together live.","index":136,"end_time":369.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then we have a different website request that I wanted to go over with you so that I can connect you with the person who''s gonna be like the lead on that.","index":137,"end_time":380.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So.","index":138,"end_time":380.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, whenever you''re done with your stuff, we''ll cover that stuff.","index":139,"end_time":383.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Or whenever you want to go, let''s do it.","index":140,"end_time":387.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then just starting with your podcast updates, we are able to get two podcast episodes complete this one with Brian Hopkins is going to go live on Monday, and then we''re working on wrapping up two more episodes.","index":141,"end_time":401.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":402.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other.","index":143,"end_time":402.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just thoughts or questions on this.","index":144,"end_time":404.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"One?","index":145,"end_time":407.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Question for you popped into my head.","index":146,"end_time":409.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"There was a recent podcast that I started watching, and I kind of went back to some of their old episodes, and they stopped including the episode number in the title.","index":147,"end_time":420.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Is that something that people have started doing, like, just eliminating episode numbers?","index":148,"end_time":424.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yes.","index":149,"end_time":425.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":426.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so do you want us to stop including those?","index":151,"end_time":431.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you.","index":152,"end_time":432.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"If it''s, like, a best practice to not include them, then I think we should just follow the best practice.","index":153,"end_time":437.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":154,"end_time":440.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Episode numbers are really helpful if you have, like, a chronological series where, like, you need to listen to episode one for, like, the following episodes to make sense.","index":155,"end_time":451.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, your series, you could hop in at any episode, so I. I don''t think we need them.","index":156,"end_time":457.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":157,"end_time":459.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":158,"end_time":460.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And so internally, it helps with organization to have the episode numbers, but externally, I think we should just eliminate them.","index":159,"end_time":467.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":160,"end_time":468.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":161,"end_time":469.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":162,"end_time":470.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":163,"end_time":471.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Do you want us to go back retroactively and remove any of these or.","index":164,"end_time":476.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just moving forward, what do you think is best practice around that?","index":165,"end_time":480.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t see it hurting, but I also didn''t see it helping, so I don''t think it matters.","index":166,"end_time":493.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if you want things to look clean and consistent, I mean, it would take 15 minutes to remove all of them.","index":167,"end_time":499.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think, you know me, clean and consistent.","index":168,"end_time":502.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So, yeah, let''s do it.","index":169,"end_time":503.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.86,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":170,"end_time":504.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we can go.","index":171,"end_time":505.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can remove those pretty easily.","index":172,"end_time":506.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":507.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"If it''s not a lot of work, let''s do that.","index":174,"end_time":509.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, but just.","index":175,"end_time":510.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Just to confirm internally with, like, the folders of content and all that stuff, that''ll still have the episode numbers on it.","index":176,"end_time":517.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yes.","index":177,"end_time":519.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that should.","index":178,"end_time":521.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":179,"end_time":522.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s gonna be the.","index":180,"end_time":523.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The title.","index":181,"end_time":524.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The only thing that we want episode numbers eliminated from is just the title that''s posted to, like, Spotify and Apple.","index":182,"end_time":532.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.67,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, the actual podcast title.","index":183,"end_time":534.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yep.","index":184,"end_time":535.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":185,"end_time":535.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":186,"end_time":536.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":536.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll make.","index":188,"end_time":537.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll make sure that''s updated.","index":189,"end_time":538.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":190,"end_time":540.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.469,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So then, just looking at your stats, podcast has been doing really great.","index":191,"end_time":544.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So 290 downloads in the last 30 days.","index":192,"end_time":548.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a lot higher than most of the podcasts were running.","index":193,"end_time":553.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think it just comes from a lot of consistency.","index":194,"end_time":558.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you.","index":195,"end_time":559.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve had several episodes, get over a hundred, and that is, like a.","index":196,"end_time":563.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a really big benchmark that most podcasts don''t hit.","index":197,"end_time":567.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re doing really great there.","index":198,"end_time":570.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I thought it was really interesting that this episode got a lot of downloads.","index":199,"end_time":576.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This one about common agency traps.","index":200,"end_time":579.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that one''s done really well.","index":201,"end_time":581.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":202,"end_time":582.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":583.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then your YouTube channel also is continues to grow.","index":204,"end_time":589.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve gotten quite a few more views over the last 28 days.","index":205,"end_time":593.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And again, I think that''s just coming from.","index":206,"end_time":595.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re posting a lot more consistency.","index":207,"end_time":597.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You have a ton of content going out.","index":208,"end_time":600.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":209,"end_time":601.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then you''re getting most of your traffic from the shorts.","index":210,"end_time":607.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is what I''m seeing across the board.","index":211,"end_time":610.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is where a lot of traffic comes.","index":212,"end_time":612.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s where most new people find you.","index":213,"end_time":614.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, yeah, just most of that is people are coming directly to your page or they don''t know why they''re coming to your page.","index":214,"end_time":626.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then this channel, pages one is cool too.","index":215,"end_time":630.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s like similar channels to yours.","index":216,"end_time":632.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know how YouTube will like recommend your next video.","index":217,"end_time":634.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s a really good thing that you''re, you''re starting to get recommended more often.","index":218,"end_time":640.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":219,"end_time":642.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":642.699,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any questions on this?","index":221,"end_time":643.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.699,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so the Next on our LinkedIn outreach sequence, we sent a message about this yesterday, but we''ve gone through the list that we were working off of.","index":222,"end_time":659.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we did just barely launch like relaunch the campaign for anyone who didn''t accept the initial connection request.","index":223,"end_time":668.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They never got a message.","index":224,"end_time":669.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re trying again with all of those people to see if we can get a response there.","index":225,"end_time":675.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We talked about this last month.","index":226,"end_time":677.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Overall, most of the responses were positive, but they weren''t really initiating like a next step.","index":227,"end_time":685.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we did tweak the campaign a little bit, but didn''t see much of a change there.","index":228,"end_time":691.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So either I think we need to try a new audience or we should just try a different approach entirely with the messages.","index":229,"end_time":701.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know you guys are doing stuff internally as well.","index":230,"end_time":703.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Where are you seeing this be successful?","index":231,"end_time":706.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The only success we''ve seen so far.","index":232,"end_time":712.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And Steven, you can, you know, I''ll have you add to this or, or challenge it, but it feels like the only success we''ve had is when I do like hand raiser posts.","index":233,"end_time":723.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.71,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":234,"end_time":724.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you know, ask people to reply to those to get some lead magnet and, and then they''ll reply and then we''ll start a conversation and you know, a small percentage.","index":235,"end_time":736.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t have the exact data like you have, but it''s probably not far off of your data.","index":236,"end_time":739.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":740.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":238,"end_time":740.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe one out of every ten turns into a conversation and then those, you know, we have sold a couple of memberships I think over the year.","index":239,"end_time":749.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.31,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"You know, last year or two.","index":240,"end_time":751.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But that''s really the only traction we''ve had is.","index":241,"end_time":753.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Is through lead magnets on posts that I make.","index":242,"end_time":758.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":760.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.27,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And it feels like the response is really good.","index":244,"end_time":762.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.71,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And then like Matt said, the conversation.","index":245,"end_time":764.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.99,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"It''s a very, very low conversion.","index":246,"end_time":767.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.23,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"We have sold a coup.","index":247,"end_time":768.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.15,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"But I. I assume it''d be low like this.","index":248,"end_time":771.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And I thank you guys for letting me know who I need to follow up with on this campaign.","index":249,"end_time":775.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.25,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And I did.","index":250,"end_time":776.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.37,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And those didn''t lead anywhere.","index":251,"end_time":778.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.09,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"They didn''t respond to.","index":252,"end_time":779.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.05,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"There was only a few opportunities there.","index":253,"end_time":782.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.25,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":783.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It seems like from what we''ve been talking through, you tend to see a lot of success at your live events.","index":255,"end_time":790.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that usually where you see the most conversions?","index":256,"end_time":793.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":795.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":258,"end_time":796.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can.","index":259,"end_time":799.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can keep doing this if maybe like the goal is just to grow your network on LinkedIn, Matt.","index":260,"end_time":806.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But it doesn''t seem to, I mean, like, start a lot of conversations.","index":261,"end_time":812.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s a waste necessarily to do it, but it is really good if you''re just looking to grow your network.","index":262,"end_time":817.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or we can try something different, like maybe if we can plug into some of the stuff you''re doing at events and.","index":263,"end_time":825.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And help there, if that''s already an area that''s successful.","index":264,"end_time":829.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":265,"end_time":831.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"If you don''t mind, just think of some strategy stuff around this.","index":266,"end_time":836.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like it feel.","index":267,"end_time":837.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"If it feels like we now have experimented enough with this to know that it''s probably not worth the effort and energy.","index":268,"end_time":844.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.02,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":844.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":844.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":845.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And maybe redirect that to something else.","index":271,"end_time":847.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t know what that something else would be.","index":272,"end_time":849.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So you''re really good at coming up with different ideas.","index":273,"end_time":852.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So.","index":274,"end_time":853.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.71,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe just brainstorm it and let us know what you think we should do.","index":275,"end_time":858.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Or just hold a plug on it and redirect that to the stuff that is working.","index":276,"end_time":862.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":863.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":278,"end_time":864.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":279,"end_time":865.629,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":864.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"We''ll get back to you on that.","index":280,"end_time":867.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the Next is with RB2B.","index":281,"end_time":871.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is the tool we have on your website that''s helping de.","index":282,"end_time":876.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anonymize the traffic that''s coming there.","index":283,"end_time":878.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve been working with Abner on this and yeah, he''s just been approving a lot of these.","index":284,"end_time":885.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And this is where we''ve been adding new people into the campaign, so seems to be working decently.","index":285,"end_time":890.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well.","index":286,"end_time":890.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did notice that there are still a couple that haven''t been reviewed yet, so I can follow up to make sure those get reviewed so we can add them into the campaign.","index":287,"end_time":902.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":288,"end_time":904.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.8,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So then for your social updates, we have so much content.","index":289,"end_time":911.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve got lots of stuff scheduled from all of your episodes, so you can see all the ones that are scheduled on there.","index":290,"end_time":918.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re working on adding additional ones from those recent podcast episodes and blog posts.","index":291,"end_time":924.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But do you have any events coming up soon or anything that we should keep in mind for your calendar on?","index":292,"end_time":931.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We will have a workshop.","index":293,"end_time":941.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yes, that I''ll work with you on, the one that we talked about.","index":294,"end_time":945.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":946.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So once that.","index":296,"end_time":947.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Once that content is created, I''ll let you know.","index":297,"end_time":950.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.67,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then our next event after that is going to be lidapalooza, which is not until February.","index":298,"end_time":960.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like, mid.","index":299,"end_time":962.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Mid February.","index":300,"end_time":963.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":962.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":965,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ve got content scheduled through the end of December.","index":302,"end_time":969.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor, correct me if I''m wrong.","index":303,"end_time":971.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can probably start doing stuff for lidapalooza.","index":304,"end_time":975.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, just as soon as you have more information.","index":305,"end_time":977,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I. I love to get ahead on this stuff because it makes things a lot easier.","index":306,"end_time":983.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":307,"end_time":985,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":985.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I think Light of Palooza, we''re good to start, like, promoting that, you know, early January, so.","index":309,"end_time":991.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":310,"end_time":991.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"As we.","index":311,"end_time":993.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"As we get a little further into December, we should have more information.","index":312,"end_time":996.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":313,"end_time":997.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, May, if you get information sooner than that about the sessions and the days and times and stuff, then we can have them start working on that.","index":314,"end_time":1004.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"What we would want to promote for Light of Palooza is really like four things.","index":315,"end_time":1011.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Number one is our booth.","index":316,"end_time":1012.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So, you know, hey, come visit our booth.","index":317,"end_time":1014.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then Stephen will have some copy on getting people to book appointments with us.","index":318,"end_time":1021.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So, Stephen, if you could work with Bailey on that, on the strategy for.","index":319,"end_time":1027.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"For getting people to book appointments at our booth.","index":320,"end_time":1030.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then the other three things are the three sessions that I''m running.","index":321,"end_time":1034.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so may should have information on those.","index":322,"end_time":1038.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The title, the day and time, that kind of thing.","index":323,"end_time":1040.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1038.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, love that.","index":324,"end_time":1042.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do they give you a list of people that will be at the event or how do you historically, like, reach out to people?","index":325,"end_time":1050.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is this just all we''re doing?","index":326,"end_time":1051.829,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just all organic, social, or is there anything we can do?","index":327,"end_time":1055.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.829,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s socials, and we just blast everyone in HubSpot with an email.","index":328,"end_time":1064.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.55,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"So just everyone in your.","index":329,"end_time":1066.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m open to other ideas and strategies around that because we''ve done that a few times.","index":330,"end_time":1072.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1067.33,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"In addition, we''ll have to create.","index":331,"end_time":1074.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.85,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And I don''t know if the other landing page can just be altered.","index":332,"end_time":1077.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.69,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And Fernando, I don''t know if you''re already working on this with Bailey like we talked about, but we''ll need a similar landing page for the scheduling, just like we did.","index":333,"end_time":1086.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.53,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Procedure.","index":334,"end_time":1086.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.09,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1087.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":336,"end_time":1090.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Stephen, we learned some things from cd.","index":337,"end_time":1093.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Are you implementing those into the new Landing page.","index":338,"end_time":1096.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, and it''s going to be.","index":339,"end_time":1099.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.5,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And Fernando and I are working sidebar on this, but there''s going to be less of us there.","index":340,"end_time":1103.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.02,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"So we''ll be able to highlight the certain calendars and stuff.","index":341,"end_time":1107.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.82,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"And so all that''s in the works already.","index":342,"end_time":1109.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.22,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":343,"end_time":1110.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1109.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And.","index":344,"end_time":1114.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Because this could potentially be a good area where we can collaborate on if, if this is something you, you want help with, especially if you''re going to be speaking at this event, Matt.","index":345,"end_time":1127.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean there''s a lot we can do to promote it, similar to what we''ve done before with a lot of organic posts.","index":346,"end_time":1134.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I''ve also like seen people do like, if you don''t have access to a list, I''ve seen people do like GEO targeting.","index":347,"end_time":1144.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you wanted to run some ads that are just in the area where the event''s running during the time, that''s something I''ve seen be successful.","index":348,"end_time":1154.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then obviously we can do a ton of follow up.","index":349,"end_time":1157.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like if you can get.","index":350,"end_time":1158.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you know if they''ll have like a filming crew there?","index":351,"end_time":1161.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anything for the speaking events?","index":352,"end_time":1163.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Probably.","index":353,"end_time":1166.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1166.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I, yeah, I think, I think I actually know the person who will be there filming.","index":354,"end_time":1174.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1169.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":355,"end_time":1175.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":356,"end_time":1179.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If they have someone on site who films, then we can make a ton of content that you can promote afterwards.","index":357,"end_time":1186.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That stuff always, I mean it just looks so good, especially if they have like a professional there.","index":358,"end_time":1191.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Um, that''s great.","index":359,"end_time":1193.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have been noticing that people are hiring video less often, so it sounds like they have someone.","index":360,"end_time":1201.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If they don''t though, like we can maybe send over a few suggestions so you can just record it on a phone and get like a lav mic so we at least have something.","index":361,"end_time":1211.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, let me know.","index":362,"end_time":1213.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1211.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''m.","index":363,"end_time":1214.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I mean, I think, you know, at this point we''re open to suggestions.","index":364,"end_time":1216.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So if you think about ways you can collaborate, you know, it sounds like Stephen and Fernando are gathering their instructions to give to you on, you know, what to change on the landing page.","index":365,"end_time":1226.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1216.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But, but by all means, if you have ideas about, you know, the goals that we have are to get people to book appointments at the booth because our booth has nothing sexy.","index":366,"end_time":1239,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like we''re in a room of booths that have sexy technology.","index":367,"end_time":1242.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1239,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1242.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And people have no reason to come to our booth and you know, because they''re not like sitting there with a bleeding wound.","index":369,"end_time":1248.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1242.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"They''re like, oh, you guys come fix my wound.","index":370,"end_time":1250.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So, you know, we need to get them to book appointments with us.","index":371,"end_time":1254.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so maybe you and Steven can have a separate conversation about that on what he has planned and Then if you have some ideas, we''re certainly open to that.","index":372,"end_time":1263.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":373,"end_time":1264.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":374,"end_time":1264.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Stephen, if you want to book sometime in the next couple weeks, let''s.","index":375,"end_time":1267.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''d love to get your thoughts and we can brainstorm some ideas.","index":376,"end_time":1271.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":377,"end_time":1272.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.98,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Cool.","index":378,"end_time":1274.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1273.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":379,"end_time":1274.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1274.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, then I''ll kick it over to Igor to chat through these things because he''s been heading up all of these projects.","index":380,"end_time":1283.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":381,"end_time":1285.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thanks, Bailey.","index":382,"end_time":1286.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1285.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, these are some, as you could see for me, really exciting projects, and as you could see, some beautiful designs.","index":383,"end_time":1295.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1287.499,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Really nice.","index":384,"end_time":1297.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I do have a question for the Flywheel Effect page.","index":385,"end_time":1304.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1299.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So who should receive notifications for the form submission?","index":386,"end_time":1310.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1305.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So which email should that go to?","index":387,"end_time":1312.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1310.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And are we keeping the same URL as the current page?","index":388,"end_time":1316.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1313.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So that''s for development for the next stage.","index":389,"end_time":1319.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1317.03,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Both my PR page and the Flywheel Effect forms can go to my email because May manages that anyway.","index":390,"end_time":1329.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1323.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So unless May, you.","index":391,"end_time":1332.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"You want them to go to both of our emails.","index":392,"end_time":1334.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''m fine with yours.","index":393,"end_time":1337.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":394,"end_time":1338.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":395,"end_time":1339.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then regarding the URL, Igor, I''m not sure I follow the question on that one.","index":396,"end_time":1346.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I think I would suggest we should probably create a separate URL because, like, we already have a Flywheel Effect page on your website.","index":397,"end_time":1358.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1347.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think that this won''t be a replacement.","index":398,"end_time":1362.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1359.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''ll just be an additional page.","index":399,"end_time":1365.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":400,"end_time":1367.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think, similarly, we had talked about adding your PR page to the footer.","index":401,"end_time":1371.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1367.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ll do that the same for this PR page.","index":402,"end_time":1374.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just say, like, do you.","index":403,"end_time":1375.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you want to be a guest or do you want to sponsor our podcast?","index":404,"end_time":1380.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll have a separate link there.","index":405,"end_time":1381.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":406,"end_time":1382.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1382.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And it feels like, Bailey, maybe we should add a call to action button on our current page to this.","index":407,"end_time":1391.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1382.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"You know, something a little more obvious.","index":408,"end_time":1393.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1391.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"You know, want to be a guest or what.","index":409,"end_time":1395.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1394.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":410,"end_time":1396.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"On.","index":411,"end_time":1396.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1396.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"On our current podcast page.","index":412,"end_time":1398.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1396.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a great idea.","index":413,"end_time":1400.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":414,"end_time":1400.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we could add that to, like, that listing page and maybe each individual page as well, so people can find that really easily.","index":415,"end_time":1407.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":416,"end_time":1408.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":417,"end_time":1409.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And is there a way.","index":418,"end_time":1411.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"It feels like those forms could be great targets for bots.","index":419,"end_time":1416.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Is there a way to make sure that we''re not going to get a bunch of junk in those forms?","index":420,"end_time":1420.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":421,"end_time":1422.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You bring up a great point, Matt.","index":422,"end_time":1425.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s.","index":423,"end_time":1426.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s a couple things we can do to slow that down, but you can never filter it all out.","index":424,"end_time":1433.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can add, like, a recaptcha filter to try and filter out some of those bots.","index":425,"end_time":1441.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1434.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you start seeing a lot, just let us know and we can, like, try to make the rules a Bit stricter.","index":426,"end_time":1447.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, just let us know if it starts to get overwhelming.","index":427,"end_time":1450.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1447.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":428,"end_time":1451.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''ll leave that up to May, if you may.","index":429,"end_time":1453.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"If you see a bunch of junk come through on those forms, then just let Bailey know.","index":430,"end_time":1457.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1453.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":431,"end_time":1460.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So now we''ve got the designs for the backdrop.","index":432,"end_time":1465.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1466.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So my feedback on that.","index":434,"end_time":1467.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Do you mind if I share and I''ll just kind of walk through?","index":435,"end_time":1470.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Might be a little easier.","index":436,"end_time":1471.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yes.","index":437,"end_time":1472.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":438,"end_time":1477.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So overall, I think these are a good start.","index":439,"end_time":1483.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''ll tell you what I like about each one, and we can kind of combine them maybe.","index":440,"end_time":1489.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So one of the things that comes to mind about a backdrop is we''re going to have people and, like, chairs and stuff in front of them.","index":441,"end_time":1497.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1489.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So the backdrop is at the back of our booth, and then we have, like, you know, cocktail tables and stuff in front of it.","index":442,"end_time":1505.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So it feels like we should.","index":443,"end_time":1507.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"We should use the top two thirds.","index":444,"end_time":1510.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like, really emphasize the top two thirds of the backdrop and sort of de.","index":445,"end_time":1516.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Emphasize whatever''s down here.","index":446,"end_time":1517.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1516.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so, like, a lot of this white space towards the top feels like wasted space because that''s.","index":447,"end_time":1523.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"That''s the most visible part of the backdrop when people are walking by.","index":448,"end_time":1528.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":449,"end_time":1529.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And so I think just shifting the design a little bit to more emphasize the top.","index":450,"end_time":1534.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1530.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I actually like the visual design of these two a little bit better than I like.","index":451,"end_time":1539.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"These two feel sort of plain.","index":452,"end_time":1541.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, this one''s not bad, but this one emphasizes this random dude so much that, like, literally my eyes are just pulled into him and not the text where.","index":453,"end_time":1553.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Here.","index":454,"end_time":1553.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"My eyes are more pulled to the text.","index":455,"end_time":1555.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I kind of like the visual design of these two better.","index":456,"end_time":1558.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But something, I guess, just needs to shift to create more space for the text.","index":457,"end_time":1562.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1558.57,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"A little bit higher, and then the.","index":458,"end_time":1566.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The.","index":459,"end_time":1569.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1568.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t know how to better say this, but it feels like we need more impact with less reading.","index":460,"end_time":1578.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1569.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":461,"end_time":1579.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"People are walking by, and, you know, we get, like, I don''t know, three seconds to capture them.","index":462,"end_time":1584.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1579.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I love, like, the headline.","index":463,"end_time":1586.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I think captures them really well, but I think the brain goes into fatigue mode as it starts to digest the rest of it.","index":464,"end_time":1592.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.31,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I wonder if we could even just pare that down more.","index":465,"end_time":1595.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1592.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And I don''t know.","index":466,"end_time":1597.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1597.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t know how to do that, but that''s really the piece.","index":467,"end_time":1602.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Those are the pieces that come up for me.","index":468,"end_time":1606.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1603.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Oh, and the last one is.","index":469,"end_time":1608.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1607.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t love.","index":470,"end_time":1609.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1609.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I love the people.","index":471,"end_time":1610.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.049,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like, I think people are important.","index":472,"end_time":1612.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1611.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t love the, like, generic photos.","index":473,"end_time":1616.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I''m wondering if we could find some of, like, go back through our photos and have you use some of ours.","index":474,"end_time":1621.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t necessarily need to be the face of it, but you could use me as the face of it.","index":475,"end_time":1627.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like, I''m, you know, I''m okay with that too.","index":476,"end_time":1629.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":477,"end_time":1631.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1630.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you could find some.","index":478,"end_time":1634.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Just because none of these.","index":479,"end_time":1635.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1634.23,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I think when integrators see these images, they don''t see themselves in these images.","index":480,"end_time":1640.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, I know we''ve talked before.","index":481,"end_time":1642.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You were like, it''s construction without the hard hats and vests.","index":482,"end_time":1646.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1643.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s more casual.","index":483,"end_time":1648.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Casual.","index":484,"end_time":1649.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Less posed, maybe.","index":485,"end_time":1652.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":486,"end_time":1654.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that, that would be ideal.","index":487,"end_time":1658.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1654.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like of all of them, this guy''s probably the closest.","index":488,"end_time":1661.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1658.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Other than the fact that I think he''s on a flip phone, but I think he''s probably, he''s probably the closest.","index":489,"end_time":1670.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":490,"end_time":1671.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And do you feel like there''s too much white or do you like that?","index":491,"end_time":1677.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, it''s going to be backlit.","index":492,"end_time":1679.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":493,"end_time":1680.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I think the white actually, and I don''t.","index":494,"end_time":1683.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"This is a, this is a wild ass guess, but I''m gonna, I''m thinking the white probably isn''t ideal for backlit because it almost might be too bright.","index":495,"end_time":1690.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.11,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But.","index":496,"end_time":1692.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But I don''t know.","index":497,"end_time":1694.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1693.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I think what I, what I can tell you is this is too much green.","index":498,"end_time":1699.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":499,"end_time":1700.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right.","index":500,"end_time":1701.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.83,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so I think this is like a good balance of white versus not white.","index":501,"end_time":1706.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But I think we just need to somehow shift the design to emphasize the text up higher.","index":502,"end_time":1714.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t, I don''t know.","index":503,"end_time":1716.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.91,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"That''s.","index":504,"end_time":1716.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"This is.","index":505,"end_time":1717.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":506,"end_time":1718.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, I''m good at telling you what I don''t like, but I''m not good at giving you any further direction.","index":507,"end_time":1722.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1718.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''ve already got lots of ideas, so.","index":508,"end_time":1725.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1723.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":509,"end_time":1725.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no, no, there''s plenty.","index":510,"end_time":1727.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I almost feel like the, the.","index":511,"end_time":1730.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1728.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"This one is a, is probably the best layout.","index":512,"end_time":1733.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1730.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":513,"end_time":1734.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Minus, you know, the random dude.","index":514,"end_time":1736.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1734.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But like, I think as far as the text layout, this feels the best because the most useful stuff is in the top two thirds.","index":515,"end_time":1745.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":516,"end_time":1745.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would you be open to using less text?","index":517,"end_time":1750.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":518,"end_time":1751.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":519,"end_time":1752.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1752.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, like more pointed, powerful text.","index":520,"end_time":1757.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1753.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":521,"end_time":1758.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1757.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":522,"end_time":1759.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1758.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then you really just want them to stop and go.","index":523,"end_time":1761.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like, what do you guys do?","index":524,"end_time":1763.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1761.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Because as soon as they do.","index":525,"end_time":1764.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"As soon as they just stop.","index":526,"end_time":1765.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1764.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And we want this to just generate curiosity as soon as they stop and go.","index":527,"end_time":1769.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1765.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like we want to give them enough information that they think they know what we do and then have them sort of like ask for a little bit more.","index":528,"end_time":1777.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":529,"end_time":1778.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"May, would you mind letting Brandon and Graham know that I might be a little late?","index":530,"end_time":1782.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Cool, thank you.","index":531,"end_time":1784.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then do you know do we get two side panels on this thing?","index":532,"end_time":1790.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I think we have both sides that we can print on.","index":533,"end_time":1794.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Right.","index":534,"end_time":1794.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''ll need to double check the print specs.","index":535,"end_time":1800.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1797.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I''ll look into that.","index":536,"end_time":1804.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":537,"end_time":1806.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah, so if we do have two sides, I think we might want to put just the same thing on either side or, I don''t know, wrap part of the design around one side.","index":538,"end_time":1815.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1806.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I''ll look for your guys suggestion on that.","index":539,"end_time":1818.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":540,"end_time":1821.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we will, we''ll work on those revisions, but thanks for reviewing that.","index":541,"end_time":1827.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1822.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":542,"end_time":1829.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Thank you guys for the ideas.","index":543,"end_time":1830.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1829.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":544,"end_time":1831.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then I think last we just have some website stuff.","index":545,"end_time":1836.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1833.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know you said you wanted to do some.","index":546,"end_time":1839.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you said unique stuff on your website.","index":547,"end_time":1841.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, yeah, unique in that.","index":548,"end_time":1844.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So we have a bunch of partners in our industry, we''ll call them service partners just for easy description.","index":549,"end_time":1854.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"There are a bunch of other service companies and we are all complimentary.","index":550,"end_time":1859.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1854.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And what we''ve recognized is that we want to work together more cohesively.","index":551,"end_time":1865.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And the first step is like a website that shows kind of all of our services.","index":552,"end_time":1870.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1865.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so what we''re going to do with this website is I think it''s really just going to be a landing page that kind of explains what each of us does and then a form that they can fill out that would express interest in, you know, one or more of our services.","index":553,"end_time":1888.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I don''t have any further direction beyond that right now, but I at least wanted to give you the heads up.","index":554,"end_time":1896.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1890.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"We''re gonna pay for it and then we''re gonna, you know, get reimbursed by the other people.","index":555,"end_time":1900.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1896.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And so it''s not.","index":556,"end_time":1902.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1901.209,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And it''s not gonna be on vitals URL.","index":557,"end_time":1904.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1902.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"I don''t even know what URL is going to be on, but.","index":558,"end_time":1908.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1904.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But I want to pair you up with Chris Smith, who''s going to be the project manager on the project.","index":559,"end_time":1914.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1908.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"That way you and he can start talking about whatever and then, you know, you''ll work with him to.","index":560,"end_time":1921.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1915.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"On the design and then we''ll.","index":561,"end_time":1924.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1922.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Like I said, we''ll pay for it.","index":562,"end_time":1925.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1924.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":563,"end_time":1926.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That might be the easiest way to go.","index":564,"end_time":1928.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1926.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay.","index":565,"end_time":1929.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1929.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great.","index":566,"end_time":1930.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1929.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That should be pretty simple.","index":567,"end_time":1932.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s just a single page, so.","index":568,"end_time":1934.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":569,"end_time":1934.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1934.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if it ends up being a couple of pages or whatever, that''s fine too.","index":570,"end_time":1938.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1935.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"But we''re going to start there and then I''m sure eventually it will grow.","index":571,"end_time":1941.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1938.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":572,"end_time":1944.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1943.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great then that''s always good to have a place for all your partners and content to live.","index":573,"end_time":1950.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1944.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":574,"end_time":1951.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1950.65,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":575,"end_time":1951.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1951.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"So I''ll give you kind of the purpose behind it.","index":576,"end_time":1954.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1951.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"The purpose behind it, again, is for all of us to sort of start working together and see what that looks like.","index":577,"end_time":1958.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1954.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"And then we will use this as a landing page for integrators to go when they want to, you know, help their business, and then they can, you know, complete that form.","index":578,"end_time":1970.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1958.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":579,"end_time":1972.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1971.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":580,"end_time":1973.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1972.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Well, anything else?","index":581,"end_time":1974.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1973.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know we''re a couple minutes over.","index":582,"end_time":1976.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1974.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I''m good.","index":583,"end_time":1979.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1978.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Anybody else from the team have anything?","index":584,"end_time":1981.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1980.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":585,"end_time":1985.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, thanks, everyone, for hopping on today.","index":586,"end_time":1987.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, thank you, guys.","index":587,"end_time":1989.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1988.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath"},{"text":"We''ll see you guys.","index":588,"end_time":1991.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1989.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":589,"end_time":1991.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1991.1,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych"}],"dateString":"2025-11-23T14:21:53.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KARHFES76F2VZ46A7CK71NNZ","organizer_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Completed two new podcast episodes; one featuring Brian Hopkins scheduled to go live Monday.","Agreed to stop showing episode numbers in podcast titles to align with industry best practices.","Baylee introduced Igor as support to accelerate account work; Matt confirmed positive reception.","Team discussed refining event booth design with clearer layout and less dense copy up top.","LinkedIn campaign under review; team evaluating pivot toward event-focused lead strategies."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Igor is a super talented content creator and content marketer, so he''ll be able to just help keep things moving really quickly.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Cool, thank you. Good to meet you, Igor.","speaker":"Matt Bernath"},{"quote":"Podcast has been doing really great. So 290 downloads in the last 30 days.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["podcast","events","social","content","design","strategy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-23T00:23:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Content Strategy**\n\nThe podcast has shown strong growth driven by consistent episode releases and strategic content adjustments (06:50).\n\n- **Achieved 290 downloads in the last 30 days**, surpassing typical benchmarks for similar podcasts (06:50)  \n    - Several episodes have exceeded **100 downloads**, a key success indicator in the podcast space.  \n    - The episode on **common agency traps** performed particularly well, signaling audience interest in practical, industry-relevant topics.  \n    - Removing episode numbers from public titles was agreed upon to keep listings clean and accessible, as the series does not require sequential listening (07:00).  \n    - Internally, episode numbers will remain for organizational purposes, ensuring production continuity while enhancing listener experience externally.  \n- **YouTube channel growth is fueled primarily by shorts**, which attract the majority of new viewers and drive discovery (10:01)  \n    - The channel benefits from increased recommendations through “channel pages,” boosting organic exposure.  \n    - Consistent posting of diverse content types supports audience engagement and platform algorithms, reinforcing the cross-channel content approach.\n\n## **LinkedIn Outreach and Lead Generation**\n\nThe LinkedIn outreach campaign has yielded network growth but limited lead conversion, prompting a strategic reassessment (11:40).\n\n- **Current LinkedIn sequence produced positive responses but low conversion to next steps**, with a rough estimate of one conversation per ten responses (11:41)  \n    - Hand-raiser posts with lead magnets have been the most effective, directly generating some membership sales over the past year.  \n    - The existing campaign relaunch targets unresponsive connections but has not significantly increased engagement, suggesting audience or messaging fatigue.  \n    - Stephen and the team noted **live events remain the most effective conversion point**, highlighting the need to focus efforts there rather than on LinkedIn messaging alone.  \n    - A decision to pause or pivot the LinkedIn campaign is pending further brainstorming for alternative strategies aligned with proven success areas (13:11).  \n- **Future LinkedIn efforts may focus on network growth rather than lead conversion**, maintaining presence while reallocating resources to higher-impact channels (13:11)  \n    - Exploring integration with live event strategies or new audience targeting is advised to improve ROI.\n\n## **Event Planning and Promotion Strategy**\n\nUpcoming events, including a February conference, require early and coordinated promotional efforts to maximize attendance and lead capture (16:30).\n\n- **Lidapalooza event scheduled for mid-February will be promoted starting early January**, focusing on booth visits and three speaking sessions led by Stephen (16:30)  \n    - Stephen will collaborate with Bailey on copy and outreach strategy to drive appointment bookings at the booth, addressing the booth’s current lack of visual or technological appeal.  \n    - A dedicated landing page for scheduling appointments is under development by Fernando and Stephen, incorporating learnings from previous events to improve user flow and calendar management.  \n    - Social media organic posts and HubSpot email blasts to existing contacts will form the core awareness tactics, supplemented by potential GEO-targeted ads during the event.  \n    - If a filming crew is available at Lidapalooza, content capture will be leveraged for post-event promotion, enhancing long-term engagement and content assets (19:30).  \n- **Collaboration opportunities exist to strengthen event-related marketing**, with open invitation for additional creative ideas and support to improve booth traffic and lead quality (20:54).\n\n## **Website Development and Partner Collaboration**\n\nA new landing page project aims to unify service partners under one platform to enhance joint marketing and lead generation efforts (30:37).\n\n- **Plan to develop a single landing page describing complementary service partners**, featuring an interest form to streamline lead capture and referrals (30:37)  \n    - Chris Smith will manage the project, coordinating with Matt for design and content input, ensuring alignment with partner goals.  \n    - The page will not be hosted under the main company URL, reflecting its collaborative nature and distinct purpose.  \n    - This initiative is intended as a foundation for deeper integration and cooperative marketing between service companies, expanding reach and strengthening market positioning.  \n- **Implementation will start with a simple page, allowing room for growth and expansion over time**, supporting evolving partnership dynamics.\n\n## **Website Forms and Anti-Spam Measures**\n\nForm submissions on new and existing pages require management protocols to ensure quality lead capture and minimize spam (22:39).\n\n- **Form notifications for the Flywheel Effect and PR pages will be routed to Matt and May’s emails**, centralizing lead management and response accountability (22:39)  \n    - Separate URLs will be maintained for new pages, preserving current content while expanding offerings.  \n    - Anti-spam measures such as reCAPTCHA will be added to forms to reduce bot-generated junk submissions.  \n    - Monitoring will be ongoing, with the ability to adjust filters and make rules stricter if spam volume increases (23:55).  \n    - May is responsible for flagging spam issues to Bailey for technical adjustments, ensuring a smooth user experience and clean lead data.\n\n## **Trade Show Booth Design Feedback**\n\nThe booth backdrop design requires refinement to maximize visibility and impact in a crowded event environment (24:11).\n\n- **Focus to shift design emphasis to the top two-thirds of the backdrop**, which is most visible to attendees passing by (24:11)  \n    - Current designs have too much white space at the top, wasting prime visual real estate, and some include distracting imagery that diverts attention from key messages.  \n    - Preference leans toward designs with stronger text visibility and less generic photography, favoring authentic, casual images that integrators can relate to rather than staged or irrelevant visuals (27:20).  \n    - Text should be reduced to fewer, more powerful words to capture attention within about three seconds, encouraging curiosity and booth engagement (28:56).  \n    - Potential use of both side panels with consistent or wrapped designs is under consideration pending print specifications (29:38).  \n- **The goal is to create a visually compelling backdrop that sparks immediate interest and drives appointment bookings**, compensating for the booth’s lack of flashy technology or props (20:54, 28:56).  \n- **Matt and the design team will collaborate on revisions incorporating these insights**, balancing visual appeal with functional messaging.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","LinkedIn Outreach","Booth Design","Lidapalooza","Social Media Strategy","Partner Landing Page"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Achieved 290 downloads in 30 days; episodes on agency traps resonate well with listeners.  \n- **YouTube Shorts Impact:** Shorts drive new viewer engagement; diverse content supports audience retention and discovery.  \n- **LinkedIn Strategy Shift:** Low lead conversion on LinkedIn; focus on live events for better engagement and ROI.  \n- **Event Promotion Plans:** Lidapalooza in February; early promo with booth strategy, appointment landing page, and social media outreach.  \n- **Landing Page Development:** New project for service partners; aims to enhance joint marketing and streamline lead generation efforts.  \n- **Booth Design Refinement:** Design focus on top two-thirds for visibility; reduce text and use relatable images for engagement.","action_items":"\n**Matt**\nProvide feedback on booth backdrop revisions and approve final design approach (24:50)\nDiscuss appointment booking strategy with Stephen for Lidapalooza event (20:50)\nDecide on addition of call-to-action buttons linking PR and Flywheel Effect pages on current podcast page (22:50)\nMonitor form submissions for spam and communicate with May/marketing team if issues arise (23:30)\n\n**Stephen**\nCollaborate with Bailey on appointment booking copy and strategy for Lidapalooza booth (18:00)\nWork with Fernando on landing page calendar display improvements and lead generation functionality (17:50)\nSchedule a brainstorming session with Matt and Bailey to discuss LinkedIn campaign improvements or alternatives (13:50)\n\n**Bailey**\nOversee LinkedIn outreach campaign relaunch and track responses; coordinate with Matt and Stephen on strategy follow-ups (11:40)\nCoordinate with Fernando and Stephen on landing page development and event promotion plans for Lidapalooza (17:40)\nManage podcast episode title updates removing episode numbers in public listings while retaining internal organization (07:20)\nLead booth backdrop design revisions based on client feedback and coordinate with graphic designers (24:30)\nConfirm printing specifics for booth including side panels and share details with the client (29:00)\nConnect Chris Smith with Matt for new service partners landing page project handoff and management (31:00)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nLead execution and reporting on social content scheduling and creative projects (22:30)\nSupport form submission and website development queries around Flywheel Effect and PR pages (22:40)\n\n**May**\nMonitor spam/junk form submissions and inform Bailey to adjust anti-spam measures as needed (23:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c8b4cbcf-0ba8-492a-b908-83cba9a2de39","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
