INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: VITAL//New North Monthly (November)',
  '## **Podcast Performance and Content Strategy**

The podcast has shown strong growth driven by consistent episode releases and strategic content adjustments (06:50).

- **Achieved 290 downloads in the last 30 days**, surpassing typical benchmarks for similar podcasts (06:50)  
    - Several episodes have exceeded **100 downloads**, a key success indicator in the podcast space.  
    - The episode on **common agency traps** performed particularly well, signaling audience interest in practical, industry-relevant topics.  
    - Removing episode numbers from public titles was agreed upon to keep listings clean and accessible, as the series does not require sequential listening (07:00).  
    - Internally, episode numbers will remain for organizational purposes, ensuring production continuity while enhancing listener experience externally.  
- **YouTube channel growth is fueled primarily by shorts**, which attract the majority of new viewers and drive discovery (10:01)  
    - The channel benefits from increased recommendations through “channel pages,” boosting organic exposure.  
    - Consistent posting of diverse content types supports audience engagement and platform algorithms, reinforcing the cross-channel content approach.

## **LinkedIn Outreach and Lead Generation**

The LinkedIn outreach campaign has yielded network growth but limited lead conversion, prompting a strategic reassessment (11:40).

- **Current LinkedIn sequence produced positive responses but low conversion to next steps**, with a rough estimate of one conversation per ten responses (11:41)  
    - Hand-raiser posts with lead magnets have been the most effective, directly generating some membership sales over the past year.  
    - The existing campaign relaunch targets unresponsive connections but has not significantly increased engagement, suggesting audience or messaging fatigue.  
    - Stephen and the team noted **live events remain the most effective conversion point**, highlighting the need to focus efforts there rather than on LinkedIn messaging alone.  
    - A decision to pause or pivot the LinkedIn campaign is pending further brainstorming for alternative strategies aligned with proven success areas (13:11).  
- **Future LinkedIn efforts may focus on network growth rather than lead conversion**, maintaining presence while reallocating resources to higher-impact channels (13:11)  
    - Exploring integration with live event strategies or new audience targeting is advised to improve ROI.

## **Event Planning and Promotion Strategy**

Upcoming events, including a February conference, require early and coordinated promotional efforts to maximize attendance and lead capture (16:30).

- **Lidapalooza event scheduled for mid-February will be promoted starting early January**, focusing on booth visits and three speaking sessions led by Stephen (16:30)  
    - Stephen will collaborate with Bailey on copy and outreach strategy to drive appointment bookings at the booth, addressing the booth’s current lack of visual or technological appeal.  
    - A dedicated landing page for scheduling appointments is under development by Fernando and Stephen, incorporating learnings from previous events to improve user flow and calendar management.  
    - Social media organic posts and HubSpot email blasts to existing contacts will form the core awareness tactics, supplemented by potential GEO-targeted ads during the event.  
    - If a filming crew is available at Lidapalooza, content capture will be leveraged for post-event promotion, enhancing long-term engagement and content assets (19:30).  
- **Collaboration opportunities exist to strengthen event-related marketing**, with open invitation for additional creative ideas and support to improve booth traffic and lead quality (20:54).

## **Website Development and Partner Collaboration**

A new landing page project aims to unify service partners under one platform to enhance joint marketing and lead generation efforts (30:37).

- **Plan to develop a single landing page describing complementary service partners**, featuring an interest form to streamline lead capture and referrals (30:37)  
    - Chris Smith will manage the project, coordinating with Matt for design and content input, ensuring alignment with partner goals.  
    - The page will not be hosted under the main company URL, reflecting its collaborative nature and distinct purpose.  
    - This initiative is intended as a foundation for deeper integration and cooperative marketing between service companies, expanding reach and strengthening market positioning.  
- **Implementation will start with a simple page, allowing room for growth and expansion over time**, supporting evolving partnership dynamics.

## **Website Forms and Anti-Spam Measures**

Form submissions on new and existing pages require management protocols to ensure quality lead capture and minimize spam (22:39).

- **Form notifications for the Flywheel Effect and PR pages will be routed to Matt and May’s emails**, centralizing lead management and response accountability (22:39)  
    - Separate URLs will be maintained for new pages, preserving current content while expanding offerings.  
    - Anti-spam measures such as reCAPTCHA will be added to forms to reduce bot-generated junk submissions.  
    - Monitoring will be ongoing, with the ability to adjust filters and make rules stricter if spam volume increases (23:55).  
    - May is responsible for flagging spam issues to Bailey for technical adjustments, ensuring a smooth user experience and clean lead data.

## **Trade Show Booth Design Feedback**

The booth backdrop design requires refinement to maximize visibility and impact in a crowded event environment (24:11).

- **Focus to shift design emphasis to the top two-thirds of the backdrop**, which is most visible to attendees passing by (24:11)  
    - Current designs have too much white space at the top, wasting prime visual real estate, and some include distracting imagery that diverts attention from key messages.  
    - Preference leans toward designs with stronger text visibility and less generic photography, favoring authentic, casual images that integrators can relate to rather than staged or irrelevant visuals (27:20).  
    - Text should be reduced to fewer, more powerful words to capture attention within about three seconds, encouraging curiosity and booth engagement (28:56).  
    - Potential use of both side panels with consistent or wrapped designs is under consideration pending print specifications (29:38).  
- **The goal is to create a visually compelling backdrop that sparks immediate interest and drives appointment bookings**, compensating for the booth’s lack of flashy technology or props (20:54, 28:56).  
- **Matt and the design team will collaborate on revisions incorporating these insights**, balancing visual appeal with functional messaging.',
  '2025-11-23 14:21:53+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide feedback on booth backdrop revisions and approve final design approach (24:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss appointment booking strategy with Stephen for Lidapalooza event (20:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Decide on addition of call-to-action buttons linking PR and Flywheel Effect pages on current podcast page (22:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor form submissions for spam and communicate with May/marketing team if issues arise (23:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Bailey on appointment booking copy and strategy for Lidapalooza booth (18:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Work with Fernando on landing page calendar display improvements and lead generation functionality (17:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule a brainstorming session with Matt and Bailey to discuss LinkedIn campaign improvements or alternatives (13:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Oversee LinkedIn outreach campaign relaunch and track responses; coordinate with Matt and Stephen on strategy follow-ups (11:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Fernando and Stephen on landing page development and event promotion plans for Lidapalooza (17:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage podcast episode title updates removing episode numbers in public listings while retaining internal organization (07:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Lead booth backdrop design revisions based on client feedback and coordinate with graphic designers (24:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm printing specifics for booth including side panels and share details with the client (29:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Connect Chris Smith with Matt for new service partners landing page project handoff and management (31:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Lead execution and reporting on social content scheduling and creative projects (22:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Support form submission and website development queries around Flywheel Effect and PR pages (22:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor spam/junk form submissions and inform Bailey to adjust anti-spam measures as needed (23:40)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
