-- Meeting: Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting (2025-11-20 17:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ade9bb8a-fde3-4756-a63e-11ce7f227292',
    '2025-11-20 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9Z9ZTRNW3F6DGZ0MHY79Y9Z',
    'Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Lou Bogani","Nathalie Mintjens","Roz"}'::text[],
    1486,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1',
    '{"id":"01K9Z9ZTRNW3F6DGZ0MHY79Y9Z","title":"Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Guide Design and Template Improvements**\n\nThe team is finalizing the sales guide design to improve usability and visual consistency while streamlining ongoing content updates.\n\n- **Lou Bogani presented multiple table of contents design iterations** featuring variations with images, tabs, and logos to maintain brand alignment without overwhelming the layout (12:48)  \n    - Roz preferred the design with an image on the left and a left-side bar, noting it fits better with existing branding  \n    - They agreed to remove the red numbered boxes on the right, increasing font size on section headers to simplify appearance  \n    - Lou will adjust the tab width and reduce the balloon graphic size to avoid distracting from titles  \n    - Roz emphasized balancing visual appeal with clarity to avoid creating a new design system that conflicts with current branding\n\n- **Title page designs were reviewed with focus on layout and imagery** to maintain brand coherence while allowing flexibility for content length (15:29)  \n    - Roz requested versions both with and without the balloon graphic, suggesting adding the product image as an alternative  \n    - Lou committed to providing three versions: smaller balloon with narrow tab, product image replacing balloon, and product image without computer mockup for better detail visibility  \n    - Roz explained the move away from computer mockups to larger standalone product images improves clarity across all product presentations\n\n- **Roz highlighted the importance of making future content updates easier** by transferring the Battle Card template from Illustrator to InDesign after finalizing design (07:24)  \n    - Lou agreed to convert the final template to InDesign to facilitate quick content changes and reduce editing friction  \n    - Roz noted Ricoh’s detailed wording reviews require flexibility in making small text changes rapidly  \n    - This shift will streamline future updates and allow smoother collaboration between design and content teams\n\n- **The refreshed sales guide aligns with ongoing product rebranding efforts** and supports upcoming launches for Optimizer, Info Print Manager, and RPD (22:15)  \n    - Roz shared a plan to test the animated video and sales guide with Optimizer first before extending to other products  \n    - Nathalie confirmed graphics for the storyboard will be delivered today to stay on track for end-of-month deadlines (10:46)  \n    - The team acknowledged this phased rollout reduces risk and gathers feedback to improve subsequent launches\n\n## **Product Marketing Content and Launch Coordination**\n\nThe team is managing content finalization for the Optimizer product launch while preparing for subsequent product marketing efforts.\n\n- **Roz is close to completing the Optimizer Battle Card content, aiming for end-of-month readiness** to meet tight launch schedules (11:12)  \n    - The team is incorporating feedback from multiple stakeholders to refine messaging and ensure clarity  \n    - Roz emphasized the need to avoid delays due to prolonged content discussions, highlighting the importance of quick reviews  \n    - Once finalized, this Battle Card will serve as the template for other product marketing collateral, improving consistency\n\n- **Nathalie and Lou are collaborating closely to finalize graphic assets and design iterations** supporting the Optimizer launch and future campaigns (24:01)  \n    - Nathalie will send finalized graphics to Roz for review, ensuring visuals align with brand guidelines and messaging  \n    - Lou will incorporate final design feedback and prepare versions for executive review by Linea to secure approvals  \n    - Roz stressed maintaining momentum after Optimizer to quickly move on to Info Print Manager and RPD launches\n\n- **The team is balancing speed and quality in deliverables to support three back-to-back product launches** without slipping on deadlines (11:12)  \n    - Roz noted the complexity of aligning look and feel while integrating new design elements is causing some delays  \n    - They are using the Optimizer project as a test case to refine processes and tools for subsequent launches  \n    - This approach aims to reduce rework and improve efficiency across the product marketing pipeline\n\n## **Process and Tool Improvements for Design Workflow**\n\nShifting design templates to more flexible tools will reduce friction in content updates and improve responsiveness to feedback.\n\n- **Moving Battle Card templates from Illustrator to InDesign will streamline content edits** and reduce the manual work involved in adding links and formatting (07:24)  \n    - Roz described Illustrator as cumbersome for text changes and link management, impacting turnaround times  \n    - Lou confirmed willingness to convert templates once designs are finalized to improve operational efficiency  \n    - This change will empower marketing teams to make quick copy tweaks without design team bottlenecks\n\n- **Use of flexible icon sets in PowerPoint was confirmed as successful** to ease slide creation and improve visual consistency (07:19)  \n    - Roz explained that the new line drawing icons can be pulled apart and used on different backgrounds for greater versatility  \n    - This flexibility reduces design iteration time and supports accessibility-related updates  \n    - The positive reception indicates adoption of reusable assets is helping standardize presentations\n\n- **The team is mindful of balancing visual refresh with brand consistency to avoid user confusion** (13:50)  \n    - Lou kept design changes subtle to maintain continuity with existing brand elements  \n    - Roz highlighted the importance of familiar layouts for user comfort and easier adoption  \n    - This philosophy supports better market positioning by strengthening brand recognition while updating aesthetics\n\n## **Long-Term Product Marketing Strategy and Vision**\n\nThe ongoing product marketing refreshes aim to support multi-product launches with consistent, user-friendly materials that resonate with customers.\n\n- **Roz outlined a phased rollout plan for animated videos and sales guides across three key products** to build momentum and gather user feedback (11:36)  \n    - Starting with Optimizer allows the team to refine messaging based on real reactions before Info Print Manager and RPD launches  \n    - This strategic sequencing reduces risk and ensures higher quality collateral for later launches  \n    - The approach reflects a vision to create scalable marketing assets adaptable across product lines\n\n- **The refreshed collateral supports rebranding efforts aligned with current market positioning** to strengthen competitive differentiation (21:49)  \n    - Roz noted many products are undergoing rebranding, making this the ideal time to update sales materials  \n    - Lou’s designs integrate brand guide colors and elements to maintain a unified look  \n    - This alignment will help customers easily identify the brand and its evolving offerings\n\n- **The team is focused on creating materials that aid sales and marketing teams in communicating product value clearly** (12:48)  \n    - Clear, clean layouts with linked navigation and flexible imagery will improve user engagement  \n    - Removing distracting elements like numbered boxes enhances readability and professionalism  \n    - This user-centric approach supports better sales outcomes and faster onboarding of new team members\n\n## **Cross-Team Collaboration and Communication**\n\nStrong coordination between design, marketing, and leadership is driving progress toward launch targets with clear ownership and feedback loops.\n\n- **Roz is acting as the key liaison for content feedback and approvals, managing multiple stakeholders efficiently** (07:24)  \n    - She coordinates review cycles and shields the design team from protracted wording disputes with Ricoh  \n    - Roz’s focus on quick turnarounds helps keep the project on schedule despite complex details  \n    - This role is critical to balancing quality with speed in content finalization\n\n- **Lou and Nathalie are committed to rapid iteration and delivery of design assets** to support marketing’s evolving needs (22:32)  \n    - Lou plans to share updated designs with Nathalie today for further distribution to the European team  \n    - Nathalie will ensure graphics are delivered promptly for review and integration into launch materials  \n    - Their collaboration exemplifies a tight feedback loop enabling agile responses to changing requirements\n\n- **Executive input from Linea will finalize design decisions for title slides and imagery** providing clear decision authority (19:22)  \n    - Roz will present multiple design options to Linea to streamline approval and avoid further delays  \n    - This approach clarifies responsibility and prevents stalled decisions due to indecision or conflicting opinions  \n    - It ensures the final materials meet leadership expectations and strategic goals","outline":null,"keywords":["sales guide","Battle Card","Illustrator","InDesign","product launch","animated video storyboard"],"overview":"- **Sales Guide Design:** Finalizing designs to improve usability and visual consistency. Adjustments to tab width and section headers agreed upon.  \n- **Content Update Efficiency:** Transitioning Battle Card templates to InDesign for faster edits and collaboration. Will enhance content update speed.  \n- **Product Launch Coordination:** Optimizer launch content near completion, with emphasis on quick feedback to meet deadlines for subsequent launches.  \n- **Reusable Design Assets:** Successful use of flexible icons in PowerPoint supports faster slide creation and enhances visual consistency.  \n- **Phased Rollout Strategy:** Animated videos will be tested with Optimizer, gathering feedback before extending to Info Print Manager and RPD.  \n- **Cross-Team Collaboration:** Clear ownership of feedback loops ensures design speed and quality, with executive input streamlining final decisions.","action_items":"\n**Lou Bogani**\nCreate revised sales guide table of contents design iterations removing red boxed numbers and increasing headline font size (15:30)\nRefine title page layouts by making the “balloon” element smaller and narrowing the tab; prepare alternative title page versions with and without product images and without computer mockups for executive review (21:40)\nProvide updated design ideas to Nathalie Mintjens for distribution to reviewers later in the day (22:30)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nDistribute revised sales guide design ideas and storyboard graphics for the animated video once available (24:01)\nCoordinate with Roz and Lou on review feedback and content progress for the Battle Card and sales guide templates (22:30)\n\n**Rozalynne Regan**\nFinalize content for the Optimizer Battle Card and send to Lou for format transition from Illustrator to InDesign (10:35)\nContinue management and review of Optimizer brochure content aiming for end-of-month completion (11:00)\nProvide feedback on animated video storyboard graphics upon receipt (11:00)\nOversee approval process for sales guide title page versions with executive (Linea Wolken) and coordinate future launches of related product marketing materials (20:10)\n"},"duration":24.770000457763672,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Lou Bogani"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Roz"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Bad, but I''m fine.","index":0,"end_time":2.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It''s.","index":1,"end_time":2.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s been like, a really tough week, mentally.","index":2,"end_time":5.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.36,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I''m like, Monday was rough, really rough.","index":3,"end_time":10.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.56,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, Tuesday, it was like going upwards in an upwards trend, but then it''s, like, stayed there.","index":4,"end_time":17.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.24,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it isn''t going down, but it''s like, I don''t want to cook anything.","index":5,"end_time":23.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I''m ordering much.","index":6,"end_time":24.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.36,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Bunch of.","index":7,"end_time":25.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.8,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Most of the days and times of the day, I''m eating kind of bad, kind of good.","index":8,"end_time":32.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.4,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So it''s been, like, a lot, but it''s already Thursday.","index":9,"end_time":39.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.83,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":10,"end_time":39.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.19,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So.","index":11,"end_time":42.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":43.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Is this the wedding?","index":13,"end_time":44.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Did the wedding come back to haunt you?","index":14,"end_time":46.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, a lot.","index":15,"end_time":48.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.87,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":49.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I have zero sympathy for you.","index":17,"end_time":52.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was really hard.","index":18,"end_time":54.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.9,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Did you guys make it to the concert?","index":19,"end_time":56.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that was my question too.","index":20,"end_time":59.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":21,"end_time":61.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.42,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"That''s another subject.","index":22,"end_time":64.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.7,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was really, really crazy that the gig was.","index":23,"end_time":66.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.18,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Let me share you a link on how it was.","index":24,"end_time":73.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.22,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, here I was like, I had Liam 50 meters away.","index":25,"end_time":83.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.14,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I was in the middle of the.","index":26,"end_time":84.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Here''s like, I shared you a link of a video from Twitter of the concert in Argentina.","index":27,"end_time":91.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.55,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":28,"end_time":97.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m sure.","index":29,"end_time":98.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, dude, that''s just a mass of people.","index":30,"end_time":105.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":31,"end_time":108.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":106.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it was.","index":32,"end_time":110.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was.","index":33,"end_time":111.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.51,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was.","index":34,"end_time":111.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was huge.","index":35,"end_time":113.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.83,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, really huge.","index":36,"end_time":114.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"What happens if someone is in some kind of medical distress in the middle of that?","index":37,"end_time":120.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Good luck.","index":38,"end_time":122.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, apparently.","index":39,"end_time":124.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Only.","index":40,"end_time":125.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.99,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The only thing that you can say is like, good luck.","index":41,"end_time":128.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.63,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"You shouldn''t be.","index":42,"end_time":129.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.15,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"You shouldn''t be there.","index":43,"end_time":130.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.95,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"May the odds be ever in your favor.","index":44,"end_time":133.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like the Hunger Games.","index":45,"end_time":135.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":46,"end_time":137.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.81,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":47,"end_time":137.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.37,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"No, it was like.","index":48,"end_time":139.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.25,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"There was 90k people in the city.","index":49,"end_time":141.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.29,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":142.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":143.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, I remember we were talking about that before you left, and I was like, yeah, we don''t even have, like, we don''t even have a place in Vancouver to put that many people.","index":52,"end_time":150.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Seriously.","index":53,"end_time":151.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"There was.","index":54,"end_time":152.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.61,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"There was a lot of foreign people, like, from this.","index":55,"end_time":154.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.13,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"From the uk, from the States, Australia, all across Europe.","index":56,"end_time":159.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.57,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"They were, like, wanted to.","index":57,"end_time":162.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.53,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"To.","index":58,"end_time":162.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"To live and experience the.","index":59,"end_time":164.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.87,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The.","index":60,"end_time":165.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The.","index":61,"end_time":165.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.11,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The concert in Argentina.","index":62,"end_time":166.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Because while Argentinians are widely known that they are crazy when.","index":63,"end_time":170.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.63,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"When it comes to, like, concerts and rock bands and all that, and our Oasis, that was like 16 years without playing here.","index":64,"end_time":179.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.19,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Gine was like, over the top, but it was amazing.","index":65,"end_time":183.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was really, really.","index":66,"end_time":185.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"They played a lot of songs.","index":67,"end_time":188.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.96,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"They played, like, almost two hours, I think, or two hours and a half.","index":68,"end_time":190.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.28,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":192.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was worth it.","index":70,"end_time":192.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.2,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I was like.","index":71,"end_time":193.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.96,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I was telling Natalie.","index":72,"end_time":194.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.68,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I was like, my body was destroyed, my voice was destroyed, my mind was destroyed.","index":73,"end_time":201.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.8,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But it was.","index":74,"end_time":204.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.4,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was really a really amazing weekend.","index":75,"end_time":207.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Between the.","index":76,"end_time":208.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.6,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Within the.","index":77,"end_time":209.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.4,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Between the.","index":78,"end_time":209.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.08,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The wedding and the concert.","index":79,"end_time":211.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.56,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was really cool.","index":80,"end_time":212.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.92,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":81,"end_time":213.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You''re gonna sleep all this weekend, aren''t you?","index":82,"end_time":217.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m probably will.","index":83,"end_time":218.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.99,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I won''t leave my house at all.","index":84,"end_time":220.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.87,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The UberEats guy is gonna be your friend or doordash or whatever it is you have down there.","index":85,"end_time":228.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s already my friend.","index":86,"end_time":229.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.869,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I''ve been ordering food the whole week.","index":87,"end_time":231.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.95,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":88,"end_time":232.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.67,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I don''t want to cook.","index":89,"end_time":232.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, I''m slacking a lot this week.","index":90,"end_time":235.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.67,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"My mind is between work and all the stuff that I have to do in my house.","index":91,"end_time":240.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.43,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was.","index":92,"end_time":241.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.63,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It''s like, I don''t want to move a finger from my house.","index":93,"end_time":245.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I want to sit here, enjoy or order, like, food, like comfort food to.","index":94,"end_time":251.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.49,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"To eat, watching movies, series, whatever.","index":95,"end_time":255.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.57,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But.","index":96,"end_time":255.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.09,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":256.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.65,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":98,"end_time":259.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I have no sympathy for you at all.","index":99,"end_time":261.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Lack of planning does not constitute an emergency, my friend.","index":100,"end_time":268.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":101,"end_time":271.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.66,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":102,"end_time":272.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s so funny.","index":103,"end_time":274.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":104,"end_time":276.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.86,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":277.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.7,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, dear.","index":106,"end_time":279.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, but as long as you had fun.","index":107,"end_time":282.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I mean, you''re young, you''ll get over.","index":108,"end_time":284.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.5,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No, yeah, it was awesome.","index":109,"end_time":286.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.18,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, I. I don''t regret.","index":110,"end_time":288.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.22,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I don''t regret it a bit.","index":111,"end_time":289.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.18,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, it was an amazing weekend and also the concert.","index":112,"end_time":292.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.34,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I went with my father, my brother, his wife, my.","index":113,"end_time":297.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.98,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"My girlfriend.","index":114,"end_time":298.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.72,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So it was like the.","index":115,"end_time":300.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.44,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Between the concert, the wedding was like an amazing weekend.","index":116,"end_time":302.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.4,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, can''t complain there.","index":117,"end_time":305.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was a good wedding.","index":118,"end_time":306.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Then you guys had like a fun time and everything went.","index":119,"end_time":309.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it was amazing.","index":120,"end_time":311.359,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.68,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The only thing that it kind of a storm breakthrough in the middle of the night and we have to like, take everything, like all the, like the equipment from the, like the music, DJ lights, all the stuff.","index":121,"end_time":324.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.36,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"We had to take it, like, inside.","index":122,"end_time":327.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.78,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But once that was, like, already covered.","index":123,"end_time":331.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.14,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It was like, keep partying, keep enjoying and.","index":124,"end_time":335.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.42,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Good.","index":125,"end_time":336.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, Good.","index":126,"end_time":337.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.499,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":127,"end_time":339.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m glad to hear it went well.","index":128,"end_time":341.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":129,"end_time":342.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.34,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Even if you are suffering.","index":130,"end_time":344.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We knew it would come.","index":131,"end_time":348.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":351.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.91,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, dear.","index":133,"end_time":356.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The older you get, the less you''re able to do these kinds of things, so.","index":134,"end_time":360.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And also you recover slower, slowly.","index":135,"end_time":364.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, God, you have no idea.","index":136,"end_time":366.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You really have no idea.","index":137,"end_time":369.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"My.","index":138,"end_time":371.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"My friends and I, you know, we''re all in our 50s, so this.","index":139,"end_time":376.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":140,"end_time":377.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Things start to shift.","index":141,"end_time":378.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"What became quantity now becomes quality when you''re.","index":142,"end_time":384.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"When you''re out partying and drinking.","index":143,"end_time":385.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So we consider a good night with, you know, quality cocktails and home by 10.","index":144,"end_time":391.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m not joking.","index":145,"end_time":392.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, sorry, do you have a good night?","index":146,"end_time":396.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And we''re not quite at the, you know, we''re not quite at the old fuddy duddy home by, you know, six Thing, but we''re closing in on it.","index":147,"end_time":407.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, dear.","index":148,"end_time":413.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, our.","index":149,"end_time":414.269,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just our quality of alcohol has gotten much better, though.","index":150,"end_time":416.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.269,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''re more fussy about it.","index":151,"end_time":418.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":152,"end_time":419.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.27,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":420.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, dear.","index":154,"end_time":425.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Anyway, Natalie, take us away.","index":155,"end_time":427.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, so from my side.","index":156,"end_time":431.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I thought we could use most of the time going through the sales guide template.","index":157,"end_time":436.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Lou has a few designs to show.","index":158,"end_time":438.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":159,"end_time":439.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just before that, just wanted to check.","index":160,"end_time":441.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So the icon set, the PowerPoint.","index":161,"end_time":443.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is that all good?","index":162,"end_time":444.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":163,"end_time":445.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks great.","index":164,"end_time":446.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thanks so much for that.","index":165,"end_time":447.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just find that recently we''ve been using those little line drawings just on different backgrounds.","index":166,"end_time":453.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So this is just to make my life easier.","index":167,"end_time":455.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Well, every owns life a little bit easier.","index":168,"end_time":457.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":455.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So thank you so much for adding those and then having them be able to be like, pulled apart because there''s certain times when we want to just use the background too.","index":169,"end_time":467.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s just to give us a little bit more flexibility.","index":170,"end_time":470.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think it looked just fine.","index":171,"end_time":473.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And, you know, we added the new ones that we had just made in like the accessibility or the whatever it was like the low power and all the rest of it.","index":172,"end_time":482.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Those were fine.","index":173,"end_time":482.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think we''re in good.","index":174,"end_time":484.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"In good form for that.","index":175,"end_time":486.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that you can close that one off.","index":176,"end_time":488.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I did have one question before I forget for you guys.","index":177,"end_time":492.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And so on the.","index":178,"end_time":494.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On the Battle Card template, for whatever reason, that template was done in Illustrator, and I''m just wondering if there''s a reason for that, because I need to update a few things on it and have been doing that while we''re, you know, we''re solidifying the Battle Card for Optimizer.","index":179,"end_time":511.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And it''s just a massive pain in the backside to add links and you can''t color the bullets.","index":180,"end_time":520.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, it has to have, like, little boxes over top of the gray bullets because it only does that.","index":181,"end_time":525.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.96,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m just wondering if there''s a reason we did it in illustrator and not InDesign.","index":182,"end_time":529.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"For me, it''s easier for.","index":183,"end_time":531.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.68,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"To design in Illustrator than InDesign.","index":184,"end_time":534.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.88,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But we can transfer.","index":185,"end_time":536,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.2,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, we can translate this.","index":186,"end_time":537.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I need to design if we.","index":187,"end_time":539.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.92,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"That was my question.","index":188,"end_time":540.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, is it possible now that we''ve solidified the design of everything, we could transfer it over to InDesign so that when I''m making these, all these little content changes, it''s just.","index":189,"end_time":551.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s just so much easier because it''s just going to get painful.","index":190,"end_time":554.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":191,"end_time":554.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.52,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, standby on that.","index":192,"end_time":556.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"What I will do is we''re just finishing up on the content on the Optimizer Battle Card.","index":193,"end_time":561.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I''ll send it back to you if.","index":194,"end_time":563.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And if you can just keep, you know, the template as is and just flip it over to InDesign for me, I''d be over the moon because it''s just so much easier to make those content changes.","index":195,"end_time":572.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Ricoh tends to get really fiddly with words like the nuance of things.","index":196,"end_time":581.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We.","index":197,"end_time":582.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We can kind of go down a bit.","index":198,"end_time":584.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Unfortunately, we can kind of go down a bit of a rabbit hole with a particular word and what it means, particularly as it pertains to printing and all workflows and all this other stuff.","index":199,"end_time":594.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, Yeah, I know.","index":200,"end_time":596.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m just trying to shield you guys from having to go through all of that, and I just need to be able to make content changes really quickly for that kind of.","index":201,"end_time":603.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it has.","index":202,"end_time":604.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s completely our fault, not yours.","index":203,"end_time":606.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.5,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But, yeah, if we could do it in InDesign once we finalized everything, that would be really helpful for me, if that''s okay.","index":204,"end_time":614.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":205,"end_time":615.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.78,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":206,"end_time":616.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":207,"end_time":617.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m just sending out the last, like, review to the ladies, and I will, once they finalize them, they''re good with it.","index":208,"end_time":628.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I will.","index":209,"end_time":629.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I will shift it over to you for that.","index":210,"end_time":633.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":630.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just that switch, and then we can use it moving forward with everything else as well.","index":211,"end_time":636.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Great.","index":212,"end_time":639.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.72,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":213,"end_time":640.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":214,"end_time":641.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That was.","index":215,"end_time":643.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All I had, was just those.","index":216,"end_time":644.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Those items.","index":217,"end_time":645.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":646.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then for just the update on the animated video.","index":219,"end_time":650,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So the team is going to have the new graphics for the storyboard done today.","index":220,"end_time":654.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":650.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":221,"end_time":655.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right over on the call last week, so I''ll send them for you to review.","index":222,"end_time":659.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''d be great.","index":223,"end_time":661.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think I had on my list of things to have that done.","index":224,"end_time":665.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I want to say no later than the end of this month.","index":225,"end_time":668.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Is that timing still good?","index":226,"end_time":670.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, have, like, finished.","index":227,"end_time":672.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":228,"end_time":672.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":229,"end_time":673.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just.","index":230,"end_time":674.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I know we''re doing something a bit different here, and it''s taking a bit longer while we suss out, like, a look and feel and all the rest of it, so.","index":231,"end_time":680.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":674.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I just wanted to be trying to keep my mind on my dates right now because of these.","index":232,"end_time":686.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"These three launches that are coming back to back.","index":233,"end_time":691.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just can''t have anything slip, so.","index":234,"end_time":694.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right.","index":235,"end_time":695.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''re gonna do similar ones for other products, right?","index":236,"end_time":699.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we may do.","index":237,"end_time":701.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I. I just really wanted to test drive it with this first.","index":238,"end_time":704.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it''s for Optimizer memory Serve, so this is the first launch, and I just want to test drive it with that, get people''s feedback, which, you know, of course, can take, like, a thousand years in my world, you know, just takes a Long time, sometimes just getting people''s attention on it.","index":239,"end_time":719.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But if people are kind of happy with how that looks, then I would definitely like to do it for info Print manager that is desperate for an update.","index":240,"end_time":727.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then we can do the same thing for, you know, hopefully for rpd.","index":241,"end_time":732.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that''s my nefarious plan, is to get the three of them done for the launches.","index":242,"end_time":737.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":243,"end_time":739.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":244,"end_time":740.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.15,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, that''s everything I had.","index":245,"end_time":743.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Lou, if you want to go over the designs.","index":246,"end_time":745.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, just give me a second.","index":247,"end_time":749.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":248,"end_time":751.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.87,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So what I''m going to show you, Ross, is like the first iterations and different designs that I made for this sales guide.","index":249,"end_time":761.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.95,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The entire sales guide isn''t like, edit just the pages that we want to like.","index":250,"end_time":766.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.95,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":768.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I felt the content pages were fine.","index":252,"end_time":772.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, they''re not too stop signy.","index":253,"end_time":773.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"They''re clear.","index":254,"end_time":774.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, they made sense to me.","index":255,"end_time":776.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So yeah, I was just like, man, I don''t think we need to change those unless you see something like, really horrifying.","index":256,"end_time":782.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But they are pretty clean and neat.","index":257,"end_time":784.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I was like, me.","index":258,"end_time":785.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":784.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that works.","index":259,"end_time":786.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, okay, so here are some.","index":260,"end_time":789.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Some ideas of the table of contents.","index":261,"end_time":791.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.51,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like design, including the picture on the left as the battle card designs with the tab on the and the logo on the bottom.","index":262,"end_time":799.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.11,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Then you have like another one without the image just to see how it looks.","index":263,"end_time":802.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Maybe it looks cleaner, maybe it doesn''t.","index":264,"end_time":804.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The image on top with the logo on the on again with the tab.","index":265,"end_time":809.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"This is with the gray background that maybe we can like, maybe emphasize a bit more.","index":266,"end_time":815.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.77,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like the tab, it pops up a bit more.","index":267,"end_time":818.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.65,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But I didn''t deviate too much because I don''t want to go over the top with the design.","index":268,"end_time":824.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.97,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":825.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":824.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because we don''t want to feel like it''s totally another design system.","index":270,"end_time":829.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.29,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yes, yes, absolutely.","index":271,"end_time":832.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes, yes, yes.","index":272,"end_time":832.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You hit the nail on the head.","index":273,"end_time":834.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":274,"end_time":835.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.37,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I think for the table of contents, I like the first one because you''re right.","index":275,"end_time":839.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it matches a little bit better with that bar down the left.","index":276,"end_time":842.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I really like that.","index":277,"end_time":843.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"One thing I really like to get rid of and you guys can tell me what you think are those red squares with the 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 in them.","index":278,"end_time":852.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":844.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ve never been a fan of that.","index":279,"end_time":854.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"There''s something about the number in the far right hand corner that just annoys me to no end.","index":280,"end_time":858.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I just.","index":281,"end_time":860.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":282,"end_time":861.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.43,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, what do you think?","index":283,"end_time":863.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":861.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, do you think maybe, you know, it would be okay to get rid of them?","index":284,"end_time":866.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Do we still need a number?","index":285,"end_time":868.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, you have the number.","index":286,"end_time":870.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.71,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, you have the number of the section on the right.","index":287,"end_time":873.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.63,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So for my.","index":288,"end_time":874.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.27,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"In my perspective, like, the page.","index":289,"end_time":876.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, they are kind of necessary.","index":290,"end_time":878.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.31,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And we can, like, maybe increase a bit the size of the text on the headliners.","index":291,"end_time":883.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.63,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like maybe a bit, like 1, 2 points, and then remove the box maybe.","index":292,"end_time":888.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.95,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Looks way better, I think.","index":293,"end_time":890.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So let''s do that.","index":294,"end_time":891.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I am not married to those boxes.","index":295,"end_time":892.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If anything, I never really liked them, but I was just.","index":296,"end_time":895.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just didn''t have time to, you know, get into it with the previous designers.","index":297,"end_time":899.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I just love it because no one.","index":298,"end_time":901.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.51,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No one really was like, oh, my God, I absolutely hate it.","index":299,"end_time":904.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it was just kind of one of those it''s okay things, but it''s not doing anything for me now.","index":300,"end_time":910.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":301,"end_time":910.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I like your idea.","index":302,"end_time":912.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s get rid of them completely and just maybe increase the font slightly on the red titles.","index":303,"end_time":918.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because you''re right, the page numbers on the right hand side and it''s all linked or it will be all linked.","index":304,"end_time":923.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I don''t know that we need the 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 anymore, honestly.","index":305,"end_time":927.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''ll do that.","index":306,"end_time":928.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.98,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":307,"end_time":929.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.7,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":308,"end_time":929.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then we have.","index":309,"end_time":930.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.9,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And then we have, like, the title pages.","index":310,"end_time":932.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.66,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, here I made a bit more of iterations.","index":311,"end_time":935.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.54,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Here you have again the tab with the title on top, gray background with the balloon and the picture on the top.","index":312,"end_time":941.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.3,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Then you have again the title inside of the tab with, again, the balloon a bit.","index":313,"end_time":948.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.05,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"No, it''s the same, but with a gay background at the top, like, encapsulating all the text.","index":314,"end_time":953.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.05,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Here you have another one with the image on the bottom, the logo on the far right corner, title on top tab again.","index":315,"end_time":962.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.89,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And then on the bottom part of the page, you have the sections.","index":316,"end_time":966.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.89,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The nav.","index":317,"end_time":967.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":318,"end_time":968.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Then we have another one that is kind of overlapping and kind of giving that layering that kind of.","index":319,"end_time":972.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.58,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I think it looks really cool.","index":320,"end_time":974.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.66,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And then we have another one that it''s switching up the colors also.","index":321,"end_time":979.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.86,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And, like, I''m not.","index":322,"end_time":981.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.78,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":323,"end_time":982.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.02,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I''m not fan of this one, but.","index":324,"end_time":984.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.86,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I wanted to try that one.","index":325,"end_time":984.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I was going to say that one''s not.","index":326,"end_time":986.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That one''s not blowing my skirt up either.","index":327,"end_time":988.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":989.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it''s the one above, actually, that I. I think this is interesting to me.","index":329,"end_time":994.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":989.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think the balloon could be a little bit smaller because my eye keeps on drawing towards it.","index":330,"end_time":1000.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So maybe make sure.","index":331,"end_time":1000.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1000.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Maybe it''s.","index":332,"end_time":1002.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The tab isn''t as wide, the balloon is a little bit smaller, and it''s sitting on that corner, similar to what we''ve done on the title.","index":333,"end_time":1010.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1002.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":334,"end_time":1011.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Page.","index":335,"end_time":1011.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.35,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, if you go back up to the very top.","index":336,"end_time":1013.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":337,"end_time":1015.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, like that, you know, like that size, that tab.","index":338,"end_time":1019.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like the same, you know, the same placements there.","index":339,"end_time":1022.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If we can.","index":340,"end_time":1023.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that would be a nice kind of mirror to the title page as well.","index":341,"end_time":1028.919,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1024.439,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then.","index":342,"end_time":1030.599,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.039,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Sorry, could you go back to the other one?","index":343,"end_time":1033.399,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.599,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, keep going, keep going, keep going.","index":344,"end_time":1035.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1033.479,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So this one, is it on a white background or gray.","index":345,"end_time":1039.879,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.399,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s a gray background.","index":346,"end_time":1041.479,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.439,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like the gradient.","index":347,"end_time":1042.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.479,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The gray gradient.","index":348,"end_time":1042.839,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.039,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Light gray gradient.","index":349,"end_time":1043.839,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.919,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1044.199,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.839,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":351,"end_time":1044.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.199,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1044.879,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.639,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And that.","index":353,"end_time":1045.119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.879,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I''m just.","index":354,"end_time":1045.719,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.119,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"For that, I chose that color and that gradient just to see the bottom containers.","index":355,"end_time":1053.799,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.759,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, I know exactly what you did.","index":356,"end_time":1055.399,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.199,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s fine.","index":357,"end_time":1056.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.399,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I have no problem.","index":358,"end_time":1057.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just.","index":359,"end_time":1057.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s hard for me to see on, you know, screens.","index":360,"end_time":1060.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just so.","index":361,"end_time":1062.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, no, I''m zen with that.","index":362,"end_time":1063.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1062.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m zen with that gradient because it''s similar to what we use on the.","index":363,"end_time":1067.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1063.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On the PowerPoint.","index":364,"end_time":1068.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1067.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, I took.","index":365,"end_time":1069.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I took all the.","index":366,"end_time":1070.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.7,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"All the colors.","index":367,"end_time":1071.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.46,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I took them from the brand guide.","index":368,"end_time":1072.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.14,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So, yeah, yeah, I''m here for it.","index":369,"end_time":1075.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think that one is the winner with just that slight little bit of, you know, adjustment.","index":370,"end_time":1081.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just because the balloon is just.","index":371,"end_time":1083.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just a.","index":372,"end_time":1084.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1083.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s just too big for me.","index":373,"end_time":1085.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1084.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That''s where my eye is going.","index":374,"end_time":1086.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And it should be going to the.","index":375,"end_time":1087.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Why it should be going to the title.","index":376,"end_time":1090.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, we can squeeze up.","index":377,"end_time":1092.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1090.88,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"We can maybe squeeze a bit like more the tab and then move the balloon to the, like, the same position as the title and make it a bit smaller, like here.","index":378,"end_time":1100.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.2,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like maybe squish the tab.","index":379,"end_time":1102.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.88,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I''m not saying.","index":380,"end_time":1102.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not saying the title needs to.","index":381,"end_time":1104.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The title tab and balloon need to be in that exact placement.","index":382,"end_time":1108.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1104.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I actually don''t mind the placement where it is because it gives me.","index":383,"end_time":1111.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It gives me space to be able to put more or less text, depending on, you know, on what''s going on.","index":384,"end_time":1118.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.52,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m just saying that I think that the tab can be a little bit narrower so that the balloon can edge off of that bottom right hand corner and be, you know, like quite a bit smaller.","index":385,"end_time":1130.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like half as small as that.","index":386,"end_time":1131.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1130.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I would say.","index":387,"end_time":1132.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":388,"end_time":1133.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.42,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":389,"end_time":1133.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1134.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":391,"end_time":1134.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.26,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So, yeah, no, I don''t draw attention.","index":392,"end_time":1136.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.42,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I don''t hate it.","index":393,"end_time":1137.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And did we think about.","index":394,"end_time":1139.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I know, because usually on these pages we have, like an image of the.","index":395,"end_time":1144.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The original had an image of the.","index":396,"end_time":1146.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, that had the original image.","index":397,"end_time":1150.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1147.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Did we think of any way to still continue to use that, like the product image there, or do we just decide to go away from it?","index":398,"end_time":1159.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"My.","index":399,"end_time":1162.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.01,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"My thoughts about.","index":400,"end_time":1163.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.37,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I didn''t thought about that much.","index":401,"end_time":1165.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.77,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"We can maybe.","index":402,"end_time":1167.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.25,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Because it, it kind of depends on the amount of text of the body copy on that.","index":403,"end_time":1171.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.53,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Because if we had like.","index":404,"end_time":1172.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.13,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Absolutely, if you have a few copy, we can maybe squeeze it.","index":405,"end_time":1177.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.17,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But it will look a bit crowded with image and the product image and the balloon.","index":406,"end_time":1181.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.21,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"We can remove the balloon.","index":407,"end_time":1182.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.45,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"That''s what I was just about to say.","index":408,"end_time":1185.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I was going to say do.","index":409,"end_time":1186.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1185.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"How do we feel about removing the like, give me two versions and I''ll put them both up in front of Linea and she can choose.","index":410,"end_time":1193.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Quite frankly, she''s kind of my executive decision when it comes to stuff like this.","index":411,"end_time":1196.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1193.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So maybe make this version but without the balloon.","index":412,"end_time":1200.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Add the, the image of the product shot on top of it in that layered way that we''ve been going.","index":413,"end_time":1207.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, let''s see what it looks like.","index":414,"end_time":1210.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1208.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I could go either way with this.","index":415,"end_time":1212.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think what I could get away with is that this particular image as well happens to have the image shot on the little computer.","index":416,"end_time":1220.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But that''s not necessarily the case other time the case.","index":417,"end_time":1224.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, not necessarily the case.","index":418,"end_time":1226.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1224.67,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So it''s weird.","index":419,"end_time":1226.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, I''m actually okay with it not being there, but I know it''s because I can see it on the image banner.","index":420,"end_time":1232.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I know also that that banner image isn''t necessarily going to have, you know, the GUI of the product in it.","index":421,"end_time":1239.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like some of them are just, you know, lifestyle slots.","index":422,"end_time":1241.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1239.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So if we could maybe try it in that way, I would be.","index":423,"end_time":1244.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I will give you three ideas from this.","index":424,"end_time":1246.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.21,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I will give you the idea of the balloon a bit smaller and the narrow, narrower tab.","index":425,"end_time":1251.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.77,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I will give you a one with the.","index":426,"end_time":1252.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.53,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Without the balloon and the product image.","index":427,"end_time":1254.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1252.69,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And I will give you another one with the product image without the computer mock up, if that makes sense.","index":428,"end_time":1259.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.45,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"No, I was going to say actually get rid of the computer mock up completely.","index":429,"end_time":1264.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So just the two, we haven''t.","index":430,"end_time":1266.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''ve been kind of going.","index":431,"end_time":1267.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1266.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, just the image.","index":432,"end_time":1269.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1268.53,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''ve been going away from it being on the computer because you can''t see the finer detail when the computer is so small.","index":433,"end_time":1279.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then the image of the product gets smaller as well.","index":434,"end_time":1281.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1279.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right.","index":435,"end_time":1282.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1281.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that''s why we''ve been going towards like bigger images without it superimposed on a, on a computer because you can see it better.","index":436,"end_time":1291.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So yeah, just the two I think would be fine.","index":437,"end_time":1293.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And get rid of the computer mock up completely.","index":438,"end_time":1295.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1293.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":439,"end_time":1296.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.68,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":440,"end_time":1296.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.36,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":441,"end_time":1297.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.08,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1298.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":443,"end_time":1299.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s going in, in a nice direction.","index":444,"end_time":1301.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1299.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s definitely, you know, it''s taking in the elements of the items that we''ve already done.","index":445,"end_time":1306.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":446,"end_time":1307.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1306.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks good.","index":447,"end_time":1307.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":448,"end_time":1308.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Great.","index":449,"end_time":1308.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.52,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Thank you, Russ.","index":450,"end_time":1309.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.84,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, no, absolutely.","index":451,"end_time":1311.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So exciting.","index":452,"end_time":1312.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I love refreshing things.","index":453,"end_time":1313.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1312.6,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Makes my life easier, so.","index":454,"end_time":1315.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1314.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It does.","index":455,"end_time":1317.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was so much better.","index":456,"end_time":1318.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You get.","index":457,"end_time":1319.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.7,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"People get used to seeing things.","index":458,"end_time":1320.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I think what''s great too is that we''re rebranding like a lot of these.","index":459,"end_time":1325.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''re rebranding a lot of these, what do you call it?","index":460,"end_time":1329.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.18,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Products right now.","index":461,"end_time":1330.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So the refreshing of them is coming at exactly the right time.","index":462,"end_time":1334.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1330.86,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":463,"end_time":1335.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1335.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":464,"end_time":1336.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.9,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1337.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":466,"end_time":1337.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Looks great.","index":467,"end_time":1338.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.66,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":468,"end_time":1339.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I look forward to seeing the.","index":469,"end_time":1341.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The that two versions of the.","index":470,"end_time":1343.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Those internals title slides.","index":471,"end_time":1345.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it''ll look great.","index":472,"end_time":1346.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":473,"end_time":1350.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":474,"end_time":1351.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1350.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1352.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1352.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Are those all your questions, Lou?","index":476,"end_time":1353.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Everything clear?","index":477,"end_time":1355.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Everything''s good.","index":478,"end_time":1356.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.84,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, I will get into that comments and I think that for later today, I will have them the ideas to share with Natalie and she can send it to Euros.","index":479,"end_time":1367.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.56,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":480,"end_time":1368.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":481,"end_time":1369.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Thank you so much for that.","index":482,"end_time":1370.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1369.09,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":483,"end_time":1371.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.13,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And once I get this battle card back from everyone with all the different comments, you know, addressed for the content, I will send that over to you guys as well.","index":484,"end_time":1381.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":485,"end_time":1383.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1383.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m so close to having this Optimizer brochure finished that I can taste it.","index":486,"end_time":1388.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1383.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So I will be sending you, Natalie, I''ll put in your little transfer folder.","index":487,"end_time":1394.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1388.97,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Folder can''t speak the final.","index":488,"end_time":1397.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that you guys have the absolute final of everything.","index":489,"end_time":1400.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Of what that.","index":490,"end_time":1401.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1400.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, what that looks like.","index":491,"end_time":1402.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And we can use that as our template.","index":492,"end_time":1404.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1402.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just massage.","index":493,"end_time":1405.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s really more around the content.","index":494,"end_time":1407.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1405.88,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Again, a slight tweaking here or there, like moving little elements, but like within, you know, pixels of each other.","index":495,"end_time":1416.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So anyway, we''ll use that one as our template once it''s finalized and then we can go from there on all the other battle cards and we can swing into action with those and what they look like, so.","index":496,"end_time":1428.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":497,"end_time":1430.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":498,"end_time":1431.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.72,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okie doke.","index":499,"end_time":1432.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.52,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''re getting there, guys.","index":500,"end_time":1433.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I promise.","index":501,"end_time":1434.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It can be painful, but we''re getting there slowly but surely.","index":502,"end_time":1438.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":503,"end_time":1441.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ll send over the graphics as well once they''re done.","index":504,"end_time":1444.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just.","index":505,"end_time":1445.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":506,"end_time":1448.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":507,"end_time":1449.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1449.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"More to come, I promise.","index":508,"end_time":1451.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1449.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, but it''s.","index":509,"end_time":1452.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It''s coming along.","index":510,"end_time":1452.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And once we get Optimizer dealt with, I will start feeding you guys stuff for info Print Manager, because we''re starting to work on that right now too, so.","index":511,"end_time":1460.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay.","index":512,"end_time":1461.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.51,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"And then our PD will be coming right behind it.","index":513,"end_time":1463.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":514,"end_time":1464.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.19,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okey doke.","index":515,"end_time":1467.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.99,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":516,"end_time":1468.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.19,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Well, thanks, guys.","index":517,"end_time":1469.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1468.83,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I appreciate the time, as always.","index":518,"end_time":1471.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1469.75,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If there''s anything.","index":519,"end_time":1472.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1471.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Natalie, you know where I am and I will keep my eyes peeled for your emails.","index":520,"end_time":1476.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Us.","index":521,"end_time":1476.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.17,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":522,"end_time":1477.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":523,"end_time":1478.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.73,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"All right, take care.","index":524,"end_time":1479.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1478.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Take care.","index":525,"end_time":1481.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.57,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Bye.","index":526,"end_time":1481.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1481.05,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"}],"dateString":"2025-11-20T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85828735088?pwd=b9W3cDKwBeJQyK00Qs0iP3vvCmTxIZ.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com,kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com,rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca,linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","lou.bogani@marketersindemand.com","kiyan.klocker@marketersindemand.com","rosalynne.regan@ricoh.ca","linnea.wolken@ricoh-usa.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9Z9ZTRNW3F6DGZ0MHY79Y9Z","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Agreed to convert final Battle Card layout from Illustrator to InDesign for easier content edits.","Roz confirmed new icon set is approved and can now be closed out in the workflow.","Lou to deliver updated internal title page iterations with and without product imagery.","Storyboard graphics for animated video expected today to keep Optimizer launch on track.","Roz reiterated target to finalize Optimizer materials by month-end to stay aligned with three launches."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think it''s going in, in a nice direction.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"We''re getting there, guys. I promise.","speaker":"Roz"},{"quote":"Everything''s good. Yeah, I will get into that comments...","speaker":"Lou Bogani"}],"topics":["delivery","design","launch"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-21T18:46:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Guide Design and Template Improvements**\n\nThe team is finalizing the sales guide design to improve usability and visual consistency while streamlining ongoing content updates.\n\n- **Lou Bogani presented multiple table of contents design iterations** featuring variations with images, tabs, and logos to maintain brand alignment without overwhelming the layout (12:48)  \n    - Roz preferred the design with an image on the left and a left-side bar, noting it fits better with existing branding  \n    - They agreed to remove the red numbered boxes on the right, increasing font size on section headers to simplify appearance  \n    - Lou will adjust the tab width and reduce the balloon graphic size to avoid distracting from titles  \n    - Roz emphasized balancing visual appeal with clarity to avoid creating a new design system that conflicts with current branding\n\n- **Title page designs were reviewed with focus on layout and imagery** to maintain brand coherence while allowing flexibility for content length (15:29)  \n    - Roz requested versions both with and without the balloon graphic, suggesting adding the product image as an alternative  \n    - Lou committed to providing three versions: smaller balloon with narrow tab, product image replacing balloon, and product image without computer mockup for better detail visibility  \n    - Roz explained the move away from computer mockups to larger standalone product images improves clarity across all product presentations\n\n- **Roz highlighted the importance of making future content updates easier** by transferring the Battle Card template from Illustrator to InDesign after finalizing design (07:24)  \n    - Lou agreed to convert the final template to InDesign to facilitate quick content changes and reduce editing friction  \n    - Roz noted Ricoh’s detailed wording reviews require flexibility in making small text changes rapidly  \n    - This shift will streamline future updates and allow smoother collaboration between design and content teams\n\n- **The refreshed sales guide aligns with ongoing product rebranding efforts** and supports upcoming launches for Optimizer, Info Print Manager, and RPD (22:15)  \n    - Roz shared a plan to test the animated video and sales guide with Optimizer first before extending to other products  \n    - Nathalie confirmed graphics for the storyboard will be delivered today to stay on track for end-of-month deadlines (10:46)  \n    - The team acknowledged this phased rollout reduces risk and gathers feedback to improve subsequent launches\n\n## **Product Marketing Content and Launch Coordination**\n\nThe team is managing content finalization for the Optimizer product launch while preparing for subsequent product marketing efforts.\n\n- **Roz is close to completing the Optimizer Battle Card content, aiming for end-of-month readiness** to meet tight launch schedules (11:12)  \n    - The team is incorporating feedback from multiple stakeholders to refine messaging and ensure clarity  \n    - Roz emphasized the need to avoid delays due to prolonged content discussions, highlighting the importance of quick reviews  \n    - Once finalized, this Battle Card will serve as the template for other product marketing collateral, improving consistency\n\n- **Nathalie and Lou are collaborating closely to finalize graphic assets and design iterations** supporting the Optimizer launch and future campaigns (24:01)  \n    - Nathalie will send finalized graphics to Roz for review, ensuring visuals align with brand guidelines and messaging  \n    - Lou will incorporate final design feedback and prepare versions for executive review by Linea to secure approvals  \n    - Roz stressed maintaining momentum after Optimizer to quickly move on to Info Print Manager and RPD launches\n\n- **The team is balancing speed and quality in deliverables to support three back-to-back product launches** without slipping on deadlines (11:12)  \n    - Roz noted the complexity of aligning look and feel while integrating new design elements is causing some delays  \n    - They are using the Optimizer project as a test case to refine processes and tools for subsequent launches  \n    - This approach aims to reduce rework and improve efficiency across the product marketing pipeline\n\n## **Process and Tool Improvements for Design Workflow**\n\nShifting design templates to more flexible tools will reduce friction in content updates and improve responsiveness to feedback.\n\n- **Moving Battle Card templates from Illustrator to InDesign will streamline content edits** and reduce the manual work involved in adding links and formatting (07:24)  \n    - Roz described Illustrator as cumbersome for text changes and link management, impacting turnaround times  \n    - Lou confirmed willingness to convert templates once designs are finalized to improve operational efficiency  \n    - This change will empower marketing teams to make quick copy tweaks without design team bottlenecks\n\n- **Use of flexible icon sets in PowerPoint was confirmed as successful** to ease slide creation and improve visual consistency (07:19)  \n    - Roz explained that the new line drawing icons can be pulled apart and used on different backgrounds for greater versatility  \n    - This flexibility reduces design iteration time and supports accessibility-related updates  \n    - The positive reception indicates adoption of reusable assets is helping standardize presentations\n\n- **The team is mindful of balancing visual refresh with brand consistency to avoid user confusion** (13:50)  \n    - Lou kept design changes subtle to maintain continuity with existing brand elements  \n    - Roz highlighted the importance of familiar layouts for user comfort and easier adoption  \n    - This philosophy supports better market positioning by strengthening brand recognition while updating aesthetics\n\n## **Long-Term Product Marketing Strategy and Vision**\n\nThe ongoing product marketing refreshes aim to support multi-product launches with consistent, user-friendly materials that resonate with customers.\n\n- **Roz outlined a phased rollout plan for animated videos and sales guides across three key products** to build momentum and gather user feedback (11:36)  \n    - Starting with Optimizer allows the team to refine messaging based on real reactions before Info Print Manager and RPD launches  \n    - This strategic sequencing reduces risk and ensures higher quality collateral for later launches  \n    - The approach reflects a vision to create scalable marketing assets adaptable across product lines\n\n- **The refreshed collateral supports rebranding efforts aligned with current market positioning** to strengthen competitive differentiation (21:49)  \n    - Roz noted many products are undergoing rebranding, making this the ideal time to update sales materials  \n    - Lou’s designs integrate brand guide colors and elements to maintain a unified look  \n    - This alignment will help customers easily identify the brand and its evolving offerings\n\n- **The team is focused on creating materials that aid sales and marketing teams in communicating product value clearly** (12:48)  \n    - Clear, clean layouts with linked navigation and flexible imagery will improve user engagement  \n    - Removing distracting elements like numbered boxes enhances readability and professionalism  \n    - This user-centric approach supports better sales outcomes and faster onboarding of new team members\n\n## **Cross-Team Collaboration and Communication**\n\nStrong coordination between design, marketing, and leadership is driving progress toward launch targets with clear ownership and feedback loops.\n\n- **Roz is acting as the key liaison for content feedback and approvals, managing multiple stakeholders efficiently** (07:24)  \n    - She coordinates review cycles and shields the design team from protracted wording disputes with Ricoh  \n    - Roz’s focus on quick turnarounds helps keep the project on schedule despite complex details  \n    - This role is critical to balancing quality with speed in content finalization\n\n- **Lou and Nathalie are committed to rapid iteration and delivery of design assets** to support marketing’s evolving needs (22:32)  \n    - Lou plans to share updated designs with Nathalie today for further distribution to the European team  \n    - Nathalie will ensure graphics are delivered promptly for review and integration into launch materials  \n    - Their collaboration exemplifies a tight feedback loop enabling agile responses to changing requirements\n\n- **Executive input from Linea will finalize design decisions for title slides and imagery** providing clear decision authority (19:22)  \n    - Roz will present multiple design options to Linea to streamline approval and avoid further delays  \n    - This approach clarifies responsibility and prevents stalled decisions due to indecision or conflicting opinions  \n    - It ensures the final materials meet leadership expectations and strategic goals","outline":null,"keywords":["sales guide","Battle Card","Illustrator","InDesign","product launch","animated video storyboard"],"overview":"- **Sales Guide Design:** Finalizing designs to improve usability and visual consistency. Adjustments to tab width and section headers agreed upon.  \n- **Content Update Efficiency:** Transitioning Battle Card templates to InDesign for faster edits and collaboration. Will enhance content update speed.  \n- **Product Launch Coordination:** Optimizer launch content near completion, with emphasis on quick feedback to meet deadlines for subsequent launches.  \n- **Reusable Design Assets:** Successful use of flexible icons in PowerPoint supports faster slide creation and enhances visual consistency.  \n- **Phased Rollout Strategy:** Animated videos will be tested with Optimizer, gathering feedback before extending to Info Print Manager and RPD.  \n- **Cross-Team Collaboration:** Clear ownership of feedback loops ensures design speed and quality, with executive input streamlining final decisions.","action_items":"\n**Lou Bogani**\nCreate revised sales guide table of contents design iterations removing red boxed numbers and increasing headline font size (15:30)\nRefine title page layouts by making the “balloon” element smaller and narrowing the tab; prepare alternative title page versions with and without product images and without computer mockups for executive review (21:40)\nProvide updated design ideas to Nathalie Mintjens for distribution to reviewers later in the day (22:30)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nDistribute revised sales guide design ideas and storyboard graphics for the animated video once available (24:01)\nCoordinate with Roz and Lou on review feedback and content progress for the Battle Card and sales guide templates (22:30)\n\n**Rozalynne Regan**\nFinalize content for the Optimizer Battle Card and send to Lou for format transition from Illustrator to InDesign (10:35)\nContinue management and review of Optimizer brochure content aiming for end-of-month completion (11:00)\nProvide feedback on animated video storyboard graphics upon receipt (11:00)\nOversee approval process for sales guide title page versions with executive (Linea Wolken) and coordinate future launches of related product marketing materials (20:10)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"b9521616-8d46-4f87-9ccd-9ff31d820ca6","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
