INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Sales Guide Design and Template Improvements**

The team is finalizing the sales guide design to improve usability and visual consistency while streamlining ongoing content updates.

- **Lou Bogani presented multiple table of contents design iterations** featuring variations with images, tabs, and logos to maintain brand alignment without overwhelming the layout (12:48)  
    - Roz preferred the design with an image on the left and a left-side bar, noting it fits better with existing branding  
    - They agreed to remove the red numbered boxes on the right, increasing font size on section headers to simplify appearance  
    - Lou will adjust the tab width and reduce the balloon graphic size to avoid distracting from titles  
    - Roz emphasized balancing visual appeal with clarity to avoid creating a new design system that conflicts with current branding

- **Title page designs were reviewed with focus on layout and imagery** to maintain brand coherence while allowing flexibility for content length (15:29)  
    - Roz requested versions both with and without the balloon graphic, suggesting adding the product image as an alternative  
    - Lou committed to providing three versions: smaller balloon with narrow tab, product image replacing balloon, and product image without computer mockup for better detail visibility  
    - Roz explained the move away from computer mockups to larger standalone product images improves clarity across all product presentations

- **Roz highlighted the importance of making future content updates easier** by transferring the Battle Card template from Illustrator to InDesign after finalizing design (07:24)  
    - Lou agreed to convert the final template to InDesign to facilitate quick content changes and reduce editing friction  
    - Roz noted Ricoh’s detailed wording reviews require flexibility in making small text changes rapidly  
    - This shift will streamline future updates and allow smoother collaboration between design and content teams

- **The refreshed sales guide aligns with ongoing product rebranding efforts** and supports upcoming launches for Optimizer, Info Print Manager, and RPD (22:15)  
    - Roz shared a plan to test the animated video and sales guide with Optimizer first before extending to other products  
    - Nathalie confirmed graphics for the storyboard will be delivered today to stay on track for end-of-month deadlines (10:46)  
    - The team acknowledged this phased rollout reduces risk and gathers feedback to improve subsequent launches

## **Product Marketing Content and Launch Coordination**

The team is managing content finalization for the Optimizer product launch while preparing for subsequent product marketing efforts.

- **Roz is close to completing the Optimizer Battle Card content, aiming for end-of-month readiness** to meet tight launch schedules (11:12)  
    - The team is incorporating feedback from multiple stakeholders to refine messaging and ensure clarity  
    - Roz emphasized the need to avoid delays due to prolonged content discussions, highlighting the importance of quick reviews  
    - Once finalized, this Battle Card will serve as the template for other product marketing collateral, improving consistency

- **Nathalie and Lou are collaborating closely to finalize graphic assets and design iterations** supporting the Optimizer launch and future campaigns (24:01)  
    - Nathalie will send finalized graphics to Roz for review, ensuring visuals align with brand guidelines and messaging  
    - Lou will incorporate final design feedback and prepare versions for executive review by Linea to secure approvals  
    - Roz stressed maintaining momentum after Optimizer to quickly move on to Info Print Manager and RPD launches

- **The team is balancing speed and quality in deliverables to support three back-to-back product launches** without slipping on deadlines (11:12)  
    - Roz noted the complexity of aligning look and feel while integrating new design elements is causing some delays  
    - They are using the Optimizer project as a test case to refine processes and tools for subsequent launches  
    - This approach aims to reduce rework and improve efficiency across the product marketing pipeline

## **Process and Tool Improvements for Design Workflow**

Shifting design templates to more flexible tools will reduce friction in content updates and improve responsiveness to feedback.

- **Moving Battle Card templates from Illustrator to InDesign will streamline content edits** and reduce the manual work involved in adding links and formatting (07:24)  
    - Roz described Illustrator as cumbersome for text changes and link management, impacting turnaround times  
    - Lou confirmed willingness to convert templates once designs are finalized to improve operational efficiency  
    - This change will empower marketing teams to make quick copy tweaks without design team bottlenecks

- **Use of flexible icon sets in PowerPoint was confirmed as successful** to ease slide creation and improve visual consistency (07:19)  
    - Roz explained that the new line drawing icons can be pulled apart and used on different backgrounds for greater versatility  
    - This flexibility reduces design iteration time and supports accessibility-related updates  
    - The positive reception indicates adoption of reusable assets is helping standardize presentations

- **The team is mindful of balancing visual refresh with brand consistency to avoid user confusion** (13:50)  
    - Lou kept design changes subtle to maintain continuity with existing brand elements  
    - Roz highlighted the importance of familiar layouts for user comfort and easier adoption  
    - This philosophy supports better market positioning by strengthening brand recognition while updating aesthetics

## **Long-Term Product Marketing Strategy and Vision**

The ongoing product marketing refreshes aim to support multi-product launches with consistent, user-friendly materials that resonate with customers.

- **Roz outlined a phased rollout plan for animated videos and sales guides across three key products** to build momentum and gather user feedback (11:36)  
    - Starting with Optimizer allows the team to refine messaging based on real reactions before Info Print Manager and RPD launches  
    - This strategic sequencing reduces risk and ensures higher quality collateral for later launches  
    - The approach reflects a vision to create scalable marketing assets adaptable across product lines

- **The refreshed collateral supports rebranding efforts aligned with current market positioning** to strengthen competitive differentiation (21:49)  
    - Roz noted many products are undergoing rebranding, making this the ideal time to update sales materials  
    - Lou’s designs integrate brand guide colors and elements to maintain a unified look  
    - This alignment will help customers easily identify the brand and its evolving offerings

- **The team is focused on creating materials that aid sales and marketing teams in communicating product value clearly** (12:48)  
    - Clear, clean layouts with linked navigation and flexible imagery will improve user engagement  
    - Removing distracting elements like numbered boxes enhances readability and professionalism  
    - This user-centric approach supports better sales outcomes and faster onboarding of new team members

## **Cross-Team Collaboration and Communication**

Strong coordination between design, marketing, and leadership is driving progress toward launch targets with clear ownership and feedback loops.

- **Roz is acting as the key liaison for content feedback and approvals, managing multiple stakeholders efficiently** (07:24)  
    - She coordinates review cycles and shields the design team from protracted wording disputes with Ricoh  
    - Roz’s focus on quick turnarounds helps keep the project on schedule despite complex details  
    - This role is critical to balancing quality with speed in content finalization

- **Lou and Nathalie are committed to rapid iteration and delivery of design assets** to support marketing’s evolving needs (22:32)  
    - Lou plans to share updated designs with Nathalie today for further distribution to the European team  
    - Nathalie will ensure graphics are delivered promptly for review and integration into launch materials  
    - Their collaboration exemplifies a tight feedback loop enabling agile responses to changing requirements

- **Executive input from Linea will finalize design decisions for title slides and imagery** providing clear decision authority (19:22)  
    - Roz will present multiple design options to Linea to streamline approval and avoid further delays  
    - This approach clarifies responsibility and prevents stalled decisions due to indecision or conflicting opinions  
    - It ensures the final materials meet leadership expectations and strategic goals',
  '2025-11-20 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Create revised sales guide table of contents design iterations removing red boxed numbers and increasing headline font size (15:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Refine title page layouts by making the “balloon” element smaller and narrowing the tab; prepare alternative title page versions with and without product images and without computer mockups for executive review (21:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide updated design ideas to Nathalie Mintjens for distribution to reviewers later in the day (22:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Distribute revised sales guide design ideas and storyboard graphics for the animated video once available (24:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Roz and Lou on review feedback and content progress for the Battle Card and sales guide templates (22:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize content for the Optimizer Battle Card and send to Lou for format transition from Illustrator to InDesign (10:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue management and review of Optimizer brochure content aiming for end-of-month completion (11:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on animated video storyboard graphics upon receipt (11:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Oversee approval process for sales guide title page versions with executive (Linea Wolken) and coordinate future launches of related product marketing materials (20:10)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards (2025-11-19 19:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1f878142-1760-4df2-805b-1f114427475d',
    '2025-11-19 19:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9YV0EPE91QP7PE5CJX855DJ',
    'MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
    '{"nancieruder","Rachel Curtis","Julia Oher (Noetic)","Nathalie Mintjens","nancieruder","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    3791,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1',
    '{"id":"01K9YV0EPE91QP7PE5CJX855DJ","title":"MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards","summary":{"notes":"## **Noetic Marketing Campaigns and Lead Management**\n\nThe team is closing in on delivering the **Thankful mailer campaign scheduled for launch tomorrow**, with attention on ensuring email signature updates to include **2025 best places to work, social handles, and woman-owned status** (06:47).\n\n- **Current delivery status shows 35 points completed and 70 points in progress for November**, with a monthly budget of **80 points** and an overage of **about 400 points worth $40,000** discussed openly by Colin Costigan (10:24).\n    - Overages stem from iterative campaign development to find effective lead quality.\n    - Colin plans to negotiate gifting points back, especially for the new AI campaign, to avoid cost penalties.\n    - The team values fairness and transparency on scope and cost.\n\n- **Lead scoring adjustments were implemented for LinkedIn form fills** to prevent low-quality leads from entering Pipedrive directly by setting a lead score threshold of **8 out of 10**, with a threshold to enter Pipedrive at **10** (17:40).\n    - This filter appears effective, as no recent lead anomalies have been reported.\n    - Specific leads like Kim Cox and Dan who completed the brand health diagnostic are actively tracked and assigned appropriately.\n    - The team is maintaining vigilance on lead quality and funnel integrity.\n\n- **Ongoing client engagement includes second calls with Waymo and Marriott contacts**, with mixed warm leads and some follow-ups pending (21:46).\n    - Marriott shows potential despite recent industry turbulence, including Sonder''s bankruptcy.\n    - The hospitality sector’s challenges could create consulting opportunities, as noted by Nathalie Mintjens and Colin Costigan.\n\n## **AI Offering Strategy and Market Positioning**\n\nNoetic is preparing to launch a **new AI service offering targeting mid-sized companies with over 100 employees**, addressing the uneven and siloed use of AI in organizations (27:18).\n\n- **The AI campaign will focus on probing questions about team-wide AI adoption and governance**, avoiding scare tactics tied to layoffs at Salesforce or Shopify (31:50).\n    - Nancy Mintjens emphasizes the importance of accessibility and empathy given budget pressures and client uncertainty.\n    - Messaging aims to highlight the gap between individual AI use and coordinated, efficient team workflows.\n\n- **Colin Costigan recommends a three to four email sequence coupled with two to three ad variations for LinkedIn**, focusing on concise, curiosity-driven messaging with scroll-stopping graphics (33:41).\n    - The ads will visually contrast siloed individual AI use versus collaborative, efficient team workflows.\n    - The creative approach will emphasize collective strength and compliance, not just individual productivity gains.\n    - Julia Oher cautioned that effective AI use requires effort and thoughtful prompting, which should be reflected in messaging.\n\n- **A dedicated landing page for the AI offering will be developed but initially kept off the main website navigation**, linked only through ads and emails to gather user interaction data before public release (34:03).\n    - The page will state the problem, showcase Noetic’s solutions, and include downloadable one-pagers plus a video featuring Nancy explaining the AI offering.\n    - The team debated where AI fits on the website, agreeing it aligns most naturally under Training and Coaching for now, with possible future site structure revisions in December.\n    - This phased approach balances resource effort with market testing and audience education.\n\n## **Content and Podcast Program Updates**\n\nThe team has **enough recorded content to sustain through November and December without new client recordings**, supporting a strategic focus on internal episodes during quieter client periods (24:09).\n\n- **Active communication with key podcast guests Mac Phil and Chris O’Boyle continues**, with some scheduling into early 2024 possible (24:11).\n    - Internal episodes are designed to promote Noetic’s services and generate interest from existing networks.\n    - Positive guest engagement is boosted by Rachel Curtis’s proactive encouragement, helping reduce guest nervousness.\n\n- **A new podcast framework template with an introductory paragraph was created** to give guests clear context and ease their participation, enhancing professionalism and personal touch (44:13).\n    - This evergreen framework aims for consistent quality and guest comfort.\n    - Rachel and Nathalie highlighted the importance of genuine guest encouragement to maintain high-quality conversations.\n\n- **Colin will produce an end-of-year compilation video** featuring podcast highlights to showcase growth and milestones from the first year of the Metamorphosis Moment series (01:02:12).\n    - This aligns with the team’s goal to celebrate progress and maintain momentum.\n    - The video project was previously on the wish list and will now be prioritized.\n\n## **Website SEO and User Engagement Improvements**\n\nTo address **declining traffic on the Insights page**, Colin proposed SEO-driven copy adjustments emphasizing \"Brand Insights for Marketing Leaders\" and related keywords to improve organic search rankings (45:48).\n\n- **Revised headline and section descriptions focus on practical frameworks, market trends, and team challenges**, aligned with common search terms rather than internal jargon (46:00).\n    - This should help increase visibility for podcasts, playbooks, and blog content.\n    - Nathalie Mintjens confirmed she can implement these copy changes directly on the website.\n\n- **Monitoring metrics show average session duration at about 2 minutes 40 seconds, three times the industry average, despite a slight bounce rate increase** (50:35).\n    - The bounce rate remains below the 60% industry benchmark, indicating good engagement quality.\n    - Colin emphasized SEO as a long-term strategy requiring ongoing adjustment and user behavior analysis.\n\n- **The website update process will include training Julia Oher on content edits**, supporting team capacity building for future site maintenance (48:52).\n    - This supports operational efficiency and internal ownership of digital assets.\n\n## **Process Automation and Reporting Enhancements**\n\nColin introduced a **new automated weekly email summarizing recent and upcoming activities** related to points delivered, purchases, and campaign status, scheduled for Fridays at 4pm Eastern Time (51:41).\n\n- **The automation extracts data from the last 14 days and the next 30 days**, providing a designed, clear summary for easy review (54:08).\n    - Nathalie Mintjens will include Rocky and Tiffany as CC recipients to increase cross-team visibility.\n    - The email includes a direct link to the dashboard for quick access to detailed data.\n\n- This improvement is expected to **reduce manual reporting effort and improve stakeholder alignment on project progress**.\n    - Colin acknowledged initial technical challenges but committed to stable delivery.\n    - The automation aligns with the team’s goal to streamline communications and provide timely updates.\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Culture Insights**\n\nThe recent **in-person retreat at Lansdowne Resort fostered valuable team bonding and strategic work on integrating AI into Noetic processes** (12:56).\n\n- The team appreciated the setting’s balance of convenience, cost, and space, supporting productive collaboration (13:20).\n    - Activities included a memorable “Disc assessment” session and creative icebreakers like a tool to punish jargon use.\n    - These sessions strengthen team cohesion, morale, and remote work balance.\n\n- Discussions highlighted the **importance of empathy for guest nerves during podcasts**, with Rachel praised for her supportive approach that helps guests relax and perform well (44:58).\n    - This cultural attention enhances content quality and client relationships.\n    - The team values humility and authenticity in interactions.\n\n- The group expressed enthusiasm for ongoing internal knowledge sharing and training, including website update skills for newer members like Julia (48:52).\n    - This promotes team growth and operational resilience.\n    - Collaborative humor and storytelling remain part of the positive team dynamic.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI integration","lead scoring","podcast updates","website SEO","campaign automation","team retreat"],"overview":"- **Thankful Mailer Campaign Launch:** Campaign launching tomorrow; updates include 2025 awards, social handles, and woman-owned status.  \n- **Delivery and Budget Status:** 35 points completed, 70 in progress; budget overage of 400 points costing $40,000 discussed for November.  \n- **Lead Quality Improvements:** New scoring for LinkedIn forms; leads now require score of 10 to enter Pipedrive, ensuring higher quality.  \n- **AI Service Strategy:** New AI offering for mid-sized companies, focusing on team-wide adoption and governance without scare tactics.  \n- **Content Strategy Updates:** Enough podcast content recorded through December; focusing on internal episodes; new template created for guest participation.  \n- **SEO Enhancements:** Revised website copy to improve traffic; average session duration is currently 2 minutes 40 seconds, indicating good engagement.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend finalized thankful mailer to Nancy and Rachel for review (08:23)\n\n**Nancy**\nConfirm and finalize email signature formats to include workplace awards and social handles prior to thankful mailer launch (06:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nReview and gift points back to Noetic for AI campaign effort and negotiate points budget adjustments with internal team (12:16)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nAssist Nancy and Colin with placing finalized AI one-pagers on offerings page and helping shape AI campaign messaging tone (34:58)\n\n**Julia Oher**\nAttend scheduled training on website content updates and ongoing site maintenance (48:59)\n"},"duration":63.18000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":1,"name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"id":2,"name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"id":3,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":4,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":5,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi.","index":0,"end_time":345.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":347.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hi, Julia.","index":2,"end_time":349.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":3,"end_time":350.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.57,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Nice to meet you too.","index":4,"end_time":352.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":351.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I was having trouble getting in, so I''m.","index":5,"end_time":355.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.17,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I''m gonna just close the loop with Rachel.","index":6,"end_time":357.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.45,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I was like sending her a message being like, oh my God, I can''t get into this meeting.","index":7,"end_time":361.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.45,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":362.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I also, I just jumped off.","index":9,"end_time":365.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":363.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I didn''t know if I had the right link.","index":10,"end_time":367.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Nor do I.","index":11,"end_time":369.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.61,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":12,"end_time":371.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like it''s the right one.","index":13,"end_time":375.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":374.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hi guys.","index":14,"end_time":383.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hello.","index":15,"end_time":384.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hi.","index":16,"end_time":384.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.21,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Natalie, did you meet Julia?","index":17,"end_time":387.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Julia, did you meet Natalie?","index":18,"end_time":389.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Briefly.","index":19,"end_time":390.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.69,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"We were reminiscing over the fact that I was like, oh my gosh, am I in the right.","index":20,"end_time":393.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.05,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Did I join the right meeting?","index":21,"end_time":395.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.61,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I sent Rachel sos.","index":22,"end_time":397.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.29,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I was having trouble getting on.","index":23,"end_time":400.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.25,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"You''re in the right place.","index":24,"end_time":401.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.17,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was having trouble getting on also.","index":25,"end_time":402.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":26,"end_time":403.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.29,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Well, that makes me feel so much better.","index":27,"end_time":406.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"All right guys, we are finishing scheduling the thankful mailer to go live tomorrow.","index":28,"end_time":411.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you for all your work.","index":29,"end_time":414.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You''re welcome.","index":30,"end_time":415.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I just gotta do Nancy, make sure your signature is good to go.","index":31,"end_time":419.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And Racky had the same issue as you, so we are.","index":32,"end_time":422.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I just asked you, can you stay on after because I am not sure.","index":33,"end_time":429.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We will figure it out.","index":34,"end_time":431.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m not sure why things are getting cut off because it did for Raki too.","index":35,"end_time":438.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":432.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We tried to do it through Tiffany on yours like on the main website of Outlook but I don''t know that it worked.","index":36,"end_time":445.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":438.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll just.","index":37,"end_time":445.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":445.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":38,"end_time":446.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It doesn''t look right to me but I hope I''m wrong.","index":39,"end_time":450.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I do too.","index":40,"end_time":452.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''re trying, Natalie.","index":41,"end_time":453.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''re trying to add our best places.","index":42,"end_time":456.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":453.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To work in 2025 and our social handles and our being woman owned into.","index":43,"end_time":464.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Our signatures and our emails and it''s such a.","index":44,"end_time":466.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":464.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sounds so easy and it''s not.","index":45,"end_time":470.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":466.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s super glitchy just in the formatting of it all.","index":46,"end_time":475.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":470.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So Rachel has been forging that and.","index":47,"end_time":477.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":475.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We really wanted to get it out.","index":48,"end_time":478.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Before the thankful mailer blasts out to.","index":49,"end_time":481.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":478.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All the people we know.","index":50,"end_time":482.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is Colin coming and he''s just running late.","index":51,"end_time":485.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it should be.","index":52,"end_time":486.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":485.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll send him.","index":53,"end_time":488.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll give him another look him another minute.","index":54,"end_time":490.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.42,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So that''s our big news on the.","index":55,"end_time":492.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Noetic marketing front is the thankful mailer.","index":56,"end_time":497.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Will go to the database tomorrow.","index":57,"end_time":499.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People, you guys have seen it.","index":58,"end_time":502.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":500.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":502.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And I''m going to set it up to go to you both now since I''m in there, I''ll send it over.","index":60,"end_time":509.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That way you guys can get it today.","index":61,"end_time":511.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":62,"end_time":514.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":513.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about being a few minutes late here guys.","index":63,"end_time":516.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":514.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":64,"end_time":517.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We all Word happens.","index":65,"end_time":518.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":517.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We were all just a little late.","index":66,"end_time":521.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I''m.","index":67,"end_time":523.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":521.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m out Thursday, Friday, and all of next week, so my work has condensed into three days.","index":68,"end_time":528.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":523.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oi, that sounds fun.","index":69,"end_time":531.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":531.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":531.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, let''s dive in.","index":71,"end_time":534.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":72,"end_time":535.289,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":534.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll pull my screen.","index":73,"end_time":536.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.289,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Colin, is this your first meeting of Julia?","index":74,"end_time":539.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":75,"end_time":540.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":539.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":76,"end_time":540.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.37,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":77,"end_time":541.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.01,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Hi, Julia.","index":78,"end_time":542.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":541.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to meet you as well for great things.","index":79,"end_time":544.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":542.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, thank you.","index":80,"end_time":545.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.29,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"And Julia is based in Chicago and.","index":81,"end_time":549.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is newer to the Noetic team, but she''s.","index":82,"end_time":552.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":550.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know, I feel like you''ve been here a while now because you''re just up to speed.","index":83,"end_time":556.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":552.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I feel the same way.","index":84,"end_time":558.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.25,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"And then I think about how short of a time it''s been and I''m shocked.","index":85,"end_time":562.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.25,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"But very happy to be joining Noetic and this team.","index":86,"end_time":565.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.21,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"We''re excited to have you.","index":87,"end_time":569.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":567.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":570.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":570.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie''s actually based in Chicago as well.","index":89,"end_time":572.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":570.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":90,"end_time":573.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":573.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I think you guys are actually near each other.","index":91,"end_time":575.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":573.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m in the West Loop.","index":92,"end_time":578.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So am I.","index":93,"end_time":579.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.72,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Really?","index":94,"end_time":580.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.92,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t recognize your background.","index":95,"end_time":583,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"So I don''t think I''m in your background, but I''m like next to Ogilvy.","index":96,"end_time":589.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":97,"end_time":590.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m like Morgan and Randolph.","index":98,"end_time":594.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Ish.","index":99,"end_time":594.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":595.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.04,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Next to all the restaurants.","index":101,"end_time":597.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":102,"end_time":598.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.6,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"All right, let''s dive in.","index":103,"end_time":602.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":601.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So usual flow today we''ll go through just a recheck on the portal and where we''re at on points delivered.","index":104,"end_time":611.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":606.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go through the playbooks, updates on the context that we checked into from pipedrive that we went over last week, some content updates, then we''ll dive into the data.","index":105,"end_time":621.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":611.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very good.","index":106,"end_time":623.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So looking at points, so so far, November, we''ve delivered 35 points and we have 70 more in working.","index":107,"end_time":629.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":624.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just waiting on.","index":108,"end_time":631.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":630.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you guys had retreat last week as well, so whenever you have a chance to review the Julie Spencer Washington, the no Hop Dolla, Bulbul and Meg episodes, let us know.","index":109,"end_time":642.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":631.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":110,"end_time":643.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so Bulbul we reviewed and sent off to her to review.","index":111,"end_time":648.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''re good on that for now.","index":112,"end_time":649.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":648.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then you now she''s higher scrutiny just because Nike''s very strict.","index":113,"end_time":655.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":114,"end_time":656.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then you all now should have every episode except for the one we recorded yesterday with Patrick.","index":115,"end_time":663.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if there''s anything missing, just let me know.","index":116,"end_time":666.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But I had the time to catch up yesterday, so they all should be there.","index":117,"end_time":670.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":118,"end_time":670.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":671.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, we saw a few submissions come through.","index":120,"end_time":673.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":671.389,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":121,"end_time":674.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":673.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":122,"end_time":675.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And Colin, overall on points, I feel.","index":123,"end_time":678.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.23,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like we were burning a lot hotter.","index":124,"end_time":680.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":678.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Than this in the past.","index":125,"end_time":682.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is this more like where we should be?","index":126,"end_time":687.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just.","index":127,"end_time":688.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":688.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":688.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I always get A little confused.","index":129,"end_time":690.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"With the working, you know.","index":130,"end_time":692.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":131,"end_time":693.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":692.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So working is.","index":132,"end_time":693.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":693.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few that close out at the end of the month for working because that''s like managing ABM or managing paid.","index":133,"end_time":699.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":694.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like every week our team is going in there and it just closes out at the end of the month.","index":134,"end_time":702.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":699.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":135,"end_time":704.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":704.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, you guys pay for 80 points a month.","index":136,"end_time":706.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":704.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have gone above that just because we''re trying to find like the right groove of campaign that''s going to bring in the right quality leads.","index":137,"end_time":713.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":707.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I can talk to Justin and Tristan also about maybe we can gift some points back to you for.","index":138,"end_time":719.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":714.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For like this AI project, for example, so that it wouldn''t cost you guys any points.","index":139,"end_time":722.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":719.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we want to do what''s fair.","index":140,"end_time":725.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":723.799,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, you know, if we''re.","index":141,"end_time":727.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If we''re over scope or overburned in the net net of it all, you know, you can, you can tell us like what you can and can''t do.","index":142,"end_time":735.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":727.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":143,"end_time":736.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":736.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, in full transparency.","index":144,"end_time":737.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":736.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ve talked to Tristan, Justin about this.","index":145,"end_time":739.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":737.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re about 400 points over, which is about $40,000.","index":146,"end_time":744.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":740.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ve also talked to them about how initially we were not hitting goals.","index":147,"end_time":748.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":744.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we needed to develop a lot of new campaigns and get into quick iterations of tests.","index":148,"end_time":752.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":748.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why I''m saying I can also talk to them about just gifting points.","index":149,"end_time":756.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":752.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, this new campaign we''re putting together for the AI offering wouldn''t actually charge you guys any points.","index":150,"end_time":761.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":756.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":151,"end_time":762.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":152,"end_time":763.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, well, we don''t want you to get in trouble.","index":153,"end_time":766.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":763.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":154,"end_time":767.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":766.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, I need to take a pause here.","index":155,"end_time":771.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":770.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was.","index":156,"end_time":772.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":772.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your Thursday, Friday session last week?","index":157,"end_time":776.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":773.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, really good.","index":158,"end_time":778.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":776.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Really good.","index":159,"end_time":779.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We.","index":160,"end_time":780.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it was technically Wednesday Thursday.","index":161,"end_time":782.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":780.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We all had dinner Wednesday, and then.","index":162,"end_time":785.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":783.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We met most of the day Thursday and we were out.","index":163,"end_time":790.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know if you are familiar, Colin, because you''re sort of local.","index":164,"end_time":795.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":791.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Ish.","index":165,"end_time":796.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s deeper into Virginia.","index":166,"end_time":798.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":796.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The Lansdowne Resort.","index":167,"end_time":800.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":798.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, I''ve heard of it.","index":168,"end_time":801.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":800.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve never been there.","index":169,"end_time":802.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":801.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s in Leesburg.","index":170,"end_time":803.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":802.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And if you ever are like bringing.","index":171,"end_time":806.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People in, it''s pretty convenient to the.","index":172,"end_time":809.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":806.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Airport, but not as expensive as if you, you know, brought people downtown.","index":173,"end_time":815.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s off by itself and very beautiful.","index":174,"end_time":818.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sits on a golf course, has very like really spacious lobby area where you.","index":175,"end_time":824.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can just like find nooks and crannies to hang out.","index":176,"end_time":826.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":824.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And they''re.","index":177,"end_time":826.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And they''re very accommodating, whether you''re like a small group like us or A bigger group.","index":178,"end_time":830.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They.","index":179,"end_time":831.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You.","index":180,"end_time":832.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.74,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"They treat you very, very well.","index":181,"end_time":833.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":832.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":182,"end_time":834.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":833.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we had.","index":183,"end_time":836.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We had just a whole bunch of.","index":184,"end_time":837.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":836.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Cool stuff that we did.","index":185,"end_time":838.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And one of the things.","index":186,"end_time":839.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":838.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That we did at the beginning of the day.","index":187,"end_time":844.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Was working on, like, AI into our own processes.","index":188,"end_time":847.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":844.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Per.","index":189,"end_time":847.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know what I shared with you.","index":190,"end_time":849.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s super exciting.","index":191,"end_time":851.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":850.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":851.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":851.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually do ours, our quarterly meetings in Richmond because that''s where Justin and Chair center based.","index":193,"end_time":856.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":851.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we were at.","index":194,"end_time":857.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":856.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is the name of the resort?","index":195,"end_time":860.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":858.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":196,"end_time":863.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":862.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Dominion Club.","index":197,"end_time":865.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":864.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":198,"end_time":866.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":866.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In Richmond.","index":199,"end_time":867.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":866.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, similar experience.","index":200,"end_time":868.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":867.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve also been in at the last agency, when we were doing quarterly leadership meetings, it was in a.","index":201,"end_time":874.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":869.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A conference room that we could rent at a very small business.","index":202,"end_time":877.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":875.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, I''ve had the small conference room.","index":203,"end_time":880.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":878.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve had the large, large conference room.","index":204,"end_time":881.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":880.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Small teams, big teams.","index":205,"end_time":882.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":881.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of got a mix of all of them.","index":206,"end_time":884.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":883.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you just make it work.","index":207,"end_time":886.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":884.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Depending upon that.","index":208,"end_time":887.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But, yeah.","index":209,"end_time":888.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What would you guys add?","index":210,"end_time":889.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":888.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Julia, Rachel, what was your favorite thing?","index":211,"end_time":893.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We.","index":212,"end_time":894.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":894.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They had the northern lights, but we.","index":213,"end_time":896.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":895.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Couldn''T open our eyes, so we took.","index":214,"end_time":899.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Our phones, just ran around trying, like.","index":215,"end_time":902.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":899.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Outside, like, Rachel truly led that initiative too.","index":216,"end_time":907.999,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.96,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I was committed.","index":217,"end_time":909.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was so committed.","index":218,"end_time":911.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I feel like we just had a lot of fun.","index":219,"end_time":914.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I wish we all got to see each other more.","index":220,"end_time":916.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But also, like, there''s perks to working remotely.","index":221,"end_time":919.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":916.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":922.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think Disc a Palooza, that was, like, total highlight, I thought.","index":223,"end_time":926.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.28,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah, me too.","index":224,"end_time":927.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We did a whole presentation on disc assessments.","index":225,"end_time":931.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":928.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''ve ever taken those, but yeah, we did, like, a dive into those, which was fun.","index":226,"end_time":937.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":931.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Talked about philanthropy, all different stuff.","index":227,"end_time":940.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":937.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it was a good mix.","index":228,"end_time":942.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.8,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":229,"end_time":943.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So little time all in person that, you know, we just.","index":230,"end_time":947.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":943.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We actually just enjoy each other.","index":231,"end_time":950.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":232,"end_time":951.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":950.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":233,"end_time":952.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":951.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s so refreshing.","index":234,"end_time":953.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":952.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right in today''s day and age of how, you know, work goes.","index":235,"end_time":955.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":953.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":236,"end_time":956.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":955.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":237,"end_time":957.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":956.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":957.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":957.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For disc assessment, actually, before New north was acquired by Marketers in Demand a few years ago, disc assessment was part of your own, like, before you got hired.","index":239,"end_time":965.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":957.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":240,"end_time":967.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I still had to do that, Colin.","index":241,"end_time":969.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, you did?","index":242,"end_time":969.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":969.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":971.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":970.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":971.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":971.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What were you guys doing?","index":245,"end_time":973.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":971.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you remember what your disc styles were?","index":246,"end_time":974.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I actually had my D and I were equal at.","index":247,"end_time":980.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":975.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At the high.","index":248,"end_time":980.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":980.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d be surprised what it would be, or I''d be interested in what it is now.","index":249,"end_time":984.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":981.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cause that was five, six, seven years ago.","index":250,"end_time":986.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":984.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":988.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sometimes you move and sometimes you don''t.","index":252,"end_time":989.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Depending.","index":253,"end_time":990.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sometimes role kind of pushes you to.","index":254,"end_time":993.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":990.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Move, but not always.","index":255,"end_time":995.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I''d be interested since I started taking more managerial roles after that.","index":256,"end_time":999.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":996.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":1000.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Natalie, do you know what you were.","index":258,"end_time":1002.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1001.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":259,"end_time":1004.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":260,"end_time":1008.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"My D and C were very high, so.","index":261,"end_time":1012.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Your dc?","index":262,"end_time":1013.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1014.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1014.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":264,"end_time":1017.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Don''t remember what that means, though.","index":265,"end_time":1018.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1017.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, it''s.","index":266,"end_time":1019.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"They''re all great.","index":267,"end_time":1020.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m an si.","index":268,"end_time":1022.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I know some.","index":269,"end_time":1024.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1023.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like attention to detail or like there''s so many different questions to go into it and ask you the same questions, just different ways to see if your answers are consistent.","index":270,"end_time":1034.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1024.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, Exactly.","index":271,"end_time":1035.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1036.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":273,"end_time":1039.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"As part of the hiring process.","index":274,"end_time":1040.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think we do it anymore because we actually.","index":275,"end_time":1045.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1041.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we do still do it, but we have less weight in it because we started noticing it really changes pretty quickly sometimes once people get integrated into the system.","index":276,"end_time":1057.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1045.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":277,"end_time":1059.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1058.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, thanks for sharing.","index":278,"end_time":1060.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1059.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1061.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1060.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some updates, Nancy, we talked about last week, developing a lead score for LinkedIn form fills when people are downloading the playbook so they don''t go directly into Pipedrive.","index":280,"end_time":1071.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1061.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we disabled the direct to Pipedrive connection and we set the lead score at 8 for these.","index":281,"end_time":1077.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1071.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason we selected 8 is because we have the threshold at 10 now and most of the other activities are a plus 2 or plus 3.","index":282,"end_time":1084.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1078.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we figured that a very good sense of, you know, interaction if they''re downloading the playbook.","index":283,"end_time":1089.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1085.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we want them to take one other step of browsing the website, responding to something so that they pass that threshold and then they''re added to pipedrive.","index":284,"end_time":1097.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1089.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":285,"end_time":1098.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1098.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And so this.","index":286,"end_time":1099.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1098.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This person, Maurizio, did not go into.","index":287,"end_time":1103.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1099.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The leads or did.","index":288,"end_time":1106.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, I don''t.","index":289,"end_time":1107.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1106.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, please.","index":290,"end_time":1108.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1107.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen it.","index":291,"end_time":1109,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t think they do.","index":292,"end_time":1109.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1109,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen him.","index":293,"end_time":1110.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we turned it off before they submitted the form.","index":294,"end_time":1113.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1110.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they shouldn''t be in Pipedrive because it''s below.","index":295,"end_time":1117.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":296,"end_time":1118.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":297,"end_time":1118.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1118.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1119.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1119.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re at 8 out of 10 right now.","index":299,"end_time":1120.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1119.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1121.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1121.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I haven''t seen any.","index":301,"end_time":1123.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Weirdness in leads.","index":302,"end_time":1128.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1125.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I also, in the last few days haven''t seen any new ones come in either, but.","index":303,"end_time":1136.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1130.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But I know there were a couple.","index":304,"end_time":1137.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1136.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s your next slide, actually.","index":305,"end_time":1139.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That you were going to clarify on.","index":306,"end_time":1141.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That I''ve not actioned because I was.","index":307,"end_time":1142.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1141.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Trying to figure out if they were.","index":308,"end_time":1143.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1142.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If they should be actioned.","index":309,"end_time":1146.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1145.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1147.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1147.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Kim Cox had submitted the brand health diagnostic and that''s why, like, it came in with such little information that pretty much the only information you guys collect before they go into the diagnostic is their email address.","index":311,"end_time":1156.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1147.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why I just had their email.","index":312,"end_time":1158.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1157.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Jacinda had signed up for the newsletter And Dan had also completed the brand diagnostic.","index":313,"end_time":1164.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1159.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":314,"end_time":1166.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think.","index":315,"end_time":1170.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What is Kim Cox''s company.","index":316,"end_time":1175.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Check.","index":317,"end_time":1177.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1177.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now?","index":318,"end_time":1180.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m having trouble finding her.","index":319,"end_time":1181.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sibley memorial hospital, johns hopkins medicine.","index":320,"end_time":1198.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1196.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so she looks like she''s sitting in the Everyone not.","index":321,"end_time":1212.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":322,"end_time":1213.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Why would that happen?","index":323,"end_time":1214.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, I''m assigning her to me.","index":324,"end_time":1219.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1220.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1220.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looked like it had been sitting since August.","index":326,"end_time":1222.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1220.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we connected forms from the website to pipedrive, she, like, passed through.","index":327,"end_time":1226.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1222.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":328,"end_time":1228.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then Jacinda is also sitting in the everyone view.","index":329,"end_time":1235.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.92,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1237.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1237.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all she had done was sign up for the newsletter.","index":331,"end_time":1239.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1237.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wouldn''t say that''s necessarily a lead.","index":332,"end_time":1242.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1240.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":333,"end_time":1243.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":334,"end_time":1244.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.5,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":335,"end_time":1244.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then Dan.","index":336,"end_time":1247.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So Dan.","index":337,"end_time":1249.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1248.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So in the case of Kim and.","index":338,"end_time":1250.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Dan, did they both fill out the brand health.","index":339,"end_time":1254.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1250.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, that''s the source.","index":340,"end_time":1255.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1254.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the source channel.","index":341,"end_time":1258.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1256.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":342,"end_time":1261.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because I think.","index":343,"end_time":1262.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because when that happens, that feeds to us.","index":344,"end_time":1266.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1263.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that Sam replied to him and then he didn''t reply back.","index":345,"end_time":1270.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1266.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I will.","index":346,"end_time":1273.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I will see if there''s something to.","index":347,"end_time":1274.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1273.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Be done on him.","index":348,"end_time":1275.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Weirdly, they.","index":349,"end_time":1278.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1277.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I could be wrong.","index":350,"end_time":1282.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But they like went back to the every one view as opposed to the Nancy Leeds view.","index":351,"end_time":1287.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1282.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I have them.","index":352,"end_time":1289.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1288.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I have them in the right place now.","index":353,"end_time":1291.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":354,"end_time":1292.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1291.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you for clarifying on those, but I haven''t seen any weirdness since.","index":355,"end_time":1296.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1292.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think, I think the filters that you either upped or reinstated seem to be working.","index":356,"end_time":1303.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1296.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep, perfect.","index":357,"end_time":1304.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1303.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then while we''re on the subject.","index":358,"end_time":1307.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of leads, I have a call, second call with Waymo tomorrow.","index":359,"end_time":1313.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1307.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":360,"end_time":1315.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1314.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I have a live meeting with one of the Marriott people.","index":361,"end_time":1319.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1315.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":362,"end_time":1321.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1320.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also have a second Marriott person.","index":363,"end_time":1324.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1321.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So there were like 10 of them.","index":364,"end_time":1325.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1324.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''ll take two out of 10 a second.","index":365,"end_time":1328.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1326.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"One who we''re just in like, you.","index":366,"end_time":1334.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1328.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Know, back and forth.","index":367,"end_time":1335.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But she wanted to know, like, more capabilities and then acknowledge receiving what I.","index":368,"end_time":1341.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1335.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The information I had sent her and.","index":369,"end_time":1342.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1341.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Said that she would follow up.","index":370,"end_time":1343.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we''re, you know, it''s not as.","index":371,"end_time":1346.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Warm, but not nothing either.","index":372,"end_time":1349.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1346.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I will definitely report back on those.","index":373,"end_time":1355.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1351.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m just looking to see if there''s anything else.","index":374,"end_time":1357.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, and then I had a call with truest, one of the truest people.","index":375,"end_time":1362.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1358.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Nothing.","index":376,"end_time":1363.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nothing really stuck there.","index":377,"end_time":1367.509,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think she''s like, she''s fairly senior.","index":378,"end_time":1370.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.509,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But I think she''s a click down.","index":379,"end_time":1371.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1370.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But they do have an internal training.","index":380,"end_time":1375.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1372.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And coaching like center of Excellence.","index":381,"end_time":1378.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And.","index":382,"end_time":1378.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1378.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so she said that she would.","index":383,"end_time":1380.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"See if she could get me introduced to somebody there.","index":384,"end_time":1383.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1380.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":385,"end_time":1384.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1383.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all great updates.","index":386,"end_time":1386.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1384.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, A little bit of action.","index":387,"end_time":1389.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1386.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There I was checking out an article earlier, and Sonder, which is a company that was bought by Marriott, apparently just announced bankruptcy.","index":388,"end_time":1397.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1389.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just more interesting things happening in the world of Marriott.","index":389,"end_time":1400.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1397.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m very anxious to talk to.","index":390,"end_time":1404.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Tanya is her name.","index":391,"end_time":1405.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1404.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Tanya Galarza.","index":392,"end_time":1407.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1405.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We had worked together years and years ago when we did a big body of work for Marriott.","index":393,"end_time":1415.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1408.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so I just want to kind.","index":394,"end_time":1417.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1415.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of get the skinny on what''s going on over there.","index":395,"end_time":1419.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, seems like a lot of drama, potentially.","index":396,"end_time":1422.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1419.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think so.","index":397,"end_time":1423.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1422.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hospitality is a tough space, but sometimes drama breeds needing consulting help, breeds opportunity.","index":398,"end_time":1432.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1423.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":399,"end_time":1432.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1432.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll see.","index":400,"end_time":1433.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1433.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":401,"end_time":1435.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1434.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":402,"end_time":1436.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1435.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":403,"end_time":1437.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1437.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we kind of already talked about new episodes that have been submitted, so we''re going to work on those.","index":404,"end_time":1442.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1437.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are all dates accurate here for upcoming episodes?","index":405,"end_time":1446.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1443.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait, so Patrick yesterday.","index":406,"end_time":1449.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1446.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":407,"end_time":1450.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1449.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that one''s coming your way, Mac McGee.","index":408,"end_time":1453.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Try as I might, we were booked to speak today to try to land him getting booked and he had to cancel last minute.","index":409,"end_time":1461.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1453.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Now meeting with him in early December.","index":410,"end_time":1463.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1461.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So right now, everything as you''re seeing it is accurate.","index":411,"end_time":1468.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1464.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that if I would say Mac Phil and Chris o'' Boyle are like, I''m in like active communication with.","index":412,"end_time":1481.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1468.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so I could see a world.","index":413,"end_time":1483.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1481.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Where dates may land with them, but.","index":414,"end_time":1486.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think anybody else, and that''s an.","index":415,"end_time":1490.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1486.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If, not an not a when I.","index":416,"end_time":1492.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Could see them also pushing into 2024.","index":417,"end_time":1495.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1492.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, you know, we''ve worked ahead.","index":418,"end_time":1496.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We have enough content that if we''re.","index":419,"end_time":1498.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1496.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not doing more recordings in November and December, we''re okay.","index":420,"end_time":1504.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And that''s also why I was, like, keen on getting the internal episodes built, both because I think we will have some quieter time.","index":421,"end_time":1513.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1504.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, we certainly have people out.","index":422,"end_time":1514.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1513.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of the office as well, but it''ll be a quieter time with clients and.","index":423,"end_time":1519.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1514.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''S a good time to do internal episodes.","index":424,"end_time":1522.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1520.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But also, you know, I think those.","index":425,"end_time":1524.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Internal episodes are hard working in a.","index":426,"end_time":1528.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1524.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Different way than the typical podcasts are.","index":427,"end_time":1530.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The typical podcasts are getting good conversation with our prospect, you know, our ideal profile.","index":428,"end_time":1536.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I think the internal episodes do a good job of hopefully.","index":429,"end_time":1540.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, you can tell me if you think they do a good job, but of promoting stuff we do that people.","index":430,"end_time":1545.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"May have interest in.","index":431,"end_time":1547.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1545.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":432,"end_time":1548.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1548.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially when the guests are sharing it with their networks as well.","index":433,"end_time":1551.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1548.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1552.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Which I saw.","index":435,"end_time":1553.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1552.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, Kate did a great post thanking you for the.","index":436,"end_time":1556.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1553.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the conversation and everything there, too.","index":437,"end_time":1558.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1556.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":438,"end_time":1558.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1558.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did I not see that?","index":439,"end_time":1563.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, she had done like a repost with insights.","index":440,"end_time":1566.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1563.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s comms person.","index":441,"end_time":1570.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I know.","index":442,"end_time":1574.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1573.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I used to have a role where I posted on LinkedIn every day.","index":443,"end_time":1576.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1574.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it just.","index":444,"end_time":1576.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1576.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That fell to the wayside very quickly.","index":445,"end_time":1579.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1577.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is a lot.","index":446,"end_time":1580.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1579.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I.","index":447,"end_time":1583.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do not see that post.","index":448,"end_time":1586.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1585.519,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":449,"end_time":1588.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1587.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got a notification for it, like, on my phone, if I can find it quickly.","index":450,"end_time":1594,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1588.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you.","index":451,"end_time":1597.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I know that the algorithm changed.","index":452,"end_time":1600.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1597.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, is Joelle Park.","index":453,"end_time":1601.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1600.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":454,"end_time":1602.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1601.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not Kate.","index":455,"end_time":1602.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1602.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":456,"end_time":1603.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1602.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":457,"end_time":1604.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":458,"end_time":1605.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1604.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":459,"end_time":1606.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, you''re freaking me out.","index":460,"end_time":1608.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.61,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I can''t find it.","index":461,"end_time":1609.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1608.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, she had commented on there.","index":462,"end_time":1610.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1609.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":463,"end_time":1612.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1611.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, because Joelle''s went live.","index":464,"end_time":1613.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Kate was the one that we just did.","index":465,"end_time":1615.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1613.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":466,"end_time":1616.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1615.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Makes more sense.","index":467,"end_time":1618.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1617.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Makes more sense.","index":468,"end_time":1619.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":469,"end_time":1621.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1621.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But let''s talk through this AI offer.","index":470,"end_time":1623.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1621.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you sent over some information there and really just wanted.","index":471,"end_time":1631.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1623.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, look through the.","index":472,"end_time":1632.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1631.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The presentation that you had put together.","index":473,"end_time":1634.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1632.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that was what you talked through with the team on Thursday, I imagine.","index":474,"end_time":1637.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1634.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":475,"end_time":1639.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1638.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, yeah, I was talking about it from, like, the angle.","index":476,"end_time":1642.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1639.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was.","index":477,"end_time":1643.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1642.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was talking about it from the angle of an offering Noetta could do.","index":478,"end_time":1646.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1643.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But also then we were, like, rolling up our sleeves and kind of doing it on ourselves a bit.","index":479,"end_time":1650.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it was kind of both those things.","index":480,"end_time":1653.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1651.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":481,"end_time":1654.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1653.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have a little bit of information here, and I know I sent this over to you as well, so, you know, what you had in there outlined, I agree with.","index":482,"end_time":1662.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1655.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that the larger companies are either bringing in people to do this already, or they''re just investing in their current team rather than bringing in an agency.","index":483,"end_time":1670.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1662.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The midsize companies is where we''re seeing the most interest in this.","index":484,"end_time":1674,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1671.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I would say is there is, like, the between 10 and 100 employee size that could still be of interest, but the budget may be in question.","index":485,"end_time":1683.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1674.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just worry that if it''s.","index":486,"end_time":1686.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.37,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"10 to 100, I just think they''re.","index":487,"end_time":1688.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1686.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re not going to be affordable to them, and I think they feel like.","index":488,"end_time":1691.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1688.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We have to figure it out.","index":489,"end_time":1694.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":490,"end_time":1695.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1694.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I. I''m happy to set the.","index":491,"end_time":1698.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Floor at 100, because I think that''s.","index":492,"end_time":1700.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1698.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The point at which it starts to get unwieldy.","index":493,"end_time":1702.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1700.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I agree with that.","index":494,"end_time":1705.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1704.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":495,"end_time":1707.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1707.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to talk through what the offer of this is, what is going to entice these people to sign up, fill out the form, have a meeting with you.","index":496,"end_time":1716.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1708.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can play with names, certainly.","index":497,"end_time":1719.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1718.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I added this screenshot in here from your slide deck because it was my favorite design.","index":498,"end_time":1725.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1719.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what it looks like.","index":499,"end_time":1728.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1726.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":500,"end_time":1729.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1728.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It reminded me of an old spongebob episode.","index":501,"end_time":1733.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1730.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be like this, this or like this, but, you know, we need to entice these people, basically giving them something they can''t say no to.","index":502,"end_time":1743.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1733.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m picturing very, very short emails thinking, honestly, between one and five sentences max on these emails, really just poking a question like, are you using AI?","index":503,"end_time":1755.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1744.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What tools are you using?","index":504,"end_time":1756.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1755.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you been built any governance policies for how your company utilizes AI?","index":505,"end_time":1761.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1756.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you looking to implement this into your systems and enhancing your people?","index":506,"end_time":1765.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1761.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those types of angles?","index":507,"end_time":1767.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1766.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and I think the number one.","index":508,"end_time":1771.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like hook, because even though, like people using it unevenly is definitely true and what''s happening, and I think people are generally aware, but I think harder working from the vantage point of.","index":509,"end_time":1789.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1774.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, let me, let me back up against that insight.","index":510,"end_time":1794.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think the fact that we, you know, train and equip people, so it''s.","index":511,"end_time":1800.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1795.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like we can kind of even that out.","index":512,"end_time":1802.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1800.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think the, the bigger thing around.","index":513,"end_time":1805,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1802.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The offering, the bigger insight or pain.","index":514,"end_time":1807.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Point to me is people are using.","index":515,"end_time":1810.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1807.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It as individuals, but not as teams.","index":516,"end_time":1814.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1810.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And further to the point, and I''m.","index":517,"end_time":1819.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Not saying you would say this in an email, but further to the point, organizations have cut back and they''re expecting more from people, and yet these workflows.","index":518,"end_time":1830.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1819.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Have not been sorted.","index":519,"end_time":1832.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1830.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":520,"end_time":1832.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1832.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s like you''re, you''re sitting in a mess for a reason, you know?","index":521,"end_time":1837.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1832.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":522,"end_time":1837.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1837.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyway, all to say, there''s of course.","index":523,"end_time":1841.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Different angles you can take it from.","index":524,"end_time":1843.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1841.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I built two longer emails that I''m.","index":525,"end_time":1852.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1843.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Tailoring to people I know, and these.","index":526,"end_time":1856.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1852.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are like, they''re going deeper than you would want to go.","index":527,"end_time":1860.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1856.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I have one for the AI.","index":528,"end_time":1863.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Infused that when I send it to.","index":529,"end_time":1865.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1863.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Whoever, like, this is my base and then I tailor it further and then one for the human skills so I.","index":530,"end_time":1874.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can send you those just as fodder.","index":531,"end_time":1877.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1874.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, they definitely come at it from an angle and there are other angles.","index":532,"end_time":1883.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I.","index":533,"end_time":1883.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And that''s where, you know, you guys will bring in your expertise to think about, like, what are the angles?","index":534,"end_time":1889.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What are, are the right angles?","index":535,"end_time":1890.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1889.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Each of them only comes at it from an angle.","index":536,"end_time":1893.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I do think it''s, it''s worth my sharing.","index":537,"end_time":1896.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just so you see, you know, I shaped it based upon what I felt like I was hearing and seeing at.","index":538,"end_time":1906.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1896.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A lot of these conferences and from.","index":539,"end_time":1908.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1906.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People when I talk to them on.","index":540,"end_time":1909.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1908.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A one by one basis.","index":541,"end_time":1910.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1909.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that makes complete sense.","index":542,"end_time":1912.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1910.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, there are so many angles.","index":543,"end_time":1913.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1912.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One that I do not think would be one to take is like the scare of like, hey, you know, Salesforce fired 75% of their staff because they''re expecting the other 20% to be able to, you know, perform at the same clip.","index":544,"end_time":1925.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1914.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Shopify did the same thing.","index":545,"end_time":1928.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1926.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t Think that''s the angle that we need to take.","index":546,"end_time":1929.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1928.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s more of like probing questions of is your team using this?","index":547,"end_time":1933.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1929.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they using it in silos?","index":548,"end_time":1935.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1933.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have like a prompt library resource for your team to like get similar results or look at the similar process for how they''re looking at these tools?","index":549,"end_time":1944.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1936.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s the angle that we lean into.","index":550,"end_time":1946.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1944.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":551,"end_time":1948.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1947.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I know there''s a lot of.","index":552,"end_time":1950.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1948.28,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Leaders out there who are stressed out about this.","index":553,"end_time":1952.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1950.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":554,"end_time":1953.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1952.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they don''t have it figured out and yeah, I think too bearing in mind.","index":555,"end_time":1959.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1954.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I will send you that and.","index":556,"end_time":1962.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1959.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Know that these are just meant as fodder.","index":557,"end_time":1964.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1962.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":558,"end_time":1965.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1964.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, if anything, also it''s always more training for me on how Nancy writes her emails.","index":559,"end_time":1970.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1965.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I talk.","index":560,"end_time":1970.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1970.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":561,"end_time":1971.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1971,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":562,"end_time":1971.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1971.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The other thing I think that is important to just bear in mind is like, how do you get somebody to move who is themselves doing more with less has tons of budget pressure and this is really like they, they really know that they''re.","index":563,"end_time":1988.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1972.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They haven''t cracked this and they don''t.","index":564,"end_time":1990.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1988.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Know how to do it.","index":565,"end_time":1990.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s like sometimes those are the things that people kind of want to avoid.","index":566,"end_time":1994.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1990.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s got to feel like accessible.","index":567,"end_time":1997.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1995.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally with you.","index":568,"end_time":2000.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1998.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think LinkedIn''s a good channel for that too.","index":569,"end_time":2002.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2000.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can come in with a really like soft open conversation starter message there.","index":570,"end_time":2008.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2002.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":571,"end_time":2009.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I''m going into like problem solution.","index":572,"end_time":2011.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2009.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think you''re probably going to.","index":573,"end_time":2013.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2011.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Be a lot more on problem.","index":574,"end_time":2014.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2013.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":575,"end_time":2015.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2015.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we need to pique their interest and then point them, you know, once we have a landing page built.","index":576,"end_time":2020.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2015.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why I have a question mark here.","index":577,"end_time":2021.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2020.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Definitely use this visual if you want.","index":578,"end_time":2023.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2021.26,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":579,"end_time":2024.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2023.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what I was thinking was a three to four email sequence.","index":580,"end_time":2028.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2026.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can make changes pretty quickly if needed.","index":581,"end_time":2030.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2028.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two to three ad variations that we''ll create and we''ll probably launch two of them as an A B test and then again, you know, bring in a third, create a new one.","index":582,"end_time":2037.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2031.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I did want to talk about a new landing page, possibly on the Noetic Consultants website for this offering.","index":583,"end_time":2042.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2038.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what would you envision that being?","index":584,"end_time":2046.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2043.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I would like to tie it to what this offer is so we would start with some information about really how Noetic views AI in this space.","index":585,"end_time":2055.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2047.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what companies, you know, what pain points they may be experiencing, but also really guiding the prospect towards this, you know, whatever we call the offer of how Noetic can, you know, come in and train your team to use AI better.","index":586,"end_time":2070.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2056.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you think Rach, I think.","index":587,"end_time":2076.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2072.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''S a cool idea.","index":588,"end_time":2077.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2076.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think AI is important for us to tap into more because I think it''s just such not known but it''s so important.","index":589,"end_time":2086.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I like the idea of us doing something with it, with the land.","index":590,"end_time":2091.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2086.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when you say landing page you mean something that people would click on through the ads or like a permanent tab on the website.","index":591,"end_time":2097.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2091.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I would like to add it actually to like the navigation.","index":592,"end_time":2101.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2098.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, we could start out with and this is something that we do often, we could start out with just having it only linked to from emails and we could have one ad variation sending people to that landing page and the other just as a lead gen form so they don''t have to leave LinkedIn.","index":593,"end_time":2115.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2102.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can collect some data, see how people interact with it and then eventually add it to the main navigation.","index":594,"end_time":2121.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2115.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you think having it as a tab within the navigation makes more sense than adding it?","index":595,"end_time":2127.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2121.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me just double check what our offerings are just so we can start.","index":596,"end_time":2131.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2128.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"To think about it because we have our services.","index":597,"end_time":2134.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2131.67,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Do you think it makes more sense under services to put AI rather than put it in like a training and coaching?","index":598,"end_time":2141.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2134.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''s a great question.","index":599,"end_time":2143.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2143.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pause for a second.","index":600,"end_time":2145.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2143.92,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I think honestly this comes down to Nancy, how, how are you thinking about it for Noetic?","index":601,"end_time":2151.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2145.36,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Like where does it sit within.","index":602,"end_time":2153.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2152,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah, the company, I mean doesn''t sit.","index":603,"end_time":2158.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2154.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Squarely in training and coaching because it.","index":604,"end_time":2163.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2158.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Involves doing a lot of stuff that.","index":605,"end_time":2166.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2163.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Comes before the training and coaching to.","index":606,"end_time":2169.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2166.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Try to figure out how AI infused.","index":607,"end_time":2171.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Infuses into the work streams.","index":608,"end_time":2173.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2171.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In the case of the infusing into work streams.","index":609,"end_time":2176.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2173.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In the case of training on the human skills, that falls squarely in the training space.","index":610,"end_time":2182,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2176.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just, it''s like as a consequence.","index":611,"end_time":2184.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2182,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of AI, these are the skills you.","index":612,"end_time":2185.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2184.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Need now what more so is the.","index":613,"end_time":2188.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2185.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Noise in my head is that we have been seeing that people don''t want.","index":614,"end_time":2195.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2188.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To leave, they don''t want to leave the platform.","index":615,"end_time":2197.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2195.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":616,"end_time":2198.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2197.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I''m just worrying about the effort.","index":617,"end_time":2200.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2198.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Versus the payoff of like do we.","index":618,"end_time":2205.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2201.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do we take the time and the.","index":619,"end_time":2207.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2205.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Effort to build a page or a.","index":620,"end_time":2210.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2207.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or a piece of a page, you know, on our site?","index":621,"end_time":2212.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2210.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or.","index":622,"end_time":2214.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Are we better off trying to get them to stay on LinkedIn?","index":623,"end_time":2220.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2216.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So because we have the email channel as well, I think that a landing page is pretty necessary because otherwise we''re just hoping that they respond and they''re likely going like we''re going to ask a probing question but they''re likely going to want to do some digging.","index":624,"end_time":2234.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2221.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just what we see across the board now people are filling forms less.","index":625,"end_time":2237.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2234.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, different.","index":626,"end_time":2238.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2237.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I got it.","index":627,"end_time":2239.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2238.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Different when it comes to an email sequence versus they''re.","index":628,"end_time":2244.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2239.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If they''re in the platform.","index":629,"end_time":2245.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2244.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":630,"end_time":2246.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2246.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":631,"end_time":2247.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2246.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So bearing that in mind, if I''m just looking at the offerings page, because.","index":632,"end_time":2255.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2247.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We Also another option, not that it''s.","index":633,"end_time":2258.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2255.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s kind of a landing page, but it''s not.","index":634,"end_time":2260.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2258.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If we had an AI1 pager on the website, we could also technically link to that.","index":635,"end_time":2266.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2260.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, we''re going to have two AI1 pagers.","index":636,"end_time":2269,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2266.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think those would be great to have on the landing page too.","index":637,"end_time":2271.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2269.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":638,"end_time":2273.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2273.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the.","index":639,"end_time":2273.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2273.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the AI one pagers, I think Rachel will go on that offerings page.","index":640,"end_time":2280.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2273.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s what I was imagining because, like, offerings are offerings.","index":641,"end_time":2283.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2280.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So to your question, Julia, about, like.","index":642,"end_time":2286.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2283.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How does this fit in the world of noetic?","index":643,"end_time":2287.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2286.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s just amplifying them because AI is such a hot point.","index":644,"end_time":2294.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2288.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":645,"end_time":2295.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2295.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that, to me feels like the.","index":646,"end_time":2299,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2296.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right place for the.","index":647,"end_time":2300.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2299,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The one sheeters.","index":648,"end_time":2302.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2300.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then it''s really just, you know, how big of a lift would it.","index":649,"end_time":2308.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2302.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Be to have them click through to a specific page?","index":650,"end_time":2315.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2308.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, like, would we do it as a.","index":651,"end_time":2317.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2315.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"As a public page or as just.","index":652,"end_time":2319.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like a page that one clicks to?","index":653,"end_time":2321.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2319.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because we''re not really set up.","index":654,"end_time":2323.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What''s.","index":655,"end_time":2323.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2323.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What''s throwing me off is that like in.","index":656,"end_time":2327.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2323.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In our current layout, in the site.","index":657,"end_time":2330.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2327.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In our current navigation, we''re not really set up for AI standing on its own.","index":658,"end_time":2337.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2330.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":659,"end_time":2340.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Do we think it''s.","index":660,"end_time":2341.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2340.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do we think it''s significant enough to rethink about how things are listed on our site as a December project?","index":661,"end_time":2352.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2343.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":662,"end_time":2354,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2353.6,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I just don''t know that we''re there yet.","index":663,"end_time":2357.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2356.08,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":664,"end_time":2358.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2358.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And that''s kind of why I said that to you, Nancy.","index":665,"end_time":2360.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2358.6,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I was like, where do you think if it''s in.","index":666,"end_time":2362.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2360.68,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I think the vision that you have and, and laid out for us last week makes it seem like, yeah, it''s hefty and deserves its own spotlight.","index":667,"end_time":2374.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2362.8,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"But I don''t know that I. I think you''re kind of getting at that, Rachel.","index":668,"end_time":2378.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2375.36,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I don''t know that I think, like, we''re necessarily there.","index":669,"end_time":2381.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2378.88,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":670,"end_time":2382.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2381.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":671,"end_time":2382.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2382.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like, do you build it and then they''ll come?","index":672,"end_time":2386.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2382.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":673,"end_time":2387.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2386.84,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Or do you get them to come and then you build it?","index":674,"end_time":2389.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2387.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":675,"end_time":2390.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2389.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think, like, I hear you calling that, like, we have to give people the ability to go somewhere.","index":676,"end_time":2395.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2390.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":677,"end_time":2396.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2396.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"That''s kind of my.","index":678,"end_time":2398.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2397.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because tomorrow in our consultant huddle, we''re talking about, like, December projects and things.","index":679,"end_time":2402.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2398.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I do think it might be worthwhile to think about how on the website we''re like listing the services or this.","index":680,"end_time":2408.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2402.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I mean, you could, to your point.","index":681,"end_time":2411.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2408.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You could have here, right where we are, you could have what''s there and then you could have.","index":682,"end_time":2417.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2411.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not going to call it very.","index":683,"end_time":2420.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2418.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, but like AI services as its.","index":684,"end_time":2423.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2420.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Own bucket and we were going to add another one.","index":685,"end_time":2426.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2423.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It might have been like CMO support or something like that.","index":686,"end_time":2430.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2426.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m just thinking now that, you know, everything keeps changing, people are wanting different things, their budgets are different.","index":687,"end_time":2438.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2430.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, do we need to kind of change how we''re packaging it on our website or how they would navigate it?","index":688,"end_time":2445.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2438.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So maybe I don''t know that we''re there yet.","index":689,"end_time":2448.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2445.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like Julia said, like, it might be a deeper discussion, but I think it''s like a good time to start talking.","index":690,"end_time":2454.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2448.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"About what we want.","index":691,"end_time":2455.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2454.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The more I think about it, the.","index":692,"end_time":2456.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2455.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"More I think it does deserve to.","index":693,"end_time":2459.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2456.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The question you''re asking that it does.","index":694,"end_time":2461.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2459.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Deserve that level of amplification.","index":695,"end_time":2463.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2461.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that said, in the chicken and.","index":696,"end_time":2466.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2464.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Egg of it all.","index":697,"end_time":2467.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2466.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are we in.","index":698,"end_time":2471.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2470.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A position where we don''t feel like.","index":699,"end_time":2472.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2471.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We can really launch email sequences until.","index":700,"end_time":2474.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2472.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We have a place to send them?","index":701,"end_time":2475.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2474.35,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think having a landing page is pretty important because of the amount of research that people want to do on how you would handle it specifically.","index":702,"end_time":2482.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2476.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s my recommendation would be to.","index":703,"end_time":2485.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2483.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To build this page, not have it in the navigation initially, but just in the links that we''re sending in the emails.","index":704,"end_time":2491.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2485.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can actually gather some information on how people are interacting with it before it''s just open to the general public.","index":705,"end_time":2496.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2491.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we could also do if we decided to do that, Nancy, is with those one pagers that we''re doing for AI within that section, we can also add a link to the hidden page.","index":706,"end_time":2509.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2498.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s like a double touch point for it.","index":707,"end_time":2513,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2510.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just something.","index":708,"end_time":2516.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2515.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The one thing I just want to.","index":709,"end_time":2519.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2517.74,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Be very real about, like amongst us.","index":710,"end_time":2521.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2519.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Chickens here is that we can''t tell stories in this space yet.","index":711,"end_time":2526.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2521.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":712,"end_time":2528.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2527.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a new offering.","index":713,"end_time":2529.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2528.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I have no doubt we can.","index":714,"end_time":2531.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2530.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do it, but like it can''t be.","index":715,"end_time":2533.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2531.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I guess I''m looking at our other pages and we name names in a general way, but we don''t name names.","index":716,"end_time":2542.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2533.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Speaking of not being able to tell stories, question for you, Colin and Natalie, since we don''t have a story to tell and this would be a standalone page, is it worthwhile, like our team or somebody recording a message about what we would do in AI, like having a video on that page because we don''t have clients we''d work with yet, like, so we can show that we''re knowledgeable.","index":717,"end_time":2568.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2544.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is there any benefit to doing that page a little differently?","index":718,"end_time":2571.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2568.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so not too differently.","index":719,"end_time":2574.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2572.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like the, the architecture or the orientation of this page, I think starts out well.","index":720,"end_time":2578.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2574.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s stating the problem that people are experiencing, stating what Noetic is able to provide.","index":721,"end_time":2582.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2578.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think we could also provide links to download those one pages you guys are referencing.","index":722,"end_time":2588.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2582.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The video I would add here is Nancy''s upcoming episode that she''s planning out for how she wants to talk about the AI offering.","index":723,"end_time":2595.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2588.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, great.","index":724,"end_time":2596.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2596.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"When I think, yeah, I think it''s.","index":725,"end_time":2598.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2597.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay that it''s not like matchy matchy to what the other services would ultimately be.","index":726,"end_time":2603.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2598.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I like.","index":727,"end_time":2605.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2605.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I like what you just described.","index":728,"end_time":2607.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2605.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we could plan to create internal episodes for those other services if we eventually did want to add the video edits the queue.","index":729,"end_time":2616.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2608.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it''s not an extra lift.","index":730,"end_time":2617.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2616.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":731,"end_time":2618.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2617.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":732,"end_time":2622.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2621.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then if somebody likes to read about it, they can read about it.","index":733,"end_time":2624.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2622.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They want to listen about it, they.","index":734,"end_time":2625.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2624.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Can listen about it.","index":735,"end_time":2626.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2625.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":736,"end_time":2626.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2626.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''ve thought through each kind of learner.","index":737,"end_time":2628.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2626.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Pick your own adventure.","index":738,"end_time":2630.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2629.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":739,"end_time":2630.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2630.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":740,"end_time":2630.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2630.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes.","index":741,"end_time":2631.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2630.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, that was a good question.","index":742,"end_time":2633.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2631.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":743,"end_time":2634.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2634.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Nancy, if you can just send over those emails that you referenced, we''ll put together some starter copy, share that with you for review, some ads, share that with you as well as landing page copy, and share that with you guys for review, and then we can go into design and development.","index":744,"end_time":2648.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2634.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":745,"end_time":2651.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2651,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":746,"end_time":2652.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2651.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I accidentally skipped over a few things.","index":747,"end_time":2654.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2653.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did add an introductory paragraph like we talked about for podcast framework template.","index":748,"end_time":2662.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2655,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just updating this.","index":749,"end_time":2663.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2662.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we want to tailor these, you know, each time a little bit, but we did just come up with kind of like the boilerplate, so you don''t need to read through it on the screen now, but we can send this over to you to review.","index":750,"end_time":2674.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2664.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":751,"end_time":2675.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2675.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":752,"end_time":2676.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2675.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And the idea of this just being.","index":753,"end_time":2678.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2676.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That we always have kind of like an evergreen way.","index":754,"end_time":2680.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2678.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":755,"end_time":2682.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2681.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a nice subtle.","index":756,"end_time":2683.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2682.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, they''re reading through the framework.","index":757,"end_time":2684.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2683.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":758,"end_time":2684.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2684.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because they need to know what they''re going to be asked, what they need to talk about.","index":759,"end_time":2687.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2684.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So having this push of Noetic services.","index":760,"end_time":2689.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2687.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is just Right, right?","index":761,"end_time":2691.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2689.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, exactly.","index":762,"end_time":2692.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2691.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s about making sure they know they have.","index":763,"end_time":2694.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2692.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That the guest themselves has good context.","index":764,"end_time":2696.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2694.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":765,"end_time":2697.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2696.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice and personal.","index":766,"end_time":2698.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2698.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":767,"end_time":2700.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2700.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that it feels personal.","index":768,"end_time":2703.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2702.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just like looking at it at a quick glance.","index":769,"end_time":2705.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2703.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":770,"end_time":2706.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2705.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":771,"end_time":2707.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2706.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And Rachel''s been doing a great job.","index":772,"end_time":2710.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2708.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of like telling the guest.","index":773,"end_time":2712.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2710.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, I know you''re doing it sincerely.","index":774,"end_time":2713.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2712.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But going out of your way to tell the guests, like, what a good job they did, which I think helps.","index":775,"end_time":2719.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2714.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People not stress about our editing.","index":776,"end_time":2722.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2719.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re so sweet.","index":777,"end_time":2724.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2723.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, you would not think some of these people would get so nervous.","index":778,"end_time":2727.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2724.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":779,"end_time":2727.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2727.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because they''re such leaders in what they''re doing and they''re so knowledgeable, but they really doubt themselves and I feel so sad about it.","index":780,"end_time":2735.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2727.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we just.","index":781,"end_time":2737.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2736.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s just one of those things.","index":782,"end_time":2738.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2737.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cheerleader.","index":783,"end_time":2739.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2738.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":784,"end_time":2740.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2739.74,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Some of them, some of them get more nervous than others, but sometimes it''s.","index":785,"end_time":2745.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2740.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Surprising the people who do.","index":786,"end_time":2747.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2745.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":787,"end_time":2748.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2747.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s nice that they''re humble, I guess.","index":788,"end_time":2749.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2748.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":789,"end_time":2750.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2749.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"One other thing that we worked on was I recommended some changes to the Insights page just to add some copy to get more traffic here organically.","index":790,"end_time":2759.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2752.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, yeah, can you say more about that?","index":791,"end_time":2763.679,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2760,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because, yeah, our numbers are going down, which is concerning.","index":792,"end_time":2766.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2763.679,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I love this page and I.","index":793,"end_time":2769.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2766.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Want it to be hard working.","index":794,"end_time":2770.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2769.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":795,"end_time":2771.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2770.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So took it from an SEO perspective.","index":796,"end_time":2773.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2771.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like our thought leadership as a H1 on here, if someone searches our thought leadership, first, I''m going to be surprised that they search that on Google.","index":797,"end_time":2781.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2773.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But second, you''re not going to rank for it.","index":798,"end_time":2783.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2781.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we came up with was this copy adjustments document.","index":799,"end_time":2789.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2784.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So landing into brand assessment or brand insights for marketing leaders.","index":800,"end_time":2794.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2790.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exploring brand insights, practical frameworks and thought leadership marketing designed for growth oriented organizations.","index":801,"end_time":2800.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2795.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So tapping in on all of those avenues that first are already linked to on that page, but also the different ways that people would mention them.","index":802,"end_time":2808.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2801.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Podcasts, playbooks and articles, break down market trends, team challenges, brand strategy and real world solutions so you can think more strategically and act with clarity.","index":803,"end_time":2817.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2809.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that would replace this section up top here.","index":804,"end_time":2821.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2819.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":805,"end_time":2822.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2821.75,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And all of that to feed the engine, correct?","index":806,"end_time":2826.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2822.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":807,"end_time":2826.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2826.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Most important being the H1, which we replace our thought leadership with this.","index":808,"end_time":2830.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2826.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brand Insights for Marketing leaders.","index":809,"end_time":2831.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2830.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, is that kind of language adjustment something we can do?","index":810,"end_time":2835.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2832.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"If they send it to us?","index":811,"end_time":2838.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2836.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can put it in.","index":812,"end_time":2840.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2838.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":813,"end_time":2841.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2840.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s easy.","index":814,"end_time":2842.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2841.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The other change was adding some copy between the image and CTA button here for each of these sections.","index":815,"end_time":2851.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2843.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or even just replacing this right here.","index":816,"end_time":2854.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2852.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I was thinking there.","index":817,"end_time":2856.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2854.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Rachel, go ahead.","index":818,"end_time":2857.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2856.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":819,"end_time":2858.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2857.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was going to say I think the best thing to do since it''s formatted would be to just adjust that top wording if we want to do it.","index":820,"end_time":2864.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2858.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep, that makes sense.","index":821,"end_time":2866.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2864.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the podcast, hear conversations that uncover brand insights.","index":822,"end_time":2869.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2866.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So using that again, Thought leadership marketing, using that again, perspectives from industry leaders for the Playbooks download guides built on practical Brand insights again, tapping into that used by marketing teams to improve clarity, alignment, and effectiveness.","index":823,"end_time":2883.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2869.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the blog, read articles covering brand insights, research driven frameworks, and real world thought leadership marketing advice.","index":824,"end_time":2890.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2884.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the idea that those just compel people to click.","index":825,"end_time":2896.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2893.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The idea being this is more of what they''re searching so you would pop up more organically.","index":826,"end_time":2901.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2897.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see, I see, I see.","index":827,"end_time":2903.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2901.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s back to the model.","index":828,"end_time":2905.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2903.26,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Not so much the pulling in.","index":829,"end_time":2907.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2905.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":830,"end_time":2907.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2907.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":831,"end_time":2908.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2907.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always something that I need to take a step back and think through, because we''re in this world every day.","index":832,"end_time":2912.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2908.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even the CMOs are in this world every day that we''re trying to reach out to and connect with.","index":833,"end_time":2916.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2912.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We refer to these things as so many different terms and even the order that we say it.","index":834,"end_time":2921.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2917.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what the SEO approach is.","index":835,"end_time":2925.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2923.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like what is the most common term that people are using, even if it doesn''t match exactly how we talk about it.","index":836,"end_time":2930.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2925.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Gotcha.","index":837,"end_time":2931.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2930.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, is this an opportunity to show.","index":838,"end_time":2934.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2932.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Julia how to make adjustments on the site?","index":839,"end_time":2936.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2934.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":840,"end_time":2939.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2939.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I could show her how to do it on the website.","index":841,"end_time":2941.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2939.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that would be great.","index":842,"end_time":2944.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2943.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That can be part of our 101.","index":843,"end_time":2946.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2944.63,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":844,"end_time":2949.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2947.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is the copy in there for.","index":845,"end_time":2951.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2950.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And it shows which section we''re updating.","index":846,"end_time":2955.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2951.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":847,"end_time":2955.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2955.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Podcast, playbooks, blog.","index":848,"end_time":2957.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2956.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":849,"end_time":2957.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2957.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Sounds good to me.","index":850,"end_time":2961.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2958.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":851,"end_time":2962.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2961.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''ll get this sent over to you guys.","index":852,"end_time":2963.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2962.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it will be very interesting.","index":853,"end_time":2965.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2964.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"To see whether or not our numbers improve.","index":854,"end_time":2968.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2965.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":855,"end_time":2970.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2969.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what we''ll monitor.","index":856,"end_time":2971.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2970.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, SEO is a long game because it''s free technically versus, like, paid ads, but it''s something that you constantly monitor and tweak.","index":857,"end_time":2981.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2971.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":858,"end_time":2983,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2982.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s good that we''re getting those keywords in too, especially with AI.","index":859,"end_time":2986.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2983.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Now is that AI will pick our website up for some of these things as well.","index":860,"end_time":2991.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2986.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes.","index":861,"end_time":2992.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2991.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that really.","index":862,"end_time":2993.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2992.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know there''s a lot of different arguments and there''s really no hard truth to what ChatGPT, like, chooses to provide as, like, a resource article when you search something.","index":863,"end_time":3002.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2993.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But at its core, Google and ChatGPT are not too different in its site experience.","index":864,"end_time":3007.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3003.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they send someone to a resource and they land, like, they stay on the website for more than a minute, they''re like, okay, this was actually a verifiable resource that they were looking at that all feeds back into the algorithm of getting you guys ranking higher and higher both in Google and ChatGPT.","index":865,"end_time":3020.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3008.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":866,"end_time":3022.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3021.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And thinking about where we think it''s going to be in the future.","index":867,"end_time":3024.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3022.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I feel like this accounts for that as well.","index":868,"end_time":3026.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3024.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":869,"end_time":3027.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3026.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":870,"end_time":3030.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3029.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then going through some of the.","index":871,"end_time":3033.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3031.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":872,"end_time":3034.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3033.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for that.","index":873,"end_time":3035.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3034.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, of course.","index":874,"end_time":3036.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3035.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going through some of the data.","index":875,"end_time":3037.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3036.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, looking at month to date, we did see a drop in average session duration, but again, this is still almost 300% of industry average.","index":876,"end_time":3045.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3037.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Industry average being 60 seconds, and we''re at about 2 minutes and 40 seconds on average.","index":877,"end_time":3050.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3045.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the bounce rate did take a slight increase, but again, 60% is that benchmark that we''re shooting for, and you guys are below that.","index":878,"end_time":3055.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3050.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to just understand this more clearly when you say their higher.","index":879,"end_time":3062.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3056.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Bounce rate means more visitors leave after one page.","index":880,"end_time":3066.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3062.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s considered a bounce if they just go to the one page and then they leave.","index":881,"end_time":3070.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3066.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":882,"end_time":3070.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3070.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they''re not browsing other pages or if they''re there for a pretty short amount of time or don''t engage with any of the content.","index":883,"end_time":3074.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3070.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":884,"end_time":3077.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3076.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":885,"end_time":3077.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3077.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":886,"end_time":3080.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3079.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":887,"end_time":3081.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3080.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I.","index":888,"end_time":3081.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3081.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just language.","index":889,"end_time":3083.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3082.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, I. I think about bounce more in the email world.","index":890,"end_time":3088.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3083.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":891,"end_time":3089.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3089.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":892,"end_time":3090.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3090.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Email bounce versus a bounce rate of.","index":893,"end_time":3092.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3090.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just pausing on that because.","index":894,"end_time":3093.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3092.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''S a different use of it, but.","index":895,"end_time":3094.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3093.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I totally follow.","index":896,"end_time":3096.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3094.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And this is why we just talked about all the language that we talked about.","index":897,"end_time":3099.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3096.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":898,"end_time":3100.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3099.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":899,"end_time":3101.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3101.36,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right.","index":900,"end_time":3102.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3102.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s one other thing that I wanted to pull up to show you, so give me one second to do so.","index":901,"end_time":3108.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3102.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve developed a new tool in our system that now automates our weekly emails.","index":902,"end_time":3115.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3109.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to share that with you guys because I know we''ve customized yours in the past.","index":903,"end_time":3119.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3116.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mean that end of week wrap up?","index":904,"end_time":3124.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3122.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Correct.","index":905,"end_time":3124.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3124.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks great.","index":906,"end_time":3138.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3138.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''ve been.","index":907,"end_time":3143.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3143.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve been back to back way too much this week, and I should have had this.","index":908,"end_time":3147.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3144.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do I look like neon to you guys?","index":909,"end_time":3150.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3148.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, what is up with my lighting?","index":910,"end_time":3152.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3150.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I look like a ghost.","index":911,"end_time":3153.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3152.56,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I look tan for once, but I kind of look like Donald Trump fan.","index":912,"end_time":3161.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3157.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, orange.","index":913,"end_time":3162.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3162,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What?","index":914,"end_time":3163.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3162.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s like the meanest thing you could say about yourself.","index":915,"end_time":3167.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3164.72,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"That is the meanest thing.","index":916,"end_time":3169.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3168.319,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But I look a little orange.","index":917,"end_time":3171.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3169.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Do I not?","index":918,"end_time":3171.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3171.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No.","index":919,"end_time":3172.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3172.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think this sweater just looks at you.","index":920,"end_time":3175.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3172.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Really?","index":921,"end_time":3176.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3175.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"On mine, I don''t feel like you do on mine.","index":922,"end_time":3178.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3176.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I look orange.","index":923,"end_time":3179.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3178.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not.","index":924,"end_time":3180.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3179.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not dying over here.","index":925,"end_time":3182.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3181,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Don''t worry.","index":926,"end_time":3183,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3182.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You guys are too funny.","index":927,"end_time":3186.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3185.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just the dim lighting.","index":928,"end_time":3188.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3187.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":929,"end_time":3189.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3188.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We try.","index":930,"end_time":3189.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3189.28,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We try.","index":931,"end_time":3190.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3189.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Your hair, though, is incredible.","index":932,"end_time":3193.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3191,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"You haven''t seen the wavy.","index":933,"end_time":3196.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3194.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":934,"end_time":3196.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3196.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You haven''t seen the wavy.","index":935,"end_time":3197.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3196.92,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So good.","index":936,"end_time":3198.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3197.72,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":937,"end_time":3199.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3198.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think it''s in all seriousness, I.","index":938,"end_time":3202.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3200.04,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Think it''s because, like the sunlight is creating like a weird vibe across my head.","index":939,"end_time":3207.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3202.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":940,"end_time":3207.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3207.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just buying you time.","index":941,"end_time":3210.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3209.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Colin, anything?","index":942,"end_time":3211.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3210.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s coming through at 250.","index":943,"end_time":3213.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3212.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had to set it at an automation.","index":944,"end_time":3215,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3213.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":945,"end_time":3215.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3215.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So hopefully in the next watch.","index":946,"end_time":3220.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3217.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so the idea is that like whatever we have, work in progress.","index":947,"end_time":3224.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3220.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Would pop into that note.","index":948,"end_time":3227.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3224.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, it''s nice and designed.","index":949,"end_time":3230.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3227.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should be coming through.","index":950,"end_time":3231.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3230.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel like a dummy if this isn''t going to come through.","index":951,"end_time":3234.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3232.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":952,"end_time":3235.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3235.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s so automated that it wouldn''t.","index":953,"end_time":3238.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3236.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s.","index":954,"end_time":3239.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3239.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would be.","index":955,"end_time":3240.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3239.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If I was not back to back since 8:30, I would have said, well.","index":956,"end_time":3244.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3240.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you can''t make it happen, here it is.","index":957,"end_time":3247.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3244.95,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":958,"end_time":3248.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3247.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right.","index":959,"end_time":3249.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3248.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is how it populates.","index":960,"end_time":3252.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3250.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it automatically does look back over the last 14 days and then the next 30 days goes through points, purchase credited, all these things, the items for you guys to take a look at what we''re working on and then items that were completed in the last 14 days.","index":961,"end_time":3266.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3252.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":962,"end_time":3267.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3267.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nancy, should I be forwarding this to Rocky or Tiffany?","index":963,"end_time":3271.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3268.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can have it sent to anyone you guys want.","index":964,"end_time":3274.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3271.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would say, like, let''s just CC them.","index":965,"end_time":3277.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3274.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think.","index":966,"end_time":3277.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3277.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I feel like they would love this.","index":967,"end_time":3280.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3278.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think so too, particularly because.","index":968,"end_time":3284.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3280.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do you want me to put their email or.","index":969,"end_time":3286.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3285.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You have them already.","index":970,"end_time":3287.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3286.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Colin, if you don''t mind just sending me an email of everyone you want on it.","index":971,"end_time":3292.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3287.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, I will send that now.","index":972,"end_time":3293.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3292.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The thing I''m wondering though is can you scroll down a little bit further?","index":973,"end_time":3298.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3294.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So does the.","index":974,"end_time":3301.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3300.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Does it still have a link to the dashboard?","index":975,"end_time":3303.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3301.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I thought it did.","index":976,"end_time":3309.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3308.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, it''s at the very bottom.","index":977,"end_time":3310.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3309.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Colin, there''s a login.","index":978,"end_time":3313.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3310.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh yeah, here it is.","index":979,"end_time":3314.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3313.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":980,"end_time":3316.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3315.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I just want to make sure.","index":981,"end_time":3317.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3316.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because that''s one of the parts that.","index":982,"end_time":3319.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3317.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Racky and Tiffany will care the most about is seeing the dashboard.","index":983,"end_time":3324.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3319.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So yeah, let''s include them on it.","index":984,"end_time":3328.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3327.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m sending email right now, Colin, and I will put everybody as CC and I will ping them to let them know what that is.","index":985,"end_time":3334.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3329.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":986,"end_time":3336.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3335.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll schedule those to go out Every Friday at 4pm Eastern Time is what we landed on.","index":987,"end_time":3343.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3338.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin, are you think.","index":988,"end_time":3344.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3343.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I''m jumping back to the AI campaign.","index":989,"end_time":3349.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3344.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can you go back to that slide?","index":990,"end_time":3354.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3352.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sure thing.","index":991,"end_time":3355.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3354.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Rachel can.","index":992,"end_time":3357.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3356.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Or do you have time to stay on with me after this to get my signature over the line?","index":993,"end_time":3361.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3357.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We will try it again.","index":994,"end_time":3362.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3361.78,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":995,"end_time":3364.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3363.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":996,"end_time":3364.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3364.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the.","index":997,"end_time":3365.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3364.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, I thought so.","index":998,"end_time":3366.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3365.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we did.","index":999,"end_time":3367.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3366.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We kind of skipped over it.","index":1000,"end_time":3368.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3367.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So you have here two to three ad Variations.","index":1001,"end_time":3372.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3369.06,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Can you talk a little bit about that?","index":1002,"end_time":3374.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3373.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We talked about the email sequences, we talked about the episode, we talked about everything else, but we didn''t really talk.","index":1003,"end_time":3380.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3374.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"About the AD variations.","index":1004,"end_time":3381.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3380.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just like, what are you imagining there?","index":1005,"end_time":3383.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3381.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it''s going to be similar language to the emails, but a little less.","index":1006,"end_time":3386.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3383.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to be a little harder, I guess, is the right word.","index":1007,"end_time":3391.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3389.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or like scroll stopper is what I''m looking for.","index":1008,"end_time":3394.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3391.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where I think that we can utilize some of the elements we were talking about earlier of like the micro versus macro use of AI or like, is your team in a silo of using this?","index":1009,"end_time":3405.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3394.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s like some pretty cool graphics.","index":1010,"end_time":3406.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3405.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just imagining right now of how we can do that.","index":1011,"end_time":3408.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3406.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":1012,"end_time":3410.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3410.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was wondering about.","index":1013,"end_time":3412.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3410.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because it enables you to get into graphics.","index":1014,"end_time":3414.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3412.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":1015,"end_time":3415.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3415.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m imagining like, I wish there.","index":1016,"end_time":3418.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3415.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Were and maybe there is a graphic that would be a quick get around.","index":1017,"end_time":3423.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3418.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This idea that people are working individually.","index":1018,"end_time":3429.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3423.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Frankly, people are kind of like hoarding.","index":1019,"end_time":3432.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3429.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Their AI efficiency and productivity, but nobody.","index":1020,"end_time":3436.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3432.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is doing it across.","index":1021,"end_time":3437.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3436.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And if that''s a problem for you as a leader, not the least of.","index":1022,"end_time":3444.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3439.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Which because of like, are they even compliant?","index":1023,"end_time":3447.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3444.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do they.","index":1024,"end_time":3448.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3447.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do you.","index":1025,"end_time":3448.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3448.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Have you even given them guidance of what compliance means?","index":1026,"end_time":3451.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3448.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But also just because the unevenness that.","index":1027,"end_time":3454.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3451.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, the lack of value of bringing.","index":1028,"end_time":3457.559,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3454.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It across and the unevenness in your team where it might take this person five minutes and this person a day.","index":1029,"end_time":3466.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3457.559,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1030,"end_time":3467.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3467.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s a few different ways, I mean, office spaces in my head, thinking of like, cubicles and like, we could show like the difference in people that are using AI versus not.","index":1031,"end_time":3476.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3467.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could have like the.","index":1032,"end_time":3477.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3476.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The view of the back of someone at their desk in like a to do pile and a done pile, showing the difference between how you utilize AI and how much more efficient you can be.","index":1033,"end_time":3486.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3477.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So things like that.","index":1034,"end_time":3486.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3486.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think where it''s.","index":1035,"end_time":3488.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3487.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I. I like all of that.","index":1036,"end_time":3490.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3488.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think where it''s tricky though, is like, I don''t want people to think that this is about us enhancing individual productivity, though it though it would because for the people who are quote unquote behind, it would help catch them up.","index":1037,"end_time":3504.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3490.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s more about the leader getting AI properly leveraged across.","index":1038,"end_time":3511.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3504.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1039,"end_time":3512.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3512.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can I jump in to say, I think sometimes AI is given a little too much credit as being this thing that makes us more efficient.","index":1040,"end_time":3522.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3512.98,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I think that''s lacking a little bit of nuance because I think AI, good AI and good use of it takes a lot of work.","index":1041,"end_time":3531.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3523.03,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Right.","index":1042,"end_time":3532.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3531.75,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Creating the right prompt is not a fast process.","index":1043,"end_time":3536.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3532.15,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"And so, like, I see your.","index":1044,"end_time":3541.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3539.11,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"Your rationale with, like, the to do list, the big to do list.","index":1045,"end_time":3544.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3541.51,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"But I would almost argue it''s just your output that becomes stronger versus your streamline efficiency.","index":1046,"end_time":3552.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3545.03,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"So something to consider.","index":1047,"end_time":3553.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3552.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I think it''s probably both with time.","index":1048,"end_time":3556.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3554.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I hear you that, like, if.","index":1049,"end_time":3558.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3556.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You really are doing it right, you''re.","index":1050,"end_time":3561.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3558.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Doing really thoughtful prompting, which takes time to do, and in fact, you probably.","index":1051,"end_time":3566.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3561.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are doing it wrong, like, five times.","index":1052,"end_time":3569.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3566.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Until you get where you like.","index":1053,"end_time":3570.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3569.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":1054,"end_time":3571.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3570.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Not that I''ve ever had that experience.","index":1055,"end_time":3572.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3571.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I have, but I think the.","index":1056,"end_time":3576.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3574.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"More like, the.","index":1057,"end_time":3577.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3576.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The point is moving from individualized anything to team everything, even though people are still going to work as individual people.","index":1058,"end_time":3588.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3577.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But the idea that, like, I know.","index":1059,"end_time":3591.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3589.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That when I do this step of the process, I''m doing it this way with.","index":1060,"end_time":3597.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3591.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"With AI helping me in this way.","index":1061,"end_time":3599.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3597.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And when I hand it off to.","index":1062,"end_time":3601.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3600.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The next person, I know what they''re.","index":1063,"end_time":3604.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3601.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gonna do, and so on and so forth.","index":1064,"end_time":3606.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3604.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And all of that took me way.","index":1065,"end_time":3609.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3607.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"More words than one could do in a visual.","index":1066,"end_time":3611.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3609.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s kind of that idea of, like, the collective strength by individuals working.","index":1067,"end_time":3616.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3611.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"More as an orchestra as opposed to working as just individualized instruments creating a.","index":1068,"end_time":3622.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3616.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How do you say that word?","index":1069,"end_time":3625.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3623.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Cacophony.","index":1070,"end_time":3626.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3625.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Cacophony.","index":1071,"end_time":3627.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3626.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do you know that word?","index":1072,"end_time":3630.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3629.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think that''s right.","index":1073,"end_time":3630.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3630.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1074,"end_time":3631.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3631.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the symphony of the team through AI.","index":1075,"end_time":3633.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3631.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is a cool angle to think.","index":1076,"end_time":3634.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3633.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m also thinking even like a before and after type approach of, like, maybe we do have the siloed office cubicles on one side, and then, like, the team with actual time to work through things together on the other side, and it''s, like, dark and light.","index":1077,"end_time":3646.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3634.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s some things we could do there.","index":1078,"end_time":3648.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3647.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":1079,"end_time":3650.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3648.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just.","index":1080,"end_time":3650.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3650.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just better.","index":1081,"end_time":3650.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3650.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":1082,"end_time":3651.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3650.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you for circling back.","index":1083,"end_time":3653.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3651.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, I said circling back.","index":1084,"end_time":3654.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3653.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So do you have anything else?","index":1085,"end_time":3657.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3655.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because if you don''t, I''ll tell you a funny story that that is it.","index":1086,"end_time":3660.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3657.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I do have a hard stop at three, though.","index":1087,"end_time":3661.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3660.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the only thing.","index":1088,"end_time":3662.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3661.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll tell quick.","index":1089,"end_time":3663.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3662.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we did an icebreaker when we were all together, and we.","index":1090,"end_time":3666.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3663.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We had to use all the material provided in a bag.","index":1091,"end_time":3669.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3666.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it was all this, like, crafty stuff.","index":1092,"end_time":3671.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3669.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And you had different scenarios that you had to build, like, in a shark tank, like, style some kind of a product to address it.","index":1093,"end_time":3679.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3671.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Julia and I were teamed up.","index":1094,"end_time":3681.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3679.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And we chose that we had to build a tool that would punish people.","index":1095,"end_time":3685.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3681.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"For using office jargon, such as circle back.","index":1096,"end_time":3690.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3685.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":1097,"end_time":3691.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3690.41,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"We had to eliminate the use of circle back.","index":1098,"end_time":3695.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3691.61,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"We decided that punishment was the right approach.","index":1099,"end_time":3698.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3695.45,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"You''re right.","index":1100,"end_time":3699.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3699.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You''re right.","index":1101,"end_time":3700.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3699.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That was our decision.","index":1102,"end_time":3701.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3700.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we built.","index":1103,"end_time":3702.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3701.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We built a tool.","index":1104,"end_time":3704.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3702.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We built a tool.","index":1105,"end_time":3707.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3706.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We built a form of punishment.","index":1106,"end_time":3709.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3708.04,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And I think there''s a video somewhere of that.","index":1107,"end_time":3712.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3710.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m not going to lie.","index":1108,"end_time":3715.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3713.88,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"I thought that you were just, like, going off camera.","index":1109,"end_time":3717.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3715.04,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"},{"text":"No, I. I just.","index":1110,"end_time":3719.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3718.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just spilled water in my lap.","index":1111,"end_time":3720.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3719.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I was trying not to get it on my laptop.","index":1112,"end_time":3722.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3720.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, I''m not going to show it.","index":1113,"end_time":3726.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3724.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You can just imagine.","index":1114,"end_time":3727.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3726.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It will do.","index":1115,"end_time":3729.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3727.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":1116,"end_time":3730.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3729.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks very much, you guys.","index":1117,"end_time":3732.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3731.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, I will call you.","index":1118,"end_time":3733.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3732.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"One thing real quick.","index":1119,"end_time":3735.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3734.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another thing that I would like to gift to you guys is a end of year compilation video.","index":1120,"end_time":3742.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3736.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is something where we can take highlights from the podcast episodes and things that have been recorded and just kind of mash them all together to show the arc of the show.","index":1121,"end_time":3751.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3742.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to look back at the first year of metamorphosis moment.","index":1122,"end_time":3755.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3751.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was pretty cool.","index":1123,"end_time":3756.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3755.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That would be amazing because that was on our list and so.","index":1124,"end_time":3760.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3757.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes, thank you.","index":1125,"end_time":3761.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3760.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was on our wish list, but.","index":1126,"end_time":3762.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3761.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We were like, when would do it?","index":1127,"end_time":3764.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3762.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, we do.","index":1128,"end_time":3765.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3764.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":1129,"end_time":3767.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3766.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we''ll start working on that, too.","index":1130,"end_time":3768.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3767.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":1131,"end_time":3769.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3768.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Love it.","index":1132,"end_time":3770.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3769.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":1133,"end_time":3770.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3770.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very much.","index":1134,"end_time":3772.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3770.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope you have a great rest of your week.","index":1135,"end_time":3774.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3772.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And since I will be out, I hope we have a great Thanksgiving.","index":1136,"end_time":3777.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3774.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, you as well.","index":1137,"end_time":3778.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3777.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Enjoy, Colin.","index":1138,"end_time":3779.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3778.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":1139,"end_time":3780.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3779.539,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, bye, everyone.","index":1140,"end_time":3780.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3780.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":1141,"end_time":3781.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3781.06,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher (Noetic)"}],"dateString":"2025-11-19T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1","participants":["nancie@noeticconsultants.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,samantha@noeticconsultants.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rachel@noeticconsultants.com,julia@noeticconsultants.com","nancie@noeticconsultants.com","samantha@noeticconsultants.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","rachel@noeticconsultants.com","julia@noeticconsultants.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9YV0EPE91QP7PE5CJX855DJ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Scheduled ''thankful'' mailer for launch; Nathalie confirmed signatures will be finalized by tomorrow.","Colin proposed gifting AI campaign points to offset prior overages and maintain fairness.","New AI offer strategy advanced; team aligned on building a pilot landing page and targeting mid-market orgs.","Nancy confirmed multiple leads from Marriott and Waymo; follow-ups and meetings are in progress.","Insights page to be SEO-optimized; Colin provided new keyword-rich headers and intro copy."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re about 400 points over, which is about $40,000.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We want to do what''s fair… you can tell us what you can and can''t do.","speaker":"nancieruder"},{"quote":"We actually just enjoy each other.","speaker":"Rachel Curtis"}],"topics":["delivery","ai","seo","leads","email"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-21T21:33:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Noetic Marketing Campaigns and Lead Management**\n\nThe team is closing in on delivering the **Thankful mailer campaign scheduled for launch tomorrow**, with attention on ensuring email signature updates to include **2025 best places to work, social handles, and woman-owned status** (06:47).\n\n- **Current delivery status shows 35 points completed and 70 points in progress for November**, with a monthly budget of **80 points** and an overage of **about 400 points worth $40,000** discussed openly by Colin Costigan (10:24).\n    - Overages stem from iterative campaign development to find effective lead quality.\n    - Colin plans to negotiate gifting points back, especially for the new AI campaign, to avoid cost penalties.\n    - The team values fairness and transparency on scope and cost.\n\n- **Lead scoring adjustments were implemented for LinkedIn form fills** to prevent low-quality leads from entering Pipedrive directly by setting a lead score threshold of **8 out of 10**, with a threshold to enter Pipedrive at **10** (17:40).\n    - This filter appears effective, as no recent lead anomalies have been reported.\n    - Specific leads like Kim Cox and Dan who completed the brand health diagnostic are actively tracked and assigned appropriately.\n    - The team is maintaining vigilance on lead quality and funnel integrity.\n\n- **Ongoing client engagement includes second calls with Waymo and Marriott contacts**, with mixed warm leads and some follow-ups pending (21:46).\n    - Marriott shows potential despite recent industry turbulence, including Sonder''s bankruptcy.\n    - The hospitality sector’s challenges could create consulting opportunities, as noted by Nathalie Mintjens and Colin Costigan.\n\n## **AI Offering Strategy and Market Positioning**\n\nNoetic is preparing to launch a **new AI service offering targeting mid-sized companies with over 100 employees**, addressing the uneven and siloed use of AI in organizations (27:18).\n\n- **The AI campaign will focus on probing questions about team-wide AI adoption and governance**, avoiding scare tactics tied to layoffs at Salesforce or Shopify (31:50).\n    - Nancy Mintjens emphasizes the importance of accessibility and empathy given budget pressures and client uncertainty.\n    - Messaging aims to highlight the gap between individual AI use and coordinated, efficient team workflows.\n\n- **Colin Costigan recommends a three to four email sequence coupled with two to three ad variations for LinkedIn**, focusing on concise, curiosity-driven messaging with scroll-stopping graphics (33:41).\n    - The ads will visually contrast siloed individual AI use versus collaborative, efficient team workflows.\n    - The creative approach will emphasize collective strength and compliance, not just individual productivity gains.\n    - Julia Oher cautioned that effective AI use requires effort and thoughtful prompting, which should be reflected in messaging.\n\n- **A dedicated landing page for the AI offering will be developed but initially kept off the main website navigation**, linked only through ads and emails to gather user interaction data before public release (34:03).\n    - The page will state the problem, showcase Noetic’s solutions, and include downloadable one-pagers plus a video featuring Nancy explaining the AI offering.\n    - The team debated where AI fits on the website, agreeing it aligns most naturally under Training and Coaching for now, with possible future site structure revisions in December.\n    - This phased approach balances resource effort with market testing and audience education.\n\n## **Content and Podcast Program Updates**\n\nThe team has **enough recorded content to sustain through November and December without new client recordings**, supporting a strategic focus on internal episodes during quieter client periods (24:09).\n\n- **Active communication with key podcast guests Mac Phil and Chris O’Boyle continues**, with some scheduling into early 2024 possible (24:11).\n    - Internal episodes are designed to promote Noetic’s services and generate interest from existing networks.\n    - Positive guest engagement is boosted by Rachel Curtis’s proactive encouragement, helping reduce guest nervousness.\n\n- **A new podcast framework template with an introductory paragraph was created** to give guests clear context and ease their participation, enhancing professionalism and personal touch (44:13).\n    - This evergreen framework aims for consistent quality and guest comfort.\n    - Rachel and Nathalie highlighted the importance of genuine guest encouragement to maintain high-quality conversations.\n\n- **Colin will produce an end-of-year compilation video** featuring podcast highlights to showcase growth and milestones from the first year of the Metamorphosis Moment series (01:02:12).\n    - This aligns with the team’s goal to celebrate progress and maintain momentum.\n    - The video project was previously on the wish list and will now be prioritized.\n\n## **Website SEO and User Engagement Improvements**\n\nTo address **declining traffic on the Insights page**, Colin proposed SEO-driven copy adjustments emphasizing \"Brand Insights for Marketing Leaders\" and related keywords to improve organic search rankings (45:48).\n\n- **Revised headline and section descriptions focus on practical frameworks, market trends, and team challenges**, aligned with common search terms rather than internal jargon (46:00).\n    - This should help increase visibility for podcasts, playbooks, and blog content.\n    - Nathalie Mintjens confirmed she can implement these copy changes directly on the website.\n\n- **Monitoring metrics show average session duration at about 2 minutes 40 seconds, three times the industry average, despite a slight bounce rate increase** (50:35).\n    - The bounce rate remains below the 60% industry benchmark, indicating good engagement quality.\n    - Colin emphasized SEO as a long-term strategy requiring ongoing adjustment and user behavior analysis.\n\n- **The website update process will include training Julia Oher on content edits**, supporting team capacity building for future site maintenance (48:52).\n    - This supports operational efficiency and internal ownership of digital assets.\n\n## **Process Automation and Reporting Enhancements**\n\nColin introduced a **new automated weekly email summarizing recent and upcoming activities** related to points delivered, purchases, and campaign status, scheduled for Fridays at 4pm Eastern Time (51:41).\n\n- **The automation extracts data from the last 14 days and the next 30 days**, providing a designed, clear summary for easy review (54:08).\n    - Nathalie Mintjens will include Rocky and Tiffany as CC recipients to increase cross-team visibility.\n    - The email includes a direct link to the dashboard for quick access to detailed data.\n\n- This improvement is expected to **reduce manual reporting effort and improve stakeholder alignment on project progress**.\n    - Colin acknowledged initial technical challenges but committed to stable delivery.\n    - The automation aligns with the team’s goal to streamline communications and provide timely updates.\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Culture Insights**\n\nThe recent **in-person retreat at Lansdowne Resort fostered valuable team bonding and strategic work on integrating AI into Noetic processes** (12:56).\n\n- The team appreciated the setting’s balance of convenience, cost, and space, supporting productive collaboration (13:20).\n    - Activities included a memorable “Disc assessment” session and creative icebreakers like a tool to punish jargon use.\n    - These sessions strengthen team cohesion, morale, and remote work balance.\n\n- Discussions highlighted the **importance of empathy for guest nerves during podcasts**, with Rachel praised for her supportive approach that helps guests relax and perform well (44:58).\n    - This cultural attention enhances content quality and client relationships.\n    - The team values humility and authenticity in interactions.\n\n- The group expressed enthusiasm for ongoing internal knowledge sharing and training, including website update skills for newer members like Julia (48:52).\n    - This promotes team growth and operational resilience.\n    - Collaborative humor and storytelling remain part of the positive team dynamic.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI integration","lead scoring","podcast updates","website SEO","campaign automation","team retreat"],"overview":"- **Thankful Mailer Campaign Launch:** Campaign launching tomorrow; updates include 2025 awards, social handles, and woman-owned status.  \n- **Delivery and Budget Status:** 35 points completed, 70 in progress; budget overage of 400 points costing $40,000 discussed for November.  \n- **Lead Quality Improvements:** New scoring for LinkedIn forms; leads now require score of 10 to enter Pipedrive, ensuring higher quality.  \n- **AI Service Strategy:** New AI offering for mid-sized companies, focusing on team-wide adoption and governance without scare tactics.  \n- **Content Strategy Updates:** Enough podcast content recorded through December; focusing on internal episodes; new template created for guest participation.  \n- **SEO Enhancements:** Revised website copy to improve traffic; average session duration is currently 2 minutes 40 seconds, indicating good engagement.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend finalized thankful mailer to Nancy and Rachel for review (08:23)\n\n**Nancy**\nConfirm and finalize email signature formats to include workplace awards and social handles prior to thankful mailer launch (06:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nReview and gift points back to Noetic for AI campaign effort and negotiate points budget adjustments with internal team (12:16)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nAssist Nancy and Colin with placing finalized AI one-pagers on offerings page and helping shape AI campaign messaging tone (34:58)\n\n**Julia Oher**\nAttend scheduled training on website content updates and ongoing site maintenance (48:59)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"964b21df-8ba3-4210-8786-1c5c999c634a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
