INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
  '## **Noetic Marketing Campaigns and Lead Management**

The team is closing in on delivering the **Thankful mailer campaign scheduled for launch tomorrow**, with attention on ensuring email signature updates to include **2025 best places to work, social handles, and woman-owned status** (06:47).

- **Current delivery status shows 35 points completed and 70 points in progress for November**, with a monthly budget of **80 points** and an overage of **about 400 points worth $40,000** discussed openly by Colin Costigan (10:24).
    - Overages stem from iterative campaign development to find effective lead quality.
    - Colin plans to negotiate gifting points back, especially for the new AI campaign, to avoid cost penalties.
    - The team values fairness and transparency on scope and cost.

- **Lead scoring adjustments were implemented for LinkedIn form fills** to prevent low-quality leads from entering Pipedrive directly by setting a lead score threshold of **8 out of 10**, with a threshold to enter Pipedrive at **10** (17:40).
    - This filter appears effective, as no recent lead anomalies have been reported.
    - Specific leads like Kim Cox and Dan who completed the brand health diagnostic are actively tracked and assigned appropriately.
    - The team is maintaining vigilance on lead quality and funnel integrity.

- **Ongoing client engagement includes second calls with Waymo and Marriott contacts**, with mixed warm leads and some follow-ups pending (21:46).
    - Marriott shows potential despite recent industry turbulence, including Sonder''s bankruptcy.
    - The hospitality sector’s challenges could create consulting opportunities, as noted by Nathalie Mintjens and Colin Costigan.

## **AI Offering Strategy and Market Positioning**

Noetic is preparing to launch a **new AI service offering targeting mid-sized companies with over 100 employees**, addressing the uneven and siloed use of AI in organizations (27:18).

- **The AI campaign will focus on probing questions about team-wide AI adoption and governance**, avoiding scare tactics tied to layoffs at Salesforce or Shopify (31:50).
    - Nancy Mintjens emphasizes the importance of accessibility and empathy given budget pressures and client uncertainty.
    - Messaging aims to highlight the gap between individual AI use and coordinated, efficient team workflows.

- **Colin Costigan recommends a three to four email sequence coupled with two to three ad variations for LinkedIn**, focusing on concise, curiosity-driven messaging with scroll-stopping graphics (33:41).
    - The ads will visually contrast siloed individual AI use versus collaborative, efficient team workflows.
    - The creative approach will emphasize collective strength and compliance, not just individual productivity gains.
    - Julia Oher cautioned that effective AI use requires effort and thoughtful prompting, which should be reflected in messaging.

- **A dedicated landing page for the AI offering will be developed but initially kept off the main website navigation**, linked only through ads and emails to gather user interaction data before public release (34:03).
    - The page will state the problem, showcase Noetic’s solutions, and include downloadable one-pagers plus a video featuring Nancy explaining the AI offering.
    - The team debated where AI fits on the website, agreeing it aligns most naturally under Training and Coaching for now, with possible future site structure revisions in December.
    - This phased approach balances resource effort with market testing and audience education.

## **Content and Podcast Program Updates**

The team has **enough recorded content to sustain through November and December without new client recordings**, supporting a strategic focus on internal episodes during quieter client periods (24:09).

- **Active communication with key podcast guests Mac Phil and Chris O’Boyle continues**, with some scheduling into early 2024 possible (24:11).
    - Internal episodes are designed to promote Noetic’s services and generate interest from existing networks.
    - Positive guest engagement is boosted by Rachel Curtis’s proactive encouragement, helping reduce guest nervousness.

- **A new podcast framework template with an introductory paragraph was created** to give guests clear context and ease their participation, enhancing professionalism and personal touch (44:13).
    - This evergreen framework aims for consistent quality and guest comfort.
    - Rachel and Nathalie highlighted the importance of genuine guest encouragement to maintain high-quality conversations.

- **Colin will produce an end-of-year compilation video** featuring podcast highlights to showcase growth and milestones from the first year of the Metamorphosis Moment series (01:02:12).
    - This aligns with the team’s goal to celebrate progress and maintain momentum.
    - The video project was previously on the wish list and will now be prioritized.

## **Website SEO and User Engagement Improvements**

To address **declining traffic on the Insights page**, Colin proposed SEO-driven copy adjustments emphasizing "Brand Insights for Marketing Leaders" and related keywords to improve organic search rankings (45:48).

- **Revised headline and section descriptions focus on practical frameworks, market trends, and team challenges**, aligned with common search terms rather than internal jargon (46:00).
    - This should help increase visibility for podcasts, playbooks, and blog content.
    - Nathalie Mintjens confirmed she can implement these copy changes directly on the website.

- **Monitoring metrics show average session duration at about 2 minutes 40 seconds, three times the industry average, despite a slight bounce rate increase** (50:35).
    - The bounce rate remains below the 60% industry benchmark, indicating good engagement quality.
    - Colin emphasized SEO as a long-term strategy requiring ongoing adjustment and user behavior analysis.

- **The website update process will include training Julia Oher on content edits**, supporting team capacity building for future site maintenance (48:52).
    - This supports operational efficiency and internal ownership of digital assets.

## **Process Automation and Reporting Enhancements**

Colin introduced a **new automated weekly email summarizing recent and upcoming activities** related to points delivered, purchases, and campaign status, scheduled for Fridays at 4pm Eastern Time (51:41).

- **The automation extracts data from the last 14 days and the next 30 days**, providing a designed, clear summary for easy review (54:08).
    - Nathalie Mintjens will include Rocky and Tiffany as CC recipients to increase cross-team visibility.
    - The email includes a direct link to the dashboard for quick access to detailed data.

- This improvement is expected to **reduce manual reporting effort and improve stakeholder alignment on project progress**.
    - Colin acknowledged initial technical challenges but committed to stable delivery.
    - The automation aligns with the team’s goal to streamline communications and provide timely updates.

## **Team Collaboration and Culture Insights**

The recent **in-person retreat at Lansdowne Resort fostered valuable team bonding and strategic work on integrating AI into Noetic processes** (12:56).

- The team appreciated the setting’s balance of convenience, cost, and space, supporting productive collaboration (13:20).
    - Activities included a memorable “Disc assessment” session and creative icebreakers like a tool to punish jargon use.
    - These sessions strengthen team cohesion, morale, and remote work balance.

- Discussions highlighted the **importance of empathy for guest nerves during podcasts**, with Rachel praised for her supportive approach that helps guests relax and perform well (44:58).
    - This cultural attention enhances content quality and client relationships.
    - The team values humility and authenticity in interactions.

- The group expressed enthusiasm for ongoing internal knowledge sharing and training, including website update skills for newer members like Julia (48:52).
    - This promotes team growth and operational resilience.
    - Collaborative humor and storytelling remain part of the positive team dynamic.',
  '2025-11-19 19:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send finalized thankful mailer to Nancy and Rachel for review (08:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm and finalize email signature formats to include workplace awards and social handles prior to thankful mailer launch (06:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and gift points back to Noetic for AI campaign effort and negotiate points budget adjustments with internal team (12:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist Nancy and Colin with placing finalized AI one-pagers on offerings page and helping shape AI campaign messaging tone (34:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Attend scheduled training on website content updates and ongoing site maintenance (48:59)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

