    '{"id":"01KAEBWTYSZ8NNN1K9WJKH3CA2","title":"Join Teams meeting in progress","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Launch Timing and Coordination**\n\nThe team agreed to delay the **ABM campaign launch until December 1st**, after the holiday weekend, to maximize engagement (06:00).\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** voiced concerns that launching before the holiday would result in poor engagement due to people being out of office or distracted by shopping.\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** and **Samuel Bagnall** concurred, noting that cold emails sent during the holiday weekend would likely be ignored.\n- They considered a Black Friday special offer but decided against it since no such promotion is ready, reinforcing the decision to wait.\n- This timing shift aims to improve open and response rates by targeting recipients when they are more mentally available.\n\n## **Email Marketing Setup and Dependencies**\n\nThe team finalized preparations for the email outreach, with key dependencies on **Kristen''s Heyreach connection** to complete setup (02:15).\n\n- Purchased **email addresses for Kristen** and loaded content into the email tool, ensuring readiness for deployment.\n- Ruby committed to following up with Kristen to ensure the technical connection is completed without issues.\n- Once the connection is live, the team will add all remaining content and finalize the campaign setup.\n- This dependency directly influences the launch timeline, so close monitoring is essential.\n\n## **Paid Media Performance and Budget Reallocation**\n\nNovember LinkedIn ads generated **18 leads**, but the construction sector underperformed, prompting a budget shift to legal services (05:00).\n\n- A developer fixed automation issues affecting lead source tracking, ensuring accurate attribution going forward.\n- Paid media specialists found that Meta ads could increase brand awareness for construction but are unlikely to drive conversions due to poor targeting capabilities.\n- Ruby and Nathalie agreed to reallocate the construction ad budget to the upcoming **Legal Services campaign** for better ROI.\n- The legal campaign budget recommendation is pending from the paid media specialist, with implementation planned soon after.\n\n## **SEO Content Progress and Next Steps**\n\nThe team published the **most critical SEO landing page** for the upcoming campaign, awaiting review on additional pages to maintain momentum (06:40).\n\n- Samuel will follow up on the status of the remaining **three SEO landing pages** to ensure timely publication.\n- Publishing these pages supports the broader campaign by improving organic traffic and complementing paid efforts.\n- This SEO work is critical for sustained lead generation beyond the immediate campaign launch.\n\n## **Team Availability and Operational Context**\n\nKey team members confirmed availability for the week leading to the campaign launch despite personal scheduling challenges (07:50).\n\n- Ruby highlighted a busy Wednesday with multiple early school releases and Thanksgiving preparations but committed to being present.\n- Samuel and Nathalie acknowledged the logistical complexities but emphasized the importance of maintaining coverage.\n- Maintaining team presence during this critical period ensures smooth execution and quick issue resolution as the campaign rolls out.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI readiness","email campaign","LinkedIn ads","paid media","SEO landing pages","holiday marketing timing"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch Delay:** ABM campaign launch moved to December 1st to enhance engagement after holidays.  \n- **Email Marketing Setup:** Key connection to Kristen''s Heyreach is crucial; follow-up needed to ensure timely deployment.  \n- **Budget Reallocation:** November LinkedIn ads generated 18 leads; funds shifted from construction to legal services for better ROI.  \n- **SEO Progress:** Critical SEO landing page published; monitoring of three remaining pages is essential for campaign effectiveness.  \n- **Team Availability:** Team confirmed presence despite personal conflicts; maintaining coverage important for smooth campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nPublish the AI readiness scorecard page identical to the approved one (02:10)\nUpdate team when Kristen completes Heyreach connection for email tool integration (03:00)\nInform team upon receiving legal services ad budget recommendation from paid media specialist (06:50)\nOversee publishing of scorecard page and loading of LinkedIn ads when ready (07:30)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nFollow up with Kristen to confirm Heyreach connection completion (02:55)\nCoordinate with Kristen on LinkedIn integration and email tool setup (09:00)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nFollow up with Jeff on the three SEO landing pages to ensure review and completion (07:40)\n"},"duration":9.359999656677246,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"sentences":[{"text":"We go.","index":0,"end_time":0.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1,"end_time":1.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.56,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How about you?","index":2,"end_time":3.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve been kind of the opposite.","index":3,"end_time":7.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I''ve been pretty busy, so.","index":4,"end_time":8.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.6,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, so it''s kind of the opposite more just because we have our holiday party coming up, and then I''m going on a. I''m traveling beginning of December, so then after that it should slow down.","index":5,"end_time":22.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.88,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Where are you going?","index":6,"end_time":23.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Mexico.","index":7,"end_time":25.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.48,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":8,"end_time":26.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"For a wedding.","index":9,"end_time":26.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.25,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":27.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.93,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, that''ll be fun.","index":11,"end_time":29.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":30.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello.","index":13,"end_time":31.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Morning.","index":14,"end_time":33.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.65,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Going to Mexico.","index":15,"end_time":35.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":16,"end_time":35.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, Going in, like, less than two weeks.","index":17,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.01,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, fun.","index":18,"end_time":39.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Which part of Mexico?","index":19,"end_time":44.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it''s Los Cabos.","index":20,"end_time":46.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.57,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It''s on Lake Baja, California.","index":21,"end_time":48.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.57,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay, very cool.","index":22,"end_time":50.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And how about you, Ruby?","index":23,"end_time":55.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Any Thanksgiving plans coming up?","index":24,"end_time":58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll go to my aunts for Thanksgiving.","index":25,"end_time":61.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":59.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I''m not hosting, which is good.","index":26,"end_time":63.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But, yeah, it''ll be a full day of Thanksgiving going to that side of the family, and then we''ll go to John''s side of the family later in the day.","index":27,"end_time":72.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Are they all in Massachusetts?","index":28,"end_time":76.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, well, no one''s in Connecticut, but it''s just right over the line, so it''s not that big of a deal.","index":29,"end_time":83.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":30,"end_time":84.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because all of our states are so tiny that it''s like, not a big deal to, you know, have to go to another state.","index":31,"end_time":91.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":84.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":92.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":33,"end_time":94.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just looking at what we''re working on.","index":34,"end_time":105.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So not too many updates this week as we continue to set up for the ABM plan.","index":35,"end_time":111.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we did publish this AI readiness page, which Jeff looked over, so this is all good to go.","index":36,"end_time":119.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I did want to confirm with you, though, if we can publish this one as well, which is the one that is just the scorecard with nothing else.","index":37,"end_time":128.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think so as long as it''s identical to, you know, what''s on the other one.","index":38,"end_time":134.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":135.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Same questions.","index":40,"end_time":137.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":41,"end_time":138.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":138.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":139.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll publish this one as well and update from our side.","index":44,"end_time":145.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ve.","index":45,"end_time":145.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We have purchased the email addresses for Kristen and then got the content loaded up into the email tool.","index":46,"end_time":152.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s all good to go.","index":47,"end_time":153.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''re just waiting on her to do the heyreach connection.","index":48,"end_time":158.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me know if she has any trouble there.","index":49,"end_time":161.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then once that''s done, we''ll add all the content in there as well.","index":50,"end_time":165.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":51,"end_time":166.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, she seemed like she was fine with it.","index":52,"end_time":168.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"She.","index":53,"end_time":169.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know.","index":54,"end_time":170.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"She.","index":55,"end_time":170.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"She got my email.","index":56,"end_time":171.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We talked about it yesterday.","index":57,"end_time":172.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.29,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think she should be good.","index":58,"end_time":176.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ll follow up, though.","index":59,"end_time":177.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just ping her one more time.","index":60,"end_time":179.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":61,"end_time":180.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"See if she''s good.","index":62,"end_time":181.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.41,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Cool.","index":63,"end_time":184.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I was looking at the upcoming dates and I. I''m a bit like, as we get this all set up.","index":64,"end_time":192.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m a bit hesitant if it''s already by early next week to launch it just because of the holiday and stuff.","index":65,"end_time":198.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I just don''t know how engaged people would be with these cold emails.","index":66,"end_time":202.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I wanted to see your thoughts on maybe launching on the first, which is a Monday, like, after the holiday.","index":67,"end_time":208.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m fine with that.","index":68,"end_time":211.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":213.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What do you think, Sam?","index":70,"end_time":214.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense to me.","index":71,"end_time":216.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.89,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Just gonna.","index":72,"end_time":217.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.21,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Part of me is like, oh, let''s just do it now.","index":73,"end_time":220.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But you''re right.","index":74,"end_time":221.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.05,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I mean, it would just waste.","index":75,"end_time":222.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Kind of like, it would just.","index":76,"end_time":225.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Nobody was gonna be checking their email or worried about anything except for shopping over the weekend.","index":77,"end_time":232.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.05,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I feel like a lot of them might be out of office, and if they''re not, they''re just mentally not that engaged.","index":78,"end_time":240.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":240.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Now here''s the flip side.","index":80,"end_time":241.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.74,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If we had a really cool offer that would work, like Black Friday sale, like get, you know, X amount off of I Cor.","index":81,"end_time":252.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Whatever, like, that could work, but no.","index":82,"end_time":254.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":257.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":258.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":259.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sunday, do it.","index":86,"end_time":260.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":261.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Convince Mike that we''ll do a Black Friday sale for I Cor.","index":88,"end_time":266.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll aim for the first, then just hold off on launch it.","index":89,"end_time":276.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":90,"end_time":278.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for paid media.","index":91,"end_time":282.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So so far, we have 18 leads that came in from LinkedIn in November.","index":92,"end_time":287.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We did look into that one contact that had all the lead sources that kept changing around.","index":93,"end_time":293.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The developer said there was something wrong with the automation and the branches that we had set up, but he''s fixed it now, so everything should populate correctly for the lead sources.","index":94,"end_time":305.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":95,"end_time":307.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then for construction, our paid media specialists also looked into doing ads on Meta as well, seeing if that could work, since we saw that construction is not doing that well on LinkedIn.","index":96,"end_time":321.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She said it could.","index":97,"end_time":323.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It could work well for brand awareness, if that was our goal.","index":98,"end_time":327.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Might not work well for conversions.","index":99,"end_time":330.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Especially because.","index":100,"end_time":332.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Especially because on Facebook, the difference is we can''t target people by their seniority.","index":101,"end_time":341.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So what we might end up doing is putting ads in front of the actual labor force instead of, you know, managers and decision makers.","index":102,"end_time":349.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I think recommendation there is.","index":103,"end_time":353.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Construction is not working that well on LinkedIn.","index":104,"end_time":355.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can just shift that budget over to legal services now that we''re launching that.","index":105,"end_time":361.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think that''s fine.","index":106,"end_time":365.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":107,"end_time":366.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I think she''s right.","index":108,"end_time":367.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, Facebook just.","index":109,"end_time":368.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.74,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Work.","index":110,"end_time":371.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":372.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I also think, like, for conversions, it would just be silly even if we could get in front of the right people.","index":112,"end_time":378.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, people are on Facebook to entertain themselves or, you know, do normal social stuff, not make business decisions.","index":113,"end_time":388.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":389.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Totally agree.","index":115,"end_time":392.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":116,"end_time":393.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then once she''s.","index":117,"end_time":395.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Once she''s setting up this Legal Services campaign, she''ll come back with the exact number of how much budget she recommends we shift over to Legal Services.","index":118,"end_time":403.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll let you know when she''s done with that.","index":119,"end_time":406.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":120,"end_time":408.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":121,"end_time":410.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for SEO, so we got this one published.","index":122,"end_time":415.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This was the one that was most important for this upcoming campaign.","index":123,"end_time":420.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so, yeah, we''ll just wait for your review for these other ones.","index":124,"end_time":424.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And those were all my notes.","index":125,"end_time":429.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So from our side, we''ll get this scorecard page, this one, this page published, get the ads loaded in LinkedIn, and then just let us know when Kristen is done with her LinkedIn connection and then have everything planned to launch on the first.","index":126,"end_time":448.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":127,"end_time":449.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So anything else from your side?","index":128,"end_time":455.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":129,"end_time":460.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we just had to follow up with Jeff on some.","index":130,"end_time":463.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I was going to say I''ll follow up on the pages.","index":131,"end_time":467.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.389,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"The three SEO, like, landing pages.","index":132,"end_time":470.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.39,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I can do that.","index":133,"end_time":472.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.75,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"All right.","index":134,"end_time":475.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Will you both be here on Wednesday next week?","index":135,"end_time":480.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":481.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":481.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''Ll be here.","index":138,"end_time":485.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s gonna be a crazy day, though.","index":139,"end_time":487.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Both kids get out of school early, actually.","index":140,"end_time":492.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Both kids.","index":141,"end_time":493.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All sets of kids.","index":142,"end_time":495.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"There''s my kids and then John''s kids.","index":143,"end_time":499.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re all.","index":144,"end_time":499.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Everyone has an early release, and so we''re getting all of them on Wednesday after school so that they sleep over.","index":145,"end_time":506.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we have them Thursday for Thanksgiving to be full house.","index":146,"end_time":512.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But, yes, I''ll be here.","index":147,"end_time":513.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":148,"end_time":515.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m surprised they even have school, like, the day before Thanksgiving.","index":149,"end_time":520.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, they do.","index":150,"end_time":521.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":151,"end_time":523.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.94,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"My mom''s school''s on.","index":152,"end_time":524.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.02,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"They do fall break the whole week, so they don''t even go to school.","index":153,"end_time":526.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":527.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.14,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":527.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":156,"end_time":528.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.94,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":157,"end_time":531.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, it should be a fun time, Ruby.","index":158,"end_time":533.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be good.","index":159,"end_time":535.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":160,"end_time":540.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Cool.","index":161,"end_time":540.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, I''ll check with Kristen.","index":162,"end_time":541.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''ll get that connected.","index":163,"end_time":543.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And this is great.","index":164,"end_time":545.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m excited.","index":165,"end_time":547.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Me, too.","index":166,"end_time":548.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re almost there.","index":167,"end_time":549.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Almost.","index":168,"end_time":550.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":552.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right.","index":170,"end_time":553.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you both.","index":171,"end_time":553.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":172,"end_time":554.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":173,"end_time":555.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":174,"end_time":556.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"dateString":"2025-11-19T15:31:56.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/meet/259699818520?p=QtmrD7yaBsuCd7i4wj","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","fred@fireflies.ai"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KAEBWTYSZ8NNN1K9WJKH3CA2","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.6,"bullets":[],"highlights":[],"topics":[],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-21T19:06:45.654Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Launch Timing and Coordination**\n\nThe team agreed to delay the **ABM campaign launch until December 1st**, after the holiday weekend, to maximize engagement (06:00).\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** voiced concerns that launching before the holiday would result in poor engagement due to people being out of office or distracted by shopping.\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** and **Samuel Bagnall** concurred, noting that cold emails sent during the holiday weekend would likely be ignored.\n- They considered a Black Friday special offer but decided against it since no such promotion is ready, reinforcing the decision to wait.\n- This timing shift aims to improve open and response rates by targeting recipients when they are more mentally available.\n\n## **Email Marketing Setup and Dependencies**\n\nThe team finalized preparations for the email outreach, with key dependencies on **Kristen''s Heyreach connection** to complete setup (02:15).\n\n- Purchased **email addresses for Kristen** and loaded content into the email tool, ensuring readiness for deployment.\n- Ruby committed to following up with Kristen to ensure the technical connection is completed without issues.\n- Once the connection is live, the team will add all remaining content and finalize the campaign setup.\n- This dependency directly influences the launch timeline, so close monitoring is essential.\n\n## **Paid Media Performance and Budget Reallocation**\n\nNovember LinkedIn ads generated **18 leads**, but the construction sector underperformed, prompting a budget shift to legal services (05:00).\n\n- A developer fixed automation issues affecting lead source tracking, ensuring accurate attribution going forward.\n- Paid media specialists found that Meta ads could increase brand awareness for construction but are unlikely to drive conversions due to poor targeting capabilities.\n- Ruby and Nathalie agreed to reallocate the construction ad budget to the upcoming **Legal Services campaign** for better ROI.\n- The legal campaign budget recommendation is pending from the paid media specialist, with implementation planned soon after.\n\n## **SEO Content Progress and Next Steps**\n\nThe team published the **most critical SEO landing page** for the upcoming campaign, awaiting review on additional pages to maintain momentum (06:40).\n\n- Samuel will follow up on the status of the remaining **three SEO landing pages** to ensure timely publication.\n- Publishing these pages supports the broader campaign by improving organic traffic and complementing paid efforts.\n- This SEO work is critical for sustained lead generation beyond the immediate campaign launch.\n\n## **Team Availability and Operational Context**\n\nKey team members confirmed availability for the week leading to the campaign launch despite personal scheduling challenges (07:50).\n\n- Ruby highlighted a busy Wednesday with multiple early school releases and Thanksgiving preparations but committed to being present.\n- Samuel and Nathalie acknowledged the logistical complexities but emphasized the importance of maintaining coverage.\n- Maintaining team presence during this critical period ensures smooth execution and quick issue resolution as the campaign rolls out.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI readiness","email campaign","LinkedIn ads","paid media","SEO landing pages","holiday marketing timing"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch Delay:** ABM campaign launch moved to December 1st to enhance engagement after holidays.  \n- **Email Marketing Setup:** Key connection to Kristen''s Heyreach is crucial; follow-up needed to ensure timely deployment.  \n- **Budget Reallocation:** November LinkedIn ads generated 18 leads; funds shifted from construction to legal services for better ROI.  \n- **SEO Progress:** Critical SEO landing page published; monitoring of three remaining pages is essential for campaign effectiveness.  \n- **Team Availability:** Team confirmed presence despite personal conflicts; maintaining coverage important for smooth campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nPublish the AI readiness scorecard page identical to the approved one (02:10)\nUpdate team when Kristen completes Heyreach connection for email tool integration (03:00)\nInform team upon receiving legal services ad budget recommendation from paid media specialist (06:50)\nOversee publishing of scorecard page and loading of LinkedIn ads when ready (07:30)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nFollow up with Kristen to confirm Heyreach connection completion (02:55)\nCoordinate with Kristen on LinkedIn integration and email tool setup (09:00)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nFollow up with Jeff on the three SEO landing pages to ensure review and completion (07:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a55e9e9f-4e55-4d61-981e-4fa467ab0206","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
