    1598,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86061042503?pwd=x0TBEgRs7qFmrRIEItauCzbH71kaq8.1',
    '{"id":"01K9WG1YP3Y720Z37T1G3KQ9KQ","title":"Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **SMS Opt-Out Detection and Workflow Integration**\n\nThe team decided to investigate the feasibility of setting up **SMS opt-out detection in HubSpot** based on the initial logic shared by **Milan Wagner** (00:00).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** and **Yefei Jin** found the provided property data too simplified and mismatched real HubSpot fields, requiring deeper analysis (00:47).\n    - Colin requested concrete examples of opt-out replies to map properties correctly.\n    - Milan committed to sharing those examples in the team chat to aid troubleshooting.\n    - Colin will continue exploring possible workflows to automate opt-out detection and management.\n    - This setup is critical to maintain compliance and improve customer communication management.\n\n- The opt-out workflow and detection feature remain a priority with no fixed deadline yet, but ongoing investigation will inform next steps (25:04).\n    - The expected impact is reducing manual opt-out handling and avoiding messaging non-consenting contacts.\n    - Risks include inaccurate field mapping delaying implementation; mitigation involves direct example data and iterative testing.\n    - This initiative aligns with improving the messaging platform’s compliance and user experience.\n\n## **Meta Lead Integration and Sync Issues**\n\nResolving lead syncing problems with **Meta (Facebook) lead forms** is a key focus to restore data flow and lead visibility (02:17).\n\n- The team found that leads were not appearing due to account and permission mismatches between **Meta and HubSpot**, with **Josh’s** account no longer active (02:50).\n    - **Yefei Jin** and **Colin Costigan** identified that the current connection is under the email tech@powerhouse soflow.com, which lacks proper admin permissions on Facebook.\n    - Milan agreed to connect Meta and HubSpot accounts properly, ensuring the tech@powerhouse email is assigned admin rights within Facebook Business Manager.\n    - They agreed to create or assign a Facebook Business Manager account for tech@powerhouse for cleaner admin control and permission management.\n    - This fix is expected to enable seamless lead syncing, improving lead capture and marketing contact assignment.\n\n- The team encountered delays in Meta’s approval emails and login verification codes, extending setup time (15:40).\n    - Facebook’s verification process can take up to **30 minutes**, causing temporary hold-ups in access.\n    - Colin emphasized that Meta’s interface changes frequently, requiring flexibility and frequent updates to procedures.\n    - The team expects to finalize connections within the next few days, pending email approvals and account setup.\n    - Success will be measured by restored lead flow and accurate marketing contact counts.\n\n## **Lead Sync Workflow and Data Handling**\n\nAfter reconnecting accounts, the lead syncing process will automatically pull both new and recent leads without manual intervention (06:05).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** demonstrated that once connected, the system will retroactively pull leads starting from the specified date (e.g., from the 14th), ensuring no missed data (23:55).\n    - The dropdown selection “new and recent leads” controls which leads are imported.\n    - Leads will automatically be set as marketing contacts without repeated manual selection.\n    - This automation reduces manual errors and maintains up-to-date marketing lists for campaigns.\n    - The expected improvement is greater lead visibility and faster marketing response times.\n\n- The team plans to monitor lead volumes post-connection to confirm the sync works as expected (24:35).\n    - Colin will continue providing support to troubleshoot any issues during this process.\n    - Milan and Yefei will verify leads appear correctly in HubSpot dashboards and reports.\n    - This process supports the broader goal of improving data quality and marketing efficiency.\n\n## **Team Coordination and Resourcing During Holiday Period**\n\nColin notified the team he will be out of the office for the entire **Thanksgiving week** and proposed canceling the standing meeting to accommodate (25:36).\n\n- The team agreed to pause meetings during the holiday, minimizing disruption (25:52).\n    - Nina Belina will remain the primary contact during Colin’s absence, ensuring continuity.\n    - Milan plans to reach out to Nina for urgent issues next week.\n    - This approach maintains operational support while respecting holiday schedules.\n    - Planning ahead prevents delays in ongoing tasks like the opt-out workflow and lead sync fixes.\n\n- The team emphasized responsiveness and communication clarity during this period to avoid bottlenecks (26:07).\n    - Clear handoff ownership supports smooth progress on critical integrations.\n    - This scheduling flexibility aligns with team morale and work-life balance priorities.\n\n## **Reporting and Dashboard Updates**\n\nMilan confirmed that the recently added reports and dashboards meet current needs, with no immediate additional requests (02:43).\n\n- The current reporting setup supports monitoring lead activity and campaign performance.\n    - Milan will request further reports as necessary, ensuring reports evolve with business needs.\n    - This stable reporting environment allows the team to focus on resolving integration issues first.\n    - The existing dashboards provide sufficient visibility for decision-making at this stage.\n    - Maintaining this clarity supports efficient marketing and sales tracking.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","SMS opt-out","Meta lead syncing","Facebook Business Manager","user permissions","chatbot"],"overview":"- **SMS Opt-Out Workflow:** Team investigates SMS opt-out detection in HubSpot for compliance and better customer communication.\n\n- **Meta Lead Sync Issues:** Team aims to resolve Meta lead syncing problems caused by permission mismatches and inactive accounts.\n\n- **Lead Sync Automation:** Once accounts reconnect, leads will auto-pull without manual input, improving visibility and reducing errors.\n\n- **Holiday Coordination:** Team cancels meetings during Thanksgiving week to maintain operations; Nina will be the main contact in Colin''s absence.\n\n- **Reporting Stability:** Current reports and dashboards meet needs, allowing focus on integration issues; further reports can be requested as required.","action_items":"\n**Milan Wagner**\nProvide example of SMS opt-out message content (''stop'' reply) to aid in workflow development (04:27)\nApprove Facebook Business Manager user invitation for tech@powerhousesoflow.com (00:00)\nFollow up with Nina Belina for support during Colin''s absence next week (00:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nInvestigate and confirm feasibility of SMS opt-out detection and related HubSpot workflow based on provided logic and actual field compatibility (00:00)\nTroubleshoot and resolve Meta lead form syncing issue post call with Yefei (03:36)\nSend HubSpot-Facebook lead sync link to Slack for team access (00:00)\nCancel next meeting during Thanksgiving week and confirm backup support (00:00)\n\n**Yefei Jin**\nAttempt Facebook Business Manager login and approve account invitation for tech@powerhousesoflow.com (00:00)\nCoordinate with Milan on Meta permissions and sync once access granted, and re-connect lead form in HubSpot (00:00)\nMonitor email for Facebook approval code and follow up if delayed (00:00)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nServe as point of contact and provide support during Colin’s absence next week (00:00)\n"},"duration":26.6299991607666,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Milan Wagner"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Yefei Jin"},{"id":3,"name":"Yefei Jin"},{"id":4,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Okay, I''m going to drop it into ideometry air call so you guys can review this.","index":0,"end_time":6.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s what the air call sent me regarding setting up opt out.","index":1,"end_time":14.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.4,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Like SMS opt out detection in HubSpot.","index":2,"end_time":19.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.52,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, we''ll attempt that.","index":3,"end_time":40.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":4,"end_time":42.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.21,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is that even possible?","index":5,"end_time":42.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.05,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s what I.","index":6,"end_time":44.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we want to check.","index":7,"end_time":45.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":46.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.85,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Check message content.","index":9,"end_time":49.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have to dig into this, Milan, because the properties that they sent are way too simplified.","index":10,"end_time":119.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not actually like matching up to what a real property would be that we could track.","index":11,"end_time":122.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":12,"end_time":124.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.12,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, well, I''ll leave that with you then.","index":13,"end_time":128.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.2,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You let me know what we can do there.","index":14,"end_time":130.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.12,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":15,"end_time":134.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.59,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Cool.","index":16,"end_time":137.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":136.79,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Those are the three things for me.","index":17,"end_time":138.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.23,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s the SMS opt out, the chat bot.","index":18,"end_time":143.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.39,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Seems like the chat bot''s all fixed, so that''s good.","index":19,"end_time":145.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.39,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And then the.","index":20,"end_time":146.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.389,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"The most important thing is the lead with meta.","index":21,"end_time":152.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s it on my end.","index":22,"end_time":156.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.55,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":23,"end_time":163.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you didn''t have anything additional regarding the dashboards or reporting that you wanted to implement?","index":24,"end_time":169.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":163.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, I mean, you guys added the reports, correct?","index":25,"end_time":173.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.79,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I saw them this morning.","index":26,"end_time":174.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.15,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":27,"end_time":175.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.27,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, for now, that''s it.","index":28,"end_time":177.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"If I need other reports, I''ll.","index":29,"end_time":179.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.55,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''ll request them with you guys.","index":30,"end_time":180.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.11,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Ife joined on the call, so.","index":31,"end_time":184.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.26,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Ife, apparently with meta, I just screen shared and it showed that meta was active, but it was something to do with Josh''s account or setup, and they''re.","index":32,"end_time":197.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.82,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They''re digging into it even further because we''re still not seeing hot leads.","index":33,"end_time":201.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.62,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":34,"end_time":208.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":208.11,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"It seems like it''ll be as actually a.","index":35,"end_time":213.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":210.67,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Should be a straightforward fix here.","index":36,"end_time":214.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":213.23,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Yeah, it should just be checking the connection on the form.","index":37,"end_time":218.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want.","index":38,"end_time":219.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":218.83,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Do you want us to.","index":39,"end_time":220.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":219.39,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Do you want me to open up?","index":40,"end_time":221.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.11,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Open it up and try to do it right now.","index":41,"end_time":224.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":221.87,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"No, I see it is connected, so we just need to dig into the form sync itself.","index":42,"end_time":230.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":232.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.63,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"So we''ll check in as soon as we can hop off of this call.","index":44,"end_time":237.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, we should hop off now then.","index":45,"end_time":240.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":237.85,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":46,"end_time":243.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and then we''ll dig into.","index":47,"end_time":244.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, this logic they sent over is interesting, Milan.","index":48,"end_time":248.689,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really am not seeing fields match up to what they said.","index":49,"end_time":251.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.689,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Check message content.","index":50,"end_time":254.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give an example of someone that replied.","index":51,"end_time":262.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stop.","index":52,"end_time":262.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, give me two seconds.","index":53,"end_time":268.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.14,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, if you can send that, then that''ll be a lot easier to work backwards from.","index":54,"end_time":271.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":55,"end_time":273.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.58,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"All right, I''ll drop.","index":56,"end_time":276.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''ll drop it into the ideometry chat.","index":57,"end_time":278.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":58,"end_time":279.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay, here''s the issue.","index":59,"end_time":287.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Facebook is.","index":60,"end_time":293.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.83,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"There it is.","index":61,"end_time":297.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.15,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":62,"end_time":298.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.03,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Are you talking to usmilan?","index":63,"end_time":313.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was talking to the sales issue.","index":64,"end_time":317.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Just.","index":65,"end_time":318.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.84,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Hey, Geefe.","index":66,"end_time":352.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah?","index":67,"end_time":356.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.45,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Can you do me a favor and click on this link that I just sent in the Zoom chat.","index":68,"end_time":362.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":365.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.53,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Should bring you to a lead syncing page where it allows.","index":70,"end_time":369.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since you''re the person that''s connected to Facebook now and HubSpot, it''ll allow you to just connect the form.","index":71,"end_time":374.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":72,"end_time":377.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.73,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Which login to HubSpot.","index":73,"end_time":390.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.18,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Share my screen.","index":74,"end_time":421.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":420.75,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"I''m in.","index":75,"end_time":421.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.35,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":76,"end_time":423.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so on the top right, it says connect.","index":77,"end_time":432.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":434.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.55,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"If you can click on that Facebook.","index":79,"end_time":436.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":80,"end_time":439.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New and recent leads, hit that drop down.","index":81,"end_time":443.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":445.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New and recent.","index":83,"end_time":446.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that way it''ll get the ones.","index":84,"end_time":447.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From the 14th marketing contacts.","index":85,"end_time":450,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":447.68,"speaker_name":"Yefei Jin"},{"text":"Is.","index":86,"end_time":450.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":87,"end_time":450.52