    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **SMS Opt-Out Detection and Workflow Integration**\n\nThe team decided to investigate the feasibility of setting up **SMS opt-out detection in HubSpot** based on the initial logic shared by **Milan Wagner** (00:00).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** and **Yefei Jin** found the provided property data too simplified and mismatched real HubSpot fields, requiring deeper analysis (00:47).\n    - Colin requested concrete examples of opt-out replies to map properties correctly.\n    - Milan committed to sharing those examples in the team chat to aid troubleshooting.\n    - Colin will continue exploring possible workflows to automate opt-out detection and management.\n    - This setup is critical to maintain compliance and improve customer communication management.\n\n- The opt-out workflow and detection feature remain a priority with no fixed deadline yet, but ongoing investigation will inform next steps (25:04).\n    - The expected impact is reducing manual opt-out handling and avoiding messaging non-consenting contacts.\n    - Risks include inaccurate field mapping delaying implementation; mitigation involves direct example data and iterative testing.\n    - This initiative aligns with improving the messaging platform’s compliance and user experience.\n\n## **Meta Lead Integration and Sync Issues**\n\nResolving lead syncing problems with **Meta (Facebook) lead forms** is a key focus to restore data flow and lead visibility (02:17).\n\n- The team found that leads were not appearing due to account and permission mismatches between **Meta and HubSpot**, with **Josh’s** account no longer active (02:50).\n    - **Yefei Jin** and **Colin Costigan** identified that the current connection is under the email tech@powerhouse soflow.com, which lacks proper admin permissions on Facebook.\n    - Milan agreed to connect Meta and HubSpot accounts properly, ensuring the tech@powerhouse email is assigned admin rights within Facebook Business Manager.\n    - They agreed to create or assign a Facebook Business Manager account for tech@powerhouse for cleaner admin control and permission management.\n    - This fix is expected to enable seamless lead syncing, improving lead capture and marketing contact assignment.\n\n- The team encountered delays in Meta’s approval emails and login verification codes, extending setup time (15:40).\n    - Facebook’s verification process can take up to **30 minutes**, causing temporary hold-ups in access.\n    - Colin emphasized that Meta’s interface changes frequently, requiring flexibility and frequent updates to procedures.\n    - The team expects to finalize connections within the next few days, pending email approvals and account setup.\n    - Success will be measured by restored lead flow and accurate marketing contact counts.\n\n## **Lead Sync Workflow and Data Handling**\n\nAfter reconnecting accounts, the lead syncing process will automatically pull both new and recent leads without manual intervention (06:05).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** demonstrated that once connected, the system will retroactively pull leads starting from the specified date (e.g., from the 14th), ensuring no missed data (23:55).\n    - The dropdown selection “new and recent leads” controls which leads are imported.\n    - Leads will automatically be set as marketing contacts without repeated manual selection.\n    - This automation reduces manual errors and maintains up-to-date marketing lists for campaigns.\n    - The expected improvement is greater lead visibility and faster marketing response times.\n\n- The team plans to monitor lead volumes post-connection to confirm the sync works as expected (24:35).\n    - Colin will continue providing support to troubleshoot any issues during this process.\n    - Milan and Yefei will verify leads appear correctly in HubSpot dashboards and reports.\n    - This process supports the broader goal of improving data quality and marketing efficiency.\n\n## **Team Coordination and Resourcing During Holiday Period**\n\nColin notified the team he will be out of the office for the entire **Thanksgiving week** and proposed canceling the standing meeting to accommodate (25:36).\n\n- The team agreed to pause meetings during the holiday, minimizing disruption (25:52).\n    - Nina Belina will remain the primary contact during Colin’s absence, ensuring continuity.\n    - Milan plans to reach out to Nina for urgent issues next week.\n    - This approach maintains operational support while respecting holiday schedules.\n    - Planning ahead prevents delays in ongoing tasks like the opt-out workflow and lead sync fixes.\n\n- The team emphasized responsiveness and communication clarity during this period to avoid bottlenecks (26:07).\n    - Clear handoff ownership supports smooth progress on critical integrations.\n    - This scheduling flexibility aligns with team morale and work-life balance priorities.\n\n## **Reporting and Dashboard Updates**\n\nMilan confirmed that the recently added reports and dashboards meet current needs, with no immediate additional requests (02:43).\n\n- The current reporting setup supports monitoring lead activity and campaign performance.\n    - Milan will request further reports as necessary, ensuring reports evolve with business needs.\n    - This stable reporting environment allows the team to focus on resolving integration issues first.\n    - The existing dashboards provide sufficient visibility for decision-making at this stage.\n    - Maintaining this clarity supports efficient marketing and sales tracking.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","SMS opt-out","Meta lead syncing","Facebook Business Manager","user permissions","chatbot"],"overview":"- **SMS Opt-Out Workflow:** Team investigates SMS opt-out detection in HubSpot for compliance and better customer communication.\n\n- **Meta Lead Sync Issues:** Team aims to resolve Meta lead syncing problems caused by permission mismatches and inactive accounts.\n\n- **Lead Sync Automation:** Once accounts reconnect, leads will auto-pull without manual input, improving visibility and reducing errors.\n\n- **Holiday Coordination:** Team cancels meetings during Thanksgiving week to maintain operations; Nina will be the main contact in Colin''s absence.\n\n- **Reporting Stability:** Current reports and dashboards meet needs, allowing focus on integration issues; further reports can be requested as required.","action_items":"\n**Milan Wagner**\nProvide example of SMS opt-out message content (''stop'' reply) to aid in workflow development (04:27)\nApprove Facebook Business Manager user invitation for tech@powerhousesoflow.com (00:00)\nFollow up with Nina Belina for support during Colin''s absence next week (00:00)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nInvestigate and confirm feasibility of SMS opt-out detection and related HubSpot workflow based on provided logic and actual field compatibility (00:00)\nTroubleshoot and resolve Meta lead form syncing issue post call with Yefei (03:36)\nSend HubSpot-Facebook lead sync link to Slack for team access (00:00)\nCancel next meeting during Thanksgiving week and confirm backup support (00:00)\n\n**Yefei Jin**\nAttempt Facebook Business Manager login and approve account invitation for tech@powerhousesoflow.com (00:00)\nCoordinate with Milan on Meta permissions and sync once access granted, and re-connect lead form in HubSpot (00:00)\nMonitor email for Facebook approval code and follow up if delayed (00:00)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nServe as point of contact and provide support during Colin’s absence next week (00:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"d17ce491-8b1f-4852-98ea-607e134c6cb5","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
