-- Meeting: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-11-17 14:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '75b32155-1255-4d17-b437-152e300521a0',
    '2025-11-17 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9W7MRAEADEVK4ZW1QJ8A5MP',
    'New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Greg Smith","Colin Costigan","Kate ThreatMark","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    2708,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1',
    '{"id":"01K9W7MRAEADEVK4ZW1QJ8A5MP","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Content and Campaign Execution**\n\nMarketing content updates and campaign adjustments are aligned with current events and refined targeting to improve lead quality.\n\n- **The Aaron Fry episode is finalized and pending syndication across YouTube, Spotify, and Apple this week to align with International Fraud Awareness Week**, contingent on Michal’s final review and approval (06:10)  \n    - Only one mention of **PNC and Swivel Bank** was flagged and cleared per Mike’s feedback  \n    - Kate confirmed no further permission is needed to promote once edits are approved  \n    - The episode link and related resources will be shared via Slack recap for quick access  \n    - This timing leverages industry awareness week to maximize audience engagement\n\n- **Updated white paper PDFs incorporating iconography and cleaner layout were delivered and are ready for website resource updates and LinkedIn ad integration** (07:06)  \n    - Ads will be refreshed to fit the new white paper design and integrated into existing PDF ad campaigns  \n    - HubSpot workflows will be updated to include email sequences tied to these resources for continuous nurture  \n    - Rotating banner ads featuring Scan Flag, the AI vs Fraud white paper, and “Win the War Against Fraud” messaging are in design review  \n\n- **LinkedIn lead gen ads targeting a refined audience of approximately 9,400 high-intent prospects are being developed to reduce funnel friction** (18:03)  \n    - Auto-filled forms on LinkedIn will replace landing page clicks to improve conversion rates  \n    - Campaign exclusions for uninterested companies like Bank of America are carried forward to prevent wasted spend  \n    - The new campaign in draft is planned to replace the existing live campaign for better efficiency  \n    - Greg emphasized the importance of funneling leads into nurture sequences after initial LinkedIn engagement  \n\n## **Website and Technical Infrastructure**\n\nWebsite updates focus on cleaning the platform, improving user experience, and resolving security vulnerabilities with an emphasis on sustainable infrastructure management.\n\n- **Security vulnerabilities have been fully addressed, with all scripts updated and false positives resolved on both Google and Cookiebot platforms** (17:11)  \n    - Colin proposed establishing monthly maintenance checks to prevent future issues  \n    - Dynamic parameters were implemented to ensure ongoing compliance with cookie policies\n\n- **A rotating banner module is being built on the test site to allow interactive review before production deployment, with a rebuild needed on the live site due to unsynced environments** (13:00)  \n    - Colin explained the site does not support direct sync between test and production environments, requiring manual rebuilds  \n    - Kate confirmed a pending ticket to synchronize environments has faced pushback since February, with escalation planned to get developer access if necessary  \n    - Greg expressed concern about adding bloat and confirmed preference for custom PHP fields over plugins  \n\n- **Plans for website event tracking in GA4 will focus on minimal, high-value events like form conversions and homepage banner clicks to avoid bloating analytics with unreliable GDPR-compliant data** (21:29)  \n    - Greg and Kate agreed on the challenge of gathering meaningful data due to cookie consent variability  \n    - Colin will keep tracking lightweight and US-focused to maintain usable insights without overcomplication  \n    - Discussions about first-party cookies and server log analytics will be followed up for potential improvements  \n\n## **CRM and Sales Technology Optimization**\n\nCRM workflows and sales tech stack rationalization aim to improve lead source tracking and reduce system bloat while preparing for future platform upgrades.\n\n- **Lead source fields are being standardized between HubSpot and Salesforce with a flexible text field approach to allow easy population and future scalability** (29:45)  \n    - Colin detailed workflows that auto-assign lead sources based on form submissions and page interactions  \n    - Greg emphasized avoiding workflow complexity growth while ensuring accuracy  \n    - Colin to confirm HubSpot permissions and Salesforce field availability for smooth integration  \n\n- **Salesforce user access is being audited to reduce excessive permissions, with Colin tasked to identify whether current integrations require continued Salesforce access** (32:25)  \n    - Greg highlighted security concerns with overprovisioned admin rights linked to external users  \n    - Potential deprovisioning will streamline partner access and reduce risks  \n\n- **The Outreach sales engagement tool is considered redundant and underused, with plans to decommission user licenses immediately to cut costs** (39:27)  \n    - Colin and Greg agreed Outreach was never fully adopted, and its integration complexity outweighed benefits  \n    - Cost savings from eliminating Outreach user licenses will be reinvested in HubSpot-centered prospecting tools  \n    - Future sales prospecting to be managed in HubSpot while deal management remains in Salesforce for acquisition compatibility  \n\n## **Strategic Growth and GTM Planning**\n\nThe team is laying groundwork for structured sponsorship, gifting, and account-based marketing to scale engagement and operational efficiency in 2024.\n\n- **A new UK-based marketer, Julia, will start in early December to support event sponsorship execution and account-based go-to-market strategies** (42:00)  \n    - Greg emphasized the importance of locking in a full-year sponsorship calendar within weeks to avoid last-minute scrambles  \n    - Julia will oversee timeline adherence and coordination for sponsorship activities  \n    - This hire is expected to bring clarity and consistency to marketing event planning\n\n- **A formal gifting and swag program is under development with Sandosso to include swag, gifting, and direct mail, leveraging recent acquisitions like Postal to expand direct mail capabilities** (42:26)  \n    - Greg anticipates marketing support will be needed to manage this program’s rollout and vendor coordination  \n    - The program aims to enhance brand engagement through personalized outreach beyond digital channels  \n\n- **Improved market intelligence on serviceable accounts by region will drive the creation of mirrored territories in HubSpot, target account lists, and comprehensive account-based marketing efforts** (43:17)  \n    - Account personalization will extend to ads, landing pages, and email sequences for more relevant customer journeys  \n    - Greg foresees ongoing strategy and execution discussions as the team builds out this multi-channel approach  \n    - This aligns with a broader shift toward precision marketing and sales alignment  \n\n## **Team Coordination and Operational Continuity**\n\nTeam availability and meeting cadence adjustments ensure smooth collaboration during Colin’s upcoming absence.\n\n- **Colin will be on vacation starting Thursday through next week, leading to a pause of the usual Wednesday calls, with asynchronous Slack updates planned** (38:18)  \n    - Nina will cover communications and meeting facilitation during this period as needed  \n    - Greg and Kate agreed to handle questions via Slack unless critical discussions require live meetings  \n    - This approach aims to maintain momentum without overburdening team members during holidays  \n\n- **Newsletter and bulletin design updates are scheduled for November 1st, marking a test for more consistent future communications** (34:01)  \n    - Kate may request help with list setup and distribution workflows to ensure smooth execution  \n    - This initiative supports ongoing engagement with the audience through regular, branded content  \n\n- **Colin will share detailed recap links for the Aaron Fry episode, updated white paper, and lead source lists post-meeting to keep all parties aligned** (44:27)  \n    - The recap will enable quick reference and facilitate next steps in content publishing and CRM updates  \n    - Colin’s response times will be slower during vacation, but he remains available for critical needs  ","outline":null,"keywords":["White paper","HubSpot","Lead source","Website sync","LinkedIn campaigns","Outreach decommission"],"overview":"- **Aaron Fry Episode Launch:** Finalized and ready for syndication this week for International Fraud Awareness Week to boost engagement.  \n- **White Paper Updates:** New PDFs ready for website and LinkedIn ads, enhancing design and integration for lead nurturing.  \n- **LinkedIn Ads Targeting:** Developing lead gen ads for 9,400 high-intent prospects, improving conversion rates with auto-filled forms.  \n- **Website Security and Updates:** All vulnerabilities fixed; monthly maintenance proposed to ensure ongoing compliance and performance.  \n- **Salesforce Access Audit:** Streamlining user permissions to enhance security and reduce risks associated with overprovisioned access.  \n- **New UK Marketer Hire:** Starts December to oversee sponsorship and account-based marketing, aiming for improved event coordination.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend Aaron Fry episode link to Kate and include in recap message with all resource links (05:58)\nAdd updated white paper and podcast links to recap Slack message (07:42)\nCoordinate website rotating banner updates on test site and await final sign-off before production deployment (12:44)\nVerify HubSpot and Salesforce integration for lead source field population and workflow setup (29:45)\nReview GA4 event tracking capabilities and advise on compliance and tracking options (23:00)\nCheck for integrations requiring Outreach access and recommend removing ThreatMark’s Outreach user admin account (40:02)\nShare lead source list and related details in Slack with Greg and Kate after meeting (44:27)\nMonitor website environment sync ticket and coordinate timing to avoid update conflicts (26:37)\nProvide video links and app UI image options for homepage banner consideration (15:00)\nFollow up on HubSpot deal room set up regarding possible enterprise upgrade pending budget approval (34:10)\nSupport November newsletter testing and future design package needs when requested (33:50)\nAfter collaboration, verify whether Salesforce access is still needed and counsel on user reduction (32:25)\nManage asynchronous communication during upcoming vacation period (38:44)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nEnsure Michal reviews and approves white paper and campaign materials before launch (09:38)\nProvide Salesforce permission updates as lead source options are configured (32:00)\nReview and reduce user access in Salesforce, including Outreach users (39:00)\nSchedule and advise on migrating Banking Fraud Summit website to HubSpot; confirm enterprise licensing requirement (35:00)\nCollaborate with Kate to finalize lead source and marketing campaign lists for HubSpot integration (29:05)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview Aaron Fry podcast and white paper for timely promotion during International Fraud Awareness Week (06:32)\nCommunicate plans and schedules regarding website environment sync and advocate access rights if remediation delayed (26:50)\nCoordinate newsletter launch on November 1st, including list setup and audience targeting (34:10)\nProvide design specs and timing for newsletter and bulletin design package after testing phase (33:51)\nNotify Colin and Greg of new marketer onboarding timeline and event sponsorship calendar progress (42:30)\nConfirm last-minute decisions on rotating banner logo inclusion and image preferences (10:50)\n"},"duration":45.130001068115234,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Greg Smith"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":220.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.479,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":222,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":223.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":225.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":226.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was the trademark meeting moved from Wednesday to Monday?","index":5,"end_time":247.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yes, they have a event on Wednesday.","index":6,"end_time":250.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":7,"end_time":251.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hey, Greg.","index":8,"end_time":272.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":9,"end_time":273.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":10,"end_time":273.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":11,"end_time":274.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":12,"end_time":275.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not too bad.","index":13,"end_time":277.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How was the event last week?","index":14,"end_time":281.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":15,"end_time":282.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s productive.","index":16,"end_time":284.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Nice.","index":17,"end_time":285.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You got another one this week?","index":18,"end_time":286.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re.","index":19,"end_time":289.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And this one''s like a marketing one, so it''s.","index":20,"end_time":291.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s fun.","index":21,"end_time":293.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a fun one.","index":22,"end_time":294.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":295.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go see some marketing people.","index":24,"end_time":297.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":25,"end_time":299.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Kate.","index":26,"end_time":299.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":27,"end_time":300.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.95,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":28,"end_time":301.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Greg, since you were unable to make last week''s meeting, I did tell Kate about Nina joining the team.","index":29,"end_time":307.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s been on the team for a.","index":30,"end_time":308.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":307.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Few weeks, working in the background, helping.","index":31,"end_time":309.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Me out with Threatmark.","index":32,"end_time":310.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":309.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''ll be joining our calls from now on.","index":33,"end_time":313.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brings a lot of experience.","index":34,"end_time":314.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I won''t speak everything for you.","index":35,"end_time":317.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina, if you wanted to introduce yourself.","index":36,"end_time":319.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":317.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I''m the marketing strategist at Marketers In Demand.","index":37,"end_time":324.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ve been.","index":38,"end_time":325.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.73,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I started up recently and I''ve been helping Colin with everything that has to do with marketing actions that we do.","index":39,"end_time":333.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":40,"end_time":336.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So super excited to have her on the team.","index":41,"end_time":338.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are not getting rid of.","index":42,"end_time":340.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":339.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Me, though, no matter how hard you try.","index":43,"end_time":342.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":44,"end_time":343.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get into our slide deck.","index":45,"end_time":349.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, we''re still working on some things.","index":46,"end_time":350.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That I would have had prepped by.","index":47,"end_time":353.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our Wednesday meeting, so we''ll go through some of those.","index":48,"end_time":356.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":357.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, so starting off with items that we''ve completed.","index":50,"end_time":361.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":358.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the Aaron Fry episode is completed.","index":51,"end_time":364.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, I can send you the link in Slack if that''s easier.","index":52,"end_time":368.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":364.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Per Mike''s feedback, we did go through and review any mentions of PNC and Swivel Bank.","index":53,"end_time":375.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We only found one.","index":54,"end_time":376.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sent that screenshot to Mike.","index":55,"end_time":377.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He said that should be no problem, so we just kept it as is.","index":56,"end_time":379.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if there''s anything else that you need us to edit, just let us know.","index":57,"end_time":385.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":382.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Otherwise, we will go through our regular.","index":58,"end_time":386.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":385.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Syndication of adding this to the resources.","index":59,"end_time":388.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Section, putting this up on YouTube, Spotify, and Apple.","index":60,"end_time":392.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":61,"end_time":393.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Are we going to do that this week or next week?","index":62,"end_time":396.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We can do that this week if it''s approved.","index":63,"end_time":398.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that makes sense because I think this week is International Fraud Awareness Week, so that''d be great timing.","index":64,"end_time":404.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That would be.","index":65,"end_time":405.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know if Aaron has.","index":66,"end_time":406.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":405.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To review everything before we go live.","index":67,"end_time":409.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, as long as we''re happy that his ask of those particular companies have been removed.","index":68,"end_time":420.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We usually wouldn''t ask for permission to promote to post.","index":69,"end_time":423.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":70,"end_time":427.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just added that to the recap.","index":71,"end_time":429.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":427.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Message that I''ll send.","index":72,"end_time":430.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll have the link to all the resources.","index":73,"end_time":431.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":74,"end_time":434.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also updated the white paper per the feedback that we went through on our last call.","index":75,"end_time":439.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":434.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have that here as well.","index":76,"end_time":441.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys would like a markup.","index":77,"end_time":443.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":442.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Link, we can add that to markup as well.","index":78,"end_time":445.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But everything''s been updated in this PDF.","index":79,"end_time":449.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s where we made some updates to the 1234 with some icons and then breaking this out a little bit.","index":80,"end_time":468.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks a little bit cleaner.","index":81,"end_time":471.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":472.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now, I scrolled through that super fast.","index":83,"end_time":500.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anywhere you wanted to jump back to?","index":84,"end_time":502.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what page number it is, but it''s just after the graphic.","index":85,"end_time":509.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":515.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.4,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that looks good.","index":87,"end_time":532.129,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.089,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":88,"end_time":533.089,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.449,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":89,"end_time":534.609,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.049,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll do the same thing with this in our recap.","index":90,"end_time":537.569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.689,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":91,"end_time":549.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so for all approved there, just let us know.","index":92,"end_time":551.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":549.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll update the resources section on the website.","index":93,"end_time":553.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll create a new LinkedIn ad.","index":94,"end_time":555.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll just loop that in with the designs that we''re making to the rest of the PDF ads, Kate, that we talked about last week.","index":95,"end_time":561.939,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":555.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll update HubSpot workflows so.","index":96,"end_time":563.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.939,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That this has an email and then.","index":97,"end_time":565.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":563.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Goes into the regular nurture sequence.","index":98,"end_time":566.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":99,"end_time":568.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that all makes sense.","index":100,"end_time":569.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think, Kate, we do need to make sure that Michal has a chance to review before we commit to it.","index":101,"end_time":577.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":102,"end_time":578.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":578.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait for us to give you the green light on that column.","index":103,"end_time":582.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem at all.","index":104,"end_time":584.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also designed a rotating banner, so we have four to start.","index":105,"end_time":591.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":587.629,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll open this up so you can see these a little bit larger, but.","index":106,"end_time":594.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The things that we''re calling out are one for Scan flag, one for the new white paper, the AI versus fraud white paper, and then just the Win.","index":107,"end_time":601.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":594.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The war against fraud had trouble kind.","index":108,"end_time":604.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of figuring out an image for the base Win the war against fraud.","index":109,"end_time":607.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":604.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went with one of the examples from I think not the platform.","index":110,"end_time":612.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":608.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Page, but another page.","index":111,"end_time":614.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll see when I get there.","index":112,"end_time":616.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing I wanted to ask here, Kate, do you prefer having the logo in here on the phone?","index":113,"end_time":621.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":616.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I do.","index":114,"end_time":626.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s still the same comment of that is a WhatsApp screenshot rather than a screenshot of the app.","index":115,"end_time":632.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I think it makes sense in this limited context of having the logo there if it''s kind of like a standalone scroller or carousel.","index":116,"end_time":645.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Side threat question on these white papers.","index":117,"end_time":662.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Does HubSpot have any capability around doing delayed contact capture?","index":118,"end_time":673.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So kind of how?","index":119,"end_time":673.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, if you''re familiar with like Path Factory, you''ll get like the first page of an asset and then it''ll put a form up before you can carry through the rest of the asset.","index":120,"end_time":684.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Does HubSpot have anything that does that?","index":121,"end_time":686.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, I''d have to check on that.","index":122,"end_time":687.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":686.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we''ve set that up just more custom before where like the initial thing that they can get for free is the first page and then.","index":123,"end_time":694.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":687.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The form to download the rest.","index":124,"end_time":695.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d have to check on HubSpot''s capabilities there, though.","index":125,"end_time":699.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":697.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":126,"end_time":700.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Be good to know if that''s something that that is out there.","index":127,"end_time":704.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":705.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":129,"end_time":706.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":130,"end_time":710.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":131,"end_time":724.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then this is the graphic that I was talking about.","index":132,"end_time":727.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel like there''s something better for the UI or from the actual platform, but.","index":133,"end_time":733.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''S that many images that we have available.","index":134,"end_time":736.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we want to bias towards not actually showing the product.","index":135,"end_time":739.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I would.","index":136,"end_time":742.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I would strike that image.","index":137,"end_time":745.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":753.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m wondering if we just do a text based one.","index":139,"end_time":755.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":756.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":756.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just have no image on this one.","index":141,"end_time":758.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":756.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":758.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean, kind of like what it is today.","index":143,"end_time":760.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s no image.","index":144,"end_time":761.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":145,"end_time":761.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not.","index":146,"end_time":762.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Not saying that what it is today is good, but you know, there''s precedent for it.","index":147,"end_time":766.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, no problem.","index":148,"end_time":771.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our team is set to update this.","index":149,"end_time":774.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the test site so that you can interact with it before we roll it out to the live site.","index":150,"end_time":779.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":151,"end_time":781.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is it an issue that the two sites are out of sync or we.","index":152,"end_time":784.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would have to rebuild it into the production site?","index":153,"end_time":787.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":784.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the way I actually have that in our agenda today, we don''t have access to control the sync between the two environments.","index":154,"end_time":796.319,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have access to both environments.","index":155,"end_time":798.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.319,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Kate, I think you said you.","index":156,"end_time":799.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a ticket in to get that address.","index":157,"end_time":801.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, we do.","index":158,"end_time":802.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":804.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, we''ll build it in the test site, let you guys play around with it, and then if that''s all good, we''ll just rebuild it in the production site.","index":160,"end_time":810.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":804.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would love to just get to.","index":161,"end_time":811.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We make updates on tests and roll that live.","index":162,"end_time":814.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":812.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":815.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":816.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":817.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And what.","index":166,"end_time":818.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just humor me here for a second.","index":167,"end_time":821.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What would this be built in?","index":168,"end_time":825.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, are you just using.","index":169,"end_time":827.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are you using a plugin for this?","index":170,"end_time":831.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are you using default?","index":171,"end_time":833.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"To be honest, I''m not sure the specific way that our developers would build it.","index":172,"end_time":839.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":835.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assume they would probably build some.","index":173,"end_time":841.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":839.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Custom fields into a PHP file that would live on the homepage rather than a plugin, but I''ll ask them.","index":174,"end_time":850.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":175,"end_time":851.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we want to know because the site''s pretty bloated as it sits right now.","index":176,"end_time":855.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":856.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I just don''t want to introduce more bloat.","index":178,"end_time":859.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Something like this.","index":179,"end_time":862.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s pretty standard thing, so I''m sure there''s.","index":180,"end_time":866.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":181,"end_time":868.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":867.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We tend to lean away from plugins.","index":182,"end_time":870.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For that exact reason.","index":183,"end_time":871.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":184,"end_time":872.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":873.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Where are we going to do one with a video?","index":186,"end_time":876.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We could do one with the video.","index":187,"end_time":879.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we do have a.","index":188,"end_time":882.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s not particularly well liked, I don''t think.","index":189,"end_time":884.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But we do have a video from QT Connect last year.","index":190,"end_time":890.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right.","index":191,"end_time":891.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.87,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"This year and from June.","index":192,"end_time":893.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.63,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":894.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think that''s high enough quality for a homepage placement though.","index":194,"end_time":898.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"For the Win the war against fraud.","index":195,"end_time":902.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":900.749,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could do the just more general.","index":196,"end_time":904.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":902.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Threat mark overview video that we created.","index":197,"end_time":906.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you send me a link to that?","index":198,"end_time":917.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":918.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is on ChatPoint as well.","index":200,"end_time":923.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.4,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":201,"end_time":924.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That was the one we created.","index":202,"end_time":929.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s one version for Q2 and one that''s just more general.","index":203,"end_time":932.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":929.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that one.","index":204,"end_time":934.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":934.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You don''t have to send me that link.","index":206,"end_time":935.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I know what you''re talking about now.","index":207,"end_time":936.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I know.","index":208,"end_time":943.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m hesitant to do a video there because I don''t think we have the right video for there.","index":209,"end_time":949.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":210,"end_time":950.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because like, I want it to be similar quality to the Scan flag explainer.","index":211,"end_time":957.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":965.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not leaning towards that video on the homepage.","index":213,"end_time":979.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":214,"end_time":984.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How would you lock it up?","index":215,"end_time":986.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, is it like.","index":216,"end_time":986.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would you just do it as.","index":217,"end_time":987.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like.","index":218,"end_time":992.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How the video display.","index":219,"end_time":993.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":992.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":994.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like where that is.","index":221,"end_time":994.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":222,"end_time":995.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":995.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":995.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or would it be like full.","index":224,"end_time":997.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Full frame?","index":225,"end_time":998.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean, to have consistency with the other ones, I would lean towards just.","index":226,"end_time":1003,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":999.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Having it in this frame.","index":227,"end_time":1004.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have something else in mind.","index":228,"end_time":1010.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1008.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of more like this full section being a video.","index":229,"end_time":1012.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":1013.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Which I don''t.","index":231,"end_time":1014.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think I want to do.","index":232,"end_time":1015.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s too much.","index":233,"end_time":1017.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Too much change at once.","index":234,"end_time":1020.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I want to get the carousel in place first and just see.","index":235,"end_time":1026.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"See what that does.","index":236,"end_time":1028.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s just make this text and keep it simple.","index":237,"end_time":1030.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.25,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":238,"end_time":1032.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the website stuff.","index":239,"end_time":1038.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, I''d updated you in our call last week around the.","index":240,"end_time":1041.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The vulnerabilities and patches that we''re making.","index":241,"end_time":1044.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the scripts and everything have run through everything has been updated and is resolved.","index":242,"end_time":1048.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1044.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only remaining flags that are in there are false positives.","index":243,"end_time":1051.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ve updated this for Google and cookiebot using the dynamic parameters so.","index":244,"end_time":1057.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1052.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That this should be resolved moving forward as well.","index":245,"end_time":1059.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if there''s any other audits or anything coming up, obviously let us know.","index":246,"end_time":1063.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1059.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can always do a check or we can just set up like a.","index":247,"end_time":1066.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Monthly maintenance check on both environments.","index":248,"end_time":1069.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":1072.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.46,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":250,"end_time":1077.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1076.86,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is that meant to be, Alice?","index":251,"end_time":1079.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1078.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No, I can see that.","index":252,"end_time":1084.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can.","index":253,"end_time":1087.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See what you mean.","index":254,"end_time":1088.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1087.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":255,"end_time":1090.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For Q2.","index":256,"end_time":1092.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1091.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we actually are developing some ads that are more lead gen form focused rather than sending to the landing page.","index":257,"end_time":1099.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1093.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we can have just, you.","index":258,"end_time":1101.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, that auto filled form on LinkedIn and reduced and narrowed the list of people that we''re reaching out to.","index":259,"end_time":1108.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s very high intent.","index":260,"end_time":1109.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got that down to about 9,400.","index":261,"end_time":1111.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People so that we can get the.","index":262,"end_time":1113.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1111.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Most use out of the budget and.","index":263,"end_time":1115.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just, you know, reduce the barrier in the customer journey of going to a landing page, then filling out a form.","index":264,"end_time":1120.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1115.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Versus just being on LinkedIn and the form almost being filled out completely for you.","index":265,"end_time":1123.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":266,"end_time":1124.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that makes sense.","index":267,"end_time":1127.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And if I''m looking in LinkedIn, is that still.","index":268,"end_time":1133.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s two.","index":269,"end_time":1137.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s two campaigns with Q2.","index":270,"end_time":1143.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1141.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s the Q2 digital banking audience and the Q2.","index":271,"end_time":1146.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then there''s one that''s in draft.","index":272,"end_time":1148.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are you like one that''s live, one that''s draft.","index":273,"end_time":1152.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are you focusing on the one that''s in draft that will then replace the one that''s live?","index":274,"end_time":1156.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that the idea?","index":275,"end_time":1157.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Correct.","index":276,"end_time":1158.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":1159.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":278,"end_time":1161.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One of the things that I noticed in the live one was we were getting a lot of engagement from bank of America, which I don''t think they were in the, the company list.","index":279,"end_time":1175.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Maybe they were.","index":280,"end_time":1176.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":281,"end_time":1176.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They definitely don''t use Q2 and they''ve told us before to bugger off, so I put them in as a strict exclusion.","index":282,"end_time":1187.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.74,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":283,"end_time":1188.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just, we''ll just want to make sure that that carries into.","index":284,"end_time":1191.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If we''re going to switch into a new campaign.","index":285,"end_time":1193.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Carry into that.","index":286,"end_time":1196.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":287,"end_time":1197.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1205.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1205.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the campaign, for the like, audience list.","index":289,"end_time":1207.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1205.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we just selected the.","index":290,"end_time":1209.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List that you had created of companies in LinkedIn, so.","index":291,"end_time":1212.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll definitely carry that exclusion through.","index":292,"end_time":1215.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":1218.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Everything else looks about right.","index":294,"end_time":1219.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1218.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They look, they look like the companies I would expect.","index":295,"end_time":1222.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s a good thing.","index":296,"end_time":1223.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I agree that, that putting in some, some white papers to do, you know, conversion on LinkedIn is good because we just want to get them into the funnel and we can start emailing them and stuff like that from there.","index":297,"end_time":1236.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":298,"end_time":1237.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":299,"end_time":1238.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":300,"end_time":1240.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some other things we''re working on, we''re developing a report and budget recommendations for paid ads like we talked about.","index":301,"end_time":1245.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On Thursday or Wednesday.","index":302,"end_time":1247.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1245.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Update to the Scan Flag video or scanflag landing page.","index":303,"end_time":1252.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1248.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Adding a background to that video section.","index":304,"end_time":1254.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1252.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And a heading so that it stands out a little bit more.","index":305,"end_time":1257.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Updated ad creative for all of the.","index":306,"end_time":1259.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1258.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"PDF white paper ads that we have.","index":307,"end_time":1261.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Running on LinkedIn since we''ve seen a.","index":308,"end_time":1263.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1261.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Decrease in quantity of leads.","index":309,"end_time":1265.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Updating the scam flag ads just based on what we went through in our call with adding the logo and removing.","index":310,"end_time":1272.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1266.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the powered by threat mark and then also creating the rotating resources module on the Q2 landing page.","index":311,"end_time":1279.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other things.","index":312,"end_time":1286.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1285.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, did I cut you off, Greg?","index":313,"end_time":1288.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":314,"end_time":1289.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":315,"end_time":1289.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we shared the GA4 events that were set up.","index":316,"end_time":1292.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1290.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s very limited.","index":317,"end_time":1293.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1292.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s like four that are actually set up in Google Analytics.","index":318,"end_time":1296.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just wanted to know if you guys had like we want to track this button, we want to track all of these buttons.","index":319,"end_time":1301.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to track scroll on this page or every page, you know, what kind of events do you want us.","index":320,"end_time":1305.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1301.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To set up and we can get those built.","index":321,"end_time":1307.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, what''s your thought there?","index":322,"end_time":1311.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we should set up some basic ones around content.","index":323,"end_time":1317.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I also similarly tell you phrase it with the website.","index":324,"end_time":1325.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1321.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t particularly want to bloat GA4 in terms of the environment.","index":325,"end_time":1329.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1330.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"At the moment we don''t have, we have hardly any events.","index":327,"end_time":1342.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So why did you have a different thought?","index":328,"end_time":1350.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1342.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I mean I''ve often used events just in kind of the conversion world and so trying to keep them clean to conversion versus behavior.","index":329,"end_time":1365.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You could go either way.","index":330,"end_time":1370.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I just don''t.","index":331,"end_time":1372.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m skeptical that we''ve got enough people that actually have, that are accepting cookies and getting tracked to be able to have like meaningful data on that.","index":332,"end_time":1382.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1384.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1383.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I don''t know Colin, what do you typically see folks do?","index":334,"end_time":1393.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Well the last point that you made.","index":335,"end_time":1395.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1394.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is really what, what we were thinking as well.","index":336,"end_time":1398.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if it''s like purely US based.","index":337,"end_time":1401.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1398.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Traffic, let''s you know, get events.","index":338,"end_time":1403.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can, we can track everything as granular as possible.","index":339,"end_time":1405.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1403.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we have GDPR compliance and a.","index":340,"end_time":1409.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1407.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cookie banner that people have to agree.","index":341,"end_time":1411.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To, we''re going to have a mixed bag of data and we don''t want to make a decision based on it.","index":342,"end_time":1414.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s, it''s not accurate.","index":343,"end_time":1416.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":344,"end_time":1416.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1416.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we could do, I mean we have some conversion things that we''ve set up just for different ads that we''ve run in the past.","index":345,"end_time":1425.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1419.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we could also just similar to almost how we''re looking at the lead source and lead source specific have very.","index":346,"end_time":1432.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1427.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Basic buckets of activities that we look.","index":347,"end_time":1434.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At and just start very light on.","index":348,"end_time":1436.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1434.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The events that we''re tracking.","index":349,"end_time":1437.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1441.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So maybe things like click through on the homepage banner that we''re creating that would be good to understand.","index":351,"end_time":1450.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1441.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But even then like we''re gonna, it''s.","index":352,"end_time":1457.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s still gonna be.","index":353,"end_time":1457.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1457.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1458.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1457.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mixed bag gonna be X percent of total traffic and we don''t know what X is.","index":355,"end_time":1461.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1458.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":356,"end_time":1465.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stupid gdpr.","index":357,"end_time":1468.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I always made the argument that if you owned a physical store and someone came into the store, you had the right to look at them.","index":358,"end_time":1477.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So why is it not any different for a website?","index":359,"end_time":1481.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1479.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I have no idea.","index":360,"end_time":1485.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1483.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"California is trending very quickly in that direction.","index":361,"end_time":1487.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1485.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you and I have talked about.","index":362,"end_time":1488.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1487.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think by 2028 the US will.","index":363,"end_time":1490.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1488.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably be in a similar boat of compliance regulation.","index":364,"end_time":1492.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1490.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably, probably.","index":365,"end_time":1494.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anyway, so yeah, maybe we keep those really simple.","index":366,"end_time":1503.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re form conversions.","index":367,"end_time":1505.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1503.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So there''s like a conversion event and then there''s like a click through on the path to conversion.","index":368,"end_time":1514.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that way we can kind of look at okay, well how many people are landing on the conversion page versus actually converting on the conversion page.","index":369,"end_time":1524.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1515.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But even then I still don''t believe the data.","index":370,"end_time":1527.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, the path of conversion is definitely even tougher in that.","index":371,"end_time":1531.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1528.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, just.","index":372,"end_time":1533.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Depending on did they leave it open on their computer and things reset, did they come back to it later on?","index":373,"end_time":1539.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1533.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did someone send a slack message and they opened it up from there?","index":374,"end_time":1542.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1539.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a lot of things.","index":375,"end_time":1544.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1543.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we''re going to lose.","index":376,"end_time":1545.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1544.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does, does this get fixed with first party cookies if your web host is the same as your analytics provider?","index":377,"end_time":1551.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean I still think I would.","index":378,"end_time":1555.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1553.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have to check and get back to.","index":379,"end_time":1556.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1555.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You for a more concrete answer, but.","index":380,"end_time":1557.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1556.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would still think GDPR compliance is just going to throw a wrench in as much tracking.","index":381,"end_time":1563.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s specific to third party like first party cookies or forget cookies.","index":382,"end_time":1570.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just server log analytics that I think sits within the realm of possibility.","index":383,"end_time":1580.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The problem being that, you know, Google Analytics is not hosting our website and therefore we''re in a third party position.","index":384,"end_time":1588.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":385,"end_time":1591.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyway, yeah, I would have to check on that to have a better answer for you.","index":386,"end_time":1597.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1592.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1597.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1597.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then Kate, like we just talked about, you have the ticket in to get the website environments in sync.","index":388,"end_time":1603.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1599.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you could just let us know like when they plan on doing that.","index":389,"end_time":1606.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1603.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like if it was today and we''re going in to build the sliders.","index":390,"end_time":1610.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want anything to break.","index":391,"end_time":1612.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we, Greg and I were talking about this last week.","index":392,"end_time":1615.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.83,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The last time around when we tried to ask them to do it, there was a lot of pushback in terms of priorities and this not being one of them.","index":393,"end_time":1624.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And that was back in February.","index":394,"end_time":1626.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1625.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we''ve not had a staging environment anywhere near reflective of live since all production since February.","index":395,"end_time":1634.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.99,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":396,"end_time":1635.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think our approach is to say this needs to be done and if they can''t do it, our alternative is getting you access to do it yourself.","index":397,"end_time":1646.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1635.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So.","index":398,"end_time":1647.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1646.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":399,"end_time":1647.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re.","index":400,"end_time":1648.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re kind of hoping they push back so that way we can be like, great.","index":401,"end_time":1652.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just let us handle it.","index":402,"end_time":1654.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1652.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not that big of a deal.","index":403,"end_time":1658.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s always funny, but it''s like, they''d also be the first person to, like.","index":404,"end_time":1661,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1658.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Come, you know, take a shot at.","index":405,"end_time":1663.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin because something went bad on the website.","index":406,"end_time":1665.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1668.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, I was slacking you Friday.","index":408,"end_time":1670.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1669.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got the spacing and padding and everything updated on the November newsletter.","index":409,"end_time":1674.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1670.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to review that?","index":410,"end_time":1676.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1675.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good.","index":411,"end_time":1677.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1677.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":412,"end_time":1679.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then have you reviewed the updated buckets with Greg?","index":413,"end_time":1684.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1679.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg.","index":414,"end_time":1685.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is what we established in our call.","index":415,"end_time":1687.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1685.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this is just.","index":416,"end_time":1687.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1687.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I expanded it, essentially.","index":417,"end_time":1689.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just run.","index":418,"end_time":1690.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We got time, right?","index":419,"end_time":1691.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s just run through them real quick.","index":420,"end_time":1693.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So paid.","index":421,"end_time":1696.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":422,"end_time":1699.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s change FTE White.","index":423,"end_time":1702.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1700.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"White paper.","index":424,"end_time":1703.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just a fraud disruption.","index":425,"end_time":1704.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"White paper.","index":426,"end_time":1705.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":427,"end_time":1715.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":428,"end_time":1718.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, same.","index":429,"end_time":1726.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":430,"end_time":1733.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1732.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":431,"end_time":1737.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1736.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1746.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The.","index":433,"end_time":1750.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"On the organic search, do we get.","index":434,"end_time":1757.129,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Do we know if it''s actually chat GPT or is it.","index":435,"end_time":1760.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1757.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it will typically have UTM source equals chat GPT.","index":436,"end_time":1764.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1760.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If someone clicks directly from chat GPTs.","index":437,"end_time":1767.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1764.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1767.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Prompting.","index":439,"end_time":1768.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you''re.","index":440,"end_time":1770.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1769.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re basically just writing that stuff off of the UTM variable.","index":441,"end_time":1773.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that list is not enumerated.","index":442,"end_time":1775.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s.","index":443,"end_time":1776.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":444,"end_time":1776.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It is what it is, basically.","index":445,"end_time":1778.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":1778.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is why that''s a text field.","index":447,"end_time":1780.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that all looks good.","index":448,"end_time":1781.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so what''s our migration plan on that then?","index":449,"end_time":1784.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we just need the values in Salesforce to match.","index":450,"end_time":1789.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1785.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can build these in HubSpot.","index":451,"end_time":1790.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1789.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can check if we still have permission to create these values in Salesforce.","index":452,"end_time":1794.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1790.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lead source specific is a text field, so you don''t have to have.","index":453,"end_time":1798.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so we don''t even need the.","index":454,"end_time":1800.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1799.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Options, which is the point.","index":455,"end_time":1801.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1800.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that way we have flexibility around that.","index":456,"end_time":1805.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I can change the lead source field to that list right there.","index":457,"end_time":1810.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And we can go from that, I think.","index":458,"end_time":1817.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How.","index":459,"end_time":1820.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How are you thinking about building the population of that stuff in HubSpot?","index":460,"end_time":1827.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So in HubSpot, like for example, LinkedIn, these are directly connected to the form.","index":461,"end_time":1834.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1829.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll just say like, when this person, when the form is submitted, attach like this to that property.","index":462,"end_time":1839.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1834.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those are pretty easy for the paid side of things.","index":463,"end_time":1843.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1840.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Contact form, very similar.","index":464,"end_time":1845.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1843.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, we basically could just set up.","index":465,"end_time":1847.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1845.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A workflow that says, you know, if.","index":466,"end_time":1849.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1847.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They submitted here, make this, you know, the lead source and then Based on.","index":467,"end_time":1853.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1849.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whatever page they submitted.","index":468,"end_time":1854.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Make that the lead source specific.","index":469,"end_time":1856.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":470,"end_time":1857.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1856.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":471,"end_time":1858.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And we can consolidate that into a single workflow.","index":472,"end_time":1861.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, we should be able to.","index":473,"end_time":1863.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1862.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I''m just.","index":474,"end_time":1865.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''ll just be an if then branch, basically.","index":475,"end_time":1867.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":476,"end_time":1868.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I just.","index":477,"end_time":1869.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Similar to plugin bloat, I don''t want workflow bloat flows just blooming.","index":478,"end_time":1876.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1869.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":479,"end_time":1877.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1876.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think there was like 30 something.","index":480,"end_time":1879.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1877.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In there when we took over from Hyperscale.","index":481,"end_time":1881.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1879.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think some of those we can probably.","index":482,"end_time":1884.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1881.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Some.","index":483,"end_time":1885.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Some of them are active and they''re working and all that good stuff.","index":484,"end_time":1888.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think there''s some backfill stuff in there that can probably get sectioned out at some point.","index":485,"end_time":1894.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think we don''t need to do that now.","index":486,"end_time":1896.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":487,"end_time":1897.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1896.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":488,"end_time":1898.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so that list looks good.","index":489,"end_time":1899.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think you probably need to have those options available in Salesforce.","index":490,"end_time":1908.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Well, if this is a text field.","index":491,"end_time":1911.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1909.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just the lead source ones.","index":492,"end_time":1913.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1911.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just the lead.","index":493,"end_time":1913.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1913.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":494,"end_time":1913.859,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1913.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we just need these as options in Salesforce.","index":495,"end_time":1916.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1913.859,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if it''s a text field, then we''re totally fine on specific.","index":496,"end_time":1919.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a text field, which is the goal there.","index":497,"end_time":1922.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1919.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":498,"end_time":1923.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":499,"end_time":1923.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1923.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":500,"end_time":1923.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Can you just re.","index":501,"end_time":1926.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Resurface that link in the Slack thread and I''ll try to get those Salesforce today.","index":502,"end_time":1931.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1927.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And do you guys still need access to our Salesforce instance?","index":503,"end_time":1943.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''d have to just check.","index":504,"end_time":1946.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1945.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think probably not at this point.","index":505,"end_time":1950.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1946.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would just.","index":506,"end_time":1951.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1950.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to check all the integrations that we have set up between like ads and things like that.","index":507,"end_time":1954.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1951.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But everything should be flowing just through HubSpot first.","index":508,"end_time":1957.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1954.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":509,"end_time":1957.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If you.","index":510,"end_time":1958.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If you don''t mind doing a quick look and letting us know if we can deprecate your Salesforce access.","index":511,"end_time":1969.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1958.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think that would be helpful.","index":512,"end_time":1970.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ve ridiculously over provisioned and I''m trying to do a user swap and I. I need to kind of trim it back to a safe.","index":513,"end_time":1983.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1972.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, I mean no disrespect, like there''s partners from all over the place that have sysadmin level access.","index":514,"end_time":1990.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m just like, what are you guys doing?","index":515,"end_time":1991.519,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so I want to trim that down and.","index":516,"end_time":1995.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1991.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think you guys are probably out of the Salesforce business, which is a good thing.","index":517,"end_time":2002.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":518,"end_time":2003.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":519,"end_time":2005.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2005.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check through and see if we.","index":520,"end_time":2007.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2005.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have anything set up there for integrations.","index":521,"end_time":2010.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Kate, the last thing was you mentioned like newsletter and bulletin getting a design package similar to the Behind.","index":522,"end_time":2017.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2010.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enemy Lines and you wanted to share some spec for that.","index":523,"end_time":2020.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you want to take any time.","index":524,"end_time":2020.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2020.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To chat through that?","index":525,"end_time":2021.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2020.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably, yeah.","index":526,"end_time":2029.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2027.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":527,"end_time":2030.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2029.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, not today though.","index":528,"end_time":2032.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":529,"end_time":2036.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2033.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well then we are on standby.","index":530,"end_time":2038.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2036.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For whatever you need there.","index":531,"end_time":2040.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2039.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re looking at doing the November 1st tomorrow and then being more consistent with it going forward.","index":532,"end_time":2046.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2041.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But tomorrow is our test, so I might be asking for some help in terms of setting up the list or how we go about setting up a list of people we regularly reach out to.","index":533,"end_time":2058.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2047.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yep, sounds like a plan.","index":534,"end_time":2061.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2058.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Kate, I also liked you about this.","index":535,"end_time":2064.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2062.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We set up the HubSpot shared deal, Greg, just based on your like, hey, we''re probably looking to upgrade.","index":536,"end_time":2069.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2064.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I talked to our rep.","index":537,"end_time":2070.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2069.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s no rush on anything from your guys end.","index":538,"end_time":2072.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2070.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just you let me know, I''ll update our HubSpot rep and we can get.","index":539,"end_time":2075.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2072.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The deal room situated to work in your favor for.","index":540,"end_time":2077.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2075.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you guys were probably leaning.","index":541,"end_time":2079.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Towards going to enterprise on the content side, but you know, whatever we figured out with the budget.","index":542,"end_time":2083.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2079.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s probably what the answer is.","index":543,"end_time":2088.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2084.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But we got to figure out the budget side of it.","index":544,"end_time":2090.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2088.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So did I mention that one of the things that we''re thinking about from that perspective is migrating over the Banking Fraud Summit website?","index":545,"end_time":2102.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2091.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":546,"end_time":2104.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To be a HubSpot site because like to me that''s a really.","index":547,"end_time":2108.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2104.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s, it''s like a five page site.","index":548,"end_time":2110.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2108.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like not that big of a deal and it''d be a really great way to see what it''s like to host a site on HubSpot.","index":549,"end_time":2121.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2110.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And if we don''t like it then we''d move it over to webflow.","index":550,"end_time":2125.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2122.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And if we don''t like it then we''d move it back to WordPress.","index":551,"end_time":2127.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2125.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But like basically it''s a super low risk way to make sure that we dial into a platform that is set up for us for the future basically.","index":552,"end_time":2136.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2127.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":553,"end_time":2137.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2136.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that sounds great.","index":554,"end_time":2139.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2138.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which of course I think would.","index":555,"end_time":2141.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2139.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would predicate enterprise because I think to.","index":556,"end_time":2145.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2141.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Have multiple domains and brands.","index":557,"end_time":2146.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2145.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, so.","index":558,"end_time":2148.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2146.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''s that the other side of it too.","index":559,"end_time":2151.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2149.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just, just in terms of where my thinking is, there''s a ton of bloat in the sales tech stack and there may be a world because I don''t, I don''t.","index":560,"end_time":2167.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2151.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, you might have a read into this.","index":561,"end_time":2169.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2167.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like I don''t think outreach is super well loved.","index":562,"end_time":2172.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, it was brought in by a sales leader from quite a while ago and was never implemented particularly well.","index":563,"end_time":2188.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2177.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And I just don''t think anyone has any particular preference for it.","index":564,"end_time":2194.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2189.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, and it''s really expensive, so there might be a world too where we Think about, well, can we bring our salespeople in to do their prospecting out of HubSpot?","index":565,"end_time":2208.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They still would manage deals in Salesforce but kind of the pre deal prospecting might make more sense in HubSpot.","index":566,"end_time":2217.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2208.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We get significantly more visibility into what they''re doing by having it kind of fully integrated in there.","index":567,"end_time":2225.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2217.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":568,"end_time":2225.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2225.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, and that was the original.","index":569,"end_time":2228.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2227,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had been recommending HubSpot and then.","index":570,"end_time":2233.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2231,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was kind of like a.","index":571,"end_time":2234.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2233.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A hard no.","index":572,"end_time":2235.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2235.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so we built outreach and.","index":573,"end_time":2238.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2235.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Built all the integrations between Salesforce and Outreach so that we could have things tracked there.","index":574,"end_time":2241.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2238.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I totally agree.","index":575,"end_time":2242.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2241.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think having marketing and sales operating.","index":576,"end_time":2244.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2242.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out of the same system is just a benefit to both sides.","index":577,"end_time":2247.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2245.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":578,"end_time":2248.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2248.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":579,"end_time":2249.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2249.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like I, I don''t think we would move deal pursuit into HubSpot.","index":580,"end_time":2255.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2250.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we would more like first steps.","index":581,"end_time":2258.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2255.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s more like kind of the prospecting journey sits in HubSpot and then the sales journey sits in Salesforce.","index":582,"end_time":2266.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2258.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because like from a, just again speaking plainly from an acquisition perspective, it''s really, really, really hard to do the integration if your acquirer is running Salesforce and you''re running HubSpot from a deal pursuit side.","index":583,"end_time":2281.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2267.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''m a forward thinking individual.","index":584,"end_time":2287.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2283.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":585,"end_time":2290.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2288.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, okay, cool.","index":586,"end_time":2295.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2292.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":587,"end_time":2295.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2295.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":588,"end_time":2297.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2296.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The only other thing I wanted to cover is that I am going on vacation starting this Thursday and I''m out all of next week as well.","index":589,"end_time":2306.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2298.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to see what you.","index":590,"end_time":2309.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2308.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys wanted to do with our Wednesday call next week.","index":591,"end_time":2312.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2309.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina''s, you know, happy to jump in and run it or I don''t know.","index":592,"end_time":2318.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2314.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys are doing any sort of holiday.","index":593,"end_time":2320.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2318.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more obviously a United States holiday, but.","index":594,"end_time":2322.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2320.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":595,"end_time":2325.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2324.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, what do you want to do?","index":596,"end_time":2327.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2326.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we''re good to, I think we''re good to skip next week''s.","index":597,"end_time":2337.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2332.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":598,"end_time":2338.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2338.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":599,"end_time":2339.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2339.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So maybe what we do, Nina, is we just take it asynchronously on Slack and just if there''s things that we need to go through, do it from there.","index":600,"end_time":2349.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2339.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And if for some reason we need to have a conversation, we can just schedule a time.","index":601,"end_time":2352.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2349.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":602,"end_time":2354.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2353.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Does that work?","index":603,"end_time":2355.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2354.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":604,"end_time":2356.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2355.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":605,"end_time":2357.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2356.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":606,"end_time":2358.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2357.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so other than that, that''s everything that we had in our agenda.","index":607,"end_time":2362.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To go through today.","index":608,"end_time":2362.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2362.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":609,"end_time":2364.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2363.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anything else from your guys end?","index":610,"end_time":2366.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2365.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just some of the outreach point, I think.","index":611,"end_time":2369.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2367.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I was just looking.","index":612,"end_time":2370.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2369.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You guys still have a user admin user for outreach.","index":613,"end_time":2379.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2372.05,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do you need that?","index":614,"end_time":2380.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2379.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No, I mean that was.","index":615,"end_time":2382.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2381.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We basically got to a standstill, if you remember, of like we built it.","index":616,"end_time":2387.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2383.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t Remember, I think Mark and.","index":617,"end_time":2390.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2388.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A few other of the sales leaders.","index":618,"end_time":2393.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2391.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were like, cool, now we''re going to like get to know this thing and then roll it out to the team.","index":619,"end_time":2397.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2393.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was like, great, let me know.","index":620,"end_time":2399.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2397.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll build some documentation.","index":621,"end_time":2400.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2399.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After you guys do that, we''ll put in Threatmark branding.","index":622,"end_time":2403.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2400.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll be.","index":623,"end_time":2403.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2403.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is how you use outreach.","index":624,"end_time":2404.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2403.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been like seven months.","index":625,"end_time":2406,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2404.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Special, huh?","index":626,"end_time":2409.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We call that a threat, Mark.","index":627,"end_time":2410.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2409.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Special.","index":628,"end_time":2411.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2410.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":629,"end_time":2414.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2414.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the last I''ve heard of it, but yeah, I imagine we do not.","index":630,"end_time":2417.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2414.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we haven''t touched outreach.","index":631,"end_time":2418.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2417.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":632,"end_time":2419.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2419.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We probably don''t need to spend 150 bucks a month for y'' all to have access to it.","index":633,"end_time":2424.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2420.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":634,"end_time":2425.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2424.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s fair.","index":635,"end_time":2426.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2425.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With, with the most respect possible.","index":636,"end_time":2429.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2427.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The deep provision, those users.","index":637,"end_time":2431.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2429.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gregor, you''re totally fine.","index":638,"end_time":2433.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2431.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":639,"end_time":2434.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2433.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kick us out of there.","index":640,"end_time":2435.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2434.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Jeez.","index":641,"end_time":2436.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Geez.","index":642,"end_time":2436.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Geez.","index":643,"end_time":2436.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s the, the thing that just gets my blood boiling is when I see Gmail addresses and Salesforce with super admin access.","index":644,"end_time":2443.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2437.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m like, oh my God.","index":645,"end_time":2446.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2443.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So, okay, I think that all sounds like a good plan.","index":646,"end_time":2454.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2449.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So Colin, a couple things and Nina, just, just for awareness for both of you that we have kind of rolling around in our heads right now.","index":647,"end_time":2465.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2457.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One, we''re trying to establish, actually Zero, we hired a new marketer who''s starting tomorrow.","index":648,"end_time":2473.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2466.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re very, very excited to have her join.","index":649,"end_time":2476.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2474.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"She''s based out of the uk.","index":650,"end_time":2478.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2477.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Her name''s Julia and she''s going to be helping us with many things.","index":651,"end_time":2484.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2478.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But early on with event sponsorship, execution and account based, go to market.","index":652,"end_time":2492.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2484.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll see how that shakes out.","index":653,"end_time":2496.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2494.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s all real mushy.","index":654,"end_time":2498.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2497.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re all just going to do great work together.","index":655,"end_time":2501.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2499.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s, that''s the plan.","index":656,"end_time":2502.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2501.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s thing number Zero.","index":657,"end_time":2506.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2504.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So she''ll join us probably, let''s say the first week of December when we''re all kind of back, back at it.","index":658,"end_time":2515.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2506.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Number, number, real.","index":659,"end_time":2517.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2516.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Number one, we''re working on pulling together a full sponsorship calendar for next year so that way we''re not scrambling on this stuff like we were with this last one.","index":660,"end_time":2529.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I want to have that locked in in the next couple of weeks so we can start doing work backs on that.","index":661,"end_time":2540.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2531.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Julio, we''ll put together what that looks like so she''ll kind of make sure that we stay on target for it.","index":662,"end_time":2546.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2540.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I think that''ll make that process a lot smoother for us.","index":663,"end_time":2549.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2546.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Number two, we are working through establishing a formal gifting and swag program, most likely using Sandoso as a provider there for swag on demand as well as gifting, et cetera.","index":664,"end_time":2573.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2550.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''ll probably need some assistance in some of the swag space and things like that.","index":665,"end_time":2583.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2574.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We also want to introduce some direct mail into there and they bought postal couple I think it was postal a couple months ago.","index":666,"end_time":2593.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2583.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so they''re, they''re kind of growing out their direct mail program as well.","index":667,"end_time":2597.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2593.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":668,"end_time":2598.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2597.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s on the radar.","index":669,"end_time":2600.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2599.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then the last thing, we are starting to get a lot better intelligence around what our serviceable market looks like.","index":670,"end_time":2612.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2600.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So accounts by region and we will eventually be wanting to establish those as so one mirror territories and HubSpot two, create target account lists and then three, thinking through a much more account based go to market effort surrounding from.","index":671,"end_time":2639.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2613.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"From all different angles.","index":672,"end_time":2640.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2639.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''m sure there''ll be conversations around that both from a strategy and an execution perspective as we, as we get closer to it.","index":673,"end_time":2650.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2641.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, but account personalized, you know, ads, landing pages, all the, the whole nine that we can run there.","index":674,"end_time":2655.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2650.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Email sequences.","index":675,"end_time":2656.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2655.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":676,"end_time":2657.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2656.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that''s exciting.","index":677,"end_time":2658.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2657.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s, that''s kind of a bunch of the stuff that''s going on at the moment.","index":678,"end_time":2664.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2659.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":679,"end_time":2665.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2664.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":680,"end_time":2667.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2666.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":681,"end_time":2668.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2667.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well I will share the the list as I do after these meetings.","index":682,"end_time":2673.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2668.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Kate, included in there is the link to the Aaron Fry episode and.","index":683,"end_time":2677.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2673.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The updated white paper.","index":684,"end_time":2678.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2677.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Greg as well, the lead source.","index":685,"end_time":2680.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2678.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List that we just went through.","index":686,"end_time":2682.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2680.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":687,"end_time":2682.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2682.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":688,"end_time":2684.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2684.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, well if anything else pops up, please let me know.","index":689,"end_time":2687.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2684.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll be a little slow to respond while I''m out.","index":690,"end_time":2689.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2687.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But not completely ghosted.","index":691,"end_time":2690.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2689.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":692,"end_time":2693.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2693.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very.","index":693,"end_time":2695.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2694.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Much for your time.","index":694,"end_time":2696.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2695.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you have a great rest of your day.","index":695,"end_time":2697.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2696.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks both.","index":696,"end_time":2698.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2697.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":697,"end_time":2700.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2699.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Bye.","index":698,"end_time":2700.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2700.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"}],"dateString":"2025-11-17T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9W7MRAEADEVK4ZW1QJ8A5MP","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed completion and compliance checks for Aaron Fry episode; assets will publish during Fraud Awareness Week.","Updated white paper per feedback; integrated into site updates, LinkedIn ads, and email workflows.","Aligned marketing tech stack transition plans, including potential Outreach deprecation and HubSpot upgrades.","Outlined new lead source tracking logic in HubSpot and Salesforce with workflow consolidation.","Planned Q1 initiatives: sponsorship calendar, account-based GTM strategy, and formal swag/gifting program."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Putting in some white papers to do conversion on LinkedIn is good.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"Everything has been updated and is resolved; only false positives remain.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Trying to trim it back to a safe... there''s partners with sysadmin access.","speaker":"Greg Smith"}],"topics":["delivery","tracking","marketing","website","tech_stack"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-21T22:17:04Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Content and Campaign Execution**\n\nMarketing content updates and campaign adjustments are aligned with current events and refined targeting to improve lead quality.\n\n- **The Aaron Fry episode is finalized and pending syndication across YouTube, Spotify, and Apple this week to align with International Fraud Awareness Week**, contingent on Michal’s final review and approval (06:10)  \n    - Only one mention of **PNC and Swivel Bank** was flagged and cleared per Mike’s feedback  \n    - Kate confirmed no further permission is needed to promote once edits are approved  \n    - The episode link and related resources will be shared via Slack recap for quick access  \n    - This timing leverages industry awareness week to maximize audience engagement\n\n- **Updated white paper PDFs incorporating iconography and cleaner layout were delivered and are ready for website resource updates and LinkedIn ad integration** (07:06)  \n    - Ads will be refreshed to fit the new white paper design and integrated into existing PDF ad campaigns  \n    - HubSpot workflows will be updated to include email sequences tied to these resources for continuous nurture  \n    - Rotating banner ads featuring Scan Flag, the AI vs Fraud white paper, and “Win the War Against Fraud” messaging are in design review  \n\n- **LinkedIn lead gen ads targeting a refined audience of approximately 9,400 high-intent prospects are being developed to reduce funnel friction** (18:03)  \n    - Auto-filled forms on LinkedIn will replace landing page clicks to improve conversion rates  \n    - Campaign exclusions for uninterested companies like Bank of America are carried forward to prevent wasted spend  \n    - The new campaign in draft is planned to replace the existing live campaign for better efficiency  \n    - Greg emphasized the importance of funneling leads into nurture sequences after initial LinkedIn engagement  \n\n## **Website and Technical Infrastructure**\n\nWebsite updates focus on cleaning the platform, improving user experience, and resolving security vulnerabilities with an emphasis on sustainable infrastructure management.\n\n- **Security vulnerabilities have been fully addressed, with all scripts updated and false positives resolved on both Google and Cookiebot platforms** (17:11)  \n    - Colin proposed establishing monthly maintenance checks to prevent future issues  \n    - Dynamic parameters were implemented to ensure ongoing compliance with cookie policies\n\n- **A rotating banner module is being built on the test site to allow interactive review before production deployment, with a rebuild needed on the live site due to unsynced environments** (13:00)  \n    - Colin explained the site does not support direct sync between test and production environments, requiring manual rebuilds  \n    - Kate confirmed a pending ticket to synchronize environments has faced pushback since February, with escalation planned to get developer access if necessary  \n    - Greg expressed concern about adding bloat and confirmed preference for custom PHP fields over plugins  \n\n- **Plans for website event tracking in GA4 will focus on minimal, high-value events like form conversions and homepage banner clicks to avoid bloating analytics with unreliable GDPR-compliant data** (21:29)  \n    - Greg and Kate agreed on the challenge of gathering meaningful data due to cookie consent variability  \n    - Colin will keep tracking lightweight and US-focused to maintain usable insights without overcomplication  \n    - Discussions about first-party cookies and server log analytics will be followed up for potential improvements  \n\n## **CRM and Sales Technology Optimization**\n\nCRM workflows and sales tech stack rationalization aim to improve lead source tracking and reduce system bloat while preparing for future platform upgrades.\n\n- **Lead source fields are being standardized between HubSpot and Salesforce with a flexible text field approach to allow easy population and future scalability** (29:45)  \n    - Colin detailed workflows that auto-assign lead sources based on form submissions and page interactions  \n    - Greg emphasized avoiding workflow complexity growth while ensuring accuracy  \n    - Colin to confirm HubSpot permissions and Salesforce field availability for smooth integration  \n\n- **Salesforce user access is being audited to reduce excessive permissions, with Colin tasked to identify whether current integrations require continued Salesforce access** (32:25)  \n    - Greg highlighted security concerns with overprovisioned admin rights linked to external users  \n    - Potential deprovisioning will streamline partner access and reduce risks  \n\n- **The Outreach sales engagement tool is considered redundant and underused, with plans to decommission user licenses immediately to cut costs** (39:27)  \n    - Colin and Greg agreed Outreach was never fully adopted, and its integration complexity outweighed benefits  \n    - Cost savings from eliminating Outreach user licenses will be reinvested in HubSpot-centered prospecting tools  \n    - Future sales prospecting to be managed in HubSpot while deal management remains in Salesforce for acquisition compatibility  \n\n## **Strategic Growth and GTM Planning**\n\nThe team is laying groundwork for structured sponsorship, gifting, and account-based marketing to scale engagement and operational efficiency in 2024.\n\n- **A new UK-based marketer, Julia, will start in early December to support event sponsorship execution and account-based go-to-market strategies** (42:00)  \n    - Greg emphasized the importance of locking in a full-year sponsorship calendar within weeks to avoid last-minute scrambles  \n    - Julia will oversee timeline adherence and coordination for sponsorship activities  \n    - This hire is expected to bring clarity and consistency to marketing event planning\n\n- **A formal gifting and swag program is under development with Sandosso to include swag, gifting, and direct mail, leveraging recent acquisitions like Postal to expand direct mail capabilities** (42:26)  \n    - Greg anticipates marketing support will be needed to manage this program’s rollout and vendor coordination  \n    - The program aims to enhance brand engagement through personalized outreach beyond digital channels  \n\n- **Improved market intelligence on serviceable accounts by region will drive the creation of mirrored territories in HubSpot, target account lists, and comprehensive account-based marketing efforts** (43:17)  \n    - Account personalization will extend to ads, landing pages, and email sequences for more relevant customer journeys  \n    - Greg foresees ongoing strategy and execution discussions as the team builds out this multi-channel approach  \n    - This aligns with a broader shift toward precision marketing and sales alignment  \n\n## **Team Coordination and Operational Continuity**\n\nTeam availability and meeting cadence adjustments ensure smooth collaboration during Colin’s upcoming absence.\n\n- **Colin will be on vacation starting Thursday through next week, leading to a pause of the usual Wednesday calls, with asynchronous Slack updates planned** (38:18)  \n    - Nina will cover communications and meeting facilitation during this period as needed  \n    - Greg and Kate agreed to handle questions via Slack unless critical discussions require live meetings  \n    - This approach aims to maintain momentum without overburdening team members during holidays  \n\n- **Newsletter and bulletin design updates are scheduled for November 1st, marking a test for more consistent future communications** (34:01)  \n    - Kate may request help with list setup and distribution workflows to ensure smooth execution  \n    - This initiative supports ongoing engagement with the audience through regular, branded content  \n\n- **Colin will share detailed recap links for the Aaron Fry episode, updated white paper, and lead source lists post-meeting to keep all parties aligned** (44:27)  \n    - The recap will enable quick reference and facilitate next steps in content publishing and CRM updates  \n    - Colin’s response times will be slower during vacation, but he remains available for critical needs  ","outline":null,"keywords":["White paper","HubSpot","Lead source","Website sync","LinkedIn campaigns","Outreach decommission"],"overview":"- **Aaron Fry Episode Launch:** Finalized and ready for syndication this week for International Fraud Awareness Week to boost engagement.  \n- **White Paper Updates:** New PDFs ready for website and LinkedIn ads, enhancing design and integration for lead nurturing.  \n- **LinkedIn Ads Targeting:** Developing lead gen ads for 9,400 high-intent prospects, improving conversion rates with auto-filled forms.  \n- **Website Security and Updates:** All vulnerabilities fixed; monthly maintenance proposed to ensure ongoing compliance and performance.  \n- **Salesforce Access Audit:** Streamlining user permissions to enhance security and reduce risks associated with overprovisioned access.  \n- **New UK Marketer Hire:** Starts December to oversee sponsorship and account-based marketing, aiming for improved event coordination.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend Aaron Fry episode link to Kate and include in recap message with all resource links (05:58)\nAdd updated white paper and podcast links to recap Slack message (07:42)\nCoordinate website rotating banner updates on test site and await final sign-off before production deployment (12:44)\nVerify HubSpot and Salesforce integration for lead source field population and workflow setup (29:45)\nReview GA4 event tracking capabilities and advise on compliance and tracking options (23:00)\nCheck for integrations requiring Outreach access and recommend removing ThreatMark’s Outreach user admin account (40:02)\nShare lead source list and related details in Slack with Greg and Kate after meeting (44:27)\nMonitor website environment sync ticket and coordinate timing to avoid update conflicts (26:37)\nProvide video links and app UI image options for homepage banner consideration (15:00)\nFollow up on HubSpot deal room set up regarding possible enterprise upgrade pending budget approval (34:10)\nSupport November newsletter testing and future design package needs when requested (33:50)\nAfter collaboration, verify whether Salesforce access is still needed and counsel on user reduction (32:25)\nManage asynchronous communication during upcoming vacation period (38:44)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nEnsure Michal reviews and approves white paper and campaign materials before launch (09:38)\nProvide Salesforce permission updates as lead source options are configured (32:00)\nReview and reduce user access in Salesforce, including Outreach users (39:00)\nSchedule and advise on migrating Banking Fraud Summit website to HubSpot; confirm enterprise licensing requirement (35:00)\nCollaborate with Kate to finalize lead source and marketing campaign lists for HubSpot integration (29:05)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview Aaron Fry podcast and white paper for timely promotion during International Fraud Awareness Week (06:32)\nCommunicate plans and schedules regarding website environment sync and advocate access rights if remediation delayed (26:50)\nCoordinate newsletter launch on November 1st, including list setup and audience targeting (34:10)\nProvide design specs and timing for newsletter and bulletin design package after testing phase (33:51)\nNotify Colin and Greg of new marketer onboarding timeline and event sponsorship calendar progress (42:30)\nConfirm last-minute decisions on rotating banner logo inclusion and image preferences (10:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3f527a93-e6d9-4535-a4b1-795659d75605","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
