    1107,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88046600611?pwd=5o555CNd3jppz39fBqq2aKtgUYF0MV.1',
    '{"id":"01KA24FCC2Y4YYD1S75RCYWXGT","title":"NEACH // New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Hosting Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to postpone launching a new podcast for Alyssa in 2025 and instead have her take over one of Joe’s two monthly episodes, aiming for a full independent show launch in 2027 (09:29).\n\n- **The 2025 budget did not approve a new show, so Alyssa will host one episode per month under Wrestling Payments** to build recognition gradually.  \n- Meg explained that Wrestling Payments has a **small but loyal audience of about 50 members**, making a full new show risky due to starting from zero.  \n- Baylee recommended launching Alyssa’s own show for clearer branding and audience targeting, as Joe’s audience is very attached to him personally.  \n- The team agreed to cross-promote both shows via playlists and social channels to maintain audience flow and brand clarity.\n\n## **Content Performance and Audience Insights**\n\nPodcast and social content performance is stable but showing early signs of decline linked to reduced posting frequency, with YouTube driving most traffic through search and external embeds rather than subscribers (06:15).\n\n- The channel recorded **194 downloads in the last 28 days**, but overall performance dipped, likely from fewer new videos posted.  \n- Baylee noted most traffic comes from **YouTube search or external embeds**, indicating limited subscriber engagement.  \n- Meg shared that Joe’s short videos outperform full-length content, sometimes gaining up to **1,000 views**, while full videos average around **20 views**.  \n- Alyssa’s content doubled typical views, mainly driven by guests’ networks and LinkedIn promotions, suggesting different audience dynamics.\n\n## **Budget and Resource Allocation for Podcast Expansion**\n\nThe team will revisit budget options and point reconciliations to support either catching up on current services or expanding to a new show in 2026, with Justin handling financial discussions (10:44).\n\n- Meg requested clarity on the **cost or points needed to resume posting** or start new content, noting the account is currently over by **more than 100 points**.  \n- Baylee committed to consulting Justin to provide financial options and best practices for launching Alyssa’s show independently or continuing under Wrestling Payments.  \n- Meg emphasized Alyssa already has **six potential guest contacts** lined up, highlighting the urgency of resolving budget and resource planning.  \n- The team agreed to explore reallocating promotional efforts, possibly moving Alyssa’s content away from the Wrestling Payments LinkedIn page to the broader niche LinkedIn page.\n\n## **Operational and Process Updates**\n\nThe team identified a one-time submission issue with the podcast episode form, likely user error, and reinforced ongoing monitoring to avoid content delays (05:04).\n\n- Joe may have missed submitting one episode, causing a one-week delay, but the form tested fine on Baylee’s end.  \n- Meg offered to test the submission process on her side to rule out technical problems.  \n- Baylee proposed sending submission confirmations to Joe so he knows when episodes are received, preventing future oversights.  \n- The team is currently not working on new episodes aside from a recently sent one and is prioritizing adding more social content to the calendar.\n\n## **Team Expansion and Collaboration**\n\nIntroducing Igor as a new content strategist aims to support the growing workload and enhance content strategy execution (04:11).\n\n- Baylee positioned Igor as a skilled addition to help manage the expanding content pipeline and improve strategic planning.  \n- Meg and Carlos welcomed Igor, noting the importance of additional resources given the amount of content and upcoming initiatives.  \n- The team anticipates smoother operations and increased capacity to manage social and podcast content with this resource added.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast strategy","budget approval","Alyssa podcast","Wrestling Payments","YouTube analytics","content scheduling"],"overview":"- **Podcast Launch Update:** Alyssa will take over one of Joe’s episodes in 2025, full show launch pushed to 2027.  \n- **Audience Insights:** Stable performance with **194 downloads** in 28 days; YouTube traffic mainly from search and embeds.  \n- **Content Performance:** Joe’s short videos hit **up to 1,000 views**, while full-length averages **20 views**; Alyssa’s content doubled typical views.  \n- **Budget Discussion:** Team to revisit budget for expansion; currently **over 100 points** on resources, need to clarify costs.  \n- **Operational Issues:** One-week content delay due to a submission issue; testing process ongoing to prevent future problems.  \n- **Team Growth:** Igor joins as content strategist to manage increased workload and improve content strategy execution.","action_items":"\n**Meg Norlund**\nTest podcast episode submission form on their end to ensure no technical issues (06:01)\nFollow up with Joe regarding video podcast addition to Spotify to confirm if task was completed (09:06)\nCoordinate internally and update on budget preferences for 2026 podcast strategy, whether to keep Alyssa under Wrestling Payments or start new show (11:15)\nCommunicate with Baylee and Justin regarding best practices and financial implications for launching Alyssa’s branded podcast show (16:06)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor podcast episode submissions and keep client informed about any missed submissions (05:50)\nSend instructions again for adding video podcast content to Spotify if Joe has not completed the setup (09:09)\nConsult with Justin to develop financial outline and best practice recommendations for Alyssa’s podcast show launch in 2026, including possible points or budget reconciliation (10:56)\nProvide updated cost or points status report to Meg to address backlog and bring account up to date (17:52)\n\n**Justin**\nWork with Baylee on budget and points status clarifications for client account and Alyssa’s podcast show proposal (09:29)\n"},"duration":18.450000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Carlos"},{"id":1,"name":"Carlos"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Us on another meeting, and we were jumping off.","index":0,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Let''s see here.","index":1,"end_time":6.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.2,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Meg''s having issues with her.","index":2,"end_time":10.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.72,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"With her stuff.","index":3,"end_time":12.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Technology man.","index":4,"end_time":15.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":5,"end_time":15.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":15.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We were on Microsoft Teams in a meeting, and it''s like, we''re.","index":6,"end_time":19.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.84,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"You''re not logged in.","index":7,"end_time":21.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.16,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It''s not working.","index":8,"end_time":21.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And contact your it.","index":9,"end_time":23.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.76,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And we were.","index":10,"end_time":23.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.2,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And it''s like, it''s working.","index":11,"end_time":26.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.96,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":12,"end_time":27.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.8,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I don''t get it.","index":13,"end_time":28.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.44,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"That does not make sense.","index":14,"end_time":29.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m gonna see if I can help her out here.","index":15,"end_time":35.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.84,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I''m gonna share the link.","index":16,"end_time":36.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.6,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Wait, but if she''s not.","index":17,"end_time":40.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.52,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Wait, how is that a thing?","index":18,"end_time":44.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.56,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Her teams isn''t working, but.","index":19,"end_time":48.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.12,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Oh, no, he''s telling me that it''s not working.","index":20,"end_time":52.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.16,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But.","index":21,"end_time":53.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":55.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":55.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"She said it is working on it and to let you know.","index":23,"end_time":65.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.58,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay, so we won''t get Megan today, but possibly not.","index":24,"end_time":70.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":25,"end_time":70.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll see.","index":26,"end_time":71.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So sorry.","index":27,"end_time":72.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":72.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s all good.","index":28,"end_time":73.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":29,"end_time":75.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":74.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m doing good.","index":30,"end_time":76.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.7,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"How are you?","index":31,"end_time":77.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.5,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great.","index":32,"end_time":78.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":77.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got.","index":33,"end_time":79.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.95,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"You have more things on your shelves.","index":34,"end_time":80.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.11,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Nice.","index":35,"end_time":80.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.47,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yes, More things.","index":36,"end_time":82.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got more books and just trinkets and stuff.","index":37,"end_time":87.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":84.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have, like, little Christmas.","index":38,"end_time":89.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":87.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You probably.","index":39,"end_time":89.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can''t see them in the.","index":40,"end_time":91.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like, little holiday Legos.","index":41,"end_time":94.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re hidden.","index":42,"end_time":94.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can''t really see them, but Very good.","index":43,"end_time":98.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":95.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":44,"end_time":98.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And are the books empty?","index":45,"end_time":100.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.35,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Are they just blank books or.","index":46,"end_time":102.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.67,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"They''re just for decorations?","index":47,"end_time":103.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.39,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I do actually like to read books.","index":48,"end_time":107.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":104.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":49,"end_time":108.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":107.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":50,"end_time":109.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Actually, Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":110.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I usually get through a book every week or two.","index":52,"end_time":113.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":53,"end_time":114.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.95,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So love.","index":54,"end_time":116.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":114.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Love to read.","index":55,"end_time":116.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I wish I knew how to read.","index":56,"end_time":119.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.03,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"You''re probably plenty busy with your baby, so.","index":57,"end_time":125.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re just teaching.","index":58,"end_time":128.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.67,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, teaching her how to speak is the best because it''s like all her.","index":59,"end_time":132.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.31,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"She''s at that.","index":60,"end_time":133.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.75,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, she''s saying so many words now.","index":61,"end_time":135.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.47,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I mean, it''s insane.","index":62,"end_time":136.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.81,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Every time, like, people talk to her or whatever, they kind of see her.","index":63,"end_time":139.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.09,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"They''re like, what the heck is going on here?","index":64,"end_time":141.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.81,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know what we''re doing differently, but from other people, but our baby likes to chat and knows a.","index":65,"end_time":149.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.65,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Lot of words, so, yeah, she''s a talker.","index":66,"end_time":151.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.57,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yep.","index":67,"end_time":152.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.29,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I love it.","index":68,"end_time":153.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.73,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":153.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.33,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"You do anything fun for Halloween?","index":70,"end_time":157.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We just went out for.","index":71,"end_time":160.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.01,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I think we did, like, five houses.","index":72,"end_time":162.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.23,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Our house.","index":73,"end_time":163.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.99,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, since we moved to this neighborhood.","index":74,"end_time":165.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.63,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The houses are really far apart and it was so cold.","index":75,"end_time":168.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.71,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, just like.","index":76,"end_time":170.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.99,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, we did it, but I think we hit maybe five houses and we were like, we''re done.","index":77,"end_time":175.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.51,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":175.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Time to go home.","index":79,"end_time":176.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we think.","index":80,"end_time":179.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.31,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Well, I think she got sick because of that night.","index":81,"end_time":183.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.47,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And my.","index":82,"end_time":186.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.35,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"My wife, who''s a nurse with her master''s degree said that you can''t get sick by the temperature, apparently, so it''s about passing viruses and bacteria, so.","index":83,"end_time":197.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.24,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I''m like, I don''t believe you.","index":84,"end_time":199.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.44,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It''s not actually the cold, I guess.","index":85,"end_time":202.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":202.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":202.04,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":203.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.6,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I''m like, I don''t believe you.","index":88,"end_time":204.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And she''s like, fine, don''t believe me.","index":89,"end_time":205.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"She''s like, that''s the science.","index":90,"end_time":207.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":208.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.88,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It''s like, these are.","index":92,"end_time":209.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.24,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"This is science.","index":93,"end_time":209.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.12,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I''m like, but anyway, Meg, you''re in.","index":94,"end_time":215.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.92,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":95,"end_time":217,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":216.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I was having technical difficulties.","index":96,"end_time":218.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":217,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How are you doing, Megan?","index":97,"end_time":221.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":98,"end_time":222.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you for bearing with us.","index":99,"end_time":224.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":222.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Carlos got a cold and I got Covid again, which was still a thing.","index":100,"end_time":231.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":226.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Not me.","index":101,"end_time":232.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I thought it was over with, but apparently it''s still.","index":102,"end_time":234.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.04,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"No, it''s just miserable.","index":103,"end_time":236.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Brutal.","index":104,"end_time":238.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":237.68,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, not.","index":105,"end_time":241.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":238.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Not a fun time to be sick.","index":106,"end_time":242.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But it is the.","index":107,"end_time":244.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The season.","index":108,"end_time":244.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is.","index":109,"end_time":247.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":246.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do we have someone new joining us?","index":110,"end_time":250.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":248.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":111,"end_time":251.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":251.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":251.33,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, we.","index":113,"end_time":252.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":114,"end_time":253.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let me introduce you to Igor.","index":115,"end_time":255.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":253.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I should preface.","index":116,"end_time":256.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not going anywhere.","index":117,"end_time":257.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m still going to be on your account.","index":118,"end_time":258.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor is here to help out with.","index":119,"end_time":261.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":120,"end_time":261.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve got so much cool stuff going on, and he''s a really great content strategist.","index":121,"end_time":266.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome, awesome.","index":122,"end_time":267.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Igor.","index":123,"end_time":268.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":267.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Carlos.","index":124,"end_time":270.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.84,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Great.","index":125,"end_time":273.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we do have some stuff to catch up on.","index":126,"end_time":276.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s been a couple weeks, so I''ll just get into it and stop me if you have questions on anything.","index":127,"end_time":282.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":276.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got some podcast updates, social updates, and then I do just want to touch base on budget for doing a podcast for Alyssa, and then we''ll take a look at your client portal.","index":128,"end_time":297.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any questions or anything else you want to go over today?","index":129,"end_time":301.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":303.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.22,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So for your podcast, we were able to wrap up these two most recent episodes.","index":131,"end_time":310.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like Joe was having some issues with the episode form submission.","index":132,"end_time":316.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Has he talked to you about that at all?","index":133,"end_time":319.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No.","index":134,"end_time":320.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":320.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"No, I. I would say maybe he thought he had done it and probably hadn''t submitted it.","index":135,"end_time":329.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":331.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.14,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay, just let us know.","index":137,"end_time":334.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it.","index":138,"end_time":336.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, well, I. I tested it.","index":139,"end_time":340.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It worked on my end, so I don''t know.","index":140,"end_time":342.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some.","index":141,"end_time":342.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sometimes things happen, so we''ll just keep us in the loop because I. I did feel bad because a week had passed and, like, we didn''t know.","index":142,"end_time":350.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Um, so we.","index":143,"end_time":353.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.77,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We can also maybe just shoot him a message when we do get a submission so he knows or something so we don''t lose any.","index":144,"end_time":358.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, this is the first time that''s happened.","index":145,"end_time":360.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I don''t think this is an issue.","index":146,"end_time":363.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think it was probably just an oversight.","index":147,"end_time":365.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":363.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s been crazy here, so.","index":148,"end_time":367.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, we have.","index":149,"end_time":368.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":150,"end_time":369.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I can test it too, and just make sure on our end there''s no issue.","index":151,"end_time":373.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, cool, Cool.","index":152,"end_time":375.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We won''t worry about it then.","index":153,"end_time":376.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, if it happens again, we''ll try and figure something out.","index":154,"end_time":379.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then.","index":155,"end_time":383.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just for your social updates, we have so much content scheduled.","index":156,"end_time":387.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just going through your wrestling payments page, that''s been working really well.","index":157,"end_time":392.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just looking at some of your YouTube analytics, you got 194 downloads over the last 28 days.","index":158,"end_time":401.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It does look like performance is dropping.","index":159,"end_time":404.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And my guess is probably you''re just posting less content.","index":160,"end_time":408.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, there always tends to be a pretty direct correlation to that.","index":161,"end_time":412.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, these are actually really good things to see here, though.","index":162,"end_time":421.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, most of the traffic is coming from a YouTube search.","index":163,"end_time":425.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So people are either looking for you specifically or they''re like, searching topics that you''re discussing.","index":164,"end_time":431.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re.","index":165,"end_time":432.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re finding you that way, or they''re listening through, like, an external site, which would be, like, pasted on your webpage or something like that.","index":166,"end_time":441.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Does that not show the.","index":167,"end_time":445.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.53,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like the.","index":168,"end_time":446.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.85,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Subscribe, like, I know, always on the videos that people are telling you to kind of like turn on notifications or whatever.","index":169,"end_time":452.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.65,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Does it show, like, the people that are subscribed and are viewing the content or.","index":170,"end_time":459.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.13,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"No.","index":171,"end_time":459.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.13,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Could you elaborate?","index":172,"end_time":462.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, are you looking for specific people?","index":173,"end_time":464.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":464.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.6,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So, for example, like, I.","index":175,"end_time":466.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.96,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"There''s like.","index":176,"end_time":467.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.32,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like I watch the Premier League, right.","index":177,"end_time":471.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.96,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"If I want to.","index":178,"end_time":472.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.48,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"If.","index":179,"end_time":472.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.32,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"If I''m not subscribed to them, I''ll go on YouTube, search Manchester United, like Highlights or whatever.","index":180,"end_time":478.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.68,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But if I was a subscriber, I get notifications and then I will then see the video because I was already subscribed and someone notified me.","index":181,"end_time":489.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.56,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Well, the Bell notified me.","index":182,"end_time":491.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.92,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":183,"end_time":492.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To see it.","index":184,"end_time":493.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.48,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":185,"end_time":494.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":186,"end_time":495.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that would be a different source of traffic if they''re subscribed.","index":187,"end_time":498.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this.","index":188,"end_time":501.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is.","index":189,"end_time":502,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"These sets are telling me that they''re all probably new people or most of them are new people finding your channel.","index":190,"end_time":508,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got it?","index":191,"end_time":509.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.4,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":509.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did that answer your question?","index":193,"end_time":510.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, it did.","index":194,"end_time":511.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.12,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay.","index":195,"end_time":512.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.8,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So then a couple weeks ago, we had talked about that we can also add video to your Spotify account.","index":196,"end_time":522.349,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.749,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is totally optional.","index":197,"end_time":525.629,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.189,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can be a good feature to add.","index":198,"end_time":527.869,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.029,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think you just mentioned you needed to chat with Joe to see if that''s something he wants to do.","index":199,"end_time":533.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.629,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No pressure either way.","index":200,"end_time":535.229,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.949,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mentioned it to him and he seemed to think that he was capable of doing it.","index":201,"end_time":542.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.429,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So let me follow up and see if that actually happened.","index":202,"end_time":546.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.63,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":547.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I can.","index":204,"end_time":548.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If he hasn''t, I can send you these instructions.","index":205,"end_time":551.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It honestly is not that hard, but it is an extra step and like you have to get some stuff set up.","index":206,"end_time":556.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m going to guess that it did not get done, but I will follow up with him.","index":207,"end_time":561.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think I thought you did send me the instructions already.","index":208,"end_time":564.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":209,"end_time":565.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Feel like it sent him something, but let me verify that.","index":210,"end_time":569,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":565.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":211,"end_time":570.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then next is just budget for a show with Alyssa.","index":212,"end_time":577.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have you been able to chat with your team?","index":213,"end_time":579,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is this something you''re wanting to do for next year or what are you thinking?","index":214,"end_time":583,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we did actually go through our budget process and we just had our board meeting.","index":215,"end_time":588.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":583.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So this actually probably is great timing for this conversation.","index":216,"end_time":592.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":588.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So unfortunately, just based on how we did last year, it didn''t get approved to add a new show.","index":217,"end_time":597.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":592.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So Alyssa is going to take one of his episodes.","index":218,"end_time":601.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think he has two a month, if I''m remembering that correctly.","index":219,"end_time":605.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":602.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And she''ll take one, start building her recognition, and then hopefully for 2027, she''ll be able to launch a more executive focused or senior manager focused podcast under her handle of some sort.","index":220,"end_time":619.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":605.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that did bring up the question of, I know you guys have been kind of covering points for us for a bit and what that would look like to catch back up.","index":221,"end_time":628.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I know I''m just throwing new, new numbers at you and I don''t expect an answer on the fly, but if you can let us know what that either dollar amount is or where the stagnation would happen before we could start posting again, which, whichever, however that works.","index":222,"end_time":644.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":629.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be helpful.","index":223,"end_time":646.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.87,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":646.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll connect with Justin and see what we can do there in your perfect world.","index":225,"end_time":654.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I can go and talk to Justin.","index":226,"end_time":656.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would you prefer, like, if money wasn''t an issue, points weren''t an issue.","index":227,"end_time":661.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":657.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, would you prefer to have Alyssa on her own show?","index":228,"end_time":666.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like we would just do one episode of Wrestling Payments and one of her series every month.","index":229,"end_time":672.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What, like, what would be your ideal?","index":230,"end_time":675.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s hard because we''d have to start from zero again trying to get people and I mean, this small following that we has has been hard won.","index":231,"end_time":683.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.31,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s been, yeah, trying.","index":232,"end_time":685.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":684.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Being very persistent for three seasons now.","index":233,"end_time":688.469,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":685.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think if I''m remembering this correctly, I think we''re on our third season of Wrestling Payments.","index":234,"end_time":694.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":688.469,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So yeah, there''s a part of me that''s like, let''s just keep it under Wrestling Payments and see how we do.","index":235,"end_time":698.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":694.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She''s going to take it from the.","index":236,"end_time":700.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":699.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The perspective how we initially imagined Wrestling Payments where she''s going to wrestle with a topic and have that sort of conversation.","index":237,"end_time":707.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":700.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She has way more content, though, than one episode a month, unfortunately.","index":238,"end_time":713.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":707.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So she''s getting a little gypped in this process, but I think ideally, probably keeping it under wrestling payments for now.","index":239,"end_time":721.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":713.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Unless your best practices are screaming like, no, it''s got to start under her brand.","index":240,"end_time":726.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":721.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, invest this amount of dollars just to get the brand set up.","index":241,"end_time":730.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I would be curious to hear what your feedback is and Justin''s feedback on whether it makes sense for her to start under wrestling payments before branching out.","index":242,"end_time":740.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":731.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll think with Justin and give you more context, but, yeah, my.","index":243,"end_time":746.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My insides are definitely telling me it would be better to have her do her own show.","index":244,"end_time":752.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I. I know you have a great audience, but I.","index":245,"end_time":756.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And correct me if I''m wrong, I do think a lot of your audience is, like, people who love Joe and, like, they are Joe lovers, and that''s a great thing.","index":246,"end_time":767.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So sometimes it can be a little, like, jarring when you have a new host start.","index":247,"end_time":774.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we can.","index":248,"end_time":775.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If this is the direction you want to go, we can talk through some strategies of, like, bringing Alyssa on and starting to have her do some hosting things.","index":249,"end_time":783,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll make it work.","index":250,"end_time":784.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll definitely make it work if that''s the direction you want to go.","index":251,"end_time":788.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":784.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think my anecdotal feedback is the people from our membership who are watching, which I''m not even sure it''s more than, like, 50 people.","index":252,"end_time":798.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":788.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think they are.","index":253,"end_time":799.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They''re equally know Joe and Alyssa, so I think that that''s okay.","index":254,"end_time":804.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.04,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think Alyssa''s topics tend to be better for a podcast, and so I think we''re seeing some good results with, like, that fintech Shark Week that she did.","index":255,"end_time":816.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":806.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It was.","index":256,"end_time":817.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":257,"end_time":817.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She''s just got a really good cadence for podcasting.","index":258,"end_time":821.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She gets the right people, I think, on there.","index":259,"end_time":824.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":821.83,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I.","index":260,"end_time":825.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s hard to want to tie it under wrestling payments, which is very Joe focused in terms of the wrestling theme.","index":261,"end_time":832.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.03,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And.","index":262,"end_time":832.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":832.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then also he kind of speaks to our core audience, which is more your operations people, the people that are doing the work, then she''s speaking to their bosses.","index":263,"end_time":843.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":832.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So there''s a little disjointedness there as well.","index":264,"end_time":847.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But then again, one podcast episode a month.","index":265,"end_time":851.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Does that matter?","index":266,"end_time":852.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":851.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":267,"end_time":853.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":852.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know enough about any of this to see which makes better sense.","index":268,"end_time":857.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":853.2,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Um, Joe''s stuff, when it does well on YouTube, it tends to be shorts.","index":269,"end_time":862.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":858.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, the.","index":270,"end_time":863.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The shorts tend to get, you know, like, a few hundred views.","index":271,"end_time":867.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Some of them I think we''ve gotten one up to like a thousand views or whatever.","index":272,"end_time":870.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":867.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But his shorts do well and his videos not quite so well.","index":273,"end_time":876.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":870.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I mean, they''re just like averaging around like 20 views or something there.","index":274,"end_time":879.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.38,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Actually.","index":275,"end_time":881.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":880.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Top of head.","index":276,"end_time":882.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Let me see if I can quickly nav to hers on YouTube.","index":277,"end_time":886.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":882.66,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, she kind of doubles.","index":278,"end_time":889.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She doubled that.","index":279,"end_time":890.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I don''t think it stopped people from listening.","index":280,"end_time":892.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":890.69,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I would say our YouTube audience is probably not our members.","index":281,"end_time":895.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":892.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think that organic stuff is the shorts that are those hot topics and then the videos that are watches are probably from LinkedIn and like emails and stuff that we push out.","index":282,"end_time":908.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.69,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then the Alyssa''s stuff was heavily the audience that she got speakers from, so it was their contacts watching as well.","index":283,"end_time":917.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":918.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":285,"end_time":919.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":286,"end_time":919.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":919.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll make whatever direction you want to go work most of the time.","index":287,"end_time":925.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would just recommend let''s set her up on a new show.","index":288,"end_time":928.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you can cross promote too.","index":289,"end_time":931.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like if you listen to podcasts a lot, like a lot of the time you''ll hear them be like, hey, go listen to my colleagues podcast too.","index":290,"end_time":938.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They talk about xyz.","index":291,"end_time":940.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think you can help like the audience you already have know about the other show if needed.","index":292,"end_time":946.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like.","index":293,"end_time":950.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, exactly.","index":294,"end_time":954.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''ll all still be on your niche YouTube page.","index":295,"end_time":956.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll just create two playlists.","index":296,"end_time":958.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''d have a wrestling payments playlist and then Alyssa, whatever her show''s name.","index":297,"end_time":963.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I like this idea.","index":298,"end_time":966.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Can you.","index":299,"end_time":966.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can you outline what this would look like financially going forward for 2026?","index":300,"end_time":972.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":966.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":301,"end_time":973.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":302,"end_time":974.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then we could maybe even think about not pushing those on a wrestling payments LinkedIn page and just bringing it back to the niche LinkedIn page if we go in two separate directions there.","index":303,"end_time":984.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":304,"end_time":985.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nope, that would be awesome.","index":305,"end_time":987.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll chat with Justin, we''ll get back to you on what we can do.","index":306,"end_time":991.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":307,"end_time":991.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":991.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":308,"end_time":991.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":991.39,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Sorry for all the back and forth too.","index":309,"end_time":993.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":991.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re just question marks over it is all.","index":310,"end_time":997.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":993.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Good.","index":311,"end_time":997.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so then last we''ll just take a look here at your portal so you can see what''s going on.","index":312,"end_time":1005.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Mostly just working on getting more social content still on your calendar.","index":313,"end_time":1013.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have so much stuff scheduled though.","index":314,"end_time":1015.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1013.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re not working on any episodes right now.","index":315,"end_time":1019.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We just sent over that one with.","index":316,"end_time":1021.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1019.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we just sent over that one earlier this week and then.","index":317,"end_time":1026.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s pretty much it.","index":318,"end_time":1027.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1026.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":319,"end_time":1029.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1028.69,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I will check the form and make sure that it''s working.","index":320,"end_time":1032.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1029.73,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":321,"end_time":1033.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a user thing.","index":322,"end_time":1035.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.37,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And then if you want to circle back with Justin and let me know we can sort of move on that.","index":323,"end_time":1041.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I know Alyssa''s got like six.","index":324,"end_time":1042.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.13,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Six people she wants to be talking to already, so it''s a shame she couldn''t get her podcast going for this coming year.","index":325,"end_time":1049.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But, yeah, if you guys can give us a little best practice direction and you think she could do well on her own show and that would be worth looking at some dollars around that.","index":326,"end_time":1059.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":327,"end_time":1060.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll chat with Justin and get back to you.","index":328,"end_time":1063.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1061.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":329,"end_time":1064.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then whatever to make us to bring us back up current, because I think we were over on quite a bit.","index":330,"end_time":1071.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1065.139,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1072.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1071.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":332,"end_time":1072.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, I think it''s over a hundred points, so.","index":333,"end_time":1075.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s quite a bit.","index":334,"end_time":1076.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1078.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1077.71,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Give me either, like a plan for that or a dollar amount for that.","index":336,"end_time":1080.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1078.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Whichever.","index":337,"end_time":1081.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":338,"end_time":1083.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":339,"end_time":1084.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.71,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":340,"end_time":1086.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, it''s so good to see you all and we''ll be chatting again soon.","index":341,"end_time":1090.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":342,"end_time":1091.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1090.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It was great meeting you, Igor.","index":343,"end_time":1092.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1091.309,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Welcome to the niche team.","index":344,"end_time":1094.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, thank you.","index":345,"end_time":1096.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.75,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Happy to be here.","index":346,"end_time":1097.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.51,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Great.","index":347,"end_time":1098.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1097.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":348,"end_time":1099.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks so much, guys.","index":349,"end_time":1100.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Bye.","index":350,"end_time":1101.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1100.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Bye.","index":351,"end_time":1101.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-11-20T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88046600611?pwd=5o555CNd3jppz39fBqq2aKtgUYF0MV.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,cortiz@neach.org,mnorlund@neach.org,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","cortiz@neach.org","mnorlund@neach.org","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KA24FCC2Y4YYD1S75RCYWXGT","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Resolved recent podcast submission miscommunication by confirming form functionality and adding follow-up steps with Joe.","Discussed Alyssa taking over one of Joe''s episodes as a budget-friendly workaround to launching her own show.","Reviewed YouTube and podcast analytics; noted drop in engagement tied to reduced posting volume.","Agreed to explore financial planning and brand setup for launching Alyssa’s show in 2026.","Baylee to consult Justin and provide clarity on point overages and future production costs."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''ll make whatever direction you want to go work.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Yeah, I like this idea.","speaker":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"quote":"We have so much content scheduled.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","budget","analytics","podcast"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-21T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Hosting Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to postpone launching a new podcast for Alyssa in 2025 and instead have her take over one of Joe’s two monthly episodes, aiming for a full independent show launch in 2027 (09:29).\n\n- **The 2025 budget did not approve a new show, so Alyssa will host one episode per month under Wrestling Payments** to build recognition gradually.  \n- Meg explained that Wrestling Payments has a **small but loyal audience of about 50 members**, making a full new show risky due to starting from zero.  \n- Baylee recommended launching Alyssa’s own show for clearer branding and audience targeting, as Joe’s audience is very attached to him personally.  \n- The team agreed to cross-promote both shows via playlists and social channels to maintain audience flow and brand clarity.\n\n## **Content Performance and Audience Insights**\n\nPodcast and social content performance is stable but showing early signs of decline linked to reduced posting frequency, with YouTube driving most traffic through search and external embeds rather than subscribers (06:15).\n\n- The channel recorded **194 downloads in the last 28 days**, but overall performance dipped, likely from fewer new videos posted.  \n- Baylee noted most traffic comes from **YouTube search or external embeds**, indicating limited subscriber engagement.  \n- Meg shared that Joe’s short videos outperform full-length content, sometimes gaining up to **1,000 views**, while full videos average around **20 views**.  \n- Alyssa’s content doubled typical views, mainly driven by guests’ networks and LinkedIn promotions, suggesting different audience dynamics.\n\n## **Budget and Resource Allocation for Podcast Expansion**\n\nThe team will revisit budget options and point reconciliations to support either catching up on current services or expanding to a new show in 2026, with Justin handling financial discussions (10:44).\n\n- Meg requested clarity on the **cost or points needed to resume posting** or start new content, noting the account is currently over by **more than 100 points**.  \n- Baylee committed to consulting Justin to provide financial options and best practices for launching Alyssa’s show independently or continuing under Wrestling Payments.  \n- Meg emphasized Alyssa already has **six potential guest contacts** lined up, highlighting the urgency of resolving budget and resource planning.  \n- The team agreed to explore reallocating promotional efforts, possibly moving Alyssa’s content away from the Wrestling Payments LinkedIn page to the broader niche LinkedIn page.\n\n## **Operational and Process Updates**\n\nThe team identified a one-time submission issue with the podcast episode form, likely user error, and reinforced ongoing monitoring to avoid content delays (05:04).\n\n- Joe may have missed submitting one episode, causing a one-week delay, but the form tested fine on Baylee’s end.  \n- Meg offered to test the submission process on her side to rule out technical problems.  \n- Baylee proposed sending submission confirmations to Joe so he knows when episodes are received, preventing future oversights.  \n- The team is currently not working on new episodes aside from a recently sent one and is prioritizing adding more social content to the calendar.\n\n## **Team Expansion and Collaboration**\n\nIntroducing Igor as a new content strategist aims to support the growing workload and enhance content strategy execution (04:11).\n\n- Baylee positioned Igor as a skilled addition to help manage the expanding content pipeline and improve strategic planning.  \n- Meg and Carlos welcomed Igor, noting the importance of additional resources given the amount of content and upcoming initiatives.  \n- The team anticipates smoother operations and increased capacity to manage social and podcast content with this resource added.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast strategy","budget approval","Alyssa podcast","Wrestling Payments","YouTube analytics","content scheduling"],"overview":"- **Podcast Launch Update:** Alyssa will take over one of Joe’s episodes in 2025, full show launch pushed to 2027.  \n- **Audience Insights:** Stable performance with **194 downloads** in 28 days; YouTube traffic mainly from search and embeds.  \n- **Content Performance:** Joe’s short videos hit **up to 1,000 views**, while full-length averages **20 views**; Alyssa’s content doubled typical views.  \n- **Budget Discussion:** Team to revisit budget for expansion; currently **over 100 points** on resources, need to clarify costs.  \n- **Operational Issues:** One-week content delay due to a submission issue; testing process ongoing to prevent future problems.  \n- **Team Growth:** Igor joins as content strategist to manage increased workload and improve content strategy execution.","action_items":"\n**Meg Norlund**\nTest podcast episode submission form on their end to ensure no technical issues (06:01)\nFollow up with Joe regarding video podcast addition to Spotify to confirm if task was completed (09:06)\nCoordinate internally and update on budget preferences for 2026 podcast strategy, whether to keep Alyssa under Wrestling Payments or start new show (11:15)\nCommunicate with Baylee and Justin regarding best practices and financial implications for launching Alyssa’s branded podcast show (16:06)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor podcast episode submissions and keep client informed about any missed submissions (05:50)\nSend instructions again for adding video podcast content to Spotify if Joe has not completed the setup (09:09)\nConsult with Justin to develop financial outline and best practice recommendations for Alyssa’s podcast show launch in 2026, including possible points or budget reconciliation (10:56)\nProvide updated cost or points status report to Meg to address backlog and bring account up to date (17:52)\n\n**Justin**\nWork with Baylee on budget and points status clarifications for client account and Alyssa’s podcast show proposal (09:29)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a2ee57fb-3e0f-4c4b-a275-197864e358fc","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
