INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: NEACH // New North',
  '## **Podcast Production and Hosting Strategy**

The team decided to postpone launching a new podcast for Alyssa in 2025 and instead have her take over one of Joe’s two monthly episodes, aiming for a full independent show launch in 2027 (09:29).

- **The 2025 budget did not approve a new show, so Alyssa will host one episode per month under Wrestling Payments** to build recognition gradually.  
- Meg explained that Wrestling Payments has a **small but loyal audience of about 50 members**, making a full new show risky due to starting from zero.  
- Baylee recommended launching Alyssa’s own show for clearer branding and audience targeting, as Joe’s audience is very attached to him personally.  
- The team agreed to cross-promote both shows via playlists and social channels to maintain audience flow and brand clarity.

## **Content Performance and Audience Insights**

Podcast and social content performance is stable but showing early signs of decline linked to reduced posting frequency, with YouTube driving most traffic through search and external embeds rather than subscribers (06:15).

- The channel recorded **194 downloads in the last 28 days**, but overall performance dipped, likely from fewer new videos posted.  
- Baylee noted most traffic comes from **YouTube search or external embeds**, indicating limited subscriber engagement.  
- Meg shared that Joe’s short videos outperform full-length content, sometimes gaining up to **1,000 views**, while full videos average around **20 views**.  
- Alyssa’s content doubled typical views, mainly driven by guests’ networks and LinkedIn promotions, suggesting different audience dynamics.

## **Budget and Resource Allocation for Podcast Expansion**

The team will revisit budget options and point reconciliations to support either catching up on current services or expanding to a new show in 2026, with Justin handling financial discussions (10:44).

- Meg requested clarity on the **cost or points needed to resume posting** or start new content, noting the account is currently over by **more than 100 points**.  
- Baylee committed to consulting Justin to provide financial options and best practices for launching Alyssa’s show independently or continuing under Wrestling Payments.  
- Meg emphasized Alyssa already has **six potential guest contacts** lined up, highlighting the urgency of resolving budget and resource planning.  
- The team agreed to explore reallocating promotional efforts, possibly moving Alyssa’s content away from the Wrestling Payments LinkedIn page to the broader niche LinkedIn page.

## **Operational and Process Updates**

The team identified a one-time submission issue with the podcast episode form, likely user error, and reinforced ongoing monitoring to avoid content delays (05:04).

- Joe may have missed submitting one episode, causing a one-week delay, but the form tested fine on Baylee’s end.  
- Meg offered to test the submission process on her side to rule out technical problems.  
- Baylee proposed sending submission confirmations to Joe so he knows when episodes are received, preventing future oversights.  
- The team is currently not working on new episodes aside from a recently sent one and is prioritizing adding more social content to the calendar.

## **Team Expansion and Collaboration**

Introducing Igor as a new content strategist aims to support the growing workload and enhance content strategy execution (04:11).

- Baylee positioned Igor as a skilled addition to help manage the expanding content pipeline and improve strategic planning.  
- Meg and Carlos welcomed Igor, noting the importance of additional resources given the amount of content and upcoming initiatives.  
- The team anticipates smoother operations and increased capacity to manage social and podcast content with this resource added.',
  '2025-11-20 20:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Test podcast episode submission form on their end to ensure no technical issues (06:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Joe regarding video podcast addition to Spotify to confirm if task was completed (09:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally and update on budget preferences for 2026 podcast strategy, whether to keep Alyssa under Wrestling Payments or start new show (11:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate with Baylee and Justin regarding best practices and financial implications for launching Alyssa’s branded podcast show (16:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor podcast episode submissions and keep client informed about any missed submissions (05:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Send instructions again for adding video podcast content to Spotify if Joe has not completed the setup (09:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Consult with Justin to develop financial outline and best practice recommendations for Alyssa’s podcast show launch in 2026, including possible points or budget reconciliation (10:56)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide updated cost or points status report to Meg to address backlog and bring account up to date (17:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Work with Baylee on budget and points status clarifications for client account and Alyssa’s podcast show proposal (09:29)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting (2025-11-19 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2025-11-19 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9Z9ZTRS43XPW0YAJE1W08J6',
    'PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Josh Reinhard","Colin Costigan","Sam Lieberman","Nina Belina"}'::text[],
    2147,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01K9Z9ZTRS43XPW0YAJE1W08J6","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Management and CRM Integration**\n\nThe team decided to automate contact creation in **HubSpot** for LinkedIn connection acceptances to streamline lead tracking (07:43).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** emphasized this automation will reduce manual steps, as currently about **80%** of LinkedIn contacts require manual email lookup (07:53).\n- **Colin Costigan** will develop a workflow routing new contacts through **Clay** for email enrichment before HubSpot import to ensure accurate work email data (09:04).\n- The existing contact property for lead source will be expanded to distinguish outreach types, such as **LinkedIn New North** vs. email campaigns, to improve attribution reporting (04:10).\n- No auto-generated sales tasks will be created yet to avoid burdening sales reps; manual enrollment in sequences continues, with plans to maintain simplicity for new hires (06:01).\n\n## **Website Copy and Content Development**\n\nWebsite content updates are progressing with a focus on initial key pages to support marketing efforts (10:33).\n\n- The **homepage** and **webinar page** are nearly complete, with **pricing** and **integration pages** next, pending a finalized integrations list from Sam (10:35).\n- Content approval will follow a staged process: copy approval, design approval, then development in HubSpot, allowing simultaneous writing of subsequent pages (11:19).\n- Industry and persona pages will come after the core pages, targeting **HR leaders** and **employees** to improve site relevance (11:04).\n- Sam will manage redirects and copy updates for the webinar page once published to maintain traffic flow (11:42).\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe benchmark report campaign launched **9 days ago** has shown promising engagement but low conversion rates, prompting optimization discussions (17:14).\n\n- The campaign reached **756 people** with nearly **7,000 impressions**, achieving a **21.7%** audience depth, surpassing competitors, and generating **175 clicks** at under **$4 cost per click** (17:14).\n- The current ad with the highest engagement asks, “Are your PTO policies competitive?” but lead form fills remain low with only **2 form opens** and no completions this week (18:01).\n- The team plans to rotate ads after the week to test more effective creative and messaging, with particular attention to increasing form fills (17:57).\n- LinkedIn lead gen forms cost more due to targeting competitive HR audiences, confirmed by **Nina Belina**, and adjusting targeting to mid-level HR roles could reduce costs and improve conversion (19:19).\n- Sam and Colin agreed to test lowering seniority thresholds from executives to **mid-level HR managers** to increase volume and form fills, as these roles historically convert better (20:21).\n- Retargeting efforts are active, with **23 clicks** on retargeted ads despite a slight drop in click-through rate due to broader audience exposure (21:15).\n\n## **Sales and Lead Conversion Challenges**\n\nDespite marketing efforts, the team expressed concern over the lack of first meetings generated, highlighting the need for better conversion tactics (22:02).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** voiced frustration that despite good ad engagement and quality materials, no meaningful meetings are booked, stressing urgency to find what works (22:02).\n- Colin explained industry-wide shifts mean prospects need **20+ touchpoints** before engaging, much higher than past norms, requiring increased marketing velocity and multiple channels (26:15).\n- Sam emphasized the importance of sustained multi-channel contact, including LinkedIn, email, ads, webinars, and newsletters, to build awareness over time before meetings occur (33:36).\n- Josh requested insights on any additional tactics other clients use to boost meeting rates, acknowledging current efforts cover major channels but conversion lags (29:13).\n- The team agreed to monitor ongoing lead progress closely, with Josh asking for reminders on HubSpot lead management workflows to ensure proper lead status updates and follow-ups (32:13).\n- Possible adjustments to LinkedIn messaging will be considered if response rates remain low after two weeks, balancing persistence with avoiding prospect fatigue (33:05).\n\n## **Advertising Creative and Design Feedback**\n\nAd creative is focused on clarity and readability, especially for LinkedIn’s limited display space and mobile users (13:35).\n\n- Sam preferred the dropdown design concept for ads as it clearly shows available plans but suggested adding subtle design elements to avoid a bare look (13:55).\n- Colin expressed concern that adding screens or backgrounds might reduce text readability due to size constraints in LinkedIn feeds (14:31).\n- **Nina Belina** confirmed ads must remain legible on mobile, reinforcing the need for clean, bold visuals (15:09).\n- The team will continue testing different ad designs and may add human elements if it improves engagement, with ongoing performance review guiding creative changes (16:02).\n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed on clear deliverables and scheduling to maintain momentum through the end of the year and beyond (10:41).\n\n- Colin will send the homepage, webinar, pricing, and integration page copy for Sam’s review and comment, aiming for quick turnaround to move into design and development (16:56).\n- Ads for the **December 3 webinar** will be updated with new dates and sent for approval promptly to ensure timely launch (21:36).\n- Sam confirmed the survey launch will occur this week to support lead engagement and data collection (16:28).\n- Colin mentioned he will be out next week but will remain available via Slack for urgent issues to keep progress steady (35:03).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn outreach","HubSpot integration","benchmark report","website copy","marketing touch points","LinkedIn ads"],"overview":"- **Lead Management Automation:** HubSpot will automate contacts from LinkedIn accepts, reducing manual email lookups by up to 80%.  \n- **Workflow Development:** New contacts will be routed through Clay for email enrichment before HubSpot import.  \n- **Website Content Progress:** Core pages like homepage and webinar page are near completion; integration pages follow next.  \n- **Campaign Engagement Metrics:** Latest campaign reached 756 people with 7,000 impressions but low form fills; under $4 cost per click.  \n- **Lead Conversion Challenges:** Increased touchpoints needed for engagement; multi-channel strategies critical for booking meetings.  \n- **Ad Design Clarity:** Focus on legible, clean ads for mobile users; ongoing testing for engagement improvements is essential.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop Heyreach-HubSpot integration workflow to enrich LinkedIn-connected contacts with work emails via Clay before creating HubSpot records (09:04)\nComplete writing integration and pricing page copy; send homepage and webinar pages along with draft copies for review (35:27)\nUpdate LinkedIn ads for December 3 webinar, send for approval, and manage live deployment (21:36)\nAdjust benchmark report LinkedIn targeting to lower HR seniority levels (e.g., HR managers) to test for cost reduction and conversion improvement (20:21)\nContinue to increase marketing velocity across channels and monitor campaign data to inform quick iterations (23:15)\nProvide reminders or guidance to Josh on sales process and how to manage lead statuses in HubSpot if needed (31:45)\nSend homepage and webinar copy to Sam for review (35:23)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nProvide Colin with the list of integrations needed for the integration page copy (10:35)\nApprove website copy as received and handle redirects for the webinar page (11:53)\nManage sending out the survey this week as planned (16:28)\nHandle LinkedIn ad feedback and collaborate for design tweaks as appropriate (13:55)\nAssist Josh with reminders on updating HubSpot appropriately and lead follow-up best practices (32:52)\nApprove and manage copy review and feedback process (35:23)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nContinue LinkedIn outreach and coordinate with Colin/Sam when to stop emailing or adjust sequences for prospect communications (33:36)\nMonitor and track SQL stage leads in HubSpot, attempt follow-ups and report response rates (31:45)\nInform team when Heyreach-HubSpot automatic contact creation workflow is live to reduce manual data entry (35:12)\nCoordinate internally on what extra steps are needed to optimize lead management and first meeting generation (32:52)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nAssist Colin with setting up tasks related to the contact enrichment and HubSpot workflows as needed (09:04)\n"},"duration":35.779998779296875,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"id":3,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Colin?","index":0,"end_time":39.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":1,"end_time":40.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":41.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, how you doing?","index":3,"end_time":42.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.449,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m starting to think you didn''t like me.","index":4,"end_time":44.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen you in a couple weeks.","index":5,"end_time":45.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just going on.","index":6,"end_time":50.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":50.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"How is back feeling that sales role going?","index":8,"end_time":53.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re gonna put out an offer in the next couple days.","index":9,"end_time":57.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re in a good spot.","index":10,"end_time":59.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":60.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nice.","index":12,"end_time":61.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":62.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, Sam, how you doing?","index":14,"end_time":64.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Look at you.","index":15,"end_time":65.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You got.","index":16,"end_time":65.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that a quarter zip and a nice polo.","index":17,"end_time":68.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did.","index":18,"end_time":69.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had a. I had a meeting with a like a financial planner guy this morning and for some reason I felt like I needed to dress up.","index":19,"end_time":79.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":69.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know why I thought Sam.","index":20,"end_time":82.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Had a job interview.","index":21,"end_time":83.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I was worried of what was going on.","index":22,"end_time":84.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":23,"end_time":86.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Just a guy that I''m working with.","index":24,"end_time":91.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"There''s with some money stuff, but I felt like I needed to be business professional.","index":25,"end_time":95.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Clean up.","index":26,"end_time":99.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nice.","index":27,"end_time":99.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":28,"end_time":100.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.29,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":29,"end_time":101.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right guys, ready to dive in?","index":30,"end_time":105.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, sir.","index":31,"end_time":107.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, ready to go.","index":32,"end_time":108.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":33,"end_time":109.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, how are you feeling with that Slack channel?","index":34,"end_time":112.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s busy.","index":35,"end_time":116.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It is.","index":36,"end_time":117.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Seems to be working.","index":37,"end_time":119.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":120.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you weren''t in our last call and Sam, I''m not sure, you''ve probably already connected with Josh on it, but like we talked about, Josh, if you want anyone, we built a connection basically between heyreach and HubSpot.","index":39,"end_time":133.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you''re like, hey Colin, this one''s good.","index":40,"end_time":135.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can go in and just automatically export them to HubSpot.","index":41,"end_time":139.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":136.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":42,"end_time":145.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Think of how.","index":43,"end_time":146.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''Ve just been using.","index":44,"end_time":150.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve been using Zoom info and then adding them as contacts into HubSpot.","index":45,"end_time":156.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":46,"end_time":157.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only thing I want to make sure and same.","index":47,"end_time":159.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we talked about this earlier this week or late last week as well is just that the source is attributed.","index":48,"end_time":164.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we don''t source anything from like zoom info as like a lead or anything like they would be attributed to New North.","index":49,"end_time":178.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is there a way?","index":50,"end_time":179.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":51,"end_time":182.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We were.","index":52,"end_time":182.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''re working on some attribution stuff right now on like we want to make sure that like is there a way to automatically get those LinkedIn connections tag tagged as like New north leads or.","index":53,"end_time":197.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.38,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Or something?","index":54,"end_time":197.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we just built that.","index":55,"end_time":199.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what property does that connect to source?","index":56,"end_time":205.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Was the property on the contact record?","index":57,"end_time":209.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"On the contact.","index":58,"end_time":209.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":59,"end_time":211.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the, the tricky thing or probably the thing that we''ve been, you guys and us have been working on to make sure attribution is tight as we have like the deal record that''s created and we have A source of New north in there and then we have contacts and there''s a different property that has like ABM or something else as a field option and then there''s an open text source property for contacts.","index":60,"end_time":233.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I wanted to make sure that we could at least track the contacts that are being sent from our campaigns into HubSpot.","index":61,"end_time":239.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If before they get a deal can.","index":62,"end_time":243.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We export it to the property that has like the drop down field, not the open text one?","index":63,"end_time":250.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.76,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, we can change it instead.","index":64,"end_time":252.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":253.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you want to add a new north option to a different one because the one that has New north as an option is only a deal property right now.","index":66,"end_time":259.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":260.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use lead source on deals as to track the FMS and that''s like what the sales team puts in.","index":68,"end_time":267.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we have a new north option but I added some options the other day to that drop down that''s like I think it''s lead source on the contact record and I think like LinkedIn New north is, is out there.","index":69,"end_time":283.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I kind of want to make sure that we''re distinguishing like this LinkedIn outreach that we''re doing and if there are LinkedIn, if there are LinkedIn connection requests that we''re like reaching out to, I want to make sure we''re like tagging that versus if you know they''re getting an email and replying.","index":70,"end_time":302.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s something different also.","index":71,"end_time":304.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":72,"end_time":305.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when they come over from heyreach automatically it goes into like the record Source drill down one and two.","index":73,"end_time":310.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll have like their Heyreach like conversation and their LinkedIn profile and things like that.","index":74,"end_time":315.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll show where it''s coming from.","index":75,"end_time":317.209,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but yeah, let me dive into your guys properties real quick.","index":76,"end_time":321.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Contacts.","index":77,"end_time":324.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were talking about this specifically today because again we want to make sure you''re getting credit for the stuff that you guys are doing.","index":78,"end_time":334.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But at the same time we don''t want it to be like overkill for what Dan or I or whomever we''re hiring to backfill this role has to do when they''re just.","index":79,"end_time":345.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When we''re still not even sure if this person''s ever going to answer.","index":80,"end_time":348.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know our LinkedIn outreach.","index":81,"end_time":351.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t want to create all these like tasks that a salesperson has to do.","index":82,"end_time":359.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":361.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we''re not doing that right now.","index":84,"end_time":362.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The integration like it won''t send from Heyreach to HubSpot unless you guys let me know and we can export it straight from heyreachtubspot.","index":85,"end_time":371.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t have a task or I haven''t developed that workflow yet to be automatically created.","index":86,"end_time":375.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can build that.","index":87,"end_time":376.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, they have a.","index":88,"end_time":382.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have a sequence of tasks that the directors just enroll them in when they get a connection to to like follow up with them.","index":89,"end_time":391.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But this property, lead source and like, you can add options in here and whatnot is what I''m going to be using to determine like LinkedIn outreach, you know, you know, Dash New north or something.","index":90,"end_time":407.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Email outreach.","index":91,"end_time":408.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Dash New North.","index":92,"end_time":409.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.78,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I want it to be a drop down so that we can like have a report or have lists of all the people that get attributed that.","index":93,"end_time":416.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And if you could set that up automatically to like, once one accepts the connection and they''re in HubSpot, to, to automatically set that up to set aside LinkedIn New North.","index":94,"end_time":434.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, so wait, do we want people to come in automatically to HubSpot just for accepting the connection requests?","index":95,"end_time":440.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I was holding off until you guys let me know, like this was a good.","index":96,"end_time":443.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or like they responded.","index":97,"end_time":444.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just because they accept our connection request.","index":98,"end_time":452.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.749,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, if they accept our connection request, we can automatically make them a contact in HubSpot.","index":99,"end_time":462.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I can?","index":100,"end_time":463.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":101,"end_time":464.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":102,"end_time":464.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then I would want to.","index":103,"end_time":465.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s like one less step that I need to do.","index":104,"end_time":467.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":105,"end_time":468.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":106,"end_time":468.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I didn''t want to like flood anything, so that''s why I was just waiting for you guys to say, like, add this one.","index":107,"end_time":473.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that would make it much.","index":108,"end_time":474.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s like one of the biggest pains of this whole process is like, I have to look them up in.","index":109,"end_time":482.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"In Zoom info.","index":110,"end_time":485.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, 80% of the time they have an email address.","index":111,"end_time":488.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sometimes they don''t.","index":112,"end_time":489.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Other times I''m like looking for other people from the same company and guessing what their email address is so that I can create a contact in HubSpot.","index":113,"end_time":497.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You could, Josh.","index":114,"end_time":498.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can also ask me to just check and enrich their work.","index":115,"end_time":500.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Email.","index":116,"end_time":500.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":117,"end_time":507.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just.","index":118,"end_time":507.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Clay just tags into a bunch of different tools like Zoom Info.","index":119,"end_time":511.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not gonna like ping you every time you get a connection across.","index":120,"end_time":515.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But that''s why if there''s a way to just like if they''re accepting and if they''re accepting a LinkedIn request, we''re going to be creating a contact for them because I''m going to be putting them into a sequence where I''m reaching out to them on LinkedIn while you''re still emailing them.","index":121,"end_time":533.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So when you let us know when to stop emailing.","index":122,"end_time":537.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":537.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We may as well create the contact in HubSpot because I have to do that anyway.","index":124,"end_time":543.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":125,"end_time":544.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I could do, I could develop a more Comprehensive workflow that actually runs through Clay first.","index":126,"end_time":551.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll collect the person that, you know accepted the connection request enrich for their work email, and then put them into HubSpot.","index":127,"end_time":559,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, don''t.","index":128,"end_time":560.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Won''t we already have their work email?","index":129,"end_time":562.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because if they''re part of this, they''re part of some other email sequence that you''re doing.","index":130,"end_time":566.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, so it just has to check, like, the list which Heyreach currently isn''t passing through because that''s just taking their LinkedIn email.","index":131,"end_time":573.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":574.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, that would be better if you can enrich it.","index":133,"end_time":578.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":578.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so, hey, Nina, we''re gonna change this flow to run through Clay and grab the enriched work email and then pass the HubSpot.","index":135,"end_time":588.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you can set up a task for that, that would be great.","index":136,"end_time":590.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Sam, I showed you where we''re at with the homepage copy.","index":137,"end_time":598.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re going through and writing a bunch of different pages.","index":138,"end_time":603.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know why I''m so zoomed in.","index":139,"end_time":605.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re going homepage.","index":140,"end_time":608.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What was the order that we talked about?","index":141,"end_time":611.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was homepage integrations page.","index":142,"end_time":616.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, homepage pricing page, integration page, and webinar page, two of which are, like, pretty much 99% done, being the homepage and the webinar page.","index":143,"end_time":629.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''m going to write the pricing page and integration page.","index":144,"end_time":631.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just need that list of integrations.","index":145,"end_time":633.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":635.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.27,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Can you just.","index":147,"end_time":636.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I will get it for you.","index":148,"end_time":637.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Can you, I guess just, like, write.","index":149,"end_time":640.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The rest of it?","index":150,"end_time":641.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, write the rest of it.","index":151,"end_time":642.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.43,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You can put in ADP workday.","index":152,"end_time":644.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.75,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, don''t worry about the names for now.","index":153,"end_time":646.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.15,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I will put a comment on the copy if there''s one that we can''t use for.","index":154,"end_time":652.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.03,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":155,"end_time":654.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After that, the next slew will be the industry pages, and then after that will be the Persona pages.","index":156,"end_time":659.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":654.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Being the HR leader and the employee of a company that''s currently using you guys.","index":157,"end_time":663.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":158,"end_time":664.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then, like, when?","index":159,"end_time":667.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess, like, as far as timing goes, like, we approve the copy, it goes into development, and then, you know, we''ll get the next pages as the approved ones are getting developed.","index":160,"end_time":679.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.96,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":680.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send over the four pages that I just outlined being the homepage price of page.","index":162,"end_time":685.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, I think we already updated the webinar page.","index":163,"end_time":687.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":689.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send all those over.","index":165,"end_time":690.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys approve the content, we''ll design the page, get that approved by you guys, and then we''ll develop it in HubSpot.","index":166,"end_time":696.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then in, like, in that design approval development, we''ll start writing the copy for the other pages.","index":167,"end_time":701.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":168,"end_time":702.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t.","index":169,"end_time":704.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I remember us talking about the webinar page.","index":170,"end_time":707.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Did you set up like a redirect to the existing URL?","index":171,"end_time":712.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I can''t find it.","index":172,"end_time":713.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.9,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I didn''t publish this one yet.","index":173,"end_time":715.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":174,"end_time":716.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s not published.","index":175,"end_time":717.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I got the new north test in here.","index":176,"end_time":721.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is where I just like restructured the content.","index":177,"end_time":727.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":178,"end_time":729.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.49,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":179,"end_time":730.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but that''s all good to go like that?","index":180,"end_time":739.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.29,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine to use.","index":181,"end_time":740.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.17,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":740.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":183,"end_time":741.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll do the redirect and thing and update the copy and everything.","index":184,"end_time":745.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":185,"end_time":746,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just let me know if you need us to do anything there.","index":186,"end_time":747.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was the session today?","index":187,"end_time":749.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you said you had one or two people registered, right?","index":188,"end_time":751.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we had four and we had two people on.","index":189,"end_time":755.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But better than nothing we had actually.","index":190,"end_time":759.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It was three people.","index":191,"end_time":760.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Someone dropped off.","index":192,"end_time":762.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right?","index":193,"end_time":762.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Someone dropped and then a different person logged in.","index":194,"end_time":766.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So there was always two people that were on, but it was three different people.","index":195,"end_time":769.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There was one that saved for the beginning and then someone that came like halfway through and saved for the end.","index":196,"end_time":773.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw that one of them asked a question, so we''ll take it.","index":197,"end_time":779.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":198,"end_time":780.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about Dan did for your jump?","index":199,"end_time":782.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dan did great.","index":200,"end_time":784.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Very good.","index":201,"end_time":785.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And Josh, any further news on.","index":202,"end_time":789.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you were having a second meeting with.","index":203,"end_time":791.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The healthcare company here in Maryland?","index":204,"end_time":797.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":205,"end_time":798.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We haven''t had that meeting yet.","index":206,"end_time":799.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":207,"end_time":800.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":208,"end_time":803.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I got a feeling that may not happen for a little while, but it should happen.","index":209,"end_time":808.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it might be like an open enrollment or something and just focus on somewhere else.","index":210,"end_time":812.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":211,"end_time":814.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam.","index":212,"end_time":815.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did mock up the ads that we talked about with kind of changing to like a drop down orientation.","index":213,"end_time":821.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have a few different looks for these.","index":214,"end_time":823.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we would just set these to expire the day of the webinar and then launch the next one with the updated date.","index":215,"end_time":834.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I like the dropdown image.","index":216,"end_time":838.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I like that concept for the ads, but it looks a little like, looks a little plain with just like convert my PTO to.","index":217,"end_time":852.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"To blank.","index":218,"end_time":852.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know if it can, if you can make it look a little bit more like, like a screen that they''re on or something.","index":219,"end_time":860.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.9,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Or just a little bit extra design there.","index":220,"end_time":865.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like it looks a little bare, I would say, from like an advertising perspective.","index":221,"end_time":871.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":222,"end_time":872.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":872.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My only worry about adding it to like a screen is it being too small to read with the amount of space that we have on a LinkedIn ad.","index":224,"end_time":879.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s gotta, you gotta.","index":225,"end_time":880.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''re even zoomed in Here compared to how it would show in your LinkedIn feed.","index":226,"end_time":885.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so you want, you want the like, options to be big enough.","index":227,"end_time":889.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":890.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To read.","index":229,"end_time":891.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.95,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I get that.","index":230,"end_time":898.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I just feel like it''s like a little.","index":231,"end_time":900.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Also they have to be readable on mobile versions, so that''s awesome.","index":232,"end_time":906.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":233,"end_time":910.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Well.","index":234,"end_time":915.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I like that.","index":235,"end_time":918.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I like the drop down option because it shows all the different plans that we have.","index":236,"end_time":922.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.24,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But that''s just my two cents.","index":237,"end_time":927.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"If it''s, if it''s not going to work with another design, that''s fine.","index":238,"end_time":929.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":927.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, we can, we can.","index":239,"end_time":931.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":240,"end_time":931.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, we could go larger.","index":241,"end_time":934.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where.","index":242,"end_time":937.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.61,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The spacing works a little differently.","index":243,"end_time":939.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":244,"end_time":941.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s another.","index":245,"end_time":945.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that.","index":246,"end_time":945.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I like that these ones a little bit better just the way that they''re laid out, but I mean, yeah, I trust you guys with like sizing and spacing and everything.","index":247,"end_time":960.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"For the, for the ads.","index":248,"end_time":961.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":962.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re not going to get like static either.","index":250,"end_time":963.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s not like we''re just going to say like, okay, cool, let''s set this for December 3rd.","index":251,"end_time":968.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s the only change we''re making.","index":252,"end_time":969.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''ll see how these perform.","index":253,"end_time":970.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe adding a person into the background could, you know, change how people interact with it.","index":254,"end_time":975.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll test with those designs as we go.","index":255,"end_time":978.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":256,"end_time":980.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":257,"end_time":981.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":258,"end_time":985.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you guys are sending out that survey this week, right?","index":259,"end_time":987.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, we''ll take care of that.","index":260,"end_time":990.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":261,"end_time":995.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":998.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re just working through the website copy stuff, monitoring benchmark report form fills, and I did spin up some new email domains to get more velocity and the way that we''re sending those benchmark report emails out.","index":263,"end_time":1012.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sweet.","index":264,"end_time":1015.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1013.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll send over the homepage copy along with the other documents, Sam, for you to take a look at and then just, we''ll write the integration page just based on what you said and then you can leave a comment with any specific tools.","index":265,"end_time":1029.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":266,"end_time":1031.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1031.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":267,"end_time":1035.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then taking a look at the data.","index":268,"end_time":1036.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So launched this benchmark report campaign now nine days ago.","index":269,"end_time":1041.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So reached 756 people, just under 7,000 impressions.","index":270,"end_time":1046.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re getting a very good depth into the audience, drilling 21.7%, which is above competitors.","index":271,"end_time":1053.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve gotten 175 clicks at under $4 calls per click, which is very competitive.","index":272,"end_time":1059.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that leads us to just looking at the landing page and seeing if we need to make any tweaks there for people to actually fill out the benchmark report.","index":273,"end_time":1068.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The top ad is, are your PTO policies competitive?","index":274,"end_time":1072.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after this week, we''ll look at Performance and see which one we need to rotate out and put a new one in.","index":275,"end_time":1080.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do we do with the people that clicked it like, or do you.","index":276,"end_time":1086.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Do we retargeting them with like different ads or do we.","index":277,"end_time":1091.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess.","index":278,"end_time":1092.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.53,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re getting retargeted through the ad roll pixel that we added to the website.","index":279,"end_time":1095.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":280,"end_time":1096.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So they''re seeing that if they go to like, you know, Wall Street Journal, those types of sites, But they unlock the power of pto.","index":281,"end_time":1105.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had two lead form opens in the past week, but I''m sorry, this week.","index":282,"end_time":1111.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But no one actually filled it out.","index":283,"end_time":1113.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cost per click is high on that one.","index":284,"end_time":1115.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m wondering, or what we''re looking at for the data right now is do we just reshift that ad, you know, to, to get more form fills there, or do we dedicate more of the budget to the benchmark report?","index":285,"end_time":1127.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1115.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What, what causes it to be high?","index":286,"end_time":1133.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.76,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like we''re competing for people.","index":287,"end_time":1136.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.6,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s about the people that we''re trying to get in front of with these higher, you know, HR director titles.","index":288,"end_time":1141.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it higher because it''s a lead gen form?","index":289,"end_time":1144.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1142.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like is it, is that more costly now?","index":290,"end_time":1147.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.04,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s not because it''s a lead gen form.","index":291,"end_time":1149.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more because of who we''re trying to get in front of.","index":292,"end_time":1151.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, I''d have to check exactly if it does have more of a cost.","index":293,"end_time":1156.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina, do you know that off the top of your head?","index":294,"end_time":1158.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, legion forms usually do cost a little bit higher, but it''s definitely due to the audience because anything related to HR is very competitive on LinkedIn, so it requires more of budget.","index":295,"end_time":1170.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1159.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for the return.","index":296,"end_time":1176.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":297,"end_time":1177.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh.","index":298,"end_time":1177.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does it matter the title of the hr, hr?","index":299,"end_time":1183.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like if we went to HR managers, does that make any difference from a cost perspective?","index":300,"end_time":1188.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it probably would because less people will be targeting them.","index":301,"end_time":1193.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wonder if we''re like, if we''re shooting too high with like chief people, officers or chros who are not converted, you know, I don''t know.","index":302,"end_time":1208.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1209.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, if, if we want to look at dropping down like the threshold of the seniority that we''re talking to or trying to get in front of, we could definitely get in front of more people at a cheaper rate.","index":304,"end_time":1219.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think that''s worth testing because we do have success with lower level HR people taking the meeting actually where as more higher the higher up they are, it''s harder to get them on, on the calendar, but.","index":305,"end_time":1241.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":306,"end_time":1246.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1246.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Well, if we do that with the benchmark report too I would imagine they''re more likely to fill it out.","index":307,"end_time":1251.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be good.","index":308,"end_time":1254.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They want something to give to their boss or they just have more time.","index":309,"end_time":1258.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I would.","index":310,"end_time":1259.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think it''s worth it.","index":311,"end_time":1260.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Trying to get our ICP more aligned with like the mid level HR people rather than a heavy focus on, you know, Chro and that exec team.","index":312,"end_time":1275.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1260.99,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right, yeah, we can make that change.","index":313,"end_time":1277.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then down here is the retargeting information.","index":314,"end_time":1279.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we saw 23 clicks from it.","index":315,"end_time":1281.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The click through rate slightly dropped from a 0.12 to a 0.10, but that''s because it got in front of 3,000 more people than the week prior.","index":316,"end_time":1291.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1282.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":317,"end_time":1292.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":318,"end_time":1294.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":319,"end_time":1295.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, so yeah, we''re going through all the pages.","index":320,"end_time":1299.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send over those when they''re ready for review.","index":321,"end_time":1301.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get these ads updated to be about the December 3 webinar, send that over for approval, and then get those live.","index":322,"end_time":1307.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s pretty much.","index":323,"end_time":1310.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1309.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty much it.","index":324,"end_time":1311.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything from your guys side that we didn''t cover that you were hoping to talk about?","index":325,"end_time":1315.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I''m all good.","index":326,"end_time":1318.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.61,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":327,"end_time":1320.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Josh, anything from you?","index":328,"end_time":1322.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think we''re.","index":329,"end_time":1324.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I just think.","index":330,"end_time":1325.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":331,"end_time":1334.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I want to give these things enough chance to like, to work.","index":332,"end_time":1337.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":333,"end_time":1338.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t want to be bouncing around from one thing to the next.","index":334,"end_time":1341.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, you know, I am, I am getting concerned that we''re having.","index":335,"end_time":1345.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re just not having any first meetings, getting generated from this stuff, which is frustrating for me because I feel like there''s a lot of work that''s being put into it on your side and on our side.","index":336,"end_time":1358.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, I''m just, I''m just curious if you''re seeing this across all of your clients that you''re just having trouble on the conversion piece, like what you''re seeing with us.","index":337,"end_time":1371.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, what we''re seeing across the board, just in the trend of marketing in general, is that people are filling out forms less.","index":338,"end_time":1378.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1373.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to see a lot more information before they want to talk to anyone.","index":339,"end_time":1381.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1378.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re much more like guarding of their time.","index":340,"end_time":1384.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we''re trying to make these quick iterations of who we''re getting in front of, how we''re getting in front of them.","index":341,"end_time":1390.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I''m trying to move as quickly as possible to get you guys those first meetings.","index":342,"end_time":1394.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1390.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just, I just am, you know, curious if there''s stuff that you can pull from other clients that''s like working for them that we''re not doing to get these conversions because again, it seems like we''re getting eyeballs on it.","index":343,"end_time":1407.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It seems like, you know, from our perspective, the stuff you guys are creating is cool and it looks good and it feels like it should work better than it''s working, but it''s like, not working right now.","index":344,"end_time":1422.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And at the end of the day, that''s what.","index":345,"end_time":1425.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s what we need, is we need the meetings at the end of the day.","index":346,"end_time":1429.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I totally hear you.","index":347,"end_time":1431.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, Sam, we were talking about this the other day of like, this being a pretty common period of like, open enrollment and that being a focus of some companies as well versus Q1 being, you know, people are probably more open to these types of meetings.","index":348,"end_time":1445.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that being said, that''s why we''re spinning up more email domains and getting, you know, just basically increasing the velocity of how many people we''re getting in front of.","index":349,"end_time":1453.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":350,"end_time":1454.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I. Yeah, you''re right, Colin.","index":351,"end_time":1458.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, I think it''s just going to take a lot more touch points than it ever did to get people to book a meeting.","index":352,"end_time":1467.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I don''t think that it''s going to be like all of a sudden, you know, we''re getting all these meetings now from, like, what we''re doing, but we need to be doing more activities to try and get the meetings.","index":353,"end_time":1484.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I know we haven''t seen anything yet.","index":354,"end_time":1485.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s disappointing.","index":355,"end_time":1486.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But, like, I agree these are all necessary steps because it''s, you know, we can''t expect to send like, you know, one email campaign and be like, okay, you know, we got five meetings.","index":356,"end_time":1499.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1486.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So, like, I don''t want to pretend like I''m trying.","index":357,"end_time":1501.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know I''m not trying to be unrealistic, like, we should have like 15 first meetings from this.","index":358,"end_time":1506.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it does feel like we should be building towards something where we''re like, okay, we''re not getting.","index":359,"end_time":1510.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not hitting our goal number, but we''re working towards it.","index":360,"end_time":1513.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I get what you''re saying.","index":361,"end_time":1515.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I just think it''s.","index":362,"end_time":1517.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s tough.","index":363,"end_time":1517.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1517.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And, you know, we are finally, like, getting, you know, we''re getting the LinkedIn out there, we''re doing the webinar, we''re doing more ads around it.","index":364,"end_time":1527.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1517.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have the benchmark report launched.","index":365,"end_time":1529.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.65,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Finally doing more ads around that.","index":366,"end_time":1531.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, think we gotta, you know, we finally have like, a decent amount of things going on as terms of marketing touchpoints, and we got to keep kind of like pushing forward with that.","index":367,"end_time":1542.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And hopefully, again, it''s kind of disappointing that it''s at the end of the year, which I think is a tough time for people to take like, you know, salute, like Benefit Solutions meetings.","index":368,"end_time":1555.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.4,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I do think it primes us well for next year, which, you know, the beginning of the year is a good time for us.","index":369,"end_time":1564.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.24,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have like, a lot of stuff that we''re doing before that has.","index":370,"end_time":1568.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1564.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Before that time has happened that I''m hoping will convert, basically.","index":371,"end_time":1575.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1569.34,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right.","index":372,"end_time":1576.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have the.","index":373,"end_time":1576.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have the benchmark report.","index":374,"end_time":1577.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re making some significant changes to the website.","index":375,"end_time":1580.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Always rotating ads.","index":376,"end_time":1582.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, Josh, to be perfectly candid, like, where in years past it was like maybe one to five touch points and someone would fill out a form and talk to you.","index":377,"end_time":1590.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1583.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s probably more in the 20 range of things that they need to see before they''re willing to give you their time.","index":378,"end_time":1596.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1590.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just looking at.","index":379,"end_time":1599.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And like, yes, this, certainly this time of year is, you know, there are competing priorities for sure.","index":380,"end_time":1607.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, that''s just the reality of hr.","index":381,"end_time":1610.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But even Sam, like, when I look back on previous years and I look from mid October until, like, mid December and look at how many first meetings we were running in the past, in this period of time, it''s like 6, 8, 10, 4, 4, 4, 8.","index":382,"end_time":1627.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s 2023, 2024.","index":383,"end_time":1629.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1627.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like 5, 10, 8, 4, 8, 5, 9.","index":384,"end_time":1633.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the weekly meetings that we''re having.","index":385,"end_time":1636.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s, what''s the, what''s the breakdown of source, though?","index":386,"end_time":1641.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, in 2023, it was mostly demanding.","index":387,"end_time":1649.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then that''s what.","index":388,"end_time":1651.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I''m.","index":389,"end_time":1653.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But that''s what I''m saying.","index":390,"end_time":1654.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s like channel.","index":391,"end_time":1655.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1654.38,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think you throw, like, I''m not looking at past years for channel.","index":392,"end_time":1659.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right.","index":393,"end_time":1660.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1659.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s a different thing.","index":394,"end_time":1661.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.34,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I, I think, like, what I''m saying is, like, you''re.","index":395,"end_time":1665.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1662.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''re never gonna have that from, From Demand Inc. And from marketing again because it has shifted so much, like, and that we need 20 touch points with these people before this time of year.","index":396,"end_time":1678.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1665.78,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right.","index":397,"end_time":1678.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So, like, now we''re building those touch points now.","index":398,"end_time":1680.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Hopefully it''ll bear fruit in, you know, the next year.","index":399,"end_time":1685.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But, you know, we.","index":400,"end_time":1686.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We basically, until we started with New north, weren''t doing enough to garner the touch points to, to get to that amount of meetings during this time.","index":401,"end_time":1695.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, we''ve just really.","index":402,"end_time":1697.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1696.04,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I know we''ve been working with New north for a while, but, like, I feel like this is like kind of the first month where we''ve like, wow.","index":403,"end_time":1704.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1698.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have a lot kind of going on with them in terms of, like, campaigns running, new offers out there and like, projects that are.","index":404,"end_time":1713.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That are Touching.","index":405,"end_time":1714.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Touching prospects, basically.","index":406,"end_time":1717.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1715.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think it''s going to take probably longer than you would think to like, really start seeing, start seeing conversions.","index":407,"end_time":1728.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1717.88,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s the, the touch point number, like Colin said, it''s doubled.","index":408,"end_time":1733.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1729.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So we have to do double the amount of.","index":409,"end_time":1734.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Number one.","index":410,"end_time":1735.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1734.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We weren''t doing enough touch points to begin with, and now we have to do double that amount of, like, what the industry average is.","index":411,"end_time":1743.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1735.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So I just think it''s gonna.","index":412,"end_time":1744.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1743.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s tough.","index":413,"end_time":1745.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1744.89,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s tough.","index":414,"end_time":1745.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.53,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s.","index":415,"end_time":1746.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I, I also don''t think it''s unique to us.","index":416,"end_time":1748.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":417,"end_time":1748.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":418,"end_time":1750.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think it''s everyone.","index":419,"end_time":1751.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1750.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I, I don''t think marketing, I.","index":420,"end_time":1753.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Guess that that''s what my question is, is more of.","index":421,"end_time":1756.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Again, it''s not like, I don''t think everyone''s working hard or we''re putting out stuff, but, like, is there, are there other things that we should be thinking because we''re not seeing the results, or are there other things that we should be layering on that other clients are doing that we''re not doing that can help us?","index":422,"end_time":1773.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1756.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because ultimately all that matters is we have to just.","index":423,"end_time":1776.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have to get it first meetings.","index":424,"end_time":1778.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And the answer of, like, it.","index":425,"end_time":1780.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s harder.","index":426,"end_time":1781.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"While that can be true, at the end of the day, like, isn''t a good enough answer because we have to get first meetings.","index":427,"end_time":1788.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, we have to, otherwise the business is not going to.","index":428,"end_time":1790.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re not going to survive.","index":429,"end_time":1792.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1791.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we just have to figure out what are other people doing that is working because there has to be something that is working.","index":430,"end_time":1797.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":431,"end_time":1799.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we''re tapping into email, LinkedIn, outreach, ads, website changes.","index":432,"end_time":1804.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have a newsletter going out.","index":433,"end_time":1805.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1804.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a webinar series now.","index":434,"end_time":1807.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1805.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, there''s not many other channels available to tap into.","index":435,"end_time":1813.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1809.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1813.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":437,"end_time":1814.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And that''s really all I wanted to make sure is.","index":438,"end_time":1817.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just want to make sure we''re doing everything that we can do.","index":439,"end_time":1820.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just trying to.","index":440,"end_time":1821.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right now we''re just increasing the velocity and the depth that we''re, we''re getting into all of these channels.","index":441,"end_time":1826.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1821.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was going to say, I think we, we do a lot across all the different channels.","index":442,"end_time":1830.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, the ultimate, like, factor is how much you do in those channels.","index":443,"end_time":1835.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And that comes down to spend.","index":444,"end_time":1837.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1835.74,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s like, you know, if we had more money to spend, we could be doing more.","index":445,"end_time":1841.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1837.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s what big companies do.","index":446,"end_time":1843.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1841.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They, they, they obviously have a lot more going on with these channels, but there''s no, like, hidden channel that we''re not aware of that we''re not touching from a marketing perspective.","index":447,"end_time":1855.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.34,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But all that said, Josh, I totally hear you.","index":448,"end_time":1860.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1859.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":449,"end_time":1862.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always on my mind and that''s what we''re always trying to double down and just get deeper into.","index":450,"end_time":1866.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1862.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just again, like, I just don''t want to get to the point in like two months that we''re, that not only are we not going to be putting more money into this, but that we''re going to have to shut the faucet off because we''re not seeing conversions.","index":451,"end_time":1879.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, that''s, you know, that that would be the worst thing.","index":452,"end_time":1883.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1879.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All of this work, like for not.","index":453,"end_time":1885.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1883.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s what I want to avoid and I know what you guys want to avoid and I know what, that''s what we''re working towards.","index":454,"end_time":1893.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1886.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I just don''t want to leave any stone unturned or if there''s more that we can do on our side to help support the stuff that you''re doing.","index":455,"end_time":1900.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1893.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like put the onus on us too.","index":456,"end_time":1903.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1901.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, you know, we gotta.","index":457,"end_time":1905.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1903.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but I guess my question is, I mean I''ve seen Dan move some of the leads coming into like SQL.","index":458,"end_time":1909.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are those conversations just.","index":459,"end_time":1911.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they not happening?","index":460,"end_time":1912.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they not responding?","index":461,"end_time":1914.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which stuff, like we''ve seen Dan move a few leads to SQL was like some of the benchmark report fills and some other things that came from LinkedIn.","index":462,"end_time":1924.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1916.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They moved from MQL to SQL status and I saw like Dan reaching out to them.","index":463,"end_time":1930.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t checked this week to see if they were responding, but I guess.","index":464,"end_time":1933.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1930.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they not really responding?","index":465,"end_time":1935.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m like, I guess maybe I''m not moving them in HubSpot the way that I should.","index":466,"end_time":1940.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1935.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Maybe it''s.","index":467,"end_time":1941.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1940.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam, I need like a little bit of a reminder on what I should, what I should be doing.","index":468,"end_time":1944.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1941.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like a lot of these people seem like the right people.","index":469,"end_time":1947.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1944.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re reaching out to them with our messaging on LinkedIn while at the same time your guys are continuing your email campaign.","index":470,"end_time":1953.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And the only stuff I''ve heard is like, no thanks.","index":471,"end_time":1956.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1953.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like no one, you know, I had the one conversion on the email, but everything else has either been like, ah, actually I''m retired and I''m just like poking around and getting more information or they don''t respond at all to the LinkedIn messages that we''re sending, which is frustrating.","index":472,"end_time":1972.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1956.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":473,"end_time":1973.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1972.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But maybe in two weeks if, if that happens, maybe we need to change what our LinkedIn messages because maybe that''s part of what the problem is.","index":474,"end_time":1984.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1974.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1985.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1985.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll write Bombard them on LinkedIn while they''re also getting emails is like, what, you know, we''re trying to walk the line between we don''t want them to like unconnect with us, disconnect with us because we want them to see the things that we post on LinkedIn and this is like a way that like, yes, they''ve accepted our invitation, now they''re going to see the things that are getting pushed out there.","index":476,"end_time":2010.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s this fine line between the two of what''s the best way to do it.","index":477,"end_time":2016.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":478,"end_time":2016.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2016.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s tough.","index":479,"end_time":2018.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2017.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But again, like, you know, we need more touch points.","index":480,"end_time":2023.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2018.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So those first couple mentions, they might not respond.","index":481,"end_time":2026.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2023.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Now they''re inner social, they''re in HubSpot, they might, you know, they''re going to get other touch points.","index":482,"end_time":2030.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2026.12,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s very possible they come back later and respond or they convert on another opportunity.","index":483,"end_time":2036.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2030.96,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like this is why all the different stuff is so important.","index":484,"end_time":2039.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2036.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like we got to keep right, you know, touching them a million times more than you think you should be touch them, you''re, you''re 100.","index":485,"end_time":2047.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2039.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right?","index":486,"end_time":2047.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2047.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t want to over bombard them, but like I do think it, the way that this works is shifting more.","index":487,"end_time":2054.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2047.53,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like we get a connection, we send them some stuff, they don''t respond, we don''t hear them, then they see a, a post that they''re interested, then they maybe go to the website and fill out a form.","index":488,"end_time":2063.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2054.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Maybe they see another ad.","index":489,"end_time":2064.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2063.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Now we have them, you know, we, we''re in front of them, which is better than, you know, we send them an email and we don''t get anything.","index":490,"end_time":2072.289,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2065.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then, you know, they''re just kind of, you know, lost to the HubSpot database like so again, I just think it''s, you know, we got to keep getting as many touch points with these prospects as possible.","index":491,"end_time":2087.089,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2072.289,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, all fair.","index":492,"end_time":2091.569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2087.809,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":493,"end_time":2094.609,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2094.049,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t have anything else for you, Colin.","index":494,"end_time":2096.929,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2095.089,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right, cool, sounds good.","index":495,"end_time":2099.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2097.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":496,"end_time":2100.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2099.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you.","index":497,"end_time":2101.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2100.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":498,"end_time":2102.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2101.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":499,"end_time":2103.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2102.59,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I know we don''t have a meeting next week because I''m out all week, but all that being said, if you guys have anything, you know, feel free to send a slack and we''ll get it worked through.","index":500,"end_time":2112.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you let us know, Kyle, when the update happens where it automatically creates the contact in HubSpot Sedan and I know that we don''t need to do that.","index":501,"end_time":2119.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2112.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":502,"end_time":2121.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2120.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, cool, thank you.","index":503,"end_time":2122.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2121.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send over the, the copy stuff whenever you get a chance as well.","index":504,"end_time":2127.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2123.35,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll do.","index":505,"end_time":2127.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have the homepage and then here''s all the webinar I just need to write the integrations and pricing.","index":506,"end_time":2134.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":507,"end_time":2135.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2134.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thanks, Colin.","index":508,"end_time":2136.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2135.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":509,"end_time":2136.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2136.34,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":510,"end_time":2137.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2136.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanksgiving.","index":511,"end_time":2137.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2137.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Enjoy next week.","index":512,"end_time":2138.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2137.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":513,"end_time":2139.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2138.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":514,"end_time":2139.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2139.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you.","index":515,"end_time":2140.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2140.339,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-19T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,josh@ptoexchange.com","sam@ptoexchange.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","josh@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9Z9ZTRS43XPW0YAJE1W08J6","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"negative","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Confirmed no first meetings generated despite increased outreach across LinkedIn, email, and ads.","Josh pressed for other working tactics; Colin noted all major marketing channels are already in use.","Colin to revise workflow to auto-create HubSpot contacts upon LinkedIn request acceptance.","Benchmark report campaign delivered 175 clicks but few form completions; revision efforts underway.","Team agreed current results aren’t meeting goals but emphasized continuing high-volume outreach."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re just not having any first meetings, getting generated from this stuff.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"All of this work, like for not.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"People are filling out forms less... they need to see a lot more information.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["lead gen","conversion","ads","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-20T16:03:10Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Management and CRM Integration**\n\nThe team decided to automate contact creation in **HubSpot** for LinkedIn connection acceptances to streamline lead tracking (07:43).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** emphasized this automation will reduce manual steps, as currently about **80%** of LinkedIn contacts require manual email lookup (07:53).\n- **Colin Costigan** will develop a workflow routing new contacts through **Clay** for email enrichment before HubSpot import to ensure accurate work email data (09:04).\n- The existing contact property for lead source will be expanded to distinguish outreach types, such as **LinkedIn New North** vs. email campaigns, to improve attribution reporting (04:10).\n- No auto-generated sales tasks will be created yet to avoid burdening sales reps; manual enrollment in sequences continues, with plans to maintain simplicity for new hires (06:01).\n\n## **Website Copy and Content Development**\n\nWebsite content updates are progressing with a focus on initial key pages to support marketing efforts (10:33).\n\n- The **homepage** and **webinar page** are nearly complete, with **pricing** and **integration pages** next, pending a finalized integrations list from Sam (10:35).\n- Content approval will follow a staged process: copy approval, design approval, then development in HubSpot, allowing simultaneous writing of subsequent pages (11:19).\n- Industry and persona pages will come after the core pages, targeting **HR leaders** and **employees** to improve site relevance (11:04).\n- Sam will manage redirects and copy updates for the webinar page once published to maintain traffic flow (11:42).\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nThe benchmark report campaign launched **9 days ago** has shown promising engagement but low conversion rates, prompting optimization discussions (17:14).\n\n- The campaign reached **756 people** with nearly **7,000 impressions**, achieving a **21.7%** audience depth, surpassing competitors, and generating **175 clicks** at under **$4 cost per click** (17:14).\n- The current ad with the highest engagement asks, “Are your PTO policies competitive?” but lead form fills remain low with only **2 form opens** and no completions this week (18:01).\n- The team plans to rotate ads after the week to test more effective creative and messaging, with particular attention to increasing form fills (17:57).\n- LinkedIn lead gen forms cost more due to targeting competitive HR audiences, confirmed by **Nina Belina**, and adjusting targeting to mid-level HR roles could reduce costs and improve conversion (19:19).\n- Sam and Colin agreed to test lowering seniority thresholds from executives to **mid-level HR managers** to increase volume and form fills, as these roles historically convert better (20:21).\n- Retargeting efforts are active, with **23 clicks** on retargeted ads despite a slight drop in click-through rate due to broader audience exposure (21:15).\n\n## **Sales and Lead Conversion Challenges**\n\nDespite marketing efforts, the team expressed concern over the lack of first meetings generated, highlighting the need for better conversion tactics (22:02).\n\n- **Josh Reinhard** voiced frustration that despite good ad engagement and quality materials, no meaningful meetings are booked, stressing urgency to find what works (22:02).\n- Colin explained industry-wide shifts mean prospects need **20+ touchpoints** before engaging, much higher than past norms, requiring increased marketing velocity and multiple channels (26:15).\n- Sam emphasized the importance of sustained multi-channel contact, including LinkedIn, email, ads, webinars, and newsletters, to build awareness over time before meetings occur (33:36).\n- Josh requested insights on any additional tactics other clients use to boost meeting rates, acknowledging current efforts cover major channels but conversion lags (29:13).\n- The team agreed to monitor ongoing lead progress closely, with Josh asking for reminders on HubSpot lead management workflows to ensure proper lead status updates and follow-ups (32:13).\n- Possible adjustments to LinkedIn messaging will be considered if response rates remain low after two weeks, balancing persistence with avoiding prospect fatigue (33:05).\n\n## **Advertising Creative and Design Feedback**\n\nAd creative is focused on clarity and readability, especially for LinkedIn’s limited display space and mobile users (13:35).\n\n- Sam preferred the dropdown design concept for ads as it clearly shows available plans but suggested adding subtle design elements to avoid a bare look (13:55).\n- Colin expressed concern that adding screens or backgrounds might reduce text readability due to size constraints in LinkedIn feeds (14:31).\n- **Nina Belina** confirmed ads must remain legible on mobile, reinforcing the need for clean, bold visuals (15:09).\n- The team will continue testing different ad designs and may add human elements if it improves engagement, with ongoing performance review guiding creative changes (16:02).\n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed on clear deliverables and scheduling to maintain momentum through the end of the year and beyond (10:41).\n\n- Colin will send the homepage, webinar, pricing, and integration page copy for Sam’s review and comment, aiming for quick turnaround to move into design and development (16:56).\n- Ads for the **December 3 webinar** will be updated with new dates and sent for approval promptly to ensure timely launch (21:36).\n- Sam confirmed the survey launch will occur this week to support lead engagement and data collection (16:28).\n- Colin mentioned he will be out next week but will remain available via Slack for urgent issues to keep progress steady (35:03).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn outreach","HubSpot integration","benchmark report","website copy","marketing touch points","LinkedIn ads"],"overview":"- **Lead Management Automation:** HubSpot will automate contacts from LinkedIn accepts, reducing manual email lookups by up to 80%.  \n- **Workflow Development:** New contacts will be routed through Clay for email enrichment before HubSpot import.  \n- **Website Content Progress:** Core pages like homepage and webinar page are near completion; integration pages follow next.  \n- **Campaign Engagement Metrics:** Latest campaign reached 756 people with 7,000 impressions but low form fills; under $4 cost per click.  \n- **Lead Conversion Challenges:** Increased touchpoints needed for engagement; multi-channel strategies critical for booking meetings.  \n- **Ad Design Clarity:** Focus on legible, clean ads for mobile users; ongoing testing for engagement improvements is essential.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop Heyreach-HubSpot integration workflow to enrich LinkedIn-connected contacts with work emails via Clay before creating HubSpot records (09:04)\nComplete writing integration and pricing page copy; send homepage and webinar pages along with draft copies for review (35:27)\nUpdate LinkedIn ads for December 3 webinar, send for approval, and manage live deployment (21:36)\nAdjust benchmark report LinkedIn targeting to lower HR seniority levels (e.g., HR managers) to test for cost reduction and conversion improvement (20:21)\nContinue to increase marketing velocity across channels and monitor campaign data to inform quick iterations (23:15)\nProvide reminders or guidance to Josh on sales process and how to manage lead statuses in HubSpot if needed (31:45)\nSend homepage and webinar copy to Sam for review (35:23)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nProvide Colin with the list of integrations needed for the integration page copy (10:35)\nApprove website copy as received and handle redirects for the webinar page (11:53)\nManage sending out the survey this week as planned (16:28)\nHandle LinkedIn ad feedback and collaborate for design tweaks as appropriate (13:55)\nAssist Josh with reminders on updating HubSpot appropriately and lead follow-up best practices (32:52)\nApprove and manage copy review and feedback process (35:23)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nContinue LinkedIn outreach and coordinate with Colin/Sam when to stop emailing or adjust sequences for prospect communications (33:36)\nMonitor and track SQL stage leads in HubSpot, attempt follow-ups and report response rates (31:45)\nInform team when Heyreach-HubSpot automatic contact creation workflow is live to reduce manual data entry (35:12)\nCoordinate internally on what extra steps are needed to optimize lead management and first meeting generation (32:52)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nAssist Colin with setting up tasks related to the contact enrichment and HubSpot workflows as needed (09:04)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7efba84f-b230-4b17-b033-ea1097fdb1b9","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
