    '{"id":"01KA1V97N2Z434PCKE1SA3YTMW","title":"GMT20251114-173117_Recording_1920x1080.mp4","summary":{"notes":"## **Homepage Development and Content Finalization**\n\nThe homepage design and copy are nearly complete, with final integration of imagery and staging environment setup pending (01:20).\n\n- **The homepage structure and copy align with the agreed site map and are ready for the next design phase** (02:35)  \n    - Kylie needs to confirm imagery treatment with the product marketer before final visuals are applied  \n    - Temporary stand-in elements will be used for UI screenshots until the marketer provides assets  \n    - The plan is to combine copy and design into an updated Figma file or image export before development  \n    - This step is critical to ensure the homepage content breathes life into the design before coding starts\n\n- **Setting up a staging environment on the existing WP Engine host is a priority to isolate development from live site risks** (04:54)  \n    - The team encountered access errors despite having granted permissions, prompting a follow-up with Jenny to resolve  \n    - The staging site will run the latest WordPress version with necessary plugins to mirror the production environment  \n    - This setup will enable safe development and testing without disrupting the live homepage  \n    - Quick resolution is essential to meet upcoming development timelines and avoid deployment delays\n\n## **Content Strategy for Persona Benefits and Integration Features**\n\nThe benefits section is structured as four distinct cards targeting key personas without explicitly naming them, preserving user-focused messaging (08:50).\n\n- **The benefits are framed as key value points that “shape your day,” using consistent card design with illustrations to enhance clarity** (09:14)  \n    - Kylie tailored benefits specifically for each persona while avoiding direct persona labels to keep messaging broad  \n    - The card layout supports quick scanning and highlights main benefits with supporting descriptions  \n    - This strategy balances targeted messaging with a clean, unified visual design to boost user engagement  \n    - The product marketer will finalize the presentation style to ensure alignment with broader brand tone and visual standards\n\n- **The integration feature section is under review and may be removed if it does not fit the current product scope or user needs** (11:00)  \n    - Jenny B. is assigned to decide whether to keep or delete the integration block based on evolving product direction  \n    - The integration’s isolated nature means it does not require deep system connections, influencing the decision  \n    - Maintaining consistent demo call-to-action (CTA) buttons across pages is planned, with potential tailoring for industry solutions  \n    - This flexibility allows marketing to customize messaging per audience without disrupting core homepage flow\n\n## **Event Spotlight Component Planning**\n\nAdding a dynamic event spotlight block to the homepage is under consideration to boost timely user engagement with upcoming events (12:41).\n\n- **The event block would automatically display the next calendar event, reducing manual updates and keeping content fresh** (12:41)  \n    - Kylie will consult with the events team to determine optimal placement and content strategy for this component  \n    - This block can be toggled on or off as needed, providing flexibility for event promotion without cluttering the page  \n    - Automating event display based on date enhances user experience and marketing agility  \n    - Current lack of upcoming events means the block is on hold but ready for future activation\n\n## **Branding and Marketing Collateral Support**\n\nThe marketing team will receive clean homepage imagery for new branded note cards to support offline promotional efforts (14:29).\n\n- **Kylie will extract and deliver the homepage image stripped of statistics for use on note cards, ensuring brand consistency** (14:29)  \n    - Delivering the image in Figma format allows for easy logo placement and further edits by the marketing team  \n    - Leslie will use these cards in upcoming outreach, linking digital brand identity with physical materials  \n    - This action supports broader branding efforts and keeps messaging visually aligned across channels  \n    - Timely delivery of these assets ensures offline marketing stays current with the new homepage look\n\n## **Project Timeline and Workflow Coordination**\n\nThe homepage updates and staging environment setup are targeted for completion by Monday or Tuesday to maintain momentum (12:56).\n\n- **Kylie aims to finalize the homepage integration and return the updated files early next week, prioritizing Monday if possible** (12:56)  \n    - This timeline aligns with the need to move quickly into development and testing phases  \n    - Coordinating staging environment access and design finalization are critical path items influencing overall schedule  \n    - Early completion supports planned marketing launches and avoids bottlenecks in multi-team workflows  \n    - Clear communication and prompt issue resolution, especially around host access, are essential to meet these milestones","outline":null,"keywords":["Homepage design","WP Engine staging","Persona benefits","Contract negotiation","Event spotlight","Figma export"],"overview":"- **Homepage Design Near Completion:** Homepage design and copy are nearly finished; awaiting confirmation on imagery from product marketer.  \n- **Staging Environment Set Up:** Setting up a staging site on WP Engine is a priority to prevent risks to the live site.  \n- **Benefits Section Tailored and Engaging:** Benefits are structured in four cards for key personas to enhance user engagement without naming them.  \n- **Event Spotlight Component Pending:** Proposed event spotlight block will auto-display events, improving content freshness, pending consultation with events team.  \n- **Marketing Collateral Support Provided:** Homepage imagery will be delivered for branded note cards, supporting offline promotional efforts and brand consistency.  \n- **Timeline for Completion Set:** Homepage updates and staging setup are aimed for completion by early next week to avoid delays.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nFollow up with Jenny to resolve WP Engine login errors and obtain necessary access for staging environment setup (07:26)\nPrepare and send clean export images from Figma of homepage visual for note cards without stats, just the base image for branding use (14:29)\nCombine homepage copy with design and deliver updated Figma file or export image to the team by Monday or Tuesday (09:14)\n\n**Jenny**\nFinalize contract negotiation and sign off on Tier 2 guide contract based on redlines circulated (00:14)\nTake lead on deciding if the integration feature remains or is removed from site map and overall design (11:00)\nCoordinate event spotlight requirements and inform design team on timing and presentation specifics (12:41)\n\n**Product Marketer**\nProvide imagery/treatment approach for UI screenshots on the homepage and guidance on the integration feature section (02:35)\n"},"duration":15.899999618530273,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Tristan.","index":0,"end_time":14.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, Kylie.","index":1,"end_time":17.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How you doing today?","index":2,"end_time":18.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":3,"end_time":19.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":20.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m doing just fine, so.","index":5,"end_time":23.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":24.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Glad we had this on the board.","index":7,"end_time":25.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Catch up before the weekend hits us.","index":8,"end_time":26.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":28.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yeah, where.","index":10,"end_time":30.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Where would you like to start?","index":11,"end_time":31.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know we were working on the home page, but.","index":12,"end_time":33.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, do you actually.","index":13,"end_time":36.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do you have an update on the Tier 2 guide?","index":14,"end_time":39.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no update.","index":15,"end_time":42.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"He''s still working with Jenny.","index":16,"end_time":43.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Try to get a contract in place.","index":17,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We haven''t done anything with that at this point.","index":18,"end_time":48.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, really?","index":19,"end_time":49.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":20,"end_time":53.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Send over a statement of work about a week ago.","index":21,"end_time":55.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then Jenny sent some.","index":22,"end_time":58.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Some red lines on the legal side, but got some back yesterday.","index":23,"end_time":63.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We don''t have that signed yet.","index":24,"end_time":65.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":25,"end_time":68.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":26,"end_time":71.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, then, yes, I do have the homepage ready to go.","index":27,"end_time":75.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You want.","index":28,"end_time":88.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You want to walk through it, share your screen?","index":29,"end_time":91.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What were you thinking there?","index":30,"end_time":92.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just sent it over to you.","index":31,"end_time":93.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry.","index":32,"end_time":94.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, that''s all right.","index":33,"end_time":95.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me.","index":34,"end_time":96.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I will pull this up here.","index":35,"end_time":113.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":36,"end_time":121.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And can you see it?","index":37,"end_time":127.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes.","index":38,"end_time":128.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, good.","index":39,"end_time":129.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":40,"end_time":129.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it looks like.","index":41,"end_time":130.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, you got everything laid out based on the.","index":42,"end_time":134.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The site map we had here.","index":43,"end_time":136.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":137.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You want to step through it or what?","index":45,"end_time":138.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What were you thinking as far as like, any.","index":46,"end_time":141.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Any other commentary around it?","index":47,"end_time":143.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, we can go through it and just make sure.","index":48,"end_time":146.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I have kind of what you guys need, but I did the waste page yesterday, so I.","index":49,"end_time":155.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That one''s not done, but I do have a couple things I want to check in on you with.","index":50,"end_time":158.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But first I''d like to see if we''re on the right track here.","index":51,"end_time":161.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":52,"end_time":165.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":165.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Structure wise, this is.","index":54,"end_time":167.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This would be what I would like to see.","index":55,"end_time":169.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So appreciate you going through that.","index":56,"end_time":171.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, just let me just go through here.","index":57,"end_time":173.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Text next to UI screenshot.","index":58,"end_time":176.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think this looks like to be everything.","index":59,"end_time":181.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"My only question, just like, up front is on the UI screenshot side and how you wanted to handle those.","index":60,"end_time":189.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I need to talk to our product marketer.","index":61,"end_time":195.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That was something she was going to be working on.","index":62,"end_time":198.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me send her a message.","index":63,"end_time":203.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I have some, but I think we need to figure out kind of the treatment we want to do as well.","index":64,"end_time":230.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I really.","index":65,"end_time":233.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I can help with the content, but less with the imagery there.","index":66,"end_time":236.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":67,"end_time":239.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe we.","index":68,"end_time":240.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We just use like, stand in elements for now.","index":69,"end_time":244.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.43,"speaker_name":null},{