    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01K9FGQJ4YTNZVVE64YBZ6007B","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Ads and Lead Quality**\n\nThe LinkedIn ad campaign spent **$2,400** over the first few weeks but generated many low-quality leads due to unclear messaging around \"resume automation\" (10:52).\n\n- **Axel Völker and Eli Bebinger identified** that the term \"resume\" confused job seekers into submitting forms meant for consulting services (08:14).\n    - This caused a flood of responses from people outside the target roles and industries.\n    - Eli messaged all form submitters; only one prospect from **Laster Pipeline** responded positively requesting a demo (08:35).\n    - Colin Costigan confirmed the positive lead came from ads, but other quality leads from **Capgemini** and **E Techie** had not yet replied (15:18).\n    - Eli will continue follow-ups and track status in a shared **OneNote** list for visibility (16:25).\n\n- The campaign used a matched contact list of **1,100 people**, with **750 matches** on LinkedIn, expanded by an AI-driven predictive audience of over a million, causing poor targeting and junk leads (12:20).\n    - Colin plans to split targeting into a **highly focused manual list** for most budget spend and a smaller AI-driven predictive group to control quality (13:54).\n    - The original budget is **$3,000/month** for LinkedIn ads plus **$500** for programmatic display, with LinkedIn charging mostly on impressions but also clicks (11:16).\n    - Cost per lead on LinkedIn is acknowledged as high, sometimes reaching **$1,000+**, but can deliver quality B2B prospects when targeted well (11:25).\n\n- The team decided to stop the current LinkedIn ads and create new ads with clearer messaging focused on IT consulting rather than resumes (10:19).\n    - Colin is preparing new ad copy promoting **free registration for Desi Dalo**, emphasizing consultant profiles, skills management, and AI-powered resource management (16:57).\n    - The LinkedIn forms will be adjusted to require **work emails** instead of personal emails to improve lead quality (17:37).\n    - The new landing page will highlight free usage, target audience, testimonials, and upgrade reasons to encourage conversions (20:04).\n    - Colin will share landing page drafts and email copy early next week for review and launch (32:43).\n\n## **Outreach and Messaging Performance**\n\nThe outreach via LinkedIn connections and messages has moderate engagement but limited conversions so far.\n\n- Eli has sent **431 connection requests** with **71 accepted** and followed up with **68 messages**, receiving **13 replies** (24:00).\n    - Most responses requested product videos, which Eli has started sending more consistently (24:07).\n    - Axel requested a tracking system via Excel or OneNote to monitor message status, reply frequency, and last contact date for both ad respondents and LinkedIn messages (24:20).\n    - Eli agreed to maintain this tracking despite the volume of messages (24:43).\n\n- To avoid LinkedIn restrictions, connection requests are throttled at **21 per day**, with the current target list of **700+ contacts** (25:49).\n    - Colin plans to refresh and expand the contact list continuously to maintain outreach flow (26:05).\n\n- Messaging strategy will shift to using **\"CV\" instead of \"resume\"** to avoid previous confusion and better resonate with the target audience (26:20).\n    - New email and LinkedIn outreach copies will launch alongside the new landing page (29:45).\n\n## **Product Positioning and Feature Messaging**\n\nThe team is refining product messaging to better highlight AI capabilities and consultant management features.\n\n- Colin confirmed the recent launch of the **AI staffing workflow feature** on Monday and wants to emphasize AI-powered resource management in marketing (20:16).\n    - Axel suggested focusing messaging on **AI workforce management**, followed by managing consultant profiles and skills utilization, avoiding over-technical terms like \"skills matrices\" (20:47).\n    - The landing page will explain what users can do for free, who the product is for, and why companies upgrade, including UI screenshots and testimonials (23:06).\n\n- Colin updated the explainer video script to cover **resource management, skills management, and project delivery** with an AI-first positioning (26:35).\n    - He created a framework for a video episode featuring a discussion between Eli and David on why utilization matters beyond billable hours, touching on global resource management complexities (27:33).\n    - Axel emphasized David’s expertise on managing consultants across multiple regions and legislations, noting the content''s uniqueness despite a smaller target audience (28:51).\n\n## **Technical and Development Updates**\n\nThe product team is developing a chat-based interface to improve user experience and functionality.\n\n- Axel demonstrated an early version of a **chatbot integrated into the application** that suggests profile improvements like missing fields and skills (29:55).\n    - Future versions will allow the bot to perform actions on the user''s behalf upon request (30:52).\n    - Users can query the system for data such as the number of project managers, showing growing AI assistance capabilities (31:19).\n    - The chatbot runs on the dev system and is designed to create a fully conversational interface for resource management tasks (32:00).\n\n## **Process Improvements and Coordination**\n\nThe team is enhancing tracking and coordination for outreach and marketing efforts.\n\n- To improve visibility, Eli will maintain detailed status tracking of all outreach contacts in shared documents to monitor engagement and follow-up needs (16:25, 24:20).\n- Colin plans to expand outreach capacity by creating additional email mailboxes for sending messages, increasing scalability for campaigns (26:05).\n- The marketing manager tool on LinkedIn requires better navigation and transparency around lists and targeting; Colin will share contact lists to Axel for clarity (12:20).\n- The team agreed to pause current ads until the new landing page and messaging are ready, ensuring alignment before relaunch (29:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Ads","Lead Generation","AI Staffing Workflows","Consultant Profiles","Landing Page","Outreach Metrics"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Ads Issues:** $2,400 spent yielded low-quality leads due to unclear messaging about \"resume automation.\"\n\n- **Targeting Strategy:** Using a matched list of 1,100 with 750 LinkedIn matches led to poor targeting; new focused targeting planned.\n\n- **Ad Campaign Changes:** Current ads paused; new ads to promote IT consulting, requiring work emails for better lead quality.\n\n- **Outreach Performance:** Eli’s outreach resulted in 431 requests, 71 accepted, and only 13 replies; need for improved tracking agreed.\n\n- **Product Messaging Update:** Emphasizing AI capabilities in marketing; new landing page to clarify user benefits and engagement.\n\n- **Chatbot Development:** Early chatbot version suggests profile improvements; aims to enhance user experience with conversational interface.","action_items":"\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFollow up and message respondents from LinkedIn ad forms, including Sam from E Techie and Capgemini contacts; track all outreach and lead responses in shared OneNote or Excel file for team visibility (16:09)\nSend personal email follow-ups to prospects who cannot be messaged or connected on LinkedIn (19:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the uploaded LinkedIn contact list used for ad targeting with team (12:29)\nDevelop new LinkedIn and email ad copy replacing ''resume'' with ''CV''; create new landing page content focusing on free Desi Dalo registration and AI resource management; share drafts and updated explainer video script early next week for approval (26:20)\nRefresh and expand outreach contact lists beyond existing 700+ profiles (26:05)\nShare updated explainer video script and framework of Episode One of series featuring discussion between David and Eli on utilization and resource management topics (27:33)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide content input and feedback on landing page sections including tool capabilities, usage process, testimonials, and upgrade rationale (23:25)\n\n**Eli Bebinger & Axel Völker**\nMaintain shared tracking system of message sends, replies, and status updates to ensure clear lead management and avoid redundant outreach (24:20)\n"},"duration":33.18000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Eli Bebinger"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":255.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":1,"end_time":282.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":287.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we are waiting for Eli.","index":3,"end_time":291.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":4,"end_time":294.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your week?","index":5,"end_time":295.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":6,"end_time":296.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Busy.","index":7,"end_time":297.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Good.","index":8,"end_time":298.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Lots of things going on.","index":9,"end_time":301.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":302.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yours?","index":11,"end_time":303.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s been a good week.","index":12,"end_time":305.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":309.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting prepped for Thanksgiving in a few weeks.","index":14,"end_time":312.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":15,"end_time":314.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When is that?","index":16,"end_time":315,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the date is 27th.","index":17,"end_time":319.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":321,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":19,"end_time":324.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Any plans for the weekend?","index":20,"end_time":327.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not really.","index":21,"end_time":332.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nice.","index":22,"end_time":333.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, I''m not sure.","index":23,"end_time":337.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let me try to pin Eli.","index":24,"end_time":339.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where is he?","index":25,"end_time":342.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I think some teams.","index":26,"end_time":357.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":27,"end_time":358.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s just.","index":28,"end_time":359.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, there''s all.","index":29,"end_time":360.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":30,"end_time":360.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s just start.","index":31,"end_time":363.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I sent that in the chat.","index":32,"end_time":367.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think.","index":33,"end_time":367.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":34,"end_time":368.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But my.","index":35,"end_time":368.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"My theory is that if you post something on LinkedIn that says resume and automation, somehow people think it''s related to recruiting because that''s because I think even LinkedIn, they call it resume for their job portals stuff.","index":36,"end_time":387.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I wondered why so many people that were open for work filled out the form.","index":37,"end_time":395.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think there''s two issues.","index":38,"end_time":399.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The one is that the targeting is not working well because those were people that were neither in the role nor in the industry.","index":39,"end_time":407.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the other is, I think they just read resume, automation.","index":40,"end_time":412.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, LinkedIn.","index":41,"end_time":414.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m looking for a job.","index":42,"end_time":414.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do it.","index":43,"end_time":415.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s free.","index":44,"end_time":416.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And otherwise.","index":45,"end_time":420,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I cannot explain how we got all these.","index":46,"end_time":422.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All these form submissions.","index":47,"end_time":426.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":48,"end_time":429,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I didn''t really get Eli''s last comment where he said he filled out the form, but on LinkedIn directly or where did that come from?","index":49,"end_time":438.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Was that someone from the ad or was that somewhere else?","index":50,"end_time":441.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I couldn''t view what he was sending.","index":51,"end_time":443.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I could also the link I couldn''t open, but he said he posted this guy, this screenshot of the guy who said, yeah, he''s interested in seeing this, but I''m not sure if that came from this LinkedIn contact automation or from the form.","index":52,"end_time":462.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, let me check his company.","index":53,"end_time":466.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me pull it up real quick.","index":54,"end_time":467.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":55,"end_time":470.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think.","index":56,"end_time":470.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I hope Eli contacted all of the ones that submitted a form and he has some feedback, but I don''t know where he is.","index":57,"end_time":476.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He does not.","index":58,"end_time":477.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, there he is.","index":59,"end_time":479.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":60,"end_time":479.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":483.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sorry, guys.","index":62,"end_time":483.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.19,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Lost track of time for a minute.","index":63,"end_time":485.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Eli, how''s it going?","index":64,"end_time":487.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":65,"end_time":488.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.07,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yourself?","index":66,"end_time":489.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.63,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":67,"end_time":490.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":68,"end_time":492.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":494.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.15,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think that you might be on to something.","index":70,"end_time":496.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There are.","index":71,"end_time":497.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So that resume is a tough word to use on LinkedIn.","index":72,"end_time":502.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.03,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So maybe we should go after a different problem, you know?","index":73,"end_time":507.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.9,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, what is it?","index":74,"end_time":509.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have you met.","index":75,"end_time":510.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have you like, messaged all of the people that submitted the form?","index":76,"end_time":514.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I messaged all of them.","index":77,"end_time":517.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.66,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"One of Them dropped back to me and asked for a demo.","index":78,"end_time":519.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.02,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Is that the one you pasted in the chat?","index":79,"end_time":522.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":80,"end_time":523.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Actually, that is from ads.","index":81,"end_time":525.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was ads?","index":82,"end_time":527.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":528.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.94,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sorry, I thought I specified that.","index":84,"end_time":529.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.38,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But like, it was weird because he asked about engine.","index":85,"end_time":535.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.86,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He asked about like architecture, but maybe he means we support engineering or architectural workflows, which to me architectural doesn''t sound their software.","index":86,"end_time":549.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But then his bio says that he does.","index":87,"end_time":553.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.66,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He''s a senior UI architect.","index":88,"end_time":555.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.77,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"They do pipeline service.","index":89,"end_time":559.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, I mean, that could be good.","index":90,"end_time":560.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.25,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Actually.","index":91,"end_time":560.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.61,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Pipeline service could need some skill, some technical skill.","index":92,"end_time":565.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.93,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Management.","index":93,"end_time":566.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.89,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I would just do.","index":94,"end_time":568.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, let''s just do it.","index":95,"end_time":570.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe you can call him or something and check what he''s actually looking for and then we can do a demo.","index":96,"end_time":577.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":97,"end_time":578.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":98,"end_time":579.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He put his phone number in the message.","index":99,"end_time":581.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, he did?","index":100,"end_time":582.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, just call him.","index":101,"end_time":583.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He put the phone number there.","index":102,"end_time":586.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s probably expecting that.","index":103,"end_time":588.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And is that okay?","index":104,"end_time":593.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that was from the ad.","index":105,"end_time":594.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, so at least it worked for kind of for one.","index":106,"end_time":600.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":107,"end_time":600.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the others, it just didn''t reply or what is about the others?","index":108,"end_time":604.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, no other replies yet.","index":109,"end_time":609.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay.","index":110,"end_time":610.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we''ll just wait.","index":111,"end_time":611.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, let''s follow up with that guy.","index":112,"end_time":613.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And Colin, you stopped the LinkedIn ads, right?","index":113,"end_time":618.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I did, yep.","index":114,"end_time":620.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.189,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":620.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":623.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to go over some changes.","index":117,"end_time":625.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know on Friday when we met last week, I had said.","index":118,"end_time":628.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to develop some new ads so that we could test them.","index":119,"end_time":631.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to present those.","index":120,"end_time":633.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it actually mirrors the messages that you.","index":121,"end_time":636.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You sent this morning and yesterday as well.","index":122,"end_time":639.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Curiosity, how much do LinkedIn ads cost?","index":123,"end_time":644.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know what you mean.","index":124,"end_time":647.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, how much did we spend on that last campaign?","index":125,"end_time":650.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.08,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Or something like that?","index":126,"end_time":651.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I have that.","index":127,"end_time":652.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So $2,400 was spent in the first few weeks.","index":128,"end_time":656.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do they charge per click or per impression or.","index":129,"end_time":661.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No one knows really.","index":130,"end_time":662.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, yeah, it''s.","index":131,"end_time":664.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s serving impression, so it''ll charge for that.","index":132,"end_time":666.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then clicks is a bit more that it''ll charge for it and it all adds up to that.","index":133,"end_time":670.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have $3,000 a month marked as the LinkedIn budget and 500 for the programmatic display on that.","index":134,"end_time":676.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lot per click, right?","index":135,"end_time":678.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":680.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s why you will probably want to be very specific or.","index":137,"end_time":685.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s why I want to update the ads.","index":138,"end_time":687.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that is on LinkedIn, that is not very expensive for click.","index":139,"end_time":690.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, a cost per lead on LinkedIn can easily be in the 1000 plus, you know, 3000 plus range.","index":140,"end_time":696.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a.","index":141,"end_time":699.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a tight B.2B marketing network.","index":142,"end_time":701.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it can be expensive but also provide great results.","index":143,"end_time":704.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we did was we took the list that we have been emailing and messaging on LinkedIn, added them into LinkedIn, but also built a predictive audience using LinkedIn''s insights.","index":144,"end_time":715.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s where some of these spam or junk results have come from.","index":145,"end_time":718.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to be sorry.","index":146,"end_time":719.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you did this user?","index":147,"end_time":721.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I finally managed to access that marketing manager, but I find it right.","index":148,"end_time":728.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not super easy to navigate.","index":149,"end_time":732.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So how does the targeting work?","index":150,"end_time":736.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It seems like you uploaded some lists which is pretty small, like 700 people or so.","index":151,"end_time":740.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That was the match.","index":152,"end_time":741.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we uploaded about 1100 people.","index":153,"end_time":743.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"700 people.","index":154,"end_time":743.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I cannot see the list.","index":155,"end_time":744.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This list is probably.","index":156,"end_time":745.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Probably you have that somewhere.","index":157,"end_time":746.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you share that?","index":158,"end_time":747.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I can''t LinkedIn.","index":159,"end_time":749.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I can share that.","index":160,"end_time":750.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":751.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, that would be good.","index":162,"end_time":752.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then.","index":163,"end_time":754.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So then they display to that people, if they have them.","index":164,"end_time":758.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Correct.","index":165,"end_time":759.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do they use for matching email?","index":166,"end_time":761.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Probably people don''t have their emails on LinkedIn, just the person, the name.","index":167,"end_time":764.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what do they use when we.","index":168,"end_time":766.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Upload it to LinkedIn?","index":169,"end_time":767.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s first name, last name, company, email.","index":170,"end_time":770.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we have Google conversion IDs and a country.","index":171,"end_time":775.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also provide their LinkedIn profile because that''s part of what we get from the enrichment.","index":172,"end_time":779.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so they should all be.","index":173,"end_time":781.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They should be able to match basically all of them somehow.","index":174,"end_time":784.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":785.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean of the 1100 that we provided, 750 of them got a match.","index":176,"end_time":789.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":177,"end_time":790.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the.","index":178,"end_time":790.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":179,"end_time":791.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then they use that to try to find like similar.","index":180,"end_time":795.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you not define categories?","index":181,"end_time":797.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you not like.","index":182,"end_time":798.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so we defined it as IT Services and IT Consulting.","index":183,"end_time":801.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But because it''s AI, it tries to expand.","index":184,"end_time":803.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''re going to do is deactivate the AI aspect of IT and do all manual for targeting.","index":185,"end_time":810.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":811.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":814.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I couldn''t really find where you said that this, this targeting stuff just sort of as a list and then there''s some auto generated with like a million.","index":188,"end_time":822.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Over a million people or so in there.","index":189,"end_time":824.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":190,"end_time":825.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the larger audience size is where we get cheaper cost per click.","index":191,"end_time":828.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we get useless, but then we.","index":192,"end_time":831.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Get some junk results.","index":193,"end_time":832.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":194,"end_time":833.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what we want to do is take and basically split it into two.","index":195,"end_time":838.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have our very targeted list that we want to dedicate most of our budget to and then a predictive audience where we''re not allowing AI to manipulate who''s being targeted, but manually controlling that with a smaller portion of the budget so we can talk to more.","index":196,"end_time":849.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People through LinkedIn''s network and the 700 list.","index":197,"end_time":854.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that, where is that coming from?","index":198,"end_time":855.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that like zoom info?","index":199,"end_time":857.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the list.","index":200,"end_time":858.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got that from Clay, which uses zoom info and a bunch of other resources.","index":201,"end_time":862.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the, the list of people that we''re sending emails and LinkedIn messages to.","index":202,"end_time":865.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":866.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":204,"end_time":869.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so while we can''t filter out people who have open to work in their profile picture frame, we can assume that it might be due to a lack of clarity in the message for the free professional profile package.","index":205,"end_time":881.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll show on the next slides the running.","index":206,"end_time":885.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, I think if you''re, if you''re looking for a job and you see a free professional profile package on LinkedIn, you think like, oh, I can.","index":207,"end_time":893.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Get my resume upgraded.","index":208,"end_time":895.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, something like that.","index":209,"end_time":896.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Looking for jobs though?","index":210,"end_time":899.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.92,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Because they have that in there.","index":211,"end_time":901.039,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.24,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"They might just not have updated it or they want recruiters.","index":212,"end_time":905.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, but I think they''re not, they''re definitely not looking for the package that we offer.","index":213,"end_time":910.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re looking for.","index":214,"end_time":911.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":215,"end_time":911.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, more likely looking for some job related package.","index":216,"end_time":916.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":917.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then the quality companies that did fill out the form were the Capgemini and the E Techie.","index":218,"end_time":923.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know we did get some quality companies coming through here.","index":219,"end_time":929.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did see a large increase in clicks.","index":220,"end_time":931.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":929.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re actually 2 1/2x industry benchmark for click through rates.","index":221,"end_time":934.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where''s the guy that replied to come?","index":222,"end_time":936.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that Etechi or where''s the guy.","index":223,"end_time":938.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That so covered Laster Pipeline?","index":224,"end_time":942.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, so I had him in low quality because actually you had said that originally and then Eli, you messaged later on that here''s a fit and it looks like his response is that he''s interested.","index":225,"end_time":951.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":226,"end_time":953.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I had him in junk.","index":227,"end_time":954.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, but the, the, the eat the E Techy and the Cap Gemini, they haven''t replied yet.","index":228,"end_time":960.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right Eli, have they responded to you?","index":229,"end_time":962.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":230,"end_time":964.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.23,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Let me double check the notes to get those people''s names and then I''ll send them another message.","index":231,"end_time":970.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":965.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":232,"end_time":972.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":977.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"E Techie was Sam Velou.","index":234,"end_time":980.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said this one looks pretty good.","index":235,"end_time":981.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the Cap.","index":236,"end_time":983.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gemini.","index":237,"end_time":984.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":985.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you make a list on somewhere in OneNote or something where we just put the names and a status?","index":239,"end_time":991.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sorry, I made a list in OneNote and I sent the link.","index":240,"end_time":995.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, just, just create a list and then put the status there and we are there.","index":241,"end_time":1000.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that guy, I''m not sure because he''s also open for work.","index":242,"end_time":1006.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not sure if he''s, if that''s valid, but we''ll see.","index":243,"end_time":1008.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just message Him.","index":244,"end_time":1009.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":245,"end_time":1016.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what I did was went ahead and like we talked about last week of having an offer run for actually just registering for Desi Dollo as a tool for free and experiencing.","index":246,"end_time":1025.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, that was the ad direction that we wanted to go in.","index":247,"end_time":1029.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So wanted to have very targeted towards IT consulting and not like boost your resume.","index":248,"end_time":1035.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So IT consulting teams can now try Desi dollar for free.","index":249,"end_time":1038.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Automate Consultant Profiles and Skills Matrices and AI plus Resource Management.","index":250,"end_time":1043.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get started for free with the headlines and on the LinkedIn.","index":251,"end_time":1050.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we shouldn''t have any resume profile stuff in here.","index":252,"end_time":1053.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Might as consultant profile.","index":253,"end_time":1054.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That may be okay.","index":254,"end_time":1055.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1054.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1057.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I wanted to change the fields that we''re collecting because on the Legion forms it''s collecting a lot of personal emails because that''s what people create their LinkedIn profile with.","index":256,"end_time":1064.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so it autofills.","index":257,"end_time":1066.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1064.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we can do is switch to a work email where they have to fill that in manually, which would be a higher quality lead.","index":258,"end_time":1071.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m actually not able to follow up with Sam from E Techie.","index":259,"end_time":1079.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.56,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I can only send him.","index":260,"end_time":1081.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.85,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I was able to send him one free message but I can''t send a follow up.","index":261,"end_time":1086.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.05,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You probably have to send him a connection request, huh?","index":262,"end_time":1089.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1090.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.85,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Which it''s not allowing me to do, weirdly.","index":264,"end_time":1093.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Can I share my screen for a second?","index":265,"end_time":1095.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.57,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":266,"end_time":1096.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t put this message button here.","index":267,"end_time":1109.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.18,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Maybe because I messaged him first through this.","index":268,"end_time":1112.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It takes away the option to connect.","index":269,"end_time":1114.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.94,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But there''s no option to connect.","index":270,"end_time":1119.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know, maybe you can switch that off somehow in LinkedIn.","index":271,"end_time":1124.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, he might have it where he can''t receive messages from anyone besides a connection.","index":272,"end_time":1130.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, but I was able to message him.","index":273,"end_time":1132.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.2,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I can''t send a connection.","index":274,"end_time":1134.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Was that as part of a connection request or just a message?","index":275,"end_time":1138.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I ran out of the things where you could do add a note in your connection request.","index":276,"end_time":1144.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So if I was able to send someone a message for free, then I was doing that.","index":277,"end_time":1149.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And what is that?","index":278,"end_time":1150.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ellipses.","index":279,"end_time":1151.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you hover over the message that ellipses to the bottom.","index":280,"end_time":1156.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":281,"e