d I know that you guys launched the AI feature, I believe Monday.","index":311,"end_time":1215.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":312,"end_time":1215.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1216.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I really wanted to tap into that as well.","index":314,"end_time":1218.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So creating consultant profiles, skills matrices and test AI powered staffing workflows.","index":315,"end_time":1224.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to make sure that was the right language for the AI aspect.","index":316,"end_time":1227.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I work with agent for.","index":317,"end_time":1234.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So for this aspect, AI powered staffing workflows.","index":318,"end_time":1244.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s where I really wanted to confirm.","index":319,"end_time":1247.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all.","index":320,"end_time":1248.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s basically all AI powered.","index":321,"end_time":1249.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s AI powered consultant.","index":322,"end_time":1255.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1250.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":323,"end_time":1255.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Create consultant profiles.","index":324,"end_time":1258.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ll zoom in.","index":325,"end_time":1260.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will.","index":326,"end_time":1260.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I will maybe change the order because great Consultant profiles is probably not.","index":327,"end_time":1263.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not the most exciting one is somehow AI workforce management.","index":328,"end_time":1271.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is it?","index":329,"end_time":1272.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s in the header.","index":330,"end_time":1273.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":331,"end_time":1273.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I was workforce manage.","index":332,"end_time":1282.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would then maybe generate skill.","index":333,"end_time":1284.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe manage consultant profiles.","index":334,"end_time":1286.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the create is just one Manage skill matrices.","index":335,"end_time":1294.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that is not super different from the.","index":336,"end_time":1296.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s kind of a bit part of the profile.","index":337,"end_time":1298.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if I would put that as a separate one.","index":338,"end_time":1300.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You can just say manage consultant profiles and skills or something like that without the matrix.","index":339,"end_time":1312.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Your skills.","index":340,"end_time":1312.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think a matrix is a bit of a technical maybe utilization.","index":341,"end_time":1320.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We should somehow bring in there like profiles, skills comma, utilization and test and test AI port stuffing, something like that.","index":342,"end_time":1343.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You really want to give the size 50 to 3000 or.","index":343,"end_time":1350.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we don''t have to, but this was part of the.","index":344,"end_time":1353.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just making sure that we''re very zoned in on the targeting so that people who may somehow land there that aren''t a fit, don''t fill it out.","index":345,"end_time":1362.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looking for like a free resume upgrade.","index":346,"end_time":1364.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":347,"end_time":1366.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if I want to limit it at the top to 3,000 at the bottom.","index":348,"end_time":1370.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe like, I mean do you want.","index":349,"end_time":1377.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To do like 10,000 plus?","index":350,"end_time":1378.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe like that.","index":351,"end_time":1381.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then as far as the sections on the page, you know what you can actually do in the tool for free, who it''s for, why people, why teams use desi$, what happens when you sign up.","index":352,"end_time":1395,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just kind of explaining through the process, having some screenshots of the UI testimonial and then why companies upgrade from the free version.","index":353,"end_time":1402.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you need input for that or you.","index":354,"end_time":1408.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll need some insight for this.","index":355,"end_time":1410.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll put together, like, the content that I can write and then highlight sections where I''ll need some.","index":356,"end_time":1414.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some help from your team.","index":357,"end_time":1415.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":358,"end_time":1417.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then so to recap where we''re at with outreach metrics, so on LinkedIn, Eli, we''ve sent out 431 connections from your profile, 71 of which have been accept accepted.","index":359,"end_time":1430.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So 68 messages have been sent.","index":360,"end_time":1432.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When I pulled this this morning, 13 of those replied.","index":361,"end_time":1436.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ve seen people ask for videos, I think is the most common thing.","index":362,"end_time":1441.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sending them that video.","index":363,"end_time":1443.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you seen any responses from those, Eli?","index":364,"end_time":1445.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not really yet.","index":365,"end_time":1448.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But are you sending the video that the link.","index":366,"end_time":1451.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":367,"end_time":1453.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sends more now, but I sent it to some people so far.","index":368,"end_time":1456.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1453.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, just send it to everyone.","index":369,"end_time":1459.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1457.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So people who finish the sequence, right?","index":370,"end_time":1462.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.57,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1464.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can we make a OneNote or an Excel somewhere where you can track those?","index":372,"end_time":1470.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like, who are the people that you messaged and what is the status?","index":373,"end_time":1478.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that we have some overview somewhere because we cannot see your LinkedIn.","index":374,"end_time":1481.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":375,"end_time":1484.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.78,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There''s a lot of messages, though, for me to put all the ones that don''t respond into an Excel, but I can do it.","index":376,"end_time":1489.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.02,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":377,"end_time":1490.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe create an Excel or a table in OneNote and then maybe an extra.","index":378,"end_time":1494.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And put the.","index":379,"end_time":1495.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The.","index":380,"end_time":1496.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The ones that reply to the ad.","index":381,"end_time":1498.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe two sheets.","index":382,"end_time":1499.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"One was the LinkedIn message here for people who respond.","index":383,"end_time":1505.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For everybody.","index":384,"end_time":1506.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Not the respondents, I would say the ones that responded.","index":385,"end_time":1509.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is the status like?","index":386,"end_time":1511.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When did you last message them?","index":387,"end_time":1512.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Did you get a reply or not?","index":388,"end_time":1516.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How many messages?","index":389,"end_time":1517.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that we have an overview and what has changed and do the same for the ones that reply to the ad, even though they''re probably not super valid.","index":390,"end_time":1526.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think we should still track and see what comes back so that we have an overview.","index":391,"end_time":1531.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I just share the link to the Excel.","index":392,"end_time":1535.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, makes sense.","index":393,"end_time":1539.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.93,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Good.","index":394,"end_time":1541.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what, Colin, that means we are halfway through your contact list.","index":395,"end_time":1545.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Even more.","index":396,"end_time":1546.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have 700 or something that we can message.","index":397,"end_time":1549.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":398,"end_time":1550.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on the LinkedIn side, because we don''t want Eli''s profile to get blacklisted by LinkedIn, we have it throttled at 21 connection requests today, but the total.","index":399,"end_time":1559.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1550.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we can send is this is like 700 something.","index":400,"end_time":1561.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Correct.","index":401,"end_time":1562.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":402,"end_time":1564.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we will go through and refresh a list also to grab more contacts that we can send some more outreach to.","index":403,"end_time":1572.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1565.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so as far as next steps, what I want to do with the messaging and email side of things, I want to create some more mailboxes to send emails from and then launch new messaging with using the term CV instead of resume and also the new landing page messaging promoting the free registration of Desi Dalo rather than the profile package.","index":404,"end_time":1591.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s try to.","index":405,"end_time":1594.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s try one.","index":406,"end_time":1595.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":407,"end_time":1595.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1595.42,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I''ll be writing those and sharing those early next week.","index":408,"end_time":1598.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1595.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also updated the script based on your feedback for the explainer video.","index":409,"end_time":1602.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is much more focused on the PDFs and PowerPoints that you had shared the content there.","index":410,"end_time":1609.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So resource management, AI agent AI first positioning and then covering all of these things at a broader scope.","index":411,"end_time":1617.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1609.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So skills management, resource management and project delivery.","index":412,"end_time":1619.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have that document here and I can share this with you in teams.","index":413,"end_time":1625.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1621.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I updated all of the visual and voiceover based on your feedback.","index":414,"end_time":1630.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is actually 120 seconds.","index":415,"end_time":1634.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll share this with you so you guys can review.","index":416,"end_time":1641.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it''s tricky to read a lot of copy on a call like this.","index":417,"end_time":1645.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":418,"end_time":1648.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ve also.","index":419,"end_time":1651.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, good.","index":420,"end_time":1652.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, go ahead.","index":421,"end_time":1653.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I was gonna say I also created the framework for what would be episode one between David and Eli.","index":422,"end_time":1660.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the topic that I came up with was why utilization matters beyond the billable hour.","index":423,"end_time":1667.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys had something else in mind, we can certainly write towards that.","index":424,"end_time":1670.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are subtopics baked into this as well, where we give Eli the opportunity to ask David about traditional versus modern approaches.","index":425,"end_time":1677.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":426,"end_time":1678.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we can ask David.","index":427,"end_time":1679.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, he''s really the global resource person for large global enterprises.","index":428,"end_time":1686.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s where it''s coming from.","index":429,"end_time":1687.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And how to do resource management across different legislations and regions.","index":430,"end_time":1693.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.759,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I''m not sure.","index":431,"end_time":1694.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The good thing is there''s probably not a lot of people that can talk about that.","index":432,"end_time":1699.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s kind of unique content.","index":433,"end_time":1703.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then the target group is also probably not that big.","index":434,"end_time":1709.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, and I did have a reference to that in here as well.","index":435,"end_time":1713.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, how do things even get more complicated with consultants across multiple, multiple regions or building skills visibility across global teams as well.","index":436,"end_time":1723,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I had some mention of those.","index":437,"end_time":1725.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1724.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1729.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But looking at these, I mean, this is kind of the simplified breakdown of it.","index":439,"end_time":1734.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you think going with a different topic would be more beneficial?","index":440,"end_time":1737.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1734.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have to check with David.","index":441,"end_time":1739.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Honestly, it has to be something where he feels comfortable talking about, I guess.","index":442,"end_time":1742.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1739.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right, gotcha.","index":443,"end_time":1744.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I didn''t write this to put any words in anyone''s mouth, but I do Eli, like have some questions that you can cover in here and then just some ideas that maybe David would want to touch on or if he wants to add his own into this as well.","index":444,"end_time":1758.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just share the link afterwards and like share with him.","index":445,"end_time":1763.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1760.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but he''s in.","index":446,"end_time":1764.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1763.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s.","index":447,"end_time":1764.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s in the chat, so.","index":448,"end_time":1765.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I see that.","index":449,"end_time":1766.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":1768.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so between the ads and the emails and the videos, that is everything that I had prepped to talk about today.","index":451,"end_time":1775.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1769.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as far as next steps, I''ll be writing updated email copy.","index":452,"end_time":1778.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll share that with you guys.","index":453,"end_time":1779.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also developing that new landing page and launching these new links or links.","index":454,"end_time":1785.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we need first landing page and then we stop the ads.","index":455,"end_time":1790.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and we''ll start the new email outreach and LinkedIn outreach, and then we''ll also expand the list.","index":456,"end_time":1794.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can quickly show you the preview of the bot.","index":457,"end_time":1801.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We just released that in the first version.","index":458,"end_time":1803.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s very early, so it''s very kind of limited.","index":459,"end_time":1807.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s already pretty cool.","index":460,"end_time":1809.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1807.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it is.","index":461,"end_time":1812.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we added it as a bot, basically, to the application.","index":462,"end_time":1819.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I can just ask anything about the application.","index":463,"end_time":1822.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the nice thing is, in the future, we''ll also be able to do stuff for you.","index":464,"end_time":1825.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1822.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So can you just say, let''s say.","index":465,"end_time":1827.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1825.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Suggest.","index":466,"end_time":1831.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that blue button could look a little better.","index":467,"end_time":1838.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1836.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"The arrow.","index":468,"end_time":1843.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1842.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What, that one here?","index":469,"end_time":1845.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1843.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":470,"end_time":1845.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1845.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s pretty standard for.","index":471,"end_time":1846.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1845.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, isn''t it?","index":472,"end_time":1848.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think, like, the shaping is a little weird, but maybe that''s.","index":473,"end_time":1851.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1848.41,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So now it says, get some gestures to improve your profile.","index":474,"end_time":1855.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Complete missing fields, location.","index":475,"end_time":1857.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You don''t have highest education specified highest add skills.","index":476,"end_time":1860.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like languages.","index":477,"end_time":1861.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1860.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s suggesting some languages that I may have, and it''s actually also suggesting some skills.","index":478,"end_time":1866.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the next iteration will.","index":479,"end_time":1867.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You will.","index":480,"end_time":1867.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Basically, he will just ask you, should I do that for you?","index":481,"end_time":1870.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then.","index":482,"end_time":1871.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then he''ll do that.","index":483,"end_time":1872.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But you can also ask, like, how many project managers do we have.","index":484,"end_time":1875.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For that first question.","index":485,"end_time":1880.019,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1879.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is a shame that people wouldn''t pay more for just upgrading one resume, because, I mean, if someone could put that in and get their resume turned around, but if they were willing to pay for it, that''d be great.","index":486,"end_time":1889.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, say that again.","index":487,"end_time":1892.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What?","index":488,"end_time":1892.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, like, you know the issue we were running into with.","index":489,"end_time":1895.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We think people are just submitting the form to get their own resume updated.","index":490,"end_time":1898.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That first response would be probably golden to those people, but they''re just not willing to pay for it.","index":491,"end_time":1902.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1898.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the problem.","index":492,"end_time":1904.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1903.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re.","index":493,"end_time":1904.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re all individuals.","index":494,"end_time":1905.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re not paying.","index":495,"end_time":1906.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1905.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, okay, it says you have two project managers.","index":496,"end_time":1910.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1907.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Who are they?","index":497,"end_time":1911.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1910.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think you can just say, who''s the.","index":498,"end_time":1915.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1913.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What system are you using?","index":499,"end_time":1918.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1917.61,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s the Zadaro.","index":500,"end_time":1921.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1920.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s a new.","index":501,"end_time":1922.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1921.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s a demo now.","index":502,"end_time":1923.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is.","index":503,"end_time":1923.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s our previous system but it''s also on the dev system and this is a bit.","index":504,"end_time":1929.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, it cannot.","index":505,"end_time":1933.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":506,"end_time":1933.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You can just kind of give you the skills.","index":507,"end_time":1935.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, you can.","index":508,"end_time":1936.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1935.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Now it''s on the dev system.","index":509,"end_time":1937.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You can also play around with that and do it.","index":510,"end_time":1939.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1937.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that''s what we are just building and extending so that we want to completely chat based experience and interface that you can do everything in a chat with the tool as an agent.","index":511,"end_time":1953.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1940.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s awesome.","index":512,"end_time":1954.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1953.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, so that''s where most of the changes are happening currently.","index":513,"end_time":1961.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Very exciting stuff.","index":514,"end_time":1964.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1963.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I will send over all the updated documents and then early next week I''ll have the email copy and the landing pages developed and I''ll share those with you guys so we can get approved to launch in this next iteration.","index":515,"end_time":1975.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1966.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":516,"end_time":1977.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1976.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":517,"end_time":1978.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1977.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":518,"end_time":1978.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1978.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":519,"end_time":1979.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1978.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well thank you all very much.","index":520,"end_time":1980.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1979.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope you have a great weekend.","index":521,"end_time":1981.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1980.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you too.","index":522,"end_time":1982.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Chat with you next week.","index":523,"end_time":1984.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1983.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":524,"end_time":1984.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bye.","index":525,"end_time":1985.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2025-11-14T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9FGQJ4YTNZVVE64YBZ6007B","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Identified LinkedIn ad targeting flaw; switching to manual targeting to reduce irrelevant leads.","One form respondent requested demo; Eli to follow up via call with provided phone number.","Colin proposed new ad copy and landing page emphasizing AI-powered staffing workflows over resumes.","Updated explainer video script aligns with PDF/PPT resources; focuses on resource and skills management.","Axel demoed early bot version enabling chat-based interaction and profile improvement suggestions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Let''s just do it. Maybe you can call him or something and check what he''s actually looking for.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"What we want to do is deactivate the AI aspect of IT and do all manual for targeting.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Yeah, I messaged all of them. One of them dropped back to me and asked for a demo.","speaker":"Eli Bebinger"}],"topics":["ads","targeting","demo","ai","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-14T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Ads and Lead Quality**\n\nThe LinkedIn ad campaign spent **$2,400** over the first few weeks but generated many low-quality leads due to unclear messaging around \"resume automation\" (10:52).\n\n- **Axel Völker and Eli Bebinger identified** that the term \"resume\" confused job seekers into submitting forms meant for consulting services (08:14).\n    - This caused a flood of responses from people outside the target roles and industries.\n    - Eli messaged all form submitters; only one prospect from **Laster Pipeline** responded positively requesting a demo (08:35).\n    - Colin Costigan confirmed the positive lead came from ads, but other quality leads from **Capgemini** and **E Techie** had not yet replied (15:18).\n    - Eli will continue follow-ups and track status in a shared **OneNote** list for visibility (16:25).\n\n- The campaign used a matched contact list of **1,100 people**, with **750 matches** on LinkedIn, expanded by an AI-driven predictive audience of over a million, causing poor targeting and junk leads (12:20).\n    - Colin plans to split targeting into a **highly focused manual list** for most budget spend and a smaller AI-driven predictive group to control quality (13:54).\n    - The original budget is **$3,000/month** for LinkedIn ads plus **$500** for programmatic display, with LinkedIn charging mostly on impressions but also clicks (11:16).\n    - Cost per lead on LinkedIn is acknowledged as high, sometimes reaching **$1,000+**, but can deliver quality B2B prospects when targeted well (11:25).\n\n- The team decided to stop the current LinkedIn ads and create new ads with clearer messaging focused on IT consulting rather than resumes (10:19).\n    - Colin is preparing new ad copy promoting **free registration for Desi Dalo**, emphasizing consultant profiles, skills management, and AI-powered resource management (16:57).\n    - The LinkedIn forms will be adjusted to require **work emails** instead of personal emails to improve lead quality (17:37).\n    - The new landing page will highlight free usage, target audience, testimonials, and upgrade reasons to encourage conversions (20:04).\n    - Colin will share landing page drafts and email copy early next week for review and launch (32:43).\n\n## **Outreach and Messaging Performance**\n\nThe outreach via LinkedIn connections and messages has moderate engagement but limited conversions so far.\n\n- Eli has sent **431 connection requests** with **71 accepted** and followed up with **68 messages**, receiving **13 replies** (24:00).\n    - Most responses requested product videos, which Eli has started sending more consistently (24:07).\n    - Axel requested a tracking system via Excel or OneNote to monitor message status, reply frequency, and last contact date for both ad respondents and LinkedIn messages (24:20).\n    - Eli agreed to maintain this tracking despite the volume of messages (24:43).\n\n- To avoid LinkedIn restrictions, connection requests are throttled at **21 per day**, with the current target list of **700+ contacts** (25:49).\n    - Colin plans to refresh and expand the contact list continuously to maintain outreach flow (26:05).\n\n- Messaging strategy will shift to using **\"CV\" instead of \"resume\"** to avoid previous confusion and better resonate with the target audience (26:20).\n    - New email and LinkedIn outreach copies will launch alongside the new landing page (29:45).\n\n## **Product Positioning and Feature Messaging**\n\nThe team is refining product messaging to better highlight AI capabilities and consultant management features.\n\n- Colin confirmed the recent launch of the **AI staffing workflow feature** on Monday and wants to emphasize AI-powered resource management in marketing (20:16).\n    - Axel suggested focusing messaging on **AI workforce management**, followed by managing consultant profiles and skills utilization, avoiding over-technical terms like \"skills matrices\" (20:47).\n    - The landing page will explain what users can do for free, who the product is for, and why companies upgrade, including UI screenshots and testimonials (23:06).\n\n- Colin updated the explainer video script to cover **resource management, skills management, and project delivery** with an AI-first positioning (26:35).\n    - He created a framework for a video episode featuring a discussion between Eli and David on why utilization matters beyond billable hours, touching on global resource management complexities (27:33).\n    - Axel emphasized David’s expertise on managing consultants across multiple regions and legislations, noting the content''s uniqueness despite a smaller target audience (28:51).\n\n## **Technical and Development Updates**\n\nThe product team is developing a chat-based interface to improve user experience and functionality.\n\n- Axel demonstrated an early version of a **chatbot integrated into the application** that suggests profile improvements like missing fields and skills (29:55).\n    - Future versions will allow the bot to perform actions on the user''s behalf upon request (30:52).\n    - Users can query the system for data such as the number of project managers, showing growing AI assistance capabilities (31:19).\n    - The chatbot runs on the dev system and is designed to create a fully conversational interface for resource management tasks (32:00).\n\n## **Process Improvements and Coordination**\n\nThe team is enhancing tracking and coordination for outreach and marketing efforts.\n\n- To improve visibility, Eli will maintain detailed status tracking of all outreach contacts in shared documents to monitor engagement and follow-up needs (16:25, 24:20).\n- Colin plans to expand outreach capacity by creating additional email mailboxes for sending messages, increasing scalability for campaigns (26:05).\n- The marketing manager tool on LinkedIn requires better navigation and transparency around lists and targeting; Colin will share contact lists to Axel for clarity (12:20).\n- The team agreed to pause current ads until the new landing page and messaging are ready, ensuring alignment before relaunch (29:50).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Ads","Lead Generation","AI Staffing Workflows","Consultant Profiles","Landing Page","Outreach Metrics"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Ads Issues:** $2,400 spent yielded low-quality leads due to unclear messaging about \"resume automation.\"\n\n- **Targeting Strategy:** Using a matched list of 1,100 with 750 LinkedIn matches led to poor targeting; new focused targeting planned.\n\n- **Ad Campaign Changes:** Current ads paused; new ads to promote IT consulting, requiring work emails for better lead quality.\n\n- **Outreach Performance:** Eli’s outreach resulted in 431 requests, 71 accepted, and only 13 replies; need for improved tracking agreed.\n\n- **Product Messaging Update:** Emphasizing AI capabilities in marketing; new landing page to clarify user benefits and engagement.\n\n- **Chatbot Development:** Early chatbot version suggests profile improvements; aims to enhance user experience with conversational interface.","action_items":"\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFollow up and message respondents from LinkedIn ad forms, including Sam from E Techie and Capgemini contacts; track all outreach and lead responses in shared OneNote or Excel file for team visibility (16:09)\nSend personal email follow-ups to prospects who cannot be messaged or connected on LinkedIn (19:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the uploaded LinkedIn contact list used for ad targeting with team (12:29)\nDevelop new LinkedIn and email ad copy replacing ''resume'' with ''CV''; create new landing page content focusing on free Desi Dalo registration and AI resource management; share drafts and updated explainer video script early next week for approval (26:20)\nRefresh and expand outreach contact lists beyond existing 700+ profiles (26:05)\nShare updated explainer video script and framework of Episode One of series featuring discussion between David and Eli on utilization and resource management topics (27:33)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide content input and feedback on landing page sections including tool capabilities, usage process, testimonials, and upgrade rationale (23:25)\n\n**Eli Bebinger & Axel Völker**\nMaintain shared tracking system of message sends, replies, and status updates to ensure clear lead management and avoid redundant outreach (24:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"da112564-c704-4e3e-a8af-81a8ba8aae8e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
