INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **LinkedIn Ads and Lead Quality**

The LinkedIn ad campaign spent **$2,400** over the first few weeks but generated many low-quality leads due to unclear messaging around "resume automation" (10:52).

- **Axel Völker and Eli Bebinger identified** that the term "resume" confused job seekers into submitting forms meant for consulting services (08:14).
    - This caused a flood of responses from people outside the target roles and industries.
    - Eli messaged all form submitters; only one prospect from **Laster Pipeline** responded positively requesting a demo (08:35).
    - Colin Costigan confirmed the positive lead came from ads, but other quality leads from **Capgemini** and **E Techie** had not yet replied (15:18).
    - Eli will continue follow-ups and track status in a shared **OneNote** list for visibility (16:25).

- The campaign used a matched contact list of **1,100 people**, with **750 matches** on LinkedIn, expanded by an AI-driven predictive audience of over a million, causing poor targeting and junk leads (12:20).
    - Colin plans to split targeting into a **highly focused manual list** for most budget spend and a smaller AI-driven predictive group to control quality (13:54).
    - The original budget is **$3,000/month** for LinkedIn ads plus **$500** for programmatic display, with LinkedIn charging mostly on impressions but also clicks (11:16).
    - Cost per lead on LinkedIn is acknowledged as high, sometimes reaching **$1,000+**, but can deliver quality B2B prospects when targeted well (11:25).

- The team decided to stop the current LinkedIn ads and create new ads with clearer messaging focused on IT consulting rather than resumes (10:19).
    - Colin is preparing new ad copy promoting **free registration for Desi Dalo**, emphasizing consultant profiles, skills management, and AI-powered resource management (16:57).
    - The LinkedIn forms will be adjusted to require **work emails** instead of personal emails to improve lead quality (17:37).
    - The new landing page will highlight free usage, target audience, testimonials, and upgrade reasons to encourage conversions (20:04).
    - Colin will share landing page drafts and email copy early next week for review and launch (32:43).

## **Outreach and Messaging Performance**

The outreach via LinkedIn connections and messages has moderate engagement but limited conversions so far.

- Eli has sent **431 connection requests** with **71 accepted** and followed up with **68 messages**, receiving **13 replies** (24:00).
    - Most responses requested product videos, which Eli has started sending more consistently (24:07).
    - Axel requested a tracking system via Excel or OneNote to monitor message status, reply frequency, and last contact date for both ad respondents and LinkedIn messages (24:20).
    - Eli agreed to maintain this tracking despite the volume of messages (24:43).

- To avoid LinkedIn restrictions, connection requests are throttled at **21 per day**, with the current target list of **700+ contacts** (25:49).
